"TC-APPT-0018","Appointment Scheduling","No-Show","Mark a scheduled appointment as Missed/No-show after the slot passes","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Scheduler; appointment scheduled for a slot that is now in the past and patient did not arrive","1. Locate the past scheduled appointment | 2. Open it | 3. Set status to Missed/No-show | 4. Save","AppointmentID=APPT-5004; Status from Scheduled to Missed","Status transitions to Missed, the change is timestamped and attributed to the user, and the appointment is excluded from active queues","Automatable","REQ-APPT-008","Clinical; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0019","Appointment Scheduling","Status Transition","Valid transition Scheduled to CheckedIn at patient arrival","State Transition","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as front-desk; appointment is Scheduled for today and patient has arrived","1. Open today's appointment list | 2. Select the patient's appointment | 3. Click Check In | 4. Confirm","AppointmentID=APPT-5005; from Scheduled to CheckedIn","Status changes to CheckedIn with an arrival timestamp; appointment appears in the active clinical queue","Automatable","REQ-APPT-009","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0020","Appointment Scheduling","Status Transition","Valid transition CheckedIn to Completed after the visit","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as provider; appointment is CheckedIn","1. Open the CheckedIn appointment | 2. Complete the visit workflow | 3. Set status to Completed | 4. Save","AppointmentID=APPT-5005; from CheckedIn to Completed","Status transitions to Completed and the appointment is closed for further status edits except by privileged roles","Automatable","REQ-APPT-009","Clinical; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0021","Appointment Scheduling","Status Transition","Invalid transition Completed back to Scheduled is rejected","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Scheduler; appointment is in status Completed","1. Open the completed appointment | 2. Attempt to set status back to Scheduled","AppointmentID=APPT-5005; attempt Completed to Scheduled","Illegal state transition is rejected with a clear message; status remains Completed","Automatable","REQ-APPT-009","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0022","Appointment Scheduling","Status Transition","Invalid transition Cancelled to CheckedIn is rejected","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as front-desk; appointment is Cancelled","1. Open the cancelled appointment | 2. Attempt to Check In the patient","AppointmentID=APPT-5006; attempt Cancelled to CheckedIn","Check-in is blocked because a cancelled appointment cannot transition to CheckedIn; status remains Cancelled","Automatable","REQ-APPT-009","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0023","Appointment Scheduling","Status Transition","State transition coverage matrix for all defined statuses","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in with privileges to change status; test appointments in each base state","1. For each source state attempt every target state | 2. Record allowed vs blocked | 3. Compare with the defined state machine","States=Scheduled, CheckedIn, Completed, Cancelled, Missed; Allowed=Scheduled->CheckedIn/Cancelled/Missed, CheckedIn->Completed/Cancelled","Only transitions defined in the state machine succeed; all undefined transitions are blocked consistently","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-009","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0024","Appointment Scheduling","Reminders","Schedule an appointment reminder for a future booking","Functional","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Scheduler; reminder service enabled; patient has a valid contact method","1. Book a future appointment | 2. Enable reminder | 3. Select reminder lead time and channel | 4. Save","Patient=Jane Synthetic (ID=10001V); Lead=24h; Channel=SMS; Contact=+15550000001","A reminder job is scheduled for 24 hours before the appointment via the chosen channel and is visible in reminder logs","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-010","Clinical; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0025","Appointment Scheduling","Reminders","Reminder is not sent for a cancelled appointment","Negative","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","A future appointment with a scheduled reminder exists","1. Cancel the appointment before the reminder lead time | 2. Wait until the reminder trigger time | 3. Check reminder dispatch log","AppointmentID=APPT-5007; Reminder lead=24h; Action=Cancel","No reminder is dispatched for the cancelled appointment; the reminder job is voided in the log","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-010","PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0026","Appointment Scheduling","Reminders","Reminder content excludes sensitive clinical details to protect PHI","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Reminder channel configured; patient consented to SMS reminders","1. Trigger a reminder for a booked appointment | 2. Inspect the delivered message content","Channel=SMS; Reminder includes date/time/location only","Reminder contains only minimum necessary information (date, time, location, clinic name) and no diagnosis or sensitive clinical detail","Manual-Only","REQ-APPT-010","PHI/Privacy; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0027","Appointment Scheduling","Recurring","Create a weekly recurring appointment series","Functional","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Scheduler; recurring appointments enabled; provider availability covers the recurrence","1. Select patient, service, provider, location | 2. Choose recurrence Weekly | 3. Set start date and occurrence count | 4. Save","Patient=Jane Synthetic (ID=10001V); Recurrence=Weekly; Start=06-Jul-2026; Occurrences=4","Four weekly appointments are created on consecutive matching weekdays, each with its own ID and linked to the series","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-011","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0028","Appointment Scheduling","Recurring","Recurring series skips occurrences that conflict with provider availability","Negative","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Scheduler; provider unavailable on one of the recurrence dates","1. Create a weekly recurring series spanning a date where the provider is off | 2. Save | 3. Review the generated occurrences","Recurrence=Weekly; ProviderOff=20-Jul-2026; Occurrences=4","Conflicting occurrence is skipped or flagged for manual resolution rather than silently overbooking","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-011","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0029","Appointment Scheduling","Recurring","Cancel a single occurrence without affecting the rest of the series","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","A recurring series of 4 appointments exists","1. Open the second occurrence | 2. Cancel only this occurrence | 3. Confirm scope This appointment only | 4. Verify other occurrences","SeriesID=SER-9001; Cancel=Occurrence 2 only","Only the selected occurrence is cancelled; the remaining occurrences in the series stay Scheduled","Automatable","REQ-APPT-011","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0030","Appointment Scheduling","Recurring","Cancel the entire future series from a chosen occurrence","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","A recurring series of 4 appointments exists; current occurrence is the second","1. Open the second occurrence | 2. Choose Cancel This and following | 3. Confirm","SeriesID=SER-9001; Cancel=From occurrence 2 onward","Occurrence 2 and all later occurrences are cancelled while earlier completed/past occurrences remain unchanged","Automatable","REQ-APPT-011","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0031","Appointment Scheduling","Pairwise","Pairwise combinations of service, location, channel and patient type","Pairwise","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Scheduler; multiple services, locations, reminder channels and patient types configured","1. Apply pairwise-selected combinations for booking | 2. Save each | 3. Verify booking and reminder behavior per combination","Services=GenMed/Cardiology; Locations=Outpatient/Telehealth; Channels=SMS/Email; PatientType=New/Returning","Each pairwise combination books successfully with the correct service, location and reminder channel applied; no invalid pairings are accepted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-012","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0032","Appointment Scheduling","Exploratory","Exploratory session on rapid status changes and concurrent edits","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Two users with edit rights open the same appointment simultaneously","1. User A checks in the patient | 2. User B simultaneously cancels | 3. Observe final state and any errors | 4. Probe rapid repeated status toggles","AppointmentID=APPT-5008; Concurrent users A and B","System resolves concurrency deterministically (last-write or lock), avoids corrupt state, and surfaces a clear conflict message; no orphaned slots","Manual-Only","REQ-APPT-009","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0033","Appointment Scheduling","Exploratory","Exploratory probe of timezone and DST handling around booking","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","High","Logged in as Scheduler; server and client in different timezones; DST transition near booking date","1. Book an appointment near a DST change boundary | 2. View it as users in different timezones | 3. Verify displayed and stored times","Date near DST change; ServerTZ=UTC; ClientTZ=US/Eastern","Stored time is unambiguous and displayed correctly per viewer timezone; no off-by-one-hour shift across DST","Manual-Only","REQ-APPT-013","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0034","Appointment Scheduling","Accessibility","Booking form is fully keyboard navigable and screen-reader labelled","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Scheduler; screen reader available; on the Add new appointment screen","1. Navigate all booking fields using Tab/Shift+Tab only | 2. Operate dropdowns and date picker via keyboard | 3. Verify each control announces a label and state","Tools=NVDA/VoiceOver; Fields=Patient, Service, Provider, Location, Date, Time","All controls are reachable and operable by keyboard, have programmatic labels, and announce required/invalid states per WCAG 2.1 AA","Manual-Only","REQ-APPT-014","Accessibility; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0035","Appointment Scheduling","Accessibility","Validation errors are announced and associated with their fields","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","On the booking form with screen reader active","1. Submit the form with missing required fields | 2. Verify error announcement | 3. Verify errors are programmatically tied to fields","ScreenReader on; Missing=Service, Time","Each error is announced, focus moves to or references the first invalid field, and aria-describedby links the message to the control","Manual-Only","REQ-APPT-014","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0036","Appointment Scheduling","Security","Unauthorized role cannot book or modify appointments","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","A user with a read-only or unrelated role is logged in","1. Attempt to open Add new appointment | 2. Attempt to cancel an existing appointment via UI and direct URL | 3. Observe access control","Role=Lab Technician (no scheduling privilege)","Booking and modification actions are not available and direct attempts are rejected with an authorization error; no data is changed","Automatable","REQ-APPT-015","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0037","Appointment Scheduling","Security","Appointment changes are written to the audit trail","Security","Regression","P1","High","High","Auditing enabled; logged in as Scheduler","1. Create, reschedule and cancel an appointment | 2. Open the audit log | 3. Verify each action is recorded","Actions=Create, Reschedule, Cancel; User=scheduler01","Audit log records user, timestamp, action and before/after values for every appointment change","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-016","Audit; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0038","Appointment Scheduling","Security","Direct object reference to another patient's appointment is blocked","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as a user scoped to a specific location/patient panel","1. Capture an appointment ID belonging to another restricted patient | 2. Request that appointment by ID via URL/API | 3. Observe response","TargetAppointmentID=APPT-7777 (out of scope)","Access is denied for the out-of-scope appointment (no IDOR); response contains no PHI for the unauthorized record","Automatable","REQ-APPT-015","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0039","Appointment Scheduling","Security","Booking input is sanitized against injection in free-text fields","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Scheduler; booking form open","1. Enter script and SQL-like payloads in notes/reason fields | 2. Save | 3. Reopen and view the appointment | 4. Inspect rendering and storage","Payload notes=<script>alert(1)</script>; reason=' OR '1'='1","Input is stored/escaped safely; no script executes on render and no query is altered; payload shown as inert text","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-015","Security","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0040","Appointment Scheduling","API","Create an appointment via the OpenMRS REST appointmentscheduling endpoint","API","Integration","P1","High","High","Valid API session/token; patient, provider, service exist","1. POST to the appointment endpoint with a valid JSON body | 2. Capture the response | 3. GET the created appointment","Endpoint=POST /ws/rest/v1/appointmentscheduling/appointment; body includes patient, timeSlot, appointmentType, status=SCHEDULED","API returns 201/200 with the new appointment UUID; a follow-up GET returns the persisted appointment with matching fields","Automatable","REQ-APPT-017","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0041","Appointment Scheduling","API","Reject API booking with a past time slot","API","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Valid API token","1. POST an appointment with a timeSlot in the past | 2. Inspect status code and error body","Endpoint=POST appointment; timeSlot start=29-Jun-2026 09:00","API rejects with a 4xx validation error and a descriptive message; no record is created","Automatable","REQ-APPT-003","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0042","Appointment Scheduling","API","Unauthenticated appointment API request is rejected","Security","Integration","P1","Critical","High","No valid session/token","1. Send GET/POST to the appointment endpoint without credentials | 2. Inspect the response","Endpoint=GET /ws/rest/v1/appointmentscheduling/appointment; no Authorization header","API responds 401 Unauthorized and returns no appointment or PHI data","Automatable","REQ-APPT-015","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0043","Appointment Scheduling","API","Pagination and filtering of appointments by date and provider","API","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Valid API token; multiple appointments exist across dates","1. GET appointments filtered by provider and date range | 2. Verify pagination parameters | 3. Verify result set","Endpoint=GET appointment?provider=uuid&fromDate=...&toDate=...&limit=10","Only appointments matching the filter are returned, correctly paginated, with consistent ordering","Automatable","REQ-APPT-017","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0044","Appointment Scheduling","FHIR","Create and read an Appointment resource via FHIR R4","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","High","FHIR R4 endpoint available; Patient and Practitioner resources exist","1. POST a FHIR Appointment with status booked and participants | 2. Read it back by id | 3. Validate required fields","Resource=Appointment; status=booked; participant.actor=Patient/123 and Practitioner/456; start/end set","FHIR server returns 201 with a resource id; the read-back Appointment conforms to R4 with correct status, participants and slot times","Automatable","REQ-APPT-018","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-APPT-0045","Appointment Scheduling","FHIR","FHIR Appointment status value set is enforced","FHIR","Regression","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint available","1. POST a FHIR Appointment with an invalid status value | 2. Inspect the OperationOutcome","Resource=Appointment; status=notarealstatus","Server rejects with an OperationOutcome citing an invalid code not in the Appointment status value set (proposed/pending/booked/arrived/fulfilled/cancelled/noshow/etc.)","Automatable","REQ-APPT-018","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-APPT-0046","Appointment Scheduling","FHIR","FHIR no-show maps to Appointment.status noshow","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint; an existing booked Appointment","1. PUT/PATCH the Appointment status to noshow | 2. Read back the resource","Resource=Appointment; transition booked->noshow","Status updates to noshow and is consistent with the internal Missed/No-show state; participant required status remains valid","Automatable","REQ-APPT-008","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-APPT-0047","Appointment Scheduling","FHIR","Search FHIR Slot for free slots before booking","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","FHIR R4 Slot and Schedule resources configured for a provider","1. GET Slot?schedule=...&status=free&start=ge2026-07-02 | 2. Verify returned slots | 3. Book into a returned free slot","Resource=Slot; status=free; schedule=Schedule/789","Only free slots are returned; booking one transitions the Slot to busy and prevents it being offered again","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-005","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-APPT-0048","Appointment Scheduling","HL7","Inbound HL7 SIU S12 creates a new appointment","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 interface engine connected; SIU feed enabled","1. Send an SIU^S12 (new appointment) message | 2. Verify the appointment is created | 3. Verify the ACK","Message=SIU^S12; SCH segment with filler appt id; PID for Jane Synthetic; AIS service","A matching appointment is created with mapped patient, service and time; an HL7 ACK (AA) is returned","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-019","Standards-HL7; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-APPT-0049","Appointment Scheduling","HL7","Inbound HL7 SIU S15 cancels an existing appointment","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 SIU feed enabled; an appointment exists matching the filler id","1. Send an SIU^S15 (appointment cancellation) referencing the existing appointment | 2. Verify status change | 3. Verify ACK","Message=SIU^S15; SCH filler id matches APPT-5009","The referenced appointment is set to Cancelled and an ACK (AA) is returned; mismatched ids produce an application reject (AE)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-019","Standards-HL7; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-APPT-0050","Appointment Scheduling","HL7","Malformed HL7 SIU message is rejected with a negative ACK","HL7","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 SIU feed enabled","1. Send an SIU message with a missing mandatory SCH field | 2. Inspect the ACK","Message=SIU^S12 with empty SCH appointment id","Message is rejected with a negative ACK (AE/AR); no partial appointment record is created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-019","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-APPT-0051","Appointment Scheduling","Database","Cancelling an appointment frees its slot and updates status atomically","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","DB read access; an appointment occupies a slot","1. Record slot and appointment row before cancel | 2. Cancel via UI | 3. Query the appointment and slot tables","AppointmentID=APPT-5010; verify status column and slot occupancy","Appointment row shows Cancelled with end-date set and the slot is released; both updates committed in a single transaction with no orphaned references","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-007","Data Integrity; Database","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0052","Appointment Scheduling","Database","Soft-deleted (voided) appointments are excluded from active queries","Database","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","DB read access; an appointment has been voided","1. Void an appointment | 2. Run the standard active-appointment query | 3. Run a query including voided rows","AppointmentID=APPT-5011; voided=true","Voided appointment is excluded from active lists but retained in the database with voided flag, reason and auditor for traceability","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-016","Database; Audit; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0053","Appointment Scheduling","Database","Referential integrity between appointment, patient and provider","Database","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","DB access; an appointment exists","1. Inspect foreign keys on the appointment row | 2. Attempt to delete a referenced provider | 3. Observe constraint behavior","AppointmentID=APPT-5012; FKs=patient_id, provider","Foreign keys reference valid patient and provider; deleting a referenced provider is blocked or handled per retire policy without orphaning the appointment","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-017","Database; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0054","Appointment Scheduling","Booking","Walk-in appointment created for today's immediate slot","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as front-desk; patient present without prior booking","1. Select the patient | 2. Create an appointment for today's next available slot | 3. Immediately check in","Patient=Walkin Synthetic (ID=10003V); Date=today; Time=next free","Appointment is created for today and can be checked in immediately, appearing in the active queue","Automatable","REQ-APPT-001","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0055","Appointment Scheduling","Booking","Booking honors patient appointment-type duration defaults","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Scheduler; appointment types have distinct default durations","1. Select each appointment type | 2. Observe the auto-set duration and end time | 3. Save","TypeNew=30min; TypeFollowUp=15min; TypeProcedure=60min","End time and slot length are set from the appointment type default and reflected on save","Automatable","REQ-APPT-002","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0056","Appointment Scheduling","Reschedule","Boundary - reschedule to the same slot leaves the appointment unchanged","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","An appointment exists at 02-Jul-2026 10:00","1. Open the appointment | 2. Click Reschedule | 3. Select the identical date and time | 4. Save","AppointmentID=APPT-5013; Same=02-Jul-2026 10:00","No conflict is raised against itself; the appointment remains at the same valid slot and no duplicate is created","Automatable","REQ-APPT-006","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0057","Appointment Scheduling","No-Show","Auto-flag no-show after grace period without manual action","Functional","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","No-show automation enabled with a grace period; appointment not checked in","1. Let a scheduled appointment pass its start plus grace period uncheck-in | 2. Run/await the no-show job | 3. Verify status","AppointmentID=APPT-5014; Grace=30min","After the grace period the appointment is automatically flagged Missed/No-show with an automated attribution in the audit log","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-008","Clinical; Audit","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0058","Appointment Scheduling","Reminders","Reminder respects patient communication consent/opt-out","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patients with varied consent flags; reminders enabled","1. For each consent combination attempt a reminder | 2. Observe whether it dispatches per channel","Pt1 SMS=opt-in,Email=opt-out; Pt2 SMS=opt-out,Email=opt-in; Pt3 all opt-out","Reminders dispatch only via consented channels; fully opted-out patients receive none; decisions are logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-010","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0059","Appointment Scheduling","Booking","Maximum-length and special characters in appointment notes field","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Booking form open; notes field present","1. Enter notes at the maximum allowed length | 2. Include valid special characters and Unicode | 3. Save and reopen","Notes length=max (e.g. 1000 chars); includes accents and emoji","Notes are saved and displayed intact up to the max length; over-max input is truncated or rejected with a clear message","Automatable","REQ-APPT-001","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0060","Appointment Scheduling","Provider Selection","Pairwise provider x service x location availability validation","Pairwise","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Multiple providers mapped to services and locations with availability","1. Apply pairwise combinations of provider, service and location | 2. Check whether slots are offered | 3. Validate against configured mappings","Providers=P1,P2; Services=S1,S2; Locations=L1,L2 pairwise set","Slots are offered only for valid provider-service-location mappings; invalid combinations show no availability","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-012","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0061","Appointment Scheduling","Status Transition","Check-in is blocked for an appointment scheduled on a future date","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as front-desk; appointment scheduled for a future date","1. Open a future-dated scheduled appointment | 2. Attempt to Check In","AppointmentID=APPT-5015; Date=05-Jul-2026 (future)","Check-in is prevented or warned for an appointment not due today; status remains Scheduled","Automatable","REQ-APPT-009","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0062","Appointment Scheduling","Cancel","Cancel propagates slot release and reminder cancellation end-to-end","Functional","E2E","P2","High","Medium","An appointment with a scheduled reminder and an occupied slot exists","1. Cancel the appointment with a reason | 2. Verify slot is freed | 3. Verify reminder voided | 4. Verify audit entry","AppointmentID=APPT-5016; Reason=Clinic closure","Status Cancelled, slot freed for rebooking, pending reminder voided, and a complete audit entry recorded across the chain","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-007","Clinical; Audit; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0063","Appointment Scheduling","Booking","End-to-end book then check-in then complete patient visit","Functional","E2E","P1","Critical","High","Logged in users for scheduling, front-desk and provider roles; patient active","1. Book a future appointment | 2. On the day, check the patient in | 3. Provider completes the visit | 4. Verify final status and history","Patient=Jane Synthetic (ID=10001V); Flow=Scheduled->CheckedIn->Completed","Appointment progresses through all valid states with timestamps and attributions; final status Completed with full history retained","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-009","Clinical; Patient Safety; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0064","Appointment Scheduling","Conflict Prevention","Concurrent booking of the last free slot by two schedulers","Negative","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Two schedulers attempt to book the same last remaining slot at the same time","1. Both users open the same free slot | 2. Both submit Save nearly simultaneously | 3. Observe outcomes","Slot=02-Jul-2026 10:00 (only one free); Users=sched01, sched02","Exactly one booking succeeds; the other is rejected with a slot-no-longer-available message; the slot is never double-booked","Partially-Automatable","REQ-APPT-004","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0065","Appointment Scheduling","Reschedule","Rescheduling preserves linkage to the originating recurring series","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","A recurring series exists; one occurrence will be moved","1. Open one occurrence of the series | 2. Reschedule it to a new valid slot | 3. Verify series linkage and other occurrences","SeriesID=SER-9002; Move=Occurrence 3 to 09-Jul-2026 11:00","The moved occurrence keeps its series association, other occurrences are unaffected, and the series view reflects the new time","Automatable","REQ-APPT-011","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-APPT-0066","Appointment Scheduling","Usability","Day, week and provider views render appointments consistently","Usability","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Multiple appointments exist across providers and times for a given week","1. Open day view | 2. Switch to week view | 3. Switch to provider view | 4. Compare appointment counts and details","Week=06-Jul-2026 to 12-Jul-2026; multiple providers","All three views show the same appointments consistently with correct times, providers and statuses; no appointment is missing or duplicated","Manual-Only","REQ-APPT-013","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-APPT-0067","Appointment Scheduling","FHIR","FHIR Appointment requires start before end (invalid period rejected)","FHIR","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","FHIR R4 endpoint available","1. POST a FHIR Appointment with end earlier than start | 2. Inspect the OperationOutcome","Resource=Appointment; start=2026-07-02T11:00; end=2026-07-02T10:00","Server rejects the resource with an OperationOutcome indicating an invalid period (end before start); no resource is created","Automatable","REQ-APPT-018","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-APPT-0068","Appointment Scheduling","Security","Session timeout requires re-authentication before further booking changes","Security","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Scheduler; idle session timeout configured","1. Authenticate and open a booking | 2. Remain idle beyond the timeout | 3. Attempt to save a change","Timeout=15 min idle","After timeout the action is blocked and the user is forced to re-authenticate; unsaved PHI is not exposed and no change persists without a valid session","Manual-Only","REQ-APPT-015","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0001","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Lab Order Entry","Create a lab order for a single test from an active visit","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician with Order Entry privilege; patient has an active visit; on the patient dashboard Orders widget","1. Open the Orders section | 2. Click Add lab order | 3. Search and select the lab test | 4. Set order urgency to Routine | 5. Enter clinical notes | 6. Click Save order","Test=Complete Blood Count; Urgency=Routine; Notes=Rule out anemia","A new lab order is created in Ordered status, linked to the active visit, with the ordering provider, date/time, and an order number displayed in the active orders list","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-001","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0002","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Lab Order Entry","Create a lab order with STAT urgency","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician with Order Entry privilege; patient has an active visit","1. Open Orders | 2. Click Add lab order | 3. Select the lab test | 4. Set urgency to STAT | 5. Save order","Test=Serum Potassium; Urgency=STAT","Order is saved with urgency STAT and is visually flagged/prioritized in the active orders list with the STAT indicator","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-001","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0003","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Lab Order Entry","Reject lab order with no test selected","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician with Order Entry privilege; patient has an active visit","1. Open Orders | 2. Click Add lab order | 3. Leave the test field empty | 4. Click Save order","Test=(empty)","Order is not saved; a validation message indicates a test must be selected and focus returns to the test field","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-002","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0004","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","CPOE Validation","Block lab order when patient has no active visit","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician with Order Entry privilege; selected patient has NO active visit","1. Navigate to patient dashboard | 2. Attempt to open Add lab order","Patient=no active visit","System prevents order entry and prompts to start a visit first; no order is created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-003","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0005","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","CPOE Validation","Warn on duplicate active lab order for same test","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active lab order for Complete Blood Count in Ordered status","1. Open Orders | 2. Add lab order | 3. Select the same test already active | 4. Save order","Test=Complete Blood Count (already ordered)","A duplicate-order warning is shown allowing override with reason or cancel; if overridden the second order is saved with the captured reason","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-003","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0006","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","CPOE Validation","Decision table for urgency vs required fields","Decision Table","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician with Order Entry privilege; active visit present","1. Add lab order | 2. Select test | 3. For each rule set urgency and scheduled date combination | 4. Attempt save | 5. Observe acceptance/rejection","R1 Routine+noDate=accept; R2 Scheduled+noDate=reject; R3 Scheduled+futureDate=accept; R4 STAT+pastDate=reject","Each rule yields the expected accept or reject outcome; Scheduled urgency mandates a future scheduled date","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-004","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0007","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Lab Order Entry","Order a panel that expands into component tests","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; active visit; lab panel set configured (Platform)","1. Add lab order | 2. Search and select the panel | 3. Save order | 4. Open the order detail","Panel=Basic Metabolic Panel","Panel order is created and its component tests are represented as a grouped order set so results can be entered per component","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-005","Clinical","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0008","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Lab Order Entry","Edit clinical notes on an existing Ordered lab order (revise)","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; an existing lab order in Ordered status","1. Open active orders | 2. Select the order | 3. Choose Modify/Revise | 4. Update clinical notes | 5. Save","Notes=Updated: fasting confirmed","A revision order is created linking to the previous order; the updated notes are reflected and history shows the prior version","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-006","Clinical; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0009","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Order Cancellation","Cancel (discontinue) an Ordered lab order with reason","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; lab order exists in Ordered status","1. Open active orders | 2. Select the order | 3. Click Discontinue/Cancel | 4. Enter cancellation reason | 5. Confirm","Reason=Ordered in error","The order moves to a discontinued/cancelled state with the reason recorded and timestamp; it no longer appears in active orders","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-007","Clinical; Audit; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0010","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Order Cancellation","Block cancellation of an already verified result order","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; lab order is in Verified status with a final result","1. Open the order | 2. Attempt to Discontinue/Cancel","Order status=Verified","Cancellation is blocked or restricted with a message that a verified/resulted order cannot be cancelled; appropriate amendment path is suggested","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-007","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0011","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Specimen Management","Record specimen collection for an Ordered lab test","State Transition","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as Lab/Phlebotomy staff; lab order in Ordered status (Platform LIS workflow)","1. Open the lab worklist | 2. Select the Ordered test | 3. Record specimen collection | 4. Enter specimen type and collection datetime | 5. Save","Specimen=Whole Blood; Container=EDTA; Collected=01-Jul-2026 09:15","Order transitions from Ordered to Collected; specimen identifier, type, and collection datetime are recorded and visible","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-008","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0012","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Specimen Management","Reject specimen collection with future collection datetime","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Lab staff; lab order in Ordered status (Platform LIS workflow)","1. Open worklist | 2. Select test | 3. Enter a collection datetime in the future | 4. Save","Collected=01-Jul-2027 09:15 (future)","Collection is rejected with a validation message that collection datetime cannot be in the future","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-008","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0013","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Specimen Management","Specimen rejection routes order back for recollection","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Lab Technician; specimen in Collected status (Platform LIS workflow)","1. Open the specimen record | 2. Mark specimen as Rejected | 3. Select rejection reason | 4. Save","Rejection reason=Hemolyzed sample","Specimen is flagged rejected with reason; the order returns to a state requiring recollection and notifies the ordering team","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-009","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0014","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Result Entry","Enter a numeric lab result within normal reference range","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Lab Technician; lab order in Collected/In-Progress status; reference ranges configured","1. Open the order in the lab worklist | 2. Enter the numeric result value | 3. Select units | 4. Save result","Test=Hemoglobin; Value=14.2; Units=g/dL","Result is saved and order transitions to Resulted; value is displayed with units and shows as within normal range (not flagged)","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-010","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0015","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Result Entry","Enter a coded (qualitative) lab result","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Lab Technician; qualitative test order in In-Progress status","1. Open the order | 2. Select the coded result value from the answer set | 3. Save","Test=Malaria Smear; Result=Positive","Coded result is saved with the selected concept answer; order transitions to Resulted and the qualitative value displays correctly","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-010","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0016","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Reference Ranges","Flag a result above the high reference range as abnormal High","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Lab Technician; reference range for Potassium configured (3.5-5.1 mmol/L)","1. Open the order | 2. Enter a value above the high limit | 3. Save result","Test=Potassium; Value=5.9; Range=3.5-5.1 mmol/L","Result is saved and automatically flagged as High/Abnormal (above range); the abnormal flag is visible on the result and patient summary","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-011","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0017","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Reference Ranges","Flag a result below the low reference range as abnormal Low","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Lab Technician; reference range for Hemoglobin configured (13.0-17.0 g/dL male)","1. Open the order | 2. Enter a value below the low limit | 3. Save result","Test=Hemoglobin; Value=9.5; Range=13.0-17.0 g/dL","Result is saved and flagged as Low/Abnormal (below range); abnormal indicator is displayed","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-011","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0018","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Reference Ranges","Boundary values exactly at low and high reference limits are normal","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Lab Technician; reference range 3.5-5.1 mmol/L configured for Potassium","1. Enter value equal to low limit and save | 2. Enter value equal to high limit on a second order and save | 3. Observe flags","Low=3.5; High=5.1; Range=3.5-5.1 mmol/L","Both boundary values (3.5 and 5.1) are treated as within normal range and are NOT flagged abnormal","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-011","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0019","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Reference Ranges","Just-outside boundary values are flagged abnormal","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Lab Technician; reference range 3.5-5.1 mmol/L configured","1. Enter a value just below low and save | 2. Enter a value just above high and save | 3. Observe flags","Just-low=3.4; Just-high=5.2; Range=3.5-5.1 mmol/L","3.4 is flagged Low and 5.2 is flagged High; both abnormal indicators appear","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-011","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0020","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Reference Ranges","Age- and sex-specific reference range selection","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Lab Technician; sex/age dependent ranges configured for Hemoglobin","1. Enter same Hemoglobin value for a male and a female patient | 2. Save each | 3. Compare flags applied","Value=13.5 g/dL; Male range 13.0-17.0; Female range 11.5-15.5","The same value is normal for the male patient and may differ for the female patient based on the sex-specific range; correct range is applied per patient demographics","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-012","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0021","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Critical Results","Critical (panic) value triggers critical flag and alert","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Lab Technician; critical thresholds configured for Potassium (>6.0 critical high)","1. Open order | 2. Enter a critical-high value | 3. Save result","Test=Potassium; Value=6.8; Critical high threshold=6.0","Result is flagged Critical (panic) distinctly from routine abnormal; a critical-result alert/notification workflow is triggered for the ordering provider","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-013","Clinical; Patient Safety; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0022","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Critical Results","Critical result acknowledgement is captured for audit","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; a critical lab result is pending acknowledgement","1. Open notifications/inbox | 2. Open the critical result | 3. Acknowledge it | 4. Record action taken","Result=Potassium 6.8 (Critical High)","Acknowledgement is recorded with user, timestamp, and action; the audit trail reflects who acknowledged the critical value and when","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-013","Clinical; Patient Safety; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0023","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Result Entry","Reject non-numeric input for a numeric test","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Lab Technician; numeric test order in In-Progress status","1. Open the order | 2. Enter alphabetic text in the numeric result field | 3. Save","Test=Glucose; Value=ABC","Save is rejected with a validation error that the value must be numeric; no result is persisted","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-010","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0024","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Result Entry","Reject negative value for a test that cannot be negative","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Lab Technician; numeric test with configured absolute range (>=0)","1. Open the order | 2. Enter a negative value | 3. Save","Test=WBC Count; Value=-5","Negative value is rejected with a validation message indicating value is outside the allowed absolute range","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-014","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0025","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Result Entry","Reject value exceeding absolute/critical implausible maximum","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Lab Technician; absolute high limit configured for the test","1. Open the order | 2. Enter an implausibly high value above the absolute max | 3. Save","Test=Hemoglobin; Value=99 g/dL; Absolute max=25","Implausible value is rejected or requires confirmation; the system warns the value is outside the absolute allowable range","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-014","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0026","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Result Verification","Verify a resulted lab result by an authorized verifier","State Transition","Sanity","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Lab Supervisor with verify privilege; order in Resulted status","1. Open the resulted order | 2. Review the entered value | 3. Click Verify/Approve | 4. Confirm","Test=Hemoglobin; Value=14.2 g/dL","Order transitions from Resulted to Verified; verifier identity and timestamp are recorded; result becomes final and visible to clinicians","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-015","Clinical; Patient Safety; Audit","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0027","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Result Verification","Prevent the same user from entering and verifying when segregation required","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Result-entry user lacks verify privilege; segregation-of-duties policy enforced (Platform)","1. Log in as result-entry-only user | 2. Enter a result | 3. Attempt to Verify the same result","User role=Lab Technician (no verify)","Verify action is unavailable or denied for the entering user; verification requires a separate authorized verifier","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-016","Security; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0028","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Result Verification","Amend a verified result creates a corrected version with audit","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Lab Supervisor; order in Verified status","1. Open the verified result | 2. Choose Amend/Correct | 3. Enter the corrected value and reason | 4. Save","Old=14.2; Corrected=4.2 g/dL; Reason=Transcription error","A corrected result version is created (original preserved); amendment reason, user, and timestamp are recorded and the corrected value is marked as amended","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-015","Clinical; Patient Safety; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0029","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Order State Machine","Full happy-path state transition Ordered to Verified","State Transition","E2E","P1","Critical","High","Logged in with appropriate roles across steps; patient active visit; LIS workflow enabled","1. Create lab order (Ordered) | 2. Record specimen collection (Collected) | 3. Start processing (In-Progress) | 4. Enter result (Resulted) | 5. Verify result (Verified)","Test=Creatinine; Value=1.0 mg/dL","Order progresses Ordered to Collected to In-Progress to Resulted to Verified; each transition records actor and timestamp; final state is Verified","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-017","Clinical; Patient Safety; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0030","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Order State Machine","Reject invalid transition from Ordered directly to Resulted","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Lab Technician; order in Ordered status; LIS enforces collection before result","1. Open an Ordered order | 2. Attempt to enter a result without recording collection","Order status=Ordered (no specimen)","System blocks result entry until specimen collection is recorded, enforcing the valid state sequence","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-017","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0031","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Order State Machine","Cannot revert a Verified order back to In-Progress","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Lab Supervisor; order in Verified status","1. Open the verified order | 2. Attempt to change status back to In-Progress","Order status=Verified","Reverse transition is not permitted; only an amendment workflow is allowed, preserving audit integrity","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-017","Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0032","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Radiology Order Entry","Create a radiology order selecting an imaging modality","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician with Order Entry privilege; active visit; radiology orderables configured","1. Open Orders | 2. Click Add radiology/imaging order | 3. Select the imaging study | 4. Select modality | 5. Enter reason for exam | 6. Save","Study=Chest X-Ray; Modality=XR; Reason=Cough x 2 weeks","Radiology order is created in Ordered status with selected modality and clinical reason; appears in the imaging worklist","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-018","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0033","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Radiology Order Entry","Capture contrast and laterality on a radiology order","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; active visit; CT orderable with contrast/laterality options (Platform)","1. Add radiology order | 2. Select CT study | 3. Set contrast = With contrast | 4. Set laterality = Left | 5. Save","Study=CT Abdomen; Contrast=With; Laterality=Left","Order saves with contrast and laterality attributes captured and displayed on the order and worklist entry","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-018","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0034","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Radiology Order Entry","Pairwise coverage of modality, urgency, contrast, portable","Pairwise","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; active visit; multiple modalities configured (Platform)","1. Execute each pairwise combination of modality x urgency x contrast x portable | 2. Save each order | 3. Verify attributes persisted","P1 XR/STAT/None/Portable; P2 CT/Routine/With/Non-portable; P3 MRI/Scheduled/With/Non-portable; P4 US/Routine/None/Portable","Each pairwise combination saves successfully with the chosen attributes persisted; no invalid combination is silently accepted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-019","Clinical","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0035","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Radiology Order Entry","Safety prompt for MRI order with documented metal implant","Decision Table","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has documented ferromagnetic implant; MRI safety screening enabled (Platform)","1. Add radiology order | 2. Select MRI study | 3. Save | 4. Observe safety screening prompt","Study=MRI Brain; Patient flag=Pacemaker implant","An MRI safety/contraindication warning is displayed requiring screening acknowledgement before the order can proceed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-020","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0036","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Radiology Reporting","Link a radiology report to its imaging order","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Logged in as Radiologist; radiology order in In-Progress with completed acquisition (Platform/PACS)","1. Open the imaging worklist | 2. Select the study | 3. Enter findings and impression | 4. Finalize report | 5. Verify linkage","Study=Chest X-Ray; Impression=No acute cardiopulmonary process","Report is saved and linked to the originating order; clinicians can open the report from the order; order transitions to Resulted/Reported","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-021","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0037","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Radiology Reporting","Critical imaging finding triggers notification","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Radiologist; critical finding workflow enabled (Platform)","1. Open the study | 2. Mark finding as Critical | 3. Enter critical finding text | 4. Finalize | 5. Confirm notification","Finding=Tension pneumothorax (Critical)","Critical imaging finding is flagged and a notification/communication is dispatched to the ordering provider with acknowledgement tracking","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-021","Patient Safety; Clinical; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0038","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Radiology Order Entry","Reject radiology order without reason for exam","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; active visit; reason-for-exam mandatory (Platform)","1. Add radiology order | 2. Select study and modality | 3. Leave reason for exam empty | 4. Save","Reason=(empty)","Order is rejected with a validation message that reason for exam is required for imaging orders","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-018","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0039","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","API - Orders","Create a lab order via REST API","API","Integration","P1","High","High","Valid API session/token; patient UUID and orderable concept UUID known; OpenMRS REST module available","1. POST to the order endpoint with type=testorder, patient, concept, orderer, careSetting | 2. Read response status and body | 3. GET the created order by UUID","patient=UUID; concept=CBC UUID; orderer=provider UUID; careSetting=OUTPATIENT","API returns 201 with the created order UUID and Ordered status; subsequent GET returns the persisted order matching the request","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-022","Clinical; Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0040","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","API - Orders","Reject API order creation with missing required field","API","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Valid API token; OpenMRS REST module available","1. POST an order payload omitting the concept field | 2. Inspect HTTP status and error body","payload missing concept","API returns a 4xx validation error identifying the missing required field; no order is created","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-022","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0041","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","API - Security","Reject order API request with invalid/expired token","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Expired or invalid authentication token","1. Send POST to the order endpoint with an invalid token | 2. Inspect HTTP status","Authorization=Bearer invalid","API returns 401 Unauthorized; no order is created and no PHI is leaked in the error response","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-023","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0042","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","API - Security","Authorization check prevents low-privilege user creating orders","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Authenticated user lacking Order Entry privilege","1. Authenticate as a user without order privileges | 2. POST a valid order payload | 3. Inspect status","User=Records Clerk (no order privilege)","API returns 403 Forbidden; order is not created; attempt is auditable","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-023","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0043","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","FHIR","Retrieve a lab order as a FHIR ServiceRequest","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint available; an existing lab order; valid auth","1. GET ServiceRequest by id or search by patient | 2. Validate resourceType and key fields | 3. Validate status and intent","ServiceRequest patient=Patient/UUID; category=Laboratory","Response is a valid FHIR R4 ServiceRequest with correct subject reference, status (active/order), intent=order, and code; passes FHIR validation","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-024","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ORDLAB-0044","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","FHIR","Lab result exposed as FHIR Observation with LOINC and reference range","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint; verified lab result exists; LOINC mapping configured","1. GET Observation for the result | 2. Validate code uses LOINC system | 3. Validate valueQuantity with UCUM units | 4. Validate referenceRange and interpretation","Observation code=LOINC 718-7 (Hemoglobin); value=14.2 g/dL","Observation contains LOINC code with system http://loinc.org, valueQuantity in UCUM units, referenceRange, and interpretation code (e.g., N/H/L) consistent with the flag","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-024","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ORDLAB-0045","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","FHIR","DiagnosticReport links results to the originating ServiceRequest","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint; verified lab panel with results; basedOn linkage supported","1. GET DiagnosticReport | 2. Validate result references to Observations | 3. Validate basedOn reference to ServiceRequest","DiagnosticReport category=LAB; basedOn=ServiceRequest/UUID","DiagnosticReport correctly references its Observation results and links basedOn to the originating ServiceRequest; status reflects final","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-025","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ORDLAB-0046","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","FHIR","Radiology order as ServiceRequest with imaging category","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","FHIR R4 endpoint; an imaging order exists","1. GET the ServiceRequest for the imaging order | 2. Validate category=Imaging | 3. Validate code (e.g., RadLex/LOINC/SNOMED)","ServiceRequest category=Imaging; code=Chest X-Ray","ServiceRequest reflects imaging category with a valid procedure code and correct subject/requester references","Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-024","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ORDLAB-0047","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","HL7","Inbound HL7 v2 ORM order message creates/updates an order","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 v2 interface engine connected; LIS sends ORM^O01 (Platform integration)","1. Send an ORM^O01 message with ORC and OBR segments | 2. Confirm ACK received | 3. Verify order state in the system","Message=ORM^O01; OBR-4=CBC; ORC-1=NW","System returns an AA acknowledgement and the order is created/updated to match the OBR/ORC content","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-026","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ORDLAB-0048","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","HL7","Inbound HL7 v2 ORU result message posts results with abnormal flags","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 v2 interface engine connected; LIS sends ORU^R01 (Platform integration)","1. Send an ORU^R01 with OBX result segments | 2. Confirm ACK | 3. Verify the result and abnormal flag posted","Message=ORU^R01; OBX-5=5.9; OBX-8=H (abnormal high)","Result is posted to the matching order with the HL7 abnormal flag (OBX-8) mapped to the system abnormal/High indicator; ACK is AA","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-027","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ORDLAB-0049","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","HL7","Malformed HL7 message is rejected with negative acknowledgement","HL7","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","HL7 v2 interface engine connected (Platform integration)","1. Send an ORU message with a missing required MSH field | 2. Inspect the acknowledgement","Message=ORU with missing MSH-9","Interface returns an AE/AR negative acknowledgement; no malformed result is persisted; error is logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-027","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ORDLAB-0050","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Database","Lab order persists correct foreign keys and status in the orders table","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Database read access; a lab order created via the UI","1. Query the orders/test_order tables for the new order | 2. Verify patient_id, concept_id, orderer, care_setting | 3. Verify order_action and date_activated","order UUID from UI","Persisted row contains correct patient, concept, orderer, and care setting foreign keys, action=NEW, and a non-null activation date matching the UI","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-028","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0051","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Database","Discontinuing an order preserves the original row and adds linkage","Database","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Database read access; an order discontinued via the UI","1. Identify the original order row | 2. Identify the discontinuation order row | 3. Verify previous_order linkage and stop/auto-expire dates","original order UUID; discontinue reason recorded","Original order row is retained (immutable history); the discontinuation order references the previous order via the linkage column with a recorded date","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-007","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0052","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Audit","Order creation and changes are captured in the audit log","Database","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Audit logging enabled; access to audit/history records","1. Create a lab order | 2. Modify it | 3. Discontinue it | 4. Review the audit/history entries","Test=CBC; actions=create, modify, discontinue","Each action is recorded with actor, timestamp, and change detail; the audit trail reconstructs the full lifecycle of the order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-029","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Security","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0053","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","PHI/Privacy","Result view access restricted to authorized roles only","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Two users: one with result-view privilege, one without","1. Log in as authorized user and open a result (allowed) | 2. Log in as unauthorized user and attempt to open the same result","Result=Hemoglobin 14.2; users with/without privilege","Authorized user views the result; unauthorized user is denied and no PHI is exposed; the denied access attempt is logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-023","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0054","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Accessibility","Lab order form is fully keyboard navigable","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; on the Add lab order form","1. Use Tab/Shift+Tab to traverse all fields | 2. Operate the test search and dropdowns via keyboard | 3. Submit using Enter | 4. Verify focus order","Keyboard-only navigation","All interactive controls are reachable and operable by keyboard in a logical order; visible focus indicators are present and the form submits without a mouse","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDLAB-030","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0055","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Accessibility","Abnormal/critical flags are not conveyed by color alone","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; results view with abnormal and critical flags present","1. Inspect abnormal and critical result indicators | 2. Verify text/icon/ARIA label accompanies color | 3. Check with a screen reader","Results with High, Low, and Critical flags","Each abnormal/critical indicator includes a non-color cue (text/icon/ARIA label) so the status is perceivable without relying on color; screen reader announces the status","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDLAB-030","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0056","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Exploratory","Exploratory session on rapid concurrent order entry and editing","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; active visit; test environment","1. Rapidly add multiple lab and radiology orders | 2. Edit and discontinue some mid-flow | 3. Switch patients quickly | 4. Observe UI consistency, duplicates, and state correctness","Mixed lab + radiology orders; rapid actions","No orphaned, duplicated, or mismatched-patient orders occur; UI remains consistent and order states stay correct; any anomalies are documented","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDLAB-031","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0057","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Exploratory","Exploratory testing of unusual specimen and result values","Exploratory","System","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Lab Technician; In-Progress orders available","1. Enter edge values (zero, very large, many decimals, scientific notation) | 2. Enter unusual units | 3. Attempt special characters in comments | 4. Observe handling","Values=0, 0.0001, 1e6, 12.3456789; comments with symbols","System handles or gracefully rejects edge inputs without crashing; rounding/units behavior is reasonable and consistent; no data corruption","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDLAB-014","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0058","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","CPOE Validation","Allergy/contraindication interaction check on order placement","Decision Table","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has a recorded contrast allergy; contrast imaging order attempted (Platform)","1. Add a contrast-enhanced imaging order for the patient | 2. Save | 3. Observe interaction/allergy alert","Patient allergy=Iodinated contrast; Order=CT with contrast","An allergy/contraindication alert is presented before the order is finalized, requiring acknowledgement or override with reason","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-020","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0059","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Order State Machine","Cancelled order cannot receive a result","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Lab Technician; an order in Cancelled/Discontinued status","1. Open the cancelled order | 2. Attempt to record specimen or enter a result","Order status=Cancelled","Result/specimen entry is blocked for cancelled orders with a clear message; no result is attached to a cancelled order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-017","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0060","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Result/Report Linkage","Resulted lab value appears on patient clinical summary linked to order","Functional","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; a verified lab result exists for the patient","1. Open the patient clinical summary/dashboard | 2. Locate the lab result | 3. Click through to the originating order","Test=Creatinine; Value=1.0 mg/dL (Verified)","The verified result is displayed on the patient summary and links back to its originating order with consistent value, units, and date","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-021","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0061","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Reference Ranges","Result without configured reference range shows no false abnormal flag","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Lab Technician; a test with no reference range configured","1. Enter a numeric result for the test | 2. Save | 3. Observe flagging","Test=Custom assay (no range); Value=42","Result is saved without an abnormal flag and indicates no reference range available; no misleading normal/abnormal indicator is shown","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-012","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0062","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Lab Order Entry","Scheduled (future-dated) lab order is queued not active","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; active visit; scheduled orders supported","1. Add lab order | 2. Set urgency=On Scheduled Date | 3. Set a future scheduled date | 4. Save | 5. Check order state on current date","Test=Lipid Panel; Scheduled date=15-Jul-2026","Order is saved as scheduled/future and is not yet active for collection until the scheduled date; it is clearly marked as future-dated","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-004","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDLAB-0063","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","Radiology Order Entry","Cancel a radiology order before image acquisition","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; radiology order in Ordered status (not yet acquired)","1. Open the imaging order | 2. Click Cancel/Discontinue | 3. Enter reason | 4. Confirm","Study=Chest X-Ray; Reason=Clinically no longer indicated","Order transitions to cancelled with reason and timestamp; it is removed from the active imaging worklist","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-007","Clinical; Audit","Platform"
"TC-ORDLAB-0064","Orders, Laboratory & Radiology","CPOE Validation","Reflex/dependent test auto-orders based on result rule","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Lab Technician; reflex rule configured (e.g., positive screen triggers confirmatory test)","1. Enter a result that meets the reflex condition | 2. Save | 3. Observe auto-generated reflex order","Screen result=Reactive; Reflex=Confirmatory test","A reflex/confirmatory order is automatically generated and linked to the triggering result per the configured rule; if condition not met, no reflex order is created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDLAB-005","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0001","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Drug Order Entry","Create a new drug order with all required attributes","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider with active visit for a patient; on the patient dashboard Orders tab","1. Click Add Drug Order | 2. Search and select a drug from the formulary | 3. Enter dose and select dose unit | 4. Select route | 5. Select frequency | 6. Enter duration and duration unit | 7. Click Save Order","Drug=Amoxicillin 500mg; Dose=500; Unit=mg; Route=Oral; Frequency=Twice daily; Duration=7; DurationUnit=Days","Drug order is created with status Active, appears in the active orders list, and an order number is generated","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-001","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0002","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Drug Order Entry","Reject drug order saved without a dose","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Provider with active visit; on the Add Drug Order form","1. Select a drug from the formulary | 2. Leave the dose field empty | 3. Select route Oral | 4. Select frequency Once daily | 5. Click Save Order","Drug=Lisinopril 10mg; Dose=(empty); Route=Oral; Frequency=Once daily","Order is not saved; a validation error indicates dose is required and the form remains open","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-001","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0003","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Drug Order Entry","Reject drug order with missing route","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Provider with active visit; on the Add Drug Order form","1. Select a drug | 2. Enter a valid dose | 3. Leave route unselected | 4. Select frequency | 5. Click Save Order","Drug=Metformin 500mg; Dose=500; Unit=mg; Route=(empty); Frequency=Twice daily","Order is not saved; a validation message indicates route is required","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0004","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Drug Order Entry","Free-text (non-coded) drug order capture","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Provider; formulary does not contain the requested drug","1. Click Add Drug Order | 2. Choose the free-text drug option | 3. Type the drug name as free text | 4. Enter dosing instructions | 5. Click Save Order","FreeTextDrug=Compounded magic mouthwash; Instructions=Swish and spit 10ml four times daily","Order is saved as a non-coded drug order and is clearly flagged as free text in the orders list","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-002","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0005","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dosing Boundary","Dose at the minimum allowed boundary is accepted","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Provider; drug with configured min dose of 1 mg","1. Add a drug order | 2. Enter the minimum valid dose | 3. Select unit mg | 4. Complete route and frequency | 5. Save Order","Drug=Warfarin; Dose=1; Unit=mg; Route=Oral; Frequency=Once daily","Order is accepted at the lower boundary value with no dosing error","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-003","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0006","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dosing Boundary","Dose just below minimum is rejected or warned","Boundary","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Provider; drug with configured min therapeutic dose","1. Add a drug order | 2. Enter a dose below the minimum threshold | 3. Complete route and frequency | 4. Attempt to Save Order","Drug=Warfarin; Dose=0.05; Unit=mg; Route=Oral; Frequency=Once daily","System warns the dose is below the safe range and requires acknowledgement or blocks the order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-003","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0007","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dosing Boundary","Dose at the maximum allowed boundary is accepted","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Provider; drug with configured max single dose","1. Add a drug order | 2. Enter the maximum valid dose | 3. Complete route and frequency | 4. Save Order","Drug=Paracetamol; Dose=1000; Unit=mg; Route=Oral; Frequency=Four times daily","Order is accepted at the upper boundary with no error","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-003","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0008","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dosing Boundary","Dose above maximum triggers overdose warning","Boundary","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; drug with configured max single dose and max daily dose","1. Add a drug order | 2. Enter a dose exceeding the maximum single dose | 3. Complete route and frequency | 4. Attempt to Save Order","Drug=Paracetamol; Dose=5000; Unit=mg; Route=Oral; Frequency=Four times daily","System raises a maximum dose exceeded / overdose alert and requires explicit override with reason or blocks save","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-003","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0009","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dosing Boundary","Reject negative dose value","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Provider on the Add Drug Order form","1. Add a drug order | 2. Enter a negative dose | 3. Complete route and frequency | 4. Attempt to Save Order","Drug=Ibuprofen; Dose=-200; Unit=mg; Route=Oral","Order is rejected with a validation error that dose must be a positive number","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-003","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0010","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dosing Boundary","Reject non-numeric dose entry","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Provider on the Add Drug Order form","1. Add a drug order | 2. Type alphabetic characters into the dose field | 3. Attempt to Save Order","Drug=Ibuprofen; Dose=abc; Unit=mg","Dose field rejects non-numeric input or validation prevents save","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-003","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0011","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Weight-Based Dosing","Pediatric weight-based dose calculation","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; pediatric patient with recorded weight; weight-based dosing configured","1. Open Add Drug Order for the pediatric patient | 2. Select a weight-based drug | 3. Enter dose per kg | 4. Confirm the system computes total dose from patient weight | 5. Save Order","Drug=Amoxicillin suspension; DosePerKg=25mg/kg; PatientWeight=20kg; ExpectedTotal=500mg","Total computed dose equals 500 mg and is displayed for confirmation before saving","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-004","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0012","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Weight-Based Dosing","Block weight-based order when patient weight missing","Negative","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as Provider; pediatric patient with no recorded weight","1. Open Add Drug Order | 2. Select a weight-based drug requiring weight | 3. Enter dose per kg | 4. Attempt to Save Order","Drug=Gentamicin; DosePerKg=5mg/kg; PatientWeight=(none)","System prompts that patient weight is required for this calculation and prevents saving until weight is recorded","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-004","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0013","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Drug Interaction Alert","Major drug-drug interaction alert is raised","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; patient already has an active warfarin order; interaction checking enabled","1. Add a new drug order for an interacting drug | 2. Complete dose route frequency | 3. Click Save Order | 4. Observe interaction alert","ExistingDrug=Warfarin; NewDrug=Aspirin; ExpectedSeverity=Major","A drug-drug interaction alert of Major severity is displayed identifying both drugs and the clinical risk","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-005","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0014","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Drug Interaction Alert","Provider override of interaction alert with reason is audited","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; interaction alert raised for the new order","1. Trigger a major interaction alert | 2. Choose to override the alert | 3. Select or enter an override reason | 4. Confirm and Save Order | 5. Review the audit log","NewDrug=Aspirin; OverrideReason=Benefit outweighs risk, monitoring INR","Order is saved, the override and reason are recorded with provider identity and timestamp in the audit trail","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-005","Patient Safety; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0015","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Drug Interaction Alert","No interaction alert for non-interacting drug pair","Negative","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Provider; patient has an active order for a drug with no known interaction with the new drug","1. Add a new drug order for a non-interacting drug | 2. Complete the order details | 3. Save Order","ExistingDrug=Paracetamol; NewDrug=Vitamin D","Order saves without any drug-drug interaction alert","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-005","Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0016","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Interaction Severity Decision","Decision table: interaction severity to system action mapping","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; interaction engine configured with severity tiers","1. For each severity tier place an interacting order | 2. Observe required action: Contraindicated blocks, Major requires override+reason, Moderate requires acknowledgement, Minor informational only | 3. Verify save behavior matches tier","Tiers=Contraindicated->Block; Major->Override+Reason; Moderate->Acknowledge; Minor->Info","Each severity tier produces the mapped system action exactly as defined in the decision table","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-006","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0017","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Interaction Severity Decision","Contraindicated combination is hard-blocked","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; patient on an MAOI; contraindicated pairing configured","1. Add an order for a drug contraindicated with the active MAOI | 2. Complete details | 3. Attempt to Save Order","ExistingDrug=Phenelzine (MAOI); NewDrug=Selegiline; Tier=Contraindicated","System hard-blocks the order with no override path and explains the contraindication","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-006","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0018","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Allergy Contraindication","Allergy alert when ordering a drug the patient is allergic to","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; patient has a documented penicillin allergy on the allergy list","1. Add a drug order for a penicillin-class drug | 2. Complete details | 3. Click Save Order | 4. Observe allergy alert","Allergy=Penicillin (Anaphylaxis); OrderedDrug=Amoxicillin","A contraindication alert is shown citing the documented penicillin allergy and reaction severity before the order can proceed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-007","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0019","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Allergy Contraindication","Cross-sensitivity allergy alert for related drug class","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Logged in as Provider; patient allergic to penicillin; cross-sensitivity rules configured","1. Add a drug order for a cephalosporin | 2. Complete details | 3. Save Order | 4. Observe cross-sensitivity warning","Allergy=Penicillin; OrderedDrug=Cephalexin; Relationship=Cross-sensitivity","A cross-sensitivity warning is displayed advising potential reaction risk","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-007","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0020","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Allergy Contraindication","Override allergy alert requires reason and is audited","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; allergy alert raised","1. Trigger an allergy contraindication alert | 2. Select override | 3. Enter an override justification | 4. Save Order | 5. Inspect audit log","OrderedDrug=Amoxicillin; OverrideReason=Prior tolerance verified, mild rash only","Order saves and the allergy override with reason, provider, and timestamp is persisted to the audit trail","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-007","Patient Safety; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0021","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Allergy Contraindication","No allergy alert when patient has no documented allergies","Negative","Integration","P2","Medium","Low","Logged in as Provider; patient allergy list explicitly marked No Known Allergies","1. Add any drug order | 2. Complete details | 3. Save Order","AllergyStatus=No Known Allergies; OrderedDrug=Amoxicillin","Order saves without an allergy contraindication alert","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-007","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0022","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Frequency & Schedule","Select a valid administration frequency","Functional","Sanity","P2","Medium","Low","Logged in as Provider on the Add Drug Order form","1. Add a drug order | 2. Open the frequency picker | 3. Select a standard frequency | 4. Complete remaining fields | 5. Save Order","Drug=Omeprazole; Frequency=Once daily before breakfast","Selected frequency is persisted and shown in the order summary","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-008","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0023","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Frequency & Schedule","PRN (as-needed) order with indication","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Provider on the Add Drug Order form","1. Add a drug order | 2. Mark the order as PRN | 3. Enter the PRN indication | 4. Complete dose route frequency | 5. Save Order","Drug=Ondansetron; PRN=Yes; Indication=Nausea; Dose=4mg","Order is saved as PRN with the indication captured and displayed","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-008","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0024","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Duration","Reject zero or negative duration","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Provider on the Add Drug Order form","1. Add a drug order | 2. Enter duration of zero | 3. Complete other fields | 4. Attempt to Save Order | 5. Repeat with a negative duration","Drug=Azithromycin; Duration=0 then -3; DurationUnit=Days","System rejects zero and negative durations with a validation error","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-009","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0025","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Duration","Scheduled future start date order","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Provider on the Add Drug Order form","1. Add a drug order | 2. Set a scheduled start date in the future | 3. Complete details | 4. Save Order","Drug=Prednisone taper; ScheduledStart=2026-07-10","Order is saved with status Scheduled and activates on the chosen start date","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-009","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0026","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Order Lifecycle","Revise an active drug order creates a new revision","State Transition","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Provider; patient has an active drug order","1. Open the active order | 2. Choose Revise/Modify | 3. Change the dose | 4. Save the revision | 5. Review order history","OriginalDose=250mg; NewDose=500mg","A new order revision is created linked to the previous order, the prior order is voided/superseded, and the active dose is now 500 mg","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-010","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0027","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Order Lifecycle","Discontinue an active drug order with reason","State Transition","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Provider; patient has an active drug order","1. Open the active order | 2. Select Discontinue/Stop | 3. Enter a discontinue reason | 4. Confirm | 5. Verify order status","Drug=Lisinopril; Reason=Adverse effect cough","Order transitions to Stopped/Discontinued with the reason and timestamp recorded; it no longer appears as active","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-010","Clinical; Audit; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0028","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Order Lifecycle","Discontinue requires a reason","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Provider; patient has an active drug order; reason mandatory","1. Open the active order | 2. Select Discontinue | 3. Leave the reason blank | 4. Attempt to confirm","Drug=Lisinopril; Reason=(blank)","System prevents discontinuation and requires a reason to be entered","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-010","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0029","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Order Lifecycle","Cannot discontinue an already stopped order","Negative","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Provider; patient has a previously stopped drug order","1. Open the order history | 2. Locate a stopped order | 3. Attempt to discontinue it again","Drug=Lisinopril; CurrentStatus=Stopped","Discontinue action is unavailable or rejected for an already-stopped order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-010","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0030","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Order Lifecycle","Order state transitions: New to Active to Stopped","State Transition","System","P1","High","Medium","Logged in as Provider; ability to place, activate, and stop orders","1. Create a new order and verify status New/Active | 2. Confirm it appears in active list | 3. Stop the order | 4. Verify it moves to Stopped | 5. Confirm history retains all states","Drug=Metformin; Lifecycle=New->Active->Stopped","Order moves through each valid state, invalid transitions are not permitted, and full history is preserved","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-010","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0031","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Refills","Order with refills decrements remaining refills on each fill","State Transition","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Pharmacist; an active order configured with refills","1. Open the order with refills remaining | 2. Process a dispense/fill | 3. Verify refills remaining decremented | 4. Repeat until exhausted","Drug=Atorvastatin; RefillsAuthorized=3","Each fill decrements the remaining refill count; after the third the count reaches zero","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-011","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0032","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Refills","Block dispense when no refills remain","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Pharmacist; order with zero refills remaining","1. Open an order with zero refills remaining | 2. Attempt to process another fill","Drug=Atorvastatin; RefillsRemaining=0","Dispense is blocked and the pharmacist is informed that authorization or a new order is required","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-011","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0033","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dispensing","Dispense medication against an active order","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Logged in as Pharmacist; active drug order pending dispense; stock available","1. Open the pharmacy dispensing queue | 2. Select the pending order | 3. Confirm drug dose and quantity | 4. Record dispense quantity | 5. Confirm dispense","Drug=Amoxicillin 500mg; Quantity=14 tablets","Dispense is recorded, inventory decrements, and the order shows a dispense event with quantity and dispenser identity","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-012","Clinical; Audit","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0034","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dispensing","Block dispense quantity exceeding ordered amount","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Pharmacist; active order with a defined total quantity","1. Open a pending order | 2. Enter a dispense quantity greater than the ordered total | 3. Attempt to confirm","Drug=Amoxicillin; Ordered=14; DispenseQty=30","Dispense is blocked or flagged because quantity exceeds the authorized amount","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-012","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0035","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dispensing","Partial dispense leaves remaining quantity outstanding","Functional","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Pharmacist; active order; insufficient stock for full quantity","1. Open a pending order | 2. Record a partial dispense quantity | 3. Confirm | 4. Verify remaining quantity","Drug=Insulin pens; Ordered=5; DispenseQty=2","Partial dispense recorded and remaining quantity of 3 stays outstanding for future fill","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-012","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0036","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Controlled Substance","Schedule II controlled substance order requires extra authorization","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider with DEA/prescriber authority; controlled-substance workflow enabled","1. Add an order for a Schedule II drug | 2. Complete dose route frequency | 3. Provide required prescriber credential / e-sign | 4. Save Order","Drug=Oxycodone; Schedule=CII; Credential=Provider DEA on file","Order requires and validates prescriber authorization/e-signature before it can be saved","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-013","Regulatory/Compliance; Patient Safety; Security; Audit","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0037","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Controlled Substance","Block controlled substance order from unauthorized prescriber","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as a provider WITHOUT controlled-substance prescribing authority","1. Attempt to add a Schedule II drug order | 2. Complete details | 3. Attempt to Save Order","Drug=Fentanyl; PrescriberAuthority=None","System blocks the order and records the unauthorized attempt; no order is created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-013","Regulatory/Compliance; Security; Audit","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0038","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Controlled Substance","No refills permitted on Schedule II prescription","Negative","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as Provider; Schedule II order being created","1. Add a Schedule II drug order | 2. Attempt to set refills greater than zero | 3. Save Order","Drug=Oxycodone; Schedule=CII; RefillsAttempted=2","System prevents authorizing refills on a Schedule II order per regulation","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-013","Regulatory/Compliance; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0039","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Controlled Substance","Controlled substance dispense logged to audit trail","Audit","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Pharmacist; Schedule II order ready to dispense","1. Dispense the controlled substance | 2. Record quantity and witness if required | 3. Confirm | 4. Inspect the controlled-substance log","Drug=Morphine; Quantity=10; Witness=Pharmacist B","Dispense is recorded in an immutable controlled-substance audit log with quantities, identities, and timestamps","Manual-Only","REQ-PHARM-013","Regulatory/Compliance; Audit; Security","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0040","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","FHIR MedicationRequest","Create order surfaces as FHIR MedicationRequest","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","Medium","FHIR API enabled; valid OAuth token; a drug order exists for the patient","1. Issue GET /MedicationRequest?patient={id} | 2. Inspect the returned resource | 3. Validate status, intent, medication, and dosageInstruction fields","PatientId=synthetic-123; Endpoint=/ws/fhir2/R4/MedicationRequest","Response returns a valid R4 MedicationRequest with status=active, intent=order, medicationCodeableConcept, and dosageInstruction matching the order","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-014","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0041","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","FHIR MedicationRequest","FHIR MedicationRequest dosage uses valid coded units","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR API enabled; a drug order with structured dosing exists","1. GET the MedicationRequest | 2. Inspect dosageInstruction.doseAndRate | 3. Verify unit code system (UCUM) and value","Drug=Amoxicillin; ExpectedUnitSystem=http://unitsofmeasure.org; Value=500; Code=mg","doseAndRate value is 500 with UCUM unit code mg from the correct code system URI","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-014","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0042","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","FHIR MedicationRequest","Reject malformed FHIR MedicationRequest POST","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR API enabled; valid token","1. POST a MedicationRequest missing required medication element | 2. Inspect HTTP response and OperationOutcome","Payload={status:active, intent:order, no medication}; Endpoint=/ws/fhir2/R4/MedicationRequest","API returns HTTP 400/422 with an OperationOutcome describing the missing required element","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-014","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0043","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","HL7 Messaging","Outbound RDE^O11 pharmacy order message generated","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 interface engine configured; pharmacy order placed","1. Place a new drug order | 2. Capture the outbound HL7 message at the interface | 3. Parse the message type and RXO/RXE segments","Drug=Amoxicillin; ExpectedMsg=RDE^O11; Segments=RXO,RXE","A well-formed RDE^O11 message is emitted with correct RXO/RXE segments reflecting the order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-015","Standards-HL7; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0044","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","HL7 Messaging","Inbound dispense status RDS^O13 updates order","HL7","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","HL7 interface configured; an order awaiting dispense status","1. Send an inbound RDS^O13 dispense message | 2. Verify the order dispense status updates | 3. Confirm RXD segment quantity is reflected","Msg=RDS^O13; RXD.Quantity=14","Order reflects the dispense status and quantity from the inbound HL7 message","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-015","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0045","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","HL7 Messaging","Malformed HL7 order message is rejected and logged","HL7","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","HL7 interface engine configured with validation","1. Send an HL7 message with a corrupt MSH segment | 2. Observe interface handling | 3. Check the error/dead-letter log","Msg=RDE^O11 with truncated MSH","Message is rejected, not processed, and the error is logged for reprocessing without crashing the interface","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-015","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0046","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Order Entry API","REST API create drug order returns created resource","API","Integration","P1","High","Medium","REST API enabled; valid session/token; active encounter exists","1. POST to the drug order endpoint with valid payload | 2. Inspect HTTP status and body | 3. GET the created order to confirm persistence","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/order; Type=drugorder; Drug=Amoxicillin","API returns 201 with the created order including a uuid, and the order is retrievable","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-016","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0047","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Order Entry API","API rejects drug order without active encounter","API","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","REST API enabled; valid token; no active encounter for patient","1. POST a drug order payload referencing a patient with no active encounter | 2. Inspect the response","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/order; Encounter=(missing)","API returns a 4xx error indicating an encounter is required and no order is created","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-016","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0048","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Security & Access","Unauthenticated API request to orders is denied","Security","Integration","P1","Critical","High","REST/FHIR API reachable; no auth credentials supplied","1. Issue a GET to the orders endpoint with no auth header | 2. Inspect the response status","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/order; Auth=none","API returns 401 Unauthorized and discloses no patient or order data","Automatable","REQ-PHARM-017","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0049","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Security & Access","Nurse role cannot create a prescriber-only drug order","Security","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as a Nurse without prescribing privilege","1. Navigate to the patient orders | 2. Attempt to create a new drug order | 3. Observe available actions","Role=Nurse; Action=Create drug order","Create drug order action is unavailable or denied based on role privileges","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-017","Security; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0050","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Security & Access","Order view access is logged for PHI audit","Audit","System","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Provider; audit logging enabled","1. Open a patient medication order | 2. View order details | 3. Inspect the access/audit log","User=DrSmith; Patient=synthetic-123","Access to the patient medication data is recorded with user, patient, action, and timestamp","Manual-Only","REQ-PHARM-017","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Security","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0051","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Database Integrity","Drug order persisted with referential integrity","Database","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Backend DB access for verification; an order was just created via UI","1. Create a drug order in the UI | 2. Query the orders table by order uuid | 3. Verify foreign keys to patient, encounter, and drug concept resolve","OrderUuid=<from UI>; Tables=orders, drug_order","Order row exists with valid non-null foreign keys to patient, encounter, and drug, and matches UI values","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-018","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0052","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Database Integrity","Voided order retains row with voided flag set","Database","Integration","P2","Medium","Low","Backend DB access; an order was discontinued/voided via UI","1. Void/discontinue an order in the UI | 2. Query the order row | 3. Verify voided flag, void reason, voided_by, and date_voided","Order=Lisinopril; Action=Void","Row is retained (soft delete) with voided=true, void reason, voided_by, and date_voided populated","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-018","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0053","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Pairwise Order Combos","Pairwise coverage of route x frequency x formulation","Pairwise","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Provider on the Add Drug Order form","1. For each pairwise-selected combination create an order | 2. Vary route, frequency, and formulation per the pairwise set | 3. Save and verify acceptance","Combos=Oral/BID/Tablet; IV/Q8H/Solution; Topical/PRN/Cream; SC/Daily/Injection","Each valid pairwise combination is accepted and persisted with the correct attributes","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-019","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0054","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Accessibility","Add Drug Order form is keyboard and screen-reader accessible","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Provider; screen reader available; on the Add Drug Order form","1. Navigate the entire form using only the keyboard | 2. Verify focus order is logical | 3. Verify each field has an accessible label | 4. Trigger a validation error and confirm it is announced","Tool=Screen reader; Standard=WCAG 2.1 AA","All fields are reachable and labeled, focus order is logical, and validation errors are announced to assistive technology","Manual-Only","REQ-PHARM-020","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-PHARM-0055","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Exploratory","Exploratory session on complex polypharmacy order entry","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Provider; patient with 8+ active medications, multiple allergies and interactions","1. Add several interacting and allergy-triggering orders | 2. Mix PRN, scheduled, taper, and weight-based orders | 3. Probe alert stacking, override flows, and order list rendering | 4. Note any defects or confusing behavior","Patient=Polypharmacy synthetic; ActiveMeds=8","No crashes, alerts are accurate and not suppressed incorrectly, overrides are audited, and any anomalies are documented","Manual-Only","REQ-PHARM-021","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PHARM-0056","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Dosing Boundary","Maximum cumulative daily dose across multiple orders","Boundary","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; patient has an existing acetaminophen-containing order","1. Note the existing acetaminophen daily total | 2. Add a second acetaminophen-containing product | 3. Confirm cumulative daily dose calculation | 4. Observe max-daily-dose alert","Existing=Paracetamol 1000mg QID=4000mg; New=Co-codamol adds 2000mg/day; Limit=4000mg/day","System detects the cumulative daily dose exceeds the safe limit and raises a duplicate-therapy/max-daily-dose alert","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-003","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0057","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Order Lifecycle","Duplicate therapy alert for same drug already active","Functional","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Provider; patient already has an active order for the same drug","1. Add a new order for a drug the patient is already taking | 2. Complete details | 3. Save Order | 4. Observe duplicate therapy alert","ExistingDrug=Lisinopril 10mg; NewDrug=Lisinopril 20mg","A duplicate therapy alert is shown identifying the existing active order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-005","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PHARM-0058","Pharmacy & Medication Orders","Renal Dosing","Renal-adjusted dose alert for impaired renal function","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as Provider; patient with documented low eGFR; renal dosing rules configured","1. Add a renally-cleared drug order at a standard dose | 2. Complete details | 3. Save Order | 4. Observe renal dosing guidance","Drug=Gabapentin; eGFR=25; StandardDose=300mg TID","System raises a renal dosing alert recommending dose adjustment for the reduced eGFR","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PHARM-022","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-RBAC-0001","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Create a new role with no inherited roles","Functional","Smoke","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator with Manage Roles privilege; on Administration > Manage Roles","1. Click Add Role | 2. Enter role name | 3. Enter description | 4. Add a single privilege | 5. Click Save","Role=Front Desk Clerk; Description=Handles patient check-in; Privilege=Add Patients","Role is created and appears in the Manage Roles list with the assigned privilege and description","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-001","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0002","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Create a role that inherits from a parent role","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; role Nurse exists with clinical privileges","1. Click Add Role | 2. Enter role name | 3. Select Nurse as inherited role | 4. Click Save | 5. Open the new role and view effective privileges","Role=Senior Nurse; Inherited Role=Nurse","New role is created and inherits all privileges from Nurse plus any directly assigned ones","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-001","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0003","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Reject creating a role with a duplicate name","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; role Nurse already exists","1. Click Add Role | 2. Enter the name of an existing role | 3. Add a privilege | 4. Click Save","Role=Nurse","System rejects the save with a validation error indicating the role name already exists; no duplicate role is created","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-002","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0004","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Reject creating a role with an empty role name","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as System Administrator; on Add Role screen","1. Leave role name blank | 2. Enter a description | 3. Click Save","Role=(blank); Description=Test role","System blocks the save and displays a required-field validation error for role name","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0005","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Role name field boundary at maximum allowed length","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as System Administrator; on Add Role screen","1. Enter a role name at the maximum allowed character length | 2. Add a privilege | 3. Click Save | 4. Re-open the role to verify persistence","Role=AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA (50 chars)","Role is saved without truncation and persists at exactly the maximum length on reload","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0006","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Prevent deletion of a role currently assigned to active users","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; role Clerk is assigned to at least one active user","1. Open Manage Roles | 2. Select role Clerk | 3. Click Delete | 4. Confirm the prompt","Role=Clerk","System prevents deletion or warns that the role is in use; assigned users are not orphaned and retain a valid access state","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-003","Security; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0007","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Delete an unused custom role","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as System Administrator; custom role Temp Role exists and is assigned to no users","1. Open Manage Roles | 2. Select Temp Role | 3. Click Delete | 4. Confirm","Role=Temp Role","Role is removed from the Manage Roles list and can no longer be assigned","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-003","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0008","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Management","Create a new privilege and assign it to a role","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; on Administration > Manage Privileges","1. Click Add Privilege | 2. Enter privilege name | 3. Enter description | 4. Save | 5. Open a role and assign the new privilege | 6. Save the role","Privilege=Void Encounters; Role=Senior Nurse","Privilege is created and successfully assignable to a role; the role reflects the new privilege","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-004","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0009","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Management","Reject creating a privilege with a duplicate name","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as System Administrator; privilege Add Patients exists","1. Click Add Privilege | 2. Enter Add Patients | 3. Click Save","Privilege=Add Patients","System rejects the duplicate privilege name with a validation error","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-004","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0010","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Provisioning","Create a new user and assign a single role","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as System Administrator with Manage Users privilege; on Administration > Manage Users > Add User","1. Search/create the associated person | 2. Enter username | 3. Set a strong password | 4. Confirm password | 5. Assign role Nurse | 6. Click Save","Username=jnurse; Password=Nurse#2026!; Person=Jane Nurse; Role=Nurse","User account is created, appears in Manage Users, and can log in with the Nurse role privileges","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-005","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0011","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Provisioning","Create a user with multiple roles assigned","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; roles Nurse and Data Manager exist","1. Add User | 2. Enter username | 3. Set password and confirm | 4. Assign Nurse and Data Manager | 5. Save | 6. Log in as the new user and verify combined access","Username=jmulti; Password=Multi#2026!; Roles=Nurse,Data Manager","User receives the union of privileges from both roles and can access features from each","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-005","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0012","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Provisioning","Reject creating a user with a duplicate username","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; user jnurse already exists","1. Add User | 2. Enter username jnurse | 3. Set password and confirm | 4. Assign a role | 5. Click Save","Username=jnurse","System blocks creation and shows a validation error that the username is already taken","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-006","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0013","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Provisioning","Reject weak password not meeting complexity policy","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; password policy requires length, upper, lower, and digit","1. Add User | 2. Enter username | 3. Enter a weak password | 4. Confirm | 5. Click Save","Username=weakuser; Password=abc","System rejects the password with a complexity policy error and does not create the user","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-007","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0014","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Provisioning","Reject mismatched password and confirmation","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as System Administrator; on Add User screen","1. Enter username | 2. Enter password | 3. Enter a different confirmation password | 4. Click Save","Username=mmuser; Password=Strong#2026!; Confirm=Strong#2025!","System blocks save and displays a password mismatch validation error","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-007","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0015","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Provisioning","Create user with no role assigned (least privilege default)","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; on Add User screen","1. Enter username | 2. Set password and confirm | 3. Assign no roles | 4. Save | 5. Log in as that user","Username=noroleuser; Password=NoRole#2026!; Roles=(none)","User can authenticate but has only baseline Anonymous/Authenticated privileges and cannot access privileged apps","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-008","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0016","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Lifecycle","Disable (retire) an active user account","State Transition","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as System Administrator; active user jnurse exists and can log in","1. Open Manage Users | 2. Select jnurse | 3. Click Disable/Retire | 4. Enter a retire reason | 5. Save | 6. Attempt to log in as jnurse","Username=jnurse; Reason=Staff offboarded","Account transitions to disabled; subsequent login attempts are rejected with an account-disabled message","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-009","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0017","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Lifecycle","Re-enable a previously disabled user account","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; user jnurse is currently disabled/retired","1. Open Manage Users | 2. Select jnurse | 3. Click Enable/Unretire | 4. Save | 5. Log in as jnurse","Username=jnurse","Account transitions back to active and the user can log in with previously assigned roles intact","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-009","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0018","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Lifecycle","Active session of a user invalidated after account disable","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","User jnurse is logged in with an active session in browser B; administrator in browser A","1. In browser A disable jnurse | 2. In browser B perform a privileged action or navigate | 3. Observe session handling","Username=jnurse","The disabled user is denied further privileged actions and is forced to re-authenticate or is logged out","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-009","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0019","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Lifecycle","Reset a user password as administrator","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; user jnurse exists","1. Open Manage Users | 2. Select jnurse | 3. Click Change Password | 4. Enter a new strong password | 5. Confirm | 6. Save | 7. Log in as jnurse with new password","Username=jnurse; NewPassword=Reset#2026!","Password is updated; user can log in with the new password and the old password no longer works","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-007","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0020","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Menu Visibility","Registration Clerk sees only registration apps on home dashboard","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as a user with only the Registration Clerk role","1. Log in as the clerk | 2. Observe the home dashboard app tiles | 3. Enumerate visible apps","Username=clerk1; Role=Registration Clerk","Only registration-related apps (e.g. Register a Patient, Find Patient) are visible; clinical and admin apps are hidden","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-010","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0021","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Menu Visibility","Doctor sees clinical apps but not system administration","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as a user with only the Clinician/Doctor role","1. Log in as the doctor | 2. Inspect home dashboard tiles | 3. Attempt to locate the System Administration app","Username=doc1; Role=Clinician","Clinical apps are visible; the System Administration tile is not displayed for the doctor","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-010","Security; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0022","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Menu Visibility","System Administrator sees the full administration menu","Functional","Smoke","P1","High","Medium","Logged in as a user with the System Developer/Administrator role","1. Log in as admin | 2. Open the System Administration app | 3. Enumerate available admin sections","Username=admin; Role=System Administrator","All administration sections (Manage Users, Roles, Privileges, Global Properties) are visible and accessible","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-010","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0023","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Clerk without prescribe privilege cannot access ordering","Negative","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk lacking the Add Orders privilege; a patient chart is open","1. Open a patient dashboard | 2. Attempt to open the Orders/Drug Order entry | 3. Observe access","Patient=Test-001; Role=Registration Clerk","Order entry is not available to the clerk; the action is blocked with insufficient privileges","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-011","Patient Safety; Security; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0024","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Doctor with prescribe privilege can place a drug order","Functional","Sanity","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician with Add Orders privilege; patient chart open with an active visit","1. Open patient dashboard | 2. Start a visit if needed | 3. Open Drug Orders | 4. Add a medication | 5. Sign/save the order","Patient=Test-001; Drug=Paracetamol 500mg; Frequency=BID","Drug order is accepted and saved, appearing in the patient active orders list","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-011","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0025","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Nurse cannot void/delete an encounter without Delete Encounters privilege","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in as Nurse without Delete Encounters privilege; an encounter exists on a patient","1. Open patient dashboard | 2. Open an existing encounter | 3. Attempt to void/delete it","Patient=Test-002; Role=Nurse","The void/delete control is hidden or the action is denied with an insufficient-privileges error","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-011","Clinical; Data Integrity; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0026","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Clerk cannot edit clinical observations","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk; patient has recorded vitals/observations","1. Open patient dashboard | 2. Locate vitals/observations | 3. Attempt to edit an observation value","Patient=Test-003; Role=Registration Clerk","Editing controls for clinical observations are not available to the clerk; the action is blocked","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-011","Clinical; Patient Safety; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0027","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","User with View Patients but not Edit Patients can view but not modify demographics","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as a user holding View Patients but not Edit Patients privilege","1. Open patient demographics | 2. Confirm details are readable | 3. Attempt to open the edit demographics form","Patient=Test-004; Privileges=View Patients only","Demographics are visible read-only; the edit action is unavailable or denied","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-011","PHI/Privacy; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0028","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Privilege matrix across roles for core patient actions","Decision Table","Regression","P1","High","High","Test users provisioned for Clerk, Nurse, Doctor, Pharmacist, Admin; one shared test patient","1. For each role attempt Register, Edit Demographics, Record Vitals, Prescribe, Void Encounter | 2. Record allowed/denied per cell | 3. Compare against the expected matrix","Roles=Clerk,Nurse,Doctor,Pharmacist,Admin; Patient=Test-005","Each role allows only the actions in its expected matrix row; all other actions are denied consistently","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-012","Security; Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0029","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Unauthorized Access","Direct URL navigation to admin page by non-admin is denied","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Nurse (non-admin); admin user-management URL is known","1. While logged in as Nurse, paste the admin Manage Users URL into the address bar | 2. Submit | 3. Observe the response","URL=/admin/users/users.list; Role=Nurse","Access is denied (redirect to an error/login or insufficient-privilege page); the admin page is not rendered","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-013","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0030","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Unauthorized Access","Forced browsing to delete action endpoint is blocked server-side","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Nurse without Delete privileges; a delete endpoint pattern is known","1. Capture a delete request URL/parameters | 2. Replay it as the nurse session | 3. Observe server response and whether data changed","Endpoint=delete encounter; Role=Nurse","Server rejects the request with a 403/insufficient-privilege response and no data is deleted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-013","Security; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0031","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Escalation","Non-admin user cannot grant themselves additional roles","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as a standard Nurse user without Manage Users privilege","1. Attempt to open own user account edit screen | 2. Attempt to add the System Administrator role to self via UI or API | 3. Observe outcome","Username=jnurse; Target Role=System Administrator","Self-escalation is blocked; the user cannot modify their own role assignments and no new role is granted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-014","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0032","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Escalation","Vertical escalation via tampered role parameter on save user is rejected","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as a Data Manager who can edit some users but not assign admin role; intercept proxy available","1. Open edit user for a low-privilege account | 2. Intercept the save request | 3. Inject the System Administrator role id | 4. Forward the request","Target=staffuser; Injected Role=System Administrator","Server validates authorization and rejects the elevated role assignment; the target user does not receive admin","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-014","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0033","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Escalation","Horizontal access prevention across provider scope","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Two clinicians at different locations; patient belongs to provider A only","1. Log in as provider B | 2. Attempt to open provider A restricted patient or order via direct id | 3. Observe access","Provider=B; Patient owned by Provider A=Test-006","Provider B is prevented from accessing or modifying the other provider's restricted record per location/scope rules","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-015","PHI/Privacy; Security","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0034","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Audit","Admin action of creating a user is recorded in the audit log","Database","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; audit/logging enabled","1. Create a new user | 2. Open the audit/admin action log or query the audit table | 3. Locate the create-user entry","Username=audituser; Actor=admin","An audit entry records the actor, action type, target user, and timestamp for the user creation","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-016","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0035","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Audit","Role assignment change is captured with before/after values","Database","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; audit logging enabled; user jnurse exists","1. Add a role to jnurse and save | 2. Inspect the audit log entry | 3. Verify before and after role sets are captured","User=jnurse; Added Role=Data Manager","Audit log shows the role change with actor, timestamp, and the prior and new role assignments","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-016","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0036","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Audit","Failed unauthorized access attempts are logged for review","Security","Regression","P2","High","High","Audit logging enabled; a non-admin user available","1. As a non-admin attempt to access an admin endpoint and get denied | 2. Query the security/audit log | 3. Locate the denied-access record","Actor=jnurse; Endpoint=Manage Users","A log entry records the denied access attempt with user, target resource, and timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-016","Audit; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0037","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Authentication","Account locks after configured consecutive failed logins","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","High","Lockout policy configured for N failed attempts; user jnurse exists","1. Attempt login with wrong password N-1 times | 2. Verify account still active | 3. Submit one more wrong attempt | 4. Then submit the correct password","Username=jnurse; Wrong attempts=N; Threshold=N","Account is unlocked at N-1 failures and becomes locked exactly at the Nth failure; correct password is rejected while locked","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-017","Security","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0038","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Authentication","Successful login resets the failed-attempt counter","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Lockout policy configured; user jnurse has some recent failed attempts below threshold","1. Submit a few wrong passwords below threshold | 2. Submit the correct password to log in | 3. Log out | 4. Submit wrong passwords again and count to lock","Username=jnurse","Failed-attempt counter resets after a successful login; lockout requires a fresh full count of failures","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-017","Security","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0039","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Session Management","Idle session timeout enforces re-authentication","Security","System","P2","High","Medium","Session timeout configured; user logged in","1. Log in as any user | 2. Leave the session idle beyond the timeout | 3. Attempt a privileged action","Username=jnurse; Idle>timeout","Session expires and the user is required to re-authenticate before any privileged action proceeds","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-018","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0040","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Provisioning","Pairwise combinations of role, location scope, and account status","Pairwise","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; multiple locations configured","1. Provision users covering pairwise combos of {Clerk,Nurse,Doctor} x {Loc-A,Loc-B} x {Active,Disabled} | 2. Attempt a representative action per combo | 3. Record results","Roles=Clerk,Nurse,Doctor; Locations=A,B; Status=Active,Disabled","Each pairwise combination behaves per policy: disabled users denied entirely; active users limited to role-appropriate actions at their location","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-012","Security; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0041","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","API Authorization","REST API rejects privileged call without authentication","API","Regression","P1","Critical","High","OpenMRS REST module enabled; no session/credentials provided","1. Send a GET to a protected REST resource without auth header | 2. Observe HTTP status and body","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/user","API responds 401 Unauthorized and returns no protected user data","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-019","Security; API; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0042","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","API Authorization","REST API denies action when authenticated user lacks privilege","API","Regression","P1","Critical","High","OpenMRS REST module enabled; credentials for a Nurse without Manage Users","1. Authenticate as the nurse | 2. POST to create a user via REST | 3. Observe status and result","Endpoint=POST /ws/rest/v1/user; Actor=jnurse","API responds 403 Forbidden and no user is created","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-019","Security; API; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0043","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","API Authorization","REST API allows privileged call for authorized admin","API","Sanity","P2","High","Medium","OpenMRS REST module enabled; admin credentials available","1. Authenticate as admin via Basic Auth | 2. GET the list of users | 3. Validate response payload","Endpoint=GET /ws/rest/v1/user; Actor=admin","API responds 200 and returns the user list the admin is authorized to see","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-019","Security; API","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0044","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","API Authorization","Expired or invalid session token is rejected","API","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A previously valid session token that has since expired or been invalidated","1. Issue a REST call using the stale token | 2. Observe response","Token=expired-session-id","API rejects the request with 401 and does not return protected data","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-018","Security; API","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0045","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","FHIR Authorization","FHIR Patient read denied without SMART scope","FHIR","Integration","P1","Critical","High","FHIR R4 endpoint protected by SMART on FHIR; token lacks patient/Patient.read scope","1. Request GET /fhir/Patient/{id} with a token missing the read scope | 2. Observe status and OperationOutcome","Scope=launch/patient only; Resource=Patient/123","Server returns 403 with an OperationOutcome indicating insufficient scope; no patient data is returned","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-020","Standards-FHIR; Security; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-RBAC-0046","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","FHIR Authorization","FHIR write scope required to create a resource","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","High","FHIR endpoint with SMART scopes; token has read but not write scope","1. POST a new Observation with a read-only token | 2. Observe response","Scope=patient/Observation.read; Resource=Observation","Server returns 403 and does not persist the Observation; OperationOutcome cites missing write scope","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-020","Standards-FHIR; Security; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-RBAC-0047","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","FHIR Authorization","Patient-scoped token cannot access another patient's record","FHIR","Integration","P1","Critical","High","SMART patient-context token bound to Patient/123","1. Use the patient-context token to GET Patient/999 | 2. Observe response","Token patient=123; Requested=Patient/999","Cross-patient access is denied (403/404 per policy); only the in-context patient is retrievable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-015","Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy; Security","Standards"
"TC-RBAC-0048","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","HL7 Authorization","Inbound HL7 ADT from unauthorized sending facility is rejected","HL7","Integration","P2","High","High","HL7 interface engine configured to accept only allow-listed sending applications/facilities","1. Send an ADT^A01 from a non-allow-listed MSH-4 sending facility | 2. Observe ACK","MSH-3=ROGUE_APP; MSH-4=ROGUE_FAC; Message=ADT^A01","Interface returns an application reject ACK (AR) and does not process the patient admit","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-021","Standards-HL7; Security; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-RBAC-0049","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","HL7 Authorization","HL7 ORM order from a sender lacking order-entry authorization is blocked","HL7","Integration","P3","High","Medium","HL7 interface restricts order messages to authorized clinical systems","1. Send an ORM^O01 order from a sending application not authorized for orders | 2. Observe ACK and downstream order state","MSH-3=LAB_VIEWER; Message=ORM^O01","Order message is rejected with a negative ACK; no order is created in the receiving system","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-021","Standards-HL7; Patient Safety; Security","Standards"
"TC-RBAC-0050","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Accessibility","Manage Users form is fully keyboard navigable","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as System Administrator; on Add/Edit User form","1. Place focus at page start | 2. Tab through all fields and controls | 3. Operate role checkboxes and Save using keyboard only","Form=Add User","All interactive elements are reachable and operable via keyboard in a logical order with a visible focus indicator","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-022","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0051","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Accessibility","Role assignment controls expose accessible names to screen readers","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Screen reader active; on Add User role selection","1. Navigate the role checkboxes with a screen reader | 2. Listen to announced labels and states","Roles list with checkboxes","Each role control announces a meaningful accessible name and its checked/unchecked state","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-022","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0052","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Accessibility","Access-denied error message is announced and not color-only","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","A non-admin user triggering an insufficient-privilege error","1. Trigger an access-denied error | 2. Verify the message is conveyed via text and ARIA, not color alone | 3. Check screen reader announcement","Role=Nurse; Action=open admin","The error is presented as text with sufficient contrast and announced to assistive technology, not relying on color only","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-022","Accessibility; Security","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0053","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Removing a privilege from a role revokes access for its users","State Transition","Regression","P1","High","High","Role Nurse has Edit Patients; a nurse user can currently edit demographics","1. As admin remove Edit Patients from the Nurse role | 2. Save | 3. As the nurse re-attempt to edit demographics","Role=Nurse; Removed Privilege=Edit Patients","After removal, the nurse can no longer edit demographics; the action becomes denied","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-011","Security; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0054","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Inherited privilege removal cascades to child roles","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Parent role Nurse grants View Clinical; child role Senior Nurse inherits it","1. Remove View Clinical from Nurse | 2. Save | 3. Inspect effective privileges of Senior Nurse and its user","Parent=Nurse; Child=Senior Nurse; Privilege=View Clinical","Senior Nurse loses the inherited privilege unless directly assigned; its users lose corresponding access","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-001","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0055","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Exploratory","Explore privilege gaps by toggling individual privileges on a sandbox role","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Admin access; a sandbox role and test user available","1. Assign sandbox role one privilege at a time | 2. Probe which UI features and endpoints unlock | 3. Note any feature accessible without an obvious matching privilege","Role=Sandbox; Privileges toggled individually","Each unlocked feature maps to an intended privilege; any feature reachable without a guarding privilege is flagged as a defect","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-011","Security; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0056","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Exploratory","Explore behavior when a user holds conflicting allow/deny role intents","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Admin access; ability to assign multiple roles to one user","1. Assign a user two roles whose privilege sets overlap and diverge | 2. Attempt boundary actions | 3. Observe how the system resolves the union","Roles=Read-Only Viewer + Data Manager","System resolves privileges as a permissive union consistently; document the effective behavior and any surprising grants","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-012","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0057","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Pharmacist can dispense but cannot register new patients","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as a user with only the Pharmacist role","1. Open dispensing/medication workflow and confirm access | 2. Attempt to open Register a Patient","Role=Pharmacist; Patient=Test-007","Pharmacist can perform dispensing actions but the Register a Patient app is unavailable/denied","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-012","Clinical; Security","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0058","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Report viewer role can run reports but cannot edit patient data","Decision Table","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as a user with only the Report Viewer role","1. Open the Reports app and run a report | 2. Attempt to open a patient and edit data","Role=Report Viewer; Report=Daily Registrations","Reports run successfully; any attempt to edit patient data is denied","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-012","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0059","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Provisioning","Username boundary at minimum allowed length","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as System Administrator; username policy defines a minimum length","1. Enter a username one character below the minimum and try to save | 2. Then enter a username at exactly the minimum and save","MinUsername=2 chars; Try=a then ab","Below-minimum username is rejected; the exact-minimum username is accepted and the user is created","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-006","Data Integrity; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0060","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Provisioning","Reject username containing invalid characters","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as System Administrator; on Add User screen","1. Enter a username with disallowed special characters | 2. Set a valid password | 3. Click Save","Username=jdoe;DROP","System rejects the invalid username with a format validation error and creates no user","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-006","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0061","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Security","Stored XSS attempt in role description is neutralized","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; on Add Role","1. Enter a script payload in the role description | 2. Save | 3. View the role in a list and detail page","Description=<script>alert(1)</script>","The payload is escaped/encoded on output; no script executes when the role is viewed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-023","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0062","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Security","SQL injection in user search is not executed","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; on Manage Users search","1. Enter an SQL injection string into the user search field | 2. Submit | 3. Observe results and logs","Search=' OR '1'='1","Input is treated as literal text; no unauthorized data is returned and no SQL error/exposure occurs","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-023","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0063","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Database","Orphaned role-privilege mapping is not left after privilege deletion","Database","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Admin access with DB read; a privilege assigned to a role exists","1. Delete a privilege that is assigned to a role (if permitted) | 2. Query the role_privilege mapping table | 3. Verify referential integrity","Privilege=Void Encounters","No dangling role-privilege rows remain; deletion is either blocked or cascades cleanly preserving integrity","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-024","Data Integrity; Database","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0064","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Database","User password is stored hashed and salted, never plaintext","Database","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Admin access with DB read; a user with a known password exists","1. Create a user with a known password | 2. Query the user/credential table | 3. Inspect the stored password value","Username=hashcheck; Password=Known#2026!","The stored credential is a salted hash, not the plaintext password; no reversible password is persisted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-024","Security; PHI/Privacy; Database","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0065","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Escalation","Disabling the last administrator account is prevented","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Only one active System Administrator account remains","1. As that admin, attempt to disable/retire the sole remaining admin account | 2. Observe outcome","Username=admin (sole admin)","System prevents removing the last administrator, avoiding a lockout with no privileged account remaining","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-025","Security; Audit","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0066","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Anonymous (unauthenticated) user cannot reach any patient data","Negative","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","No user session; application login page reachable","1. Without logging in, navigate directly to a patient dashboard URL | 2. Observe response","URL=patient dashboard; Session=none","User is redirected to login; no patient data is exposed to the anonymous request","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-013","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0067","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Provider Management","Linking a user to a provider record enables provider-scoped actions","Integration","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Admin access; a user exists; a provider record exists","1. Open Manage Providers | 2. Link the provider to the user account | 3. Log in as the user and attempt a provider-required action (e.g. be selected as ordering provider)","User=doc1; Provider=Dr Test","The user becomes selectable as a provider and can perform provider-scoped clinical actions","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-026","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0068","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Provider Management","Retiring a provider removes them from active provider selection lists","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Admin access; an active provider exists and appears in selection lists","1. Retire the provider in Manage Providers | 2. Open an order/encounter provider dropdown | 3. Search for the retired provider","Provider=Dr Test","The retired provider no longer appears in active selection lists; existing references remain intact","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-026","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0069","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Session Management","Concurrent logins for same user honored per policy","Pairwise","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Concurrent-session policy defined; user jnurse exists","1. Log in as jnurse in two browsers | 2. Perform an action in each | 3. Observe whether both sessions are permitted or one is invalidated per policy","Username=jnurse; Sessions=2","Behavior matches the configured concurrent-session policy consistently (both allowed, or earliest invalidated)","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-018","Security","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0070","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Role Management","Editing a role description does not alter its privilege set","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Admin access; an existing role with known privileges","1. Open the role | 2. Change only the description | 3. Save | 4. Reopen and verify privileges unchanged","Role=Nurse; New Description=Updated text","Description updates while the privilege set remains exactly as before","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0071","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Read-only auditor role can view audit logs but cannot modify users","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","User with an Auditor role granting audit view but not user management","1. Open the audit log view and confirm read access | 2. Attempt to open Add/Edit User","Role=Auditor","Auditor can read audit data; user-management actions are denied","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-016","Audit; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0072","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","User Lifecycle","Newly created user is forced to change password on first login","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Admin access; force-change-on-first-login policy enabled","1. Create a user with a temporary password | 2. Log in as that user for the first time | 3. Observe the prompt","Username=firstlogin; TempPassword=Temp#2026!","User is required to set a new password before accessing the application","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-007","Security","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0073","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","User retains correct access after role rename","State Transition","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Admin access; role Clerk assigned to a user","1. Rename the role Clerk to Front Desk | 2. Save | 3. Log in as the assigned user and verify privileges","Old=Clerk; New=Front Desk","The user keeps the same effective privileges after the rename; access is unaffected by the name change","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-001","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0074","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Enforcement","Clerk can register a patient but cannot delete a patient","Decision Table","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk with Add Patients but not Delete Patients","1. Register a new patient successfully | 2. Open the patient and attempt to delete/void the patient record","Role=Registration Clerk; Patient=Test-008","Registration succeeds; the delete/void patient action is unavailable or denied","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-012","Security; Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0075","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","API Authorization","Privilege-protected REST endpoint enforces same rule as UI","API","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Nurse credentials lacking Delete Encounters; REST module enabled","1. Confirm in UI the void-encounter control is hidden for the nurse | 2. Call the equivalent REST DELETE/void as the nurse | 3. Compare outcomes","Endpoint=DELETE /ws/rest/v1/encounter/{uuid}; Actor=jnurse","REST enforces the same authorization as the UI and returns 403; no encounter is voided","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-019","Security; API; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-RBAC-0076","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Audit","Password reset by admin is logged without exposing the new password","Database","Regression","P2","High","High","Admin access; audit logging enabled; user jnurse exists","1. Reset jnurse password as admin | 2. Inspect the audit log entry | 3. Confirm content","User=jnurse; Action=Password reset","Audit records the reset event with actor, target, and timestamp; the new password value is not stored in the log","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RBAC-016","Audit; Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0077","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Privilege Escalation","API parameter tampering cannot assign a privilege the actor lacks","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Data Manager credentials that can edit roles but should not grant privileges they do not themselves hold","1. As Data Manager, send a role-update API call adding a high-risk privilege they lack | 2. Observe response and resulting role","Actor=datamgr; Injected Privilege=Manage Users","Server rejects assigning a privilege the actor does not hold (no privilege escalation); role is unchanged","Manual-Only","REQ-RBAC-014","Security; Audit; API","Platform"
"TC-RBAC-0078","Roles, Privileges & User Admin","Menu Visibility","Disabled app/privilege hides corresponding home dashboard tile","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Admin access; a user whose only role grants one app","1. Remove that app's guarding privilege from the role | 2. Save | 3. Log in as the user and view the dashboard","Role with single app privilege removed","The corresponding app tile no longer appears on the user's dashboard","Automatable","REQ-RBAC-010","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0001","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Duplicate Patients","Merge two duplicate patient records selecting preferred record and verify surviving record","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as System Administrator with Merge Patients privilege; two confirmed duplicate patient records exist in the system","1. Navigate to Data Management and open Merge Patients | 2. Enter the identifiers of both patient records | 3. Click Search to load both records side by side | 4. Select the record on the left as the preferred (surviving) record | 5. Review demographic differences highlighted between records | 6. Click Merge Patients | 7. Confirm the merge in the dialog","Patient A=John Tester (ID 10001); Patient B=Jon Tester (ID 10002); Preferred=10001","The two records are merged into the preferred record 10001, the non-preferred record 10002 is voided and marked as merged, and the patient dashboard shows a single consolidated record","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-001","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0002","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Duplicate Patients","Verify all encounters from non-preferred patient are transferred to preferred patient after merge","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as System Administrator; non-preferred patient has at least 3 encounters with observations","1. Open Merge Patients and load both duplicate records | 2. Note encounter count on each record | 3. Select preferred record | 4. Execute the merge | 5. Open the preferred patient dashboard | 6. Open the Visits and Encounters section | 7. Count and inspect transferred encounters","Preferred=10001 (2 encounters); Non-preferred=10002 (3 encounters)","All 5 encounters appear under the preferred patient 10001 with original encounter dates, providers and observations intact; no encounters are lost or duplicated","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-002","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0003","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Duplicate Patients","Verify all identifiers from non-preferred patient are preserved on preferred patient after merge","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; both patients have distinct identifiers of different identifier types","1. Open Merge Patients and load both records | 2. Record identifiers on each patient | 3. Select preferred record | 4. Execute merge | 5. Open preferred patient demographics | 6. Review the Identifiers section","Preferred has OpenMRS ID 10001; Non-preferred has Old Medical Record 88-77-66","After merge the preferred patient retains its own identifier and also carries the non-preferred identifier 88-77-66 as an additional identifier; no identifier is silently discarded","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-002","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0004","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Field Resolution","Resolve conflicting demographic fields during merge using decision table of field sources","Decision Table","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; both patients have conflicting gender, birthdate and address values","1. Open Merge Patients and load conflicting records | 2. For each highlighted conflicting field choose the source record | 3. Select gender from record A, birthdate from record B, address from record A | 4. Review the resolution summary | 5. Execute merge | 6. Verify resulting field values","Gender: A=Female B=Male choose A; DOB: A=01-Jan-1980 B=02-Feb-1980 choose B; City: A=Boston B=Salem choose A","The merged record reflects Female gender, 02-Feb-1980 birthdate, and Boston city exactly per the chosen sources; unchosen values are not retained in active fields","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-003","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0005","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Field Resolution","Merge resolution decision table covering all combinations of preferred-vs-nonpreferred name selection","Decision Table","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; multiple name and address combinations exist on both records","1. Load both records into Merge Patients | 2. Apply combination row 1 (name=A, address=A) and merge a test pair | 3. Repeat for combination name=A address=B | 4. Repeat for name=B address=A | 5. Repeat for name=B address=B | 6. Verify each merged outcome against the table","Combos: AA, AB, BA, BB across 4 disposable duplicate pairs","Each of the four field-source combinations produces a merged record whose name and address exactly match the selected sources defined in the decision table","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-003","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0006","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Duplicate Patients","Prevent merging a patient record with itself","Negative","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator on the Merge Patients screen","1. Open Merge Patients | 2. Enter the same patient identifier in both the first and second search field | 3. Attempt to load both records | 4. Attempt to proceed to merge","Patient ID 10001 entered in both fields","The system blocks the operation with a validation message indicating a patient cannot be merged with itself; no merge is performed","Automatable","REQ-DATA-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0007","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Duplicate Patients","Prevent merging when the non-preferred patient is already voided","Negative","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; one candidate patient record is already voided","1. Open Merge Patients | 2. Enter a valid active patient and a voided patient | 3. Attempt to load both records | 4. Attempt to execute merge","Active=10001; Voided=10009","The system prevents the merge and shows a clear message that a voided patient cannot participate in a merge; record state is unchanged","Automatable","REQ-DATA-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0008","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Data Integrity","Verify referential integrity of orders and allergies after patient merge","Database","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as System Administrator with database read access; non-preferred patient has active drug orders and allergy records","1. Capture pre-merge counts of orders and allergies for both patients via SQL | 2. Execute merge selecting preferred record | 3. Query orders table filtered by preferred patient id | 4. Query allergies for preferred patient | 5. Confirm no orphaned rows reference the voided patient as active","SELECT count(*) FROM orders WHERE patient_id IN (10001,10002); allergy rows for 10002","All orders and allergies previously linked to the non-preferred patient now reference the preferred patient id; no active clinical row is orphaned or points to the voided patient","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-004","Data Integrity; Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0009","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Audit","Verify an audit log entry is created capturing who merged which patients and when","Security","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; audit logging enabled","1. Note current timestamp and user | 2. Execute a patient merge | 3. Navigate to the audit log or person merge log | 4. Locate the merge entry | 5. Inspect captured fields","Merging 10001 (preferred) and 10002 by user admin","An immutable audit entry records the acting user, both patient ids, the preferred record, and a timestamp; the entry cannot be edited from the UI","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-005","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0010","Data Management & Integrity","Void Patient","Void (soft-delete) a patient record with a void reason and confirm it is excluded from search","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator with Delete Patients privilege; an active test patient exists","1. Open the patient dashboard for the test patient | 2. Choose the Delete (Void) Patient action | 3. Enter a void reason | 4. Confirm the void | 5. Return to patient search and search by name | 6. Search again including voided records","Patient=Mary Synthetic (ID 10050); Reason=Created in error","The patient is soft-deleted with the void reason stored; the patient no longer appears in standard search but the underlying record is retained and retrievable by an admin including-voided search","Automatable","REQ-DATA-006","Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0011","Data Management & Integrity","Void Patient","Require a non-empty void reason when voiding a patient","Negative","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator on a patient dashboard","1. Open the Delete (Void) Patient action | 2. Leave the void reason field empty | 3. Attempt to confirm the void","Void reason = (empty)","The system rejects the action and displays a validation message that a void reason is required; the patient remains active","Automatable","REQ-DATA-006","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0012","Data Management & Integrity","Undelete Patient","Unvoid (restore) a previously voided patient and verify clinical data is restored","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; a voided patient with prior encounters exists","1. Locate the voided patient via include-voided search | 2. Open the record | 3. Choose Restore (Unvoid) Patient | 4. Confirm the restore | 5. Search for the patient in standard search | 6. Open encounters and observations","Voided patient Mary Synthetic (ID 10050)","The patient is restored to active status, reappears in standard search, and all previously associated encounters and observations are accessible again","Automatable","REQ-DATA-007","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0013","Data Management & Integrity","Void vs Hard Delete","Verify void is reversible whereas purge permanently removes the record (soft vs hard delete)","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as System Administrator; access to both Void and Purge operations on disposable test patients","1. Void patient X and confirm it is recoverable via unvoid | 2. Unvoid patient X to confirm reversibility | 3. Void patient Y | 4. Purge (permanently delete) patient Y | 5. Attempt to locate patient Y via include-voided search","Patient X=10060 (void/unvoid); Patient Y=10061 (void then purge)","Patient X transitions active to voided to active reversibly; Patient Y after purge is permanently removed and cannot be found by any search or restore action","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-008","Data Integrity; Patient Safety; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0014","Data Management & Integrity","Patient Lifecycle States","Validate full state transition lifecycle active to voided to unvoided to purged","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator with privileges for void, unvoid and purge","1. Create a disposable patient (state=active) | 2. Void it (state=voided) | 3. Unvoid it (state=active) | 4. Void it again (state=voided) | 5. Purge it (state=purged) | 6. After each transition verify visibility and recoverability","Disposable patient ID 10070","Each transition behaves per the state model: voided is hidden but recoverable, unvoided is fully active, purged is irrecoverable; no invalid transition (e.g. unvoid after purge) is permitted","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-008","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0015","Data Management & Integrity","Identifier Uniqueness","Reject creation of a patient with a duplicate identifier of a unique identifier type","Negative","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk; an existing patient already holds identifier value of a uniqueness-enforced type","1. Start registering a new patient | 2. Enter valid demographics | 3. Enter the identifier value already used by an existing patient | 4. Attempt to save the record","Existing OpenMRS ID = 10001-5; new patient reuses 10001-5","The system rejects the save with a duplicate identifier validation error; no new patient record is created","Automatable","REQ-DATA-009","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0016","Data Management & Integrity","Identifier Uniqueness","Validate identifier check digit (Luhn mod-30) for OpenMRS identifier type","Boundary","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Registration Clerk; OpenMRS Identifier type with Luhn check digit validator is configured","1. Begin patient registration | 2. Enter an identifier with an invalid check digit | 3. Attempt to save | 4. Correct to a valid check-digit identifier | 5. Save again","Invalid=10001-9; Valid=10001-5","The invalid check-digit identifier is rejected with a format validation error while the valid check-digit identifier is accepted and saved","Automatable","REQ-DATA-009","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0017","Data Management & Integrity","Identifier Uniqueness","Verify duplicate identifiers are surfaced after merge when both patients shared the same identifier value","Negative","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; both duplicate patients hold the same identifier value of the same type","1. Load both duplicates into Merge Patients | 2. Note both carry identifier value 10001-5 | 3. Select preferred record | 4. Execute merge | 5. Review identifiers on merged record","Both patients carry OpenMRS ID 10001-5","The merged record retains a single instance of the shared identifier without creating a duplicate identifier row; uniqueness constraint is upheld post-merge","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0018","Data Management & Integrity","Bulk Operations","Bulk void a list of test patients and confirm count and per-record outcome","Functional","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; a list of 50 disposable test patients exists","1. Select 50 test patients for bulk void | 2. Provide a common void reason | 3. Submit the bulk operation | 4. Wait for completion summary | 5. Spot-check 5 records | 6. Verify total active count decreased by 50","50 patient IDs 11000-11049; Reason=Bulk test cleanup","All 50 patients are voided, the operation summary reports 50 succeeded and 0 failed, and spot-checked records show the void reason; active patient count drops by exactly 50","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-010","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATA-0019","Data Management & Integrity","Bulk Operations","Verify partial-failure handling in a bulk void when some records are already voided","Negative","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; a bulk list mixes active and already-voided patients","1. Submit a bulk void of 20 patients where 5 are already voided | 2. Wait for completion | 3. Review the per-record result report","20 IDs, 5 of which are pre-voided","The operation completes with 15 succeeded and 5 skipped/failed clearly itemized; the bulk job does not abort entirely and already-voided records are not double-processed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-010","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATA-0020","Data Management & Integrity","Bulk Operations","Boundary test bulk operation at maximum supported batch size","Boundary","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; configured maximum bulk batch size is known","1. Prepare a batch exactly at the configured maximum size | 2. Submit the bulk operation | 3. Confirm it processes | 4. Prepare a batch of maximum size plus one | 5. Submit and observe handling","Max batch = 500; tests at 500 and 501 records","The batch at exactly the maximum size processes successfully; the batch exceeding the maximum is rejected or paged with a clear message and no partial corruption","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-010","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATA-0021","Data Management & Integrity","Referential Integrity","Prevent purge of a patient with dependent clinical records unless cascade is explicitly chosen","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as System Administrator; a patient has encounters, orders and observations","1. Attempt to purge a patient that has dependent clinical records | 2. Observe the system response | 3. If a cascade option is offered, decline it | 4. Re-attempt purge without cascade","Patient 10080 with 4 encounters and 6 observations","The system blocks the hard delete due to referential dependencies (or requires explicit cascade confirmation); no orphaned encounter or observation rows are left behind","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-011","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0022","Data Management & Integrity","Referential Integrity","Database verification that voiding a patient cascades void flags to dependent person rows","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator with DB read access; patient with person_name and person_address rows","1. Capture voided flags on person, person_name, person_address before void | 2. Void the patient via UI | 3. Re-query the same rows | 4. Compare voided flags and void_reason fields","Patient person_id 10090","Dependent person_name and person_address rows reflect consistent voided handling and the patient row carries voided=1 with a void_reason and voided_by populated","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-006","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0023","Data Management & Integrity","Merge API","Merge two patients via REST API and verify response and resulting state","API","Integration","P1","High","High","Valid REST session/credentials for a user with merge privilege; two duplicate patient UUIDs known","1. Send POST to the person merge or patient merge REST endpoint with preferred and non-preferred UUIDs | 2. Inspect HTTP status and response body | 3. GET the preferred patient resource | 4. GET the non-preferred patient resource","preferred UUID and nonPreferred UUID payload","The API returns a success status, the preferred patient now owns the merged data, and the non-preferred patient is voided; response reflects the merge outcome","Automatable","REQ-DATA-001","API; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0024","Data Management & Integrity","Merge API","Reject merge API call when caller lacks merge privilege","Security","Integration","P1","High","High","Valid REST credentials for a low-privilege user without merge rights","1. Authenticate as a clerk-level user | 2. Send the merge POST request with valid UUIDs | 3. Inspect the response status and body","Clerk token; valid preferred and nonPreferred UUIDs","The API responds with 403 Forbidden (or 401 if unauthenticated) and performs no merge; both patient records remain unchanged","Automatable","REQ-DATA-012","Security; API; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0025","Data Management & Integrity","Merge API","Reject merge API call with a malformed or non-existent patient UUID","Negative","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Valid REST credentials with merge privilege","1. Send merge POST with a syntactically invalid UUID | 2. Inspect response | 3. Send merge POST with a well-formed but non-existent UUID | 4. Inspect response","badUUID=not-a-uuid; ghostUUID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","Malformed UUID yields a 400 Bad Request and non-existent UUID yields a 404 Not Found; no merge occurs and no server error is exposed","Automatable","REQ-DATA-001","API; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0026","Data Management & Integrity","FHIR Patient Resource","Verify FHIR Patient.active flag reflects voided status after soft-delete","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","High","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; a patient exists and is then voided","1. GET Patient by id via FHIR R4 and note active=true | 2. Void the patient in the system | 3. GET the same Patient resource again | 4. Inspect the active element","GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient/{id}","Before void the resource shows active=true; after void the resource shows active=false (or the patient is excluded per server policy), consistent with the soft-delete state","Automatable","REQ-DATA-013","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DATA-0027","Data Management & Integrity","FHIR Patient Resource","Verify FHIR Patient $merge / link maintains references after merge","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; duplicate patients merged via the system","1. Merge two patients | 2. GET the non-preferred FHIR Patient | 3. Inspect Patient.link for replaced-by reference | 4. GET the preferred Patient and confirm it remains active","Non-preferred Patient id and preferred Patient id","The non-preferred FHIR Patient carries a link of type replaced-by pointing to the preferred patient (or returns 410 Gone per policy); the preferred remains active=true","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-013","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DATA-0028","Data Management & Integrity","FHIR Identifier","Validate FHIR Patient.identifier system URI and value correctness for identifier types","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; patient has a configured identifier type","1. GET Patient resource | 2. Inspect each identifier entry | 3. Verify system URI matches the configured identifier type URI | 4. Verify value matches the stored identifier","Patient with OpenMRS ID type","Each FHIR identifier element has a correct and stable system URI and a value that exactly matches the stored identifier; no identifier is emitted without a system","Automatable","REQ-DATA-009","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DATA-0029","Data Management & Integrity","HL7 ADT Merge","Verify HL7 v2 ADT^A40 patient merge message updates the surviving identifier correctly","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 v2 inbound interface configured to accept ADT^A40 merge messages","1. Send an ADT^A40 message with MRG segment containing the prior patient identifier | 2. Capture the ACK | 3. Query the patient record by the surviving identifier | 4. Query by the prior (merged) identifier","ADT^A40; PID-3 survivor=10001; MRG-1 prior=10002","An AA acknowledgement is returned, the surviving identifier 10001 is retained, and the prior identifier 10002 resolves to the surviving record per merge semantics","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-014","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DATA-0030","Data Management & Integrity","HL7 ADT Delete","Verify HL7 v2 ADT^A23 delete patient information message is handled or rejected per policy","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 v2 inbound interface configured; policy for delete messages defined","1. Send an ADT^A23 delete patient information message | 2. Capture the acknowledgement | 3. Verify the patient state in the system","ADT^A23 for PID 10005","The interface returns an appropriate ACK (AA if supported, AR/AE if not) and the patient state matches the documented policy; an unsupported message never silently corrupts data","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-014","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DATA-0031","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Pairwise","Pairwise coverage of merge variables: identifier overlap, encounter presence, address conflict, gender conflict","Pairwise","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; ability to construct controlled duplicate pairs","1. Construct pair 1 (idOverlap=yes, encounters=both, addrConflict=yes, genderConflict=no) and merge | 2. Construct pair 2 (idOverlap=no, encounters=oneSide, addrConflict=no, genderConflict=yes) and merge | 3. Construct pair 3 (idOverlap=yes, encounters=none, addrConflict=no, genderConflict=yes) and merge | 4. Construct pair 4 (idOverlap=no, encounters=both, addrConflict=yes, genderConflict=no) and merge | 5. Verify each merged outcome","4 pairwise-derived duplicate pairs as described","Each pairwise combination merges without error and the surviving record is internally consistent for identifiers, encounters, address and gender per the chosen sources","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-003","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0032","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Exploratory","Exploratory session probing merge behavior with unusual data (long names, diacritics, many encounters)","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; a duplicate pair with edge-case data prepared","1. Prepare duplicates with very long names, Unicode diacritics, and 100+ encounters on one side | 2. Attempt the merge | 3. Observe UI rendering, performance and field resolution | 4. Verify post-merge record integrity and search","Names with accents; 100+ encounters; 4000-char address note","The merge completes within acceptable time, Unicode and long values render and persist correctly without truncation corruption, and the surviving record passes a basic integrity review; any anomaly is logged as a finding","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-003","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0033","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Data Integrity","Verify no orphaned visits remain after merging patients with overlapping visit dates","Database","Integration","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator with DB access; both patients have visits including overlapping dates","1. Record visit ids for both patients pre-merge | 2. Execute merge | 3. Query visit table for the preferred patient | 4. Query visit table for the voided patient id | 5. Confirm visit-encounter linkage consistency","Patient 10001 and 10002 with overlapping visit dates","All visits reference the preferred patient, no visit references the voided patient as active, and each encounter still links to a valid visit; no orphaned or dangling visit rows exist","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-004","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0034","Data Management & Integrity","Concurrency","Verify concurrent merge attempts on the same patient pair are serialized safely","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Two admin sessions open; same duplicate pair loaded in both","1. In session 1 begin and submit the merge | 2. Near-simultaneously in session 2 submit the same merge | 3. Observe both responses | 4. Inspect the final record state","Both sessions merge 10001 and 10002","Exactly one merge succeeds; the second attempt is rejected or no-ops gracefully because the non-preferred is already voided; no double-processing or data corruption occurs","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-004","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-DATA-0035","Data Management & Integrity","Void Patient","Verify voided patient data is excluded from clinical reports and patient lists","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; a voided patient previously appeared in a patient list report","1. Confirm patient appears in a patient list before voiding | 2. Void the patient | 3. Re-run the same patient list report | 4. Re-run an active patients dashboard widget","Voided patient 10050","After voiding, the patient is excluded from standard clinical reports and active patient lists while remaining retrievable through explicit voided/admin views","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-006","Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0036","Data Management & Integrity","Access Control","Verify a Registration Clerk cannot access merge or purge functions","Security","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as a Registration Clerk without admin privileges","1. Attempt to navigate to the Merge Patients screen | 2. Attempt to access the purge/permanent delete action | 3. Attempt the operations directly via known URLs","Clerk role user","The merge and purge functions are not visible and direct URL access is denied with an authorization error; the clerk cannot perform destructive data operations","Automatable","REQ-DATA-012","Security; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0037","Data Management & Integrity","Data Integrity Audit","Verify void reason, voided_by user and date_voided are captured and immutable","Audit","System","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; a patient is voided","1. Void a patient with a specific reason | 2. Open the record details or query audit fields | 3. Verify voided_by, date_voided and void_reason are populated | 4. Attempt to alter these fields from the UI","Reason=Duplicate of 10001; user=admin","All three audit fields are correctly populated with the acting user, timestamp and reason; the fields are read-only and cannot be edited after the fact","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-005","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0038","Data Management & Integrity","Identifier Uniqueness","Boundary test identifier length limits at minimum and maximum allowed characters","Boundary","System","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Registration Clerk; identifier type with defined format/length","1. Enter an identifier one character below the minimum length and attempt save | 2. Enter at exactly the minimum length | 3. Enter at exactly the maximum length | 4. Enter one character above the maximum","Min=4, Max=20; tests at 3,4,20,21 chars","Identifiers below minimum and above maximum are rejected with a format error; identifiers at exactly the minimum and maximum boundary are accepted","Automatable","REQ-DATA-009","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0039","Data Management & Integrity","Undelete Patient","Prevent unvoid of a patient whose preferred merge target makes restoration ambiguous","Negative","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; a patient was voided as part of a merge into another patient","1. Locate the merged (non-preferred) voided patient | 2. Attempt to unvoid it | 3. Observe system handling and any warning","Non-preferred merged patient 10002","The system either prevents the unvoid with a message that the record was merged, or warns that restoration may create a duplicate; the merge audit trail is preserved either way","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-007","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0040","Data Management & Integrity","Bulk Operations","Bulk export of patient data set maintains record count and field integrity","Database","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; a defined cohort of patients exists for export","1. Note the source cohort count and key fields | 2. Run the bulk export | 3. Open the export output | 4. Compare exported row count and sampled field values to source","Cohort of 200 synthetic patients","The export row count equals the source cohort count and sampled identifier, name and birthdate fields match the source exactly; no records are dropped or duplicated","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-010","Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-DATA-0041","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Smoke","Smoke test that the Merge Patients screen loads and accepts two valid records","Functional","Smoke","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; two valid patients exist","1. Navigate to Data Management | 2. Open Merge Patients | 3. Enter two valid patient identifiers | 4. Click Search","Patients 10001 and 10002","The Merge Patients screen loads without error and displays both patient records side by side ready for comparison","Automatable","REQ-DATA-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0042","Data Management & Integrity","Accessibility","Verify Merge Patients screen is keyboard navigable and screen-reader labelled","Accessibility","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; assistive technology (screen reader) available","1. Open Merge Patients using keyboard only | 2. Tab through search fields, record panels and field-resolution controls | 3. Verify focus order and visible focus indicator | 4. Verify each radio/control has an accessible label announced by the screen reader","Keyboard + screen reader","All interactive elements are reachable and operable by keyboard with a visible focus indicator, and field-resolution controls have descriptive accessible labels meeting WCAG 2.1 AA","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-015","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-DATA-0043","Data Management & Integrity","Cross-Platform Adapter","Verify merge behavior is consistent across OpenMRS and adapter-backed platforms via Resource Adapter Layer","Functional","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Resource Adapter Layer configured against at least two backends (OpenMRS and omiiCARE)","1. Perform an equivalent merge through the adapter against OpenMRS | 2. Perform the equivalent merge through the adapter against omiiCARE | 3. Compare surviving record structure, identifier handling and void semantics","Equivalent duplicate pairs on each backend","The adapter produces functionally equivalent merge outcomes on both backends (surviving record, transferred encounters, voided non-preferred) within documented adapter mapping rules","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-016","Data Integrity; Standards-FHIR","Platform"
"TC-DATA-0044","Data Management & Integrity","Referential Integrity","Verify provider, user and relationship references are repointed or preserved after merge","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator with DB access; non-preferred patient has relationships and a linked provider record","1. Record relationship and provider links pre-merge | 2. Execute merge | 3. Query relationship table for both patient ids | 4. Verify provider linkage on the surviving record","Patient 10002 has a parent relationship and provider link","Relationships are repointed to the preferred patient without duplication, provider linkage remains valid, and no relationship row references the voided patient as an active endpoint","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-004","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATA-0045","Data Management & Integrity","Data Retention","Verify purge of a patient with audit/retention hold is blocked per compliance policy","Security","System","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as System Administrator; a patient is flagged under a legal/retention hold","1. Attempt to purge a patient under retention hold | 2. Observe the system response | 3. Verify the patient record is unchanged | 4. Review the compliance log entry","Patient 10099 flagged legal-hold","The purge is blocked with a compliance message referencing the retention hold, the record remains intact, and the blocked attempt is logged for audit","Manual-Only","REQ-DATA-017","Regulatory/Compliance; Audit; Security","Platform"
"TC-DATA-0046","Data Management & Integrity","Identifier Uniqueness","Verify case and whitespace normalization prevents near-duplicate identifiers","Negative","System","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Registration Clerk; identifier type with normalization configured","1. Create a patient with identifier value ABC-123 | 2. Attempt to create another patient with identifier value abc-123 (different case) | 3. Attempt with leading/trailing spaces around ABC-123","Existing=ABC-123; attempts=abc-123 and ' ABC-123 '","The system treats case and surrounding whitespace consistently per its normalization rules, preventing creation of conflicting near-duplicate identifiers or clearly allowing them by documented policy","Automatable","REQ-DATA-009","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATA-0047","Data Management & Integrity","Merge Data Integrity","Verify obs and diagnosis records retain original encounter linkage after merge","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Logged in as System Administrator; non-preferred patient has observations and a coded diagnosis tied to specific encounters","1. Record the obs and diagnosis with their encounter ids pre-merge | 2. Execute merge | 3. Open the surviving patient encounters | 4. Verify each obs and diagnosis still links to its original encounter and value","Obs vitals and ICD-coded diagnosis on encounter 5001","After merge each observation and diagnosis remains attached to its original encounter with unchanged values and codes under the surviving patient; no clinical datum is reassigned or lost","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATA-002","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0001","Reporting & Audit Logging","Run Report","Run a built-in patient summary report with valid parameters","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Data Manager with Reports privilege; at least one published report definition exists in the RefApp Reports module","1. Open the Reports app from the home screen | 2. Select the Patient Summary report from the list | 3. Enter the required parameters | 4. Click Run | 5. Wait for the report to render","ReportName=Patient Summary; StartDate=01-Jan-2026; EndDate=31-Jan-2026","Report runs to completion, status shows Completed, and a result table with patient rows matching the criteria is displayed","Automatable","REQ-RPT-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0002","Reporting & Audit Logging","Run Report","Verify report status transitions from Requested to Completed","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; a long-running report definition is available","1. Trigger the report run | 2. Observe the status immediately after submit | 3. Poll the report status page until it changes | 4. Confirm the final status","ReportName=Active Visits","Status transitions Requested -> In Progress -> Completed without entering a Failed state, and the result becomes downloadable only after Completed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0003","Reporting & Audit Logging","Run Report","Cancel an in-progress report run and verify state","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; a report is currently In Progress","1. Start a long-running report | 2. While status is In Progress click Cancel | 3. Confirm the cancellation prompt | 4. Refresh the report queue","ReportName=Encounters by Location","Report status changes to Cancelled, no result file is produced, and the queue no longer shows it as active","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0004","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Date Range","Run report with valid start and end date range","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; report requires a date range parameter","1. Select a date-range report | 2. Enter a valid start date | 3. Enter a valid end date after the start date | 4. Click Run","StartDate=01-Mar-2026; EndDate=31-Mar-2026","Report returns only records whose dates fall within the inclusive range and the parameter values are echoed in the report header","Automatable","REQ-RPT-002","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0005","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Date Range","Reject end date earlier than start date","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; date-range report selected","1. Enter a start date | 2. Enter an end date that precedes the start date | 3. Click Run","StartDate=31-Mar-2026; EndDate=01-Mar-2026","A validation error is shown, the report does not run, and no result is generated","Automatable","REQ-RPT-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0006","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Date Range","Boundary single-day range start equals end","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Data Manager; date-range report selected","1. Set start date and end date to the same calendar day | 2. Click Run","StartDate=15-Mar-2026; EndDate=15-Mar-2026","Report runs and returns records timestamped within that single day inclusive of 00:00:00 to 23:59:59","Automatable","REQ-RPT-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0007","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Date Range","Reject malformed date input","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; date-range report selected","1. Type an invalid date string into the start date field | 2. Attempt to run the report","StartDate=2026-13-45; EndDate=31-Mar-2026","Field-level validation rejects the input, report does not submit, and the user is prompted to correct the date","Automatable","REQ-RPT-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0008","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Date Range","Far-future and far-past boundary dates","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Data Manager; date-range report selected","1. Set start date to 01-Jan-1900 | 2. Set end date to 31-Dec-2099 | 3. Click Run","StartDate=01-Jan-1900; EndDate=31-Dec-2099","Report accepts the extreme but valid range and completes without overflow or crash, returning all matching records","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0009","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Location","Run report filtered by a single location","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; multiple locations configured; report has a location parameter","1. Select a location-aware report | 2. Choose a single location from the dropdown | 3. Run the report","Location=Outpatient Clinic","Result contains only records associated with the selected location and excludes records from other locations","Automatable","REQ-RPT-003","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0010","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Location","Run report across multiple selected locations","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; report supports multi-select location","1. Select a location-aware report | 2. Select two or more locations | 3. Run the report","Location=Outpatient Clinic; Location=Inpatient Ward","Result aggregates records from all selected locations and none from unselected locations","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-003","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0011","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Location","Run report with no location selected when required","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; location parameter is mandatory","1. Select a report requiring a location | 2. Leave location unselected | 3. Click Run","Location=(none)","Validation prevents the run and prompts that location is required","Automatable","REQ-RPT-003","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0012","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Pairwise","Pairwise combination of date range, location, and format","Pairwise","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; report supports date range, location, and export format parameters","1. Select date range valid | 2. Select location Inpatient Ward | 3. Select format CSV | 4. Run | 5. Repeat with empty range, all locations, PDF | 6. Repeat with single-day, single location, Excel","Combo1=ValidRange+Inpatient+CSV; Combo2=Empty+All+PDF; Combo3=SingleDay+Outpatient+Excel","Each parameter combination produces a consistent and correct result without errors, validating interaction coverage","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0013","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Decision Table","Decision table for parameter validity combinations","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; report with mandatory date range and optional location","1. Run with valid dates and location present | 2. Run with valid dates and location absent | 3. Run with invalid dates and location present | 4. Run with invalid dates and location absent","Rule1=ValidDate+Loc; Rule2=ValidDate+NoLoc; Rule3=BadDate+Loc; Rule4=BadDate+NoLoc","Rules 1 and 2 succeed, Rules 3 and 4 are blocked with validation errors; outcomes match the documented decision table","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0014","Reporting & Audit Logging","Export-CSV","Export a completed report to CSV","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; a completed report is displayed","1. Open a completed report | 2. Click Export | 3. Select CSV format | 4. Save the file | 5. Open the CSV in a spreadsheet tool","ReportName=Patient Summary; Format=CSV","A well-formed CSV downloads with a header row, one row per record, and values matching the on-screen result","Automatable","REQ-RPT-004","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0015","Reporting & Audit Logging","Export-PDF","Export a completed report to PDF","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; a completed report is displayed","1. Open a completed report | 2. Click Export | 3. Select PDF format | 4. Save and open the PDF","ReportName=Patient Summary; Format=PDF","A paginated PDF is produced with report title, run parameters, and tabular data legibly rendered","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-004","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0016","Reporting & Audit Logging","Export-Excel","Export a completed report to Excel","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; a completed report is displayed","1. Open a completed report | 2. Click Export | 3. Select Excel (xlsx) format | 4. Save and open the workbook","ReportName=Encounters; Format=Excel","An xlsx workbook downloads with correctly typed columns (dates as dates, numbers as numbers) and complete data","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-004","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0017","Reporting & Audit Logging","Export-CSV","CSV injection protection for formula-leading cell values","Security","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Data Manager; a patient name field contains a formula-like value","1. Ensure a record has a value beginning with = or + or - or @ | 2. Export the report to CSV | 3. Open the CSV in a spreadsheet","PatientName==2+5+cmd; Format=CSV","Leading formula characters are neutralized (prefixed/escaped) so no executable formula runs when opened, preventing CSV injection","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-005","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0018","Reporting & Audit Logging","Export-CSV","CSV preserves UTF-8 special characters and diacritics","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Data Manager; records contain non-ASCII names","1. Run a report including patients with accented names | 2. Export to CSV with UTF-8 | 3. Open the file","PatientName=Renee Munoz; PatientName=Bjork Gudmundsdottir","Special characters and diacritics render correctly without mojibake or data corruption","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-004","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0019","Reporting & Audit Logging","Empty-Data","Run report whose criteria match no records","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; criteria guaranteed to return zero rows","1. Select a report | 2. Enter a date range with no underlying data | 3. Run the report","StartDate=01-Jan-1995; EndDate=02-Jan-1995","Report completes successfully and displays an explicit empty-state message rather than an error or blank screen","Automatable","REQ-RPT-006","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0020","Reporting & Audit Logging","Empty-Data","Export an empty report to CSV","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Data Manager; a report returning zero rows is displayed","1. Run a report that returns no rows | 2. Export to CSV","Format=CSV; Rows=0","CSV contains only the header row with no data rows and opens without error","Automatable","REQ-RPT-006","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0021","Reporting & Audit Logging","Large-Dataset","Large-dataset readiness for high-volume report run","Functional","System","P2","High","High","Logged in as Data Manager; dataset of approximately 100000 records seeded in a performance environment","1. Select a high-volume report | 2. Set a broad date range covering all records | 3. Run the report | 4. Monitor render and memory","StartDate=01-Jan-2020; EndDate=31-Dec-2026; Records=~100000","Report completes within the agreed SLA, paginates results, and the application remains responsive without timeout or out-of-memory failure","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-007","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0022","Reporting & Audit Logging","Large-Dataset","Streamed export of a large result set to CSV","Boundary","System","P2","High","High","Logged in as Data Manager; report returns a very large result set","1. Run a high-volume report | 2. Export to CSV | 3. Verify full row count in the downloaded file","Records=~100000; Format=CSV","All rows export via streaming without truncation, the file row count equals the result count, and the browser does not crash","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-007","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0023","Reporting & Audit Logging","Large-Dataset","Concurrent report runs do not exhaust resources","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","High","Performance environment available; multiple Data Manager sessions","1. Trigger several heavy reports concurrently from different sessions | 2. Observe queueing and completion | 3. Watch server resource utilization","ConcurrentRuns=5; ReportName=Encounters by Location","Reports are queued or processed without deadlock, each completes correctly, and no run corrupts another's output","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-007","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0024","Reporting & Audit Logging","Scheduled Reports","Schedule a report to run on a recurring cron","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager with scheduler privilege","1. Open report scheduling | 2. Select a report | 3. Configure a recurring schedule | 4. Set parameters and recipients | 5. Save the schedule","ReportName=Daily Census; Cron=0 6 * * *; Recipient=ops@example.org","Schedule is saved and listed with the next run time, and the report executes automatically at the scheduled time","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-008","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0025","Reporting & Audit Logging","Scheduled Reports","Scheduled report failure triggers alert and retry","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","A scheduled report is configured; an induced failure condition exists","1. Configure a schedule referencing an invalid data source | 2. Wait for the scheduled run | 3. Inspect the run history and notifications","ReportName=Broken Source Report","Failed run is recorded with an error status, an alert is sent to the configured recipient, and retry policy behaves as configured","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-008","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0026","Reporting & Audit Logging","Scheduled Reports","Disable an active scheduled report","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","An active recurring schedule exists","1. Open the schedule list | 2. Toggle the schedule to disabled | 3. Wait past the next scheduled time","ReportName=Daily Census","Schedule moves to Disabled state, no run occurs at the next scheduled time, and it can be re-enabled later","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-008","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0027","Reporting & Audit Logging","Scheduled Reports","Scheduled report respects timezone and DST boundary","Boundary","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Scheduler configured with a specific timezone observing DST","1. Schedule a report for a time crossing the DST spring-forward boundary | 2. Observe actual execution time","Cron=30 2 * * *; Timezone=America/New_York; Date=DST-change","Report executes at the correct wall-clock time accounting for the DST shift without double-running or skipping silently","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-008","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0028","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Create","Audit log captures PHI record creation","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging enabled; logged in as Registration Clerk","1. Create a new patient record | 2. Note the timestamp and acting user | 3. Open the audit log viewer | 4. Locate the create entry","Patient=John Synthetic; DOB=01-Jan-1990","An audit entry records the create action with actor user, timestamp, patient identifier, action type CREATE, and source IP","Automatable","REQ-RPT-009","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0029","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Read","Audit log captures read access to PHI","Functional","Sanity","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging enabled; logged in as Clinician","1. Open a patient dashboard to view PHI | 2. Open the audit log viewer | 3. Filter by the patient and action READ","Patient=Jane Synthetic","A READ/ACCESS audit entry is recorded identifying who viewed which patient and when, supporting who-accessed-what queries","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-009","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0030","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Update","Audit log captures PHI record update with before and after","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging enabled; logged in as Clinician with edit rights","1. Edit a patient demographic field | 2. Save the change | 3. Open the audit log | 4. Inspect the update entry detail","Field=Address; Old=10 Old St; New=20 New Ave","An UPDATE audit entry records actor, timestamp, field changed, and the prior and new values for traceability","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-009","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0031","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Delete","Audit log captures PHI record deletion or void","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging enabled; logged in as user with delete/void rights","1. Void or delete a patient observation | 2. Open the audit log | 3. Locate the delete/void entry","Obs=Blood Pressure 120/80; Reason=Entered in error","A DELETE/VOID audit entry records actor, timestamp, target record, and the void reason","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-009","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0032","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-CRUD Decision","Decision table mapping CRUD actions to audit fields","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","High","Audit logging enabled; user able to perform all CRUD operations","1. Perform a CREATE and check captured fields | 2. Perform a READ and check fields | 3. Perform an UPDATE and check fields | 4. Perform a DELETE and check fields","Actions=Create,Read,Update,Delete","Each action produces an audit entry containing the mandatory fields (actor, timestamp, action, target, outcome) per the decision table","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-009","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0033","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Immutability","Audit log entries cannot be edited via UI","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging enabled; logged in as Administrator","1. Open an existing audit entry | 2. Attempt to modify any field via the UI | 3. Attempt to delete the entry","AuditEntryID=existing","No edit or delete control is available for audit entries, and any direct attempt is denied, preserving immutability","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-010","Audit; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0034","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Immutability","Direct database update of audit row is blocked or detected","Database","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Database access available in a test environment; audit table populated","1. Attempt an UPDATE statement against an audit log row | 2. Attempt a DELETE statement | 3. Inspect constraints/triggers","SQL=UPDATE audit_log SET action='READ' WHERE id=...","Database constraints, triggers, or append-only policy prevent or flag the modification, and tamper is detectable","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-010","Audit; Security; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0035","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Tamper-Evidence","Hash-chain tamper-evidence detects altered audit record","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Tamper-evident audit chain enabled; sequence of audit records exists","1. Compute the chain hash baseline | 2. Alter a single historical audit record at the storage layer | 3. Re-run chain verification","AlteredField=actor; ChainAlgo=SHA-256","Chain verification fails at the altered record, identifying the break point and proving tamper-evidence","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-011","Audit; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0036","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Tamper-Evidence","Sequential audit IDs detect gaps from deleted entries","Database","Regression","P2","High","High","Append-only audit store with sequential identifiers","1. Capture the current max audit sequence | 2. Remove a middle record at storage layer | 3. Run a gap-detection report","SequenceGap=missing id","Gap-detection report flags the missing sequence number, surfacing potential deletion of audit history","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-011","Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0037","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Who-Accessed","Who-accessed-what report for a single patient","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Audit logging enabled; multiple users have accessed a patient","1. Open the access report | 2. Filter by a patient identifier | 3. Run the report","Patient=MRN-100245; Range=Last 30 days","Report lists every user who accessed the patient, the action, and the timestamp, supporting HIPAA accounting of disclosures","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-012","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0038","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Who-Accessed","Detect potential snooping by same-name access","Exploratory","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Audit data includes staff accessing a patient sharing their surname","1. Run the access report | 2. Cross-reference accessor surname with patient surname | 3. Flag suspicious matches","Accessor=Dr. Smith; Patient=Smith","Suspicious self/same-name access is surfaced for privacy review, demonstrating break-the-glass monitoring capability","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-012","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Security","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0039","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Login","Successful login is recorded in the audit log","Functional","Smoke","P1","High","High","Audit logging enabled; valid user credentials available","1. Log in with valid credentials | 2. Open the security/audit log | 3. Locate the login entry","User=clerk1; Result=Success","Audit records a successful login with username, timestamp, source IP, and session identifier","Automatable","REQ-RPT-013","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0040","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Login","Failed login attempts are recorded","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Audit logging enabled; account exists","1. Enter a valid username with a wrong password | 2. Repeat the failed attempt several times | 3. Open the audit log","User=clerk1; Password=wrong; Attempts=3","Each failed login is audited with username, timestamp, and failure reason, enabling brute-force detection","Automatable","REQ-RPT-013","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0041","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Logout","Logout and session expiry are recorded","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Audit logging enabled; an active session exists","1. Log in | 2. Explicitly log out | 3. In a separate session let it expire by timeout | 4. Inspect the audit log","User=clerk1; Timeout=30min","Both explicit logout and session timeout produce distinct audit entries with timestamp and session reference","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-013","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0042","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Login","Account lockout after repeated failed logins is audited","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Lockout policy enabled; account exists","1. Exceed the configured failed-login threshold | 2. Observe the lockout | 3. Inspect the audit log","User=clerk1; Threshold=5","An account-lockout audit entry is recorded and subsequent attempts during lockout are also logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-013","Security; Audit","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0043","Reporting & Audit Logging","RBAC","Unauthorized role cannot run restricted reports","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as a low-privilege user without Reports privilege","1. Attempt to open the Reports app | 2. Attempt to run a restricted report by direct URL","User=nurse-no-report-priv","Access is denied with an authorization error, the report does not run, and the denied attempt is audited","Automatable","REQ-RPT-014","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0044","Reporting & Audit Logging","RBAC","Audit log viewer restricted to authorized roles","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as a clinical user without audit-view privilege","1. Attempt to open the audit log viewer | 2. Attempt direct API access to audit endpoints","User=clinician-no-audit-priv","Audit viewer is inaccessible, API returns 403, and the unauthorized attempt itself is logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-014","Security; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0045","Reporting & Audit Logging","API-Reporting REST","Run a report via REST API with valid token","API","Integration","P2","High","Medium","REST API enabled; valid OAuth/session token for Data Manager","1. POST a report run request to the reporting REST endpoint | 2. Poll the status endpoint | 3. GET the result","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/reportingrest; Token=valid","API returns 201/200 with a run UUID, status transitions to completed, and the result payload matches UI output","Automatable","REQ-RPT-015","Data Integrity; Standards-FHIR","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0046","Reporting & Audit Logging","API-Reporting REST","Reject report run via API with invalid token","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","REST API enabled","1. POST a report run request with a missing or expired token | 2. Inspect the response","Token=expired","API returns 401 Unauthorized, no report runs, and the unauthorized API attempt is audited","Automatable","REQ-RPT-015","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0047","Reporting & Audit Logging","API-Reporting REST","API rejects malformed parameter payload","Negative","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","REST API enabled; valid token","1. POST a report run with a malformed JSON body | 2. POST with an out-of-range date parameter | 3. Inspect responses","Body=invalid-json; Date=2026-13-40","API returns 400 Bad Request with a descriptive validation error and does not execute the report","Automatable","REQ-RPT-015","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0048","Reporting & Audit Logging","FHIR-AuditEvent","Audit entry maps to FHIR AuditEvent resource","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR module/adapter enabled; an auditable action occurred","1. Trigger a PHI read | 2. Retrieve the corresponding FHIR AuditEvent | 3. Validate the resource structure","Endpoint=/fhir2/R4/AuditEvent","AuditEvent resource includes type, action, recorded timestamp, agent (who), source, and entity (what) per FHIR R4 with valid code system URIs","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-016","Standards-FHIR; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-RPT-0049","Reporting & Audit Logging","FHIR-AuditEvent","FHIR AuditEvent action codes use correct value set","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","FHIR adapter enabled; create, read, update, delete events generated","1. Generate one AuditEvent per CRUD action | 2. Inspect the action element of each","Actions=C,R,U,D","Action codes map correctly to FHIR AuditEvent action codes (C,R,U,D) and use the canonical code system URI","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-016","Standards-FHIR; Audit","Standards"
"TC-RPT-0050","Reporting & Audit Logging","FHIR-Bundle Export","Export report results as a FHIR Bundle","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","FHIR adapter enabled; report producing patient resources","1. Run a patient-list report | 2. Request FHIR Bundle export | 3. Validate the Bundle","Format=FHIR-Bundle; Type=searchset","A valid FHIR searchset Bundle is returned with correctly typed entries and resolvable references","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-016","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-RPT-0051","Reporting & Audit Logging","HL7-Export","Audit/data export conforms to HL7 v2 message structure","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 interface/adapter configured on the platform","1. Trigger an HL7 export of an audit/ADT event | 2. Capture the outbound message | 3. Validate segments and encoding","MessageType=ADT^A08; Encoding=ER7","Message contains correctly ordered required segments (MSH, EVN, PID) with valid field separators and encoding characters","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-017","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-RPT-0052","Reporting & Audit Logging","HL7-Export","Malformed HL7 audit message is rejected and logged","Negative","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 interface configured; ability to inject a malformed message","1. Send an HL7 message missing the MSH segment | 2. Observe interface handling","Message=(no MSH)","The interface rejects the malformed message with an NAK/error and records the rejection in the audit/error log","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-017","Standards-HL7; Audit","Standards"
"TC-RPT-0053","Reporting & Audit Logging","Accessibility","Report results table is screen-reader accessible","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; a completed report is displayed; screen reader available","1. Navigate the report table using only the keyboard | 2. Use a screen reader to read headers and cells | 3. Check focus order","Tool=NVDA/VoiceOver","Table has proper header associations, cells are announced with context, focus order is logical, and all controls are keyboard reachable per WCAG 2.1 AA","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-018","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0054","Reporting & Audit Logging","Accessibility","Export controls meet contrast and label requirements","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Data Manager; report toolbar visible","1. Inspect export buttons for accessible names | 2. Measure color contrast of controls and status text | 3. Verify error messages are announced","Standard=WCAG 2.1 AA","Controls expose accessible names, contrast ratio meets at least 4.5:1 for text, and status/errors are programmatically announced","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-018","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0055","Reporting & Audit Logging","Database-Retention","Audit log retention policy enforces minimum period","Database","System","P2","High","High","Retention policy configured; audit records spanning several years","1. Inspect retention configuration | 2. Verify records older than the minimum are retained | 3. Verify archival of aged records","RetentionMin=6 years","Audit records are retained for at least the regulatory minimum (e.g., 6 years for HIPAA) and aged records are archived not silently purged","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-019","Regulatory/Compliance; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0056","Reporting & Audit Logging","Database-Performance","Audit query uses index and avoids full scan","Database","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Audit table populated with large volume; DB query plan accessible","1. Run a who-accessed-what query filtered by patient and date | 2. Capture the execution plan","Filter=patient_id+date; Rows=millions","Query plan uses appropriate indexes, avoids full table scans, and returns within the performance budget","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-019","Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0057","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Integrity","Audit timestamps use server time and are timezone-consistent","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Audit logging enabled; clients in different timezones","1. Perform auditable actions from clients in different timezones | 2. Compare recorded timestamps | 3. Verify timezone normalization","TZ1=UTC; TZ2=IST","All audit timestamps are stored in a consistent reference (e.g., UTC) preventing ambiguity and ordering errors","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-011","Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0058","Reporting & Audit Logging","Export-PHI Guard","Export masks restricted PHI per user authorization","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as a user with limited PHI authorization; report includes sensitive fields","1. Run a report containing restricted fields (e.g., HIV status) | 2. Export to CSV | 3. Inspect masked fields","RestrictedField=HIVStatus; Role=LimitedAccess","Restricted PHI is masked or omitted in the export according to the user's authorization, and the export action is audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-005","PHI/Privacy; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0059","Reporting & Audit Logging","Run Report-Exploratory","Exploratory session on report parameter edge interactions","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Data Manager; access to multiple report definitions","1. Try unusual parameter orders | 2. Switch reports mid-configuration | 3. Use browser back/forward during a run | 4. Resubmit rapidly","Charter=Probe parameter resilience","No crashes, stale parameters, or duplicate runs occur; the system handles unexpected navigation gracefully","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0060","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Read","Audit captures bulk export as an access event","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Audit logging enabled; user exports a multi-patient report","1. Run a report covering many patients | 2. Export the results | 3. Inspect the audit log for the export","Patients=250; Action=EXPORT","A single audit entry (or per-patient entries) records the bulk export as a PHI access event with actor, count, and timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RPT-009","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-RPT-0061","Reporting & Audit Logging","Parameters-Boundary","Maximum date range span boundary handling","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Data Manager; report enforces a max range span","1. Enter a range exceeding the configured maximum span | 2. Run | 3. Enter a range exactly at the maximum | 4. Run","MaxSpan=365 days; Range1=400 days; Range2=365 days","Range exceeding the maximum is rejected with a clear message; the exactly-at-maximum range is accepted","Automatable","REQ-RPT-002","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0062","Reporting & Audit Logging","Scheduled Reports","Pairwise of schedule frequency, format, and delivery channel","Pairwise","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Scheduler and delivery channels configured","1. Schedule daily + CSV + email | 2. Schedule weekly + PDF + file share | 3. Schedule monthly + Excel + secure link","Freq=daily,weekly,monthly; Format=CSV,PDF,Excel; Channel=email,share,link","Each frequency/format/channel pairing executes and delivers correctly, validating interaction coverage of scheduling options","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-008","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-RPT-0063","Reporting & Audit Logging","Audit-Immutability","Audit write succeeds even when business transaction rolls back","Database","System","P2","High","High","Audit logging enabled; ability to force a transaction rollback","1. Begin a PHI update that will fail and roll back | 2. Confirm the business change is reverted | 3. Inspect the audit log for the attempt","Action=Update-then-rollback","The attempted/failed action is still audited (audit not lost to rollback), capturing the access attempt and its outcome","Manual-Only","REQ-RPT-010","Audit; Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
