"TC-HL7-0037","HL7 v2 Messaging","Message-Sequence","Process out-of-order ADT messages using event timestamps to preserve correctness","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","High","MLLP listener running; sequencing by event time enabled","1. Send an A08 update timestamped AFTER an A03 discharge but deliver it BEFORE the A03 | 2. Then send the A03 | 3. Review final state","A08 event-time=20260701150000; A03 event-time=20260701140000 delivered after","The system orders events by event time, the later A03 does not erroneously override the newer A08 if business rules require, and the final state is consistent (or the conflict is flagged)","Manual-Only","REQ-HL7-021","Patient Safety; Data Integrity; Clinical; Standards-HL7","Standards"
"TC-HL7-0038","HL7 v2 Messaging","Message-Sequence","Reject or hold a result (ORU) that arrives before its order (ORM)","State Transition","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","MLLP listener running; order-before-result rule configured","1. Send ORU^R01 referencing an order not yet received | 2. Observe handling | 3. Send the ORM, then re-check","ORU OBR-2=ORD8001 (no prior ORM); then ORM creating ORD8001","The early result is held/queued or rejected with AE, and after the order arrives the result reconciles to the correct order (or requires reprocessing) without orphaning data","Manual-Only","REQ-HL7-021","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity; Standards-HL7","Standards"
"TC-HL7-0039","HL7 v2 Messaging","MLLP-Transport","Verify MLLP framing with correct start/end block characters","API","Integration","P2","High","Medium","MLLP listener running on configured port","1. Send a message wrapped in proper MLLP framing (VT ... FS CR) | 2. Confirm consumption | 3. Send a message missing the trailing FS CR and compare","Frame: <VT>MSH|...<FS><CR> for valid; missing <FS><CR> for invalid","The correctly framed message is consumed and ACKed; the improperly framed message is not consumed/times out, and the failure is logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-HL7-022","Data Integrity; Standards-HL7; Security","Standards"
"TC-HL7-0040","HL7 v2 Messaging","MLLP-Transport","Verify secure MLLP over TLS rejects an untrusted client certificate","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","MLLP-over-TLS listener configured with client-cert (mutual TLS) required","1. Attempt to connect with an untrusted/expired client certificate | 2. Attempt to send a message | 3. Observe connection result","Client presents self-signed cert not in the trust store","The TLS handshake is rejected, no message is accepted over the unauthenticated channel, and the rejection is logged for audit","Partially-Automatable","REQ-HL7-023","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-HL7-0041","HL7 v2 Messaging","Security-Injection","Sanitize HL7 escape sequences to prevent injection into downstream rendering","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","MLLP listener running; downstream viewer renders OBX text","1. Send an OBX whose text contains HL7 escape sequences and script-like content | 2. Confirm consumption | 3. View the result in the UI","OBX-5 text contains \\X0A\\ and <script>alert(1)</script>","Escape sequences are decoded safely and any markup is neutralized/escaped on render so no injection executes, while legitimate text displays correctly","Partially-Automatable","REQ-HL7-024","Security; PHI/Privacy; Clinical","Standards"
