"TC-HL7-0045","HL7 v2 Messaging","Boundary-Limits","Process a message at the maximum supported segment/field length boundary","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","MLLP listener running; max message size configured","1. Send an ORU^R01 with an OBX-5 text at the maximum allowed length | 2. Send one exceeding the limit | 3. Compare handling","OBX-5 length = max allowed (e.g., 65535 chars) vs max+1","The at-limit message is accepted and filed without truncation; the over-limit message is rejected/handled gracefully (no crash), with appropriate ACK in each case","Partially-Automatable","REQ-HL7-027","Data Integrity; Standards-HL7","Standards"
"TC-HL7-0046","HL7 v2 Messaging","Boundary-Limits","Handle an empty optional repeating field versus a single null component","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","MLLP listener running","1. Send ADT^A08 with an explicitly null PID-11 address using HL7 null (\\""\""\"") | 2. Send another omitting the field entirely | 3. Compare effects""","PID-11=\\""\""\"" (HL7 explicit null) vs PID-11 absent""","The explicit HL7 null clears the existing address (delete semantics) while the absent field leaves it unchanged, per HL7 null-handling rules; AA returned for both","Partially-Automatable","REQ-HL7-016","Data Integrity; Standards-HL7","Standards"
