"TC-HL7-0050","HL7 v2 Messaging","Exploratory","Exploratory session probing parser behavior with adversarial edge inputs","Exploratory","System","P2","Medium","Medium","MLLP listener running in a test environment; tester may craft arbitrary messages","1. Probe empty segments, doubled separators, extra delimiters, and trailing whitespace | 2. Inject very long repetition lists | 3. Mix valid and invalid segments | 4. Record any crash, hang, silent drop, or data corruption","Variety: MSH|||||; duplicated || fields; 1000x repeated PID-3; mixed CR/LF terminators","No crash, hang, memory blowup, or silent data corruption occurs; every input yields a deterministic accept-with-ACK or reject-with-NAK, and anomalies are logged for triage","Manual-Only","REQ-HL7-030","Patient Safety; Data Integrity; Security; Standards-HL7","Standards"
"TC-HL7-0051","HL7 v2 Messaging","Test-vs-Prod","Honor MSH-11 processing ID so test (T/D) messages do not affect production data","Decision Table","Integration","P1","High","High","MLLP listener running; processing-ID routing configured","1. Send an ADT^A01 with MSH-11=T | 2. Send an identical one with MSH-11=P | 3. Verify routing/effect of each","Msg A MSH-11=T (test); Msg B MSH-11=P (production)","The T message is routed to the test stream and does not alter production patient data; the P message updates production; routing is logged and ACKed appropriately","Partially-Automatable","REQ-HL7-031","Patient Safety; Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance; Standards-HL7","Standards"
