"TC-HL7-0056","HL7 v2 Messaging","Reliability","Re-queue and retry a message after a transient downstream outage","Functional","System","P1","High","High","MLLP listener running; downstream persistence layer temporarily unavailable; retry policy configured","1. Take the downstream store offline | 2. Send a valid ADT^A01 | 3. Restore the store | 4. Verify retry and final outcome","ADT^A01 MSG0056 while DB is down, then DB restored","The message is held/queued (not lost) during the outage, automatically retried after recovery, processed exactly once, and finally ACKed","Manual-Only","REQ-HL7-026","Data Integrity; Patient Safety; Standards-HL7","Standards"
"TC-HL7-0057","HL7 v2 Messaging","ACK-NAK","Echo correct values in the returned MSH (sender/receiver swapped) of the ACK","HL7","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","MLLP listener running","1. Send a valid ADT^A04 | 2. Capture the ACK | 3. Inspect ACK MSH-3/4/5/6","Inbound MSH-3=HIS, MSH-4=HOSP, MSH-5=EMR, MSH-6=HOSP","In the ACK, sending/receiving application and facility are correctly swapped (responder becomes sender), the ACK control ID is unique, and MSA references the original control ID","Automatable","REQ-HL7-011","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SEC-0001","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authentication","Valid credentials authenticate a clinician successfully","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","OpenMRS RefApp reachable over HTTPS; a clinician account exists and is active","1. Navigate to the login page | 2. Enter a valid username | 3. Enter the correct password | 4. Select a session location | 5. Click Log In","Username=clinician1; Password=Test@Pass123; Location=Outpatient Clinic","User is authenticated, redirected to the home dashboard, and a server-side session is established","Automatable","REQ-SEC-001","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0002","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authentication","Login fails with a wrong password and no detail leaked","Negative","Sanity","P1","High","High","A valid username exists; user is on the login page","1. Enter a valid username | 2. Enter an incorrect password | 3. Select a session location | 4. Click Log In","Username=clinician1; Password=WrongPass999","Login is rejected with a generic invalid-credentials message that does not reveal whether the username or password was wrong; no session is created","Automatable","REQ-SEC-001","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0003","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authentication","Login rejected for a non-existent username","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","User is on the login page; the username does not exist","1. Enter a username that does not exist | 2. Enter any password | 3. Select a session location | 4. Click Log In","Username=ghostuser; Password=Whatever1","Login is rejected with the same generic error used for a wrong password, preventing username enumeration","Automatable","REQ-SEC-001","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0004","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authentication","Empty username and password are rejected","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","User is on the login page","1. Leave username blank | 2. Leave password blank | 3. Click Log In","Username=; Password=","Form validation blocks submission and no authentication attempt is made against the server","Automatable","REQ-SEC-001","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0005","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authentication Strength","Password complexity policy enforced on password change","Decision Table","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as a user permitted to change own password; password policy configured (min length, mixed case, digit, symbol)","1. Open Change Password | 2. Enter current password | 3. Enter a candidate new password | 4. Confirm new password | 5. Submit | 6. Repeat for each candidate in the data set","Cases: short=Ab1!; no-digit=Abcdefg!; no-symbol=Abcdefg1; no-upper=abcdefg1!; valid=Abcd1234!","Each non-compliant candidate is rejected with a policy message; only the compliant candidate is accepted","Automatable","REQ-SEC-002","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0006","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authentication Strength","Password minimum length boundary values","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in user on Change Password screen; minimum length configured at 8","1. Submit a new password of length 7 | 2. Submit a new password of length 8 | 3. Submit a new password of length 9","len7=Abc123!; len8=Abc1234!; len9=Abc12345!","Length 7 is rejected; lengths 8 and 9 are accepted, confirming the boundary is inclusive at the minimum","Automatable","REQ-SEC-002","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0007","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authentication Strength","New password cannot equal current password","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in user on Change Password screen; password reuse prevention enabled","1. Enter current password | 2. Enter the same value as the new password | 3. Confirm | 4. Submit","Current=Abc1234!; New=Abc1234!","Change is rejected with a message that the new password must differ from the current one","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-002","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0008","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Account Lockout","Account locks after configured consecutive failed logins","State Transition","Regression","P1","High","High","Lockout threshold configured (e.g., 5 failures); a valid test account exists","1. Attempt login with wrong password repeatedly up to threshold-1 | 2. Observe account still allows attempts | 3. Submit one more wrong password reaching the threshold | 4. Attempt login again with the correct password","Username=lockuser; WrongPassword=Bad000; Threshold=5","After the threshold of failures the account transitions to a locked state and even correct credentials are refused until lockout expires or an admin unlocks","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-003","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0009","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Account Lockout","Lockout counter resets after a successful login","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Lockout threshold configured; account is below threshold","1. Submit threshold-1 failed logins | 2. Submit the correct password and log in | 3. Log out | 4. Submit one failed login | 5. Inspect that the counter restarted","Username=lockuser; Threshold=5","After a successful login the failed-attempt counter resets to zero so a subsequent single failure does not lock the account","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-003","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0010","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Account Lockout","Locked account auto-unlocks after the configured window","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Account is currently locked; auto-unlock window configured","1. Confirm account is locked | 2. Wait until the configured unlock window elapses | 3. Attempt login with the correct password","Username=lockuser; UnlockWindow=5 min","After the unlock window passes, login with the correct password succeeds and the account state returns to active","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-003","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0011","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Session Management","Session cookie is marked HttpOnly and Secure","Security","Regression","P1","High","High","User can authenticate over HTTPS; browser dev tools or a proxy available for inspection","1. Log in successfully | 2. Inspect the Set-Cookie response header for the session cookie | 3. Check the cookie attributes","Cookie name=JSESSIONID","The session cookie carries HttpOnly and Secure attributes and an appropriate SameSite value, preventing script access and plaintext transmission","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-004","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0012","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Session Management","Session ID is regenerated upon successful login","Security","Regression","P1","High","High","Pre-login session identifier captured; intercepting proxy available","1. Load the login page and record the pre-auth session ID | 2. Submit valid credentials | 3. Record the post-auth session ID | 4. Compare the two","Username=clinician1; Password=Test@Pass123","The session identifier changes after authentication, preventing session fixation","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-004","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0013","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Session Management","Idle session times out after the configured period","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Session timeout configured; user is logged in","1. Log in | 2. Leave the session idle beyond the configured timeout | 3. Attempt to access a protected page","Username=clinician1; IdleTimeout=15 min","The idle session is invalidated and the user is redirected to login when accessing protected content","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-004","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0014","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Session Management","Logout invalidates the server-side session","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","User is logged in with an active session","1. Log in | 2. Capture the session cookie | 3. Click Log Out | 4. Replay a protected request reusing the captured session cookie","Username=clinician1; ProtectedURL=/ws/rest/v1/session","After logout the server rejects the replayed session cookie and the protected request returns an unauthenticated response","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-004","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0015","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Session Management","Concurrent sessions handled per policy","Exploratory","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Concurrent-session policy defined; one account available","1. Log in from browser A | 2. Log in with the same account from browser B | 3. Perform an action in browser A | 4. Observe whether session A remains valid","Username=clinician1; Password=Test@Pass123","System behaves per the documented concurrent-session policy (either both valid or the earlier session invalidated) with no data corruption","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-004","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0016","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authorization","Role-restricted privilege blocks unauthorized clinical action","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","A user with a Receptionist role lacking the privilege to enter clinical observations is logged in","1. Log in as the receptionist | 2. Navigate to a patient dashboard | 3. Attempt to open the clinical observation entry form","Username=reception1; Patient=Demo-PT-1001","The clinical entry action is hidden or denied with an authorization error and no observation can be created","Automatable","REQ-SEC-005","Security; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0017","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authorization","Privilege grant enables the previously blocked action","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Admin can edit roles; receptionist role currently lacks the clinical privilege","1. As admin, grant the clinical-entry privilege to the role | 2. Log in as the receptionist | 3. Re-attempt the clinical observation entry","Role=Receptionist; Privilege=Add Observations","After the privilege is granted the user can perform the action, confirming authorization is privilege-driven","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-005","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0018","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authorization IDOR","Direct object reference to another patient record is denied","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as a clinician whose access is scoped; two patient UUIDs known, one outside the user scope","1. Log in as the scoped clinician | 2. Note an in-scope patient UUID | 3. Manually edit the URL to an out-of-scope patient UUID | 4. Submit the request","InScope=UUID-A; OutOfScope=UUID-B; URL=/patientDashboard.page?patientId=UUID-B","Access to the out-of-scope record is denied or filtered; the unauthorized PHI is not returned","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-006","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0019","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authorization IDOR","REST API rejects access to an unauthorized patient resource","API","Regression","P1","Critical","High","An API token for a low-privilege user; a patient UUID the user cannot access","1. Authenticate to the REST API as the low-privilege user | 2. Issue GET to the patient resource for the unauthorized UUID | 3. Inspect status and body","GET /ws/rest/v1/patient/UUID-B with low-priv token","API returns a 403 or 404 without exposing the patient demographics or PHI of the unauthorized record","Automatable","REQ-SEC-006","Security; PHI/Privacy; API","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0020","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authorization IDOR","Sequential numeric ID manipulation does not expose other encounters","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in clinician; an encounter belonging to another provider exists","1. Open an in-scope encounter and note its identifier pattern | 2. Modify the identifier to reference another provider's encounter | 3. Request the modified resource","EncounterId target outside scope","The system denies the manipulated reference and returns no encounter content the user is not authorized to view","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-006","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0021","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Input Validation","SQL injection payload in patient search is neutralized","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in with patient-search privilege; design-only test against a controlled non-production instance","1. Open patient search | 2. Enter a SQL meta-character payload in the name field | 3. Submit the search | 4. Observe results and logs","Search=' OR '1'='1","Input is treated as a literal search string; no extra records are returned, no SQL error is surfaced, and parameterized queries prevent injection","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-007","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0022","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Input Validation","Injection payload in REST query parameter is safely handled","API","Regression","P2","High","High","Valid API token; non-production controlled instance","1. Issue a patient search REST call with an injection payload in the q parameter | 2. Inspect response status and body","GET /ws/rest/v1/patient?q='%20OR%201=1--","API returns a normal empty or filtered result with no database error, stack trace, or unintended data exposure","Automatable","REQ-SEC-007","Security; API; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0023","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Input Validation","Oversized input field is rejected at the boundary","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in registration clerk; field max length defined (e.g., 50 chars for given name)","1. Enter a name of exactly the maximum length | 2. Save | 3. Enter a name of maximum length plus one | 4. Save","len50=AAAA...(50); len51=AAAA...(51)","The maximum-length value is accepted and the over-limit value is rejected or truncated per spec, preventing buffer or storage issues","Automatable","REQ-SEC-007","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0024","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Input Validation","Special and Unicode characters are stored without corruption","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in registration clerk","1. Register a patient with accented and non-Latin characters in the name | 2. Save | 3. Reopen the patient record","Given=Renee; Family=O'Brien-Muller","The characters are stored and rendered correctly without corruption, double-encoding, or injection side effects","Automatable","REQ-SEC-007","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0025","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","XSS Resilience","Stored script in a free-text field is neutralized on display","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in with privilege to enter a free-text note; controlled non-production instance","1. Enter a script payload into a free-text note field | 2. Save the note | 3. Reopen the record that renders the note","Note=<script>alert('xss')</script>","The payload is HTML-encoded or stripped on render; no script executes and the literal text or sanitized value is shown","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-008","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0026","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","XSS Resilience","Reflected input in search results is encoded","Security","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in with search privilege; controlled non-production instance","1. Submit a search containing an HTML/script payload | 2. Observe how the search term is reflected on the results page","Search=<img src=x onerror=alert(1)>","The reflected term is output-encoded so the markup is displayed as text and no event handler or image error fires","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-008","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0027","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","XSS Resilience","Attribute-context payload does not break out of attribute","Security","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in user; field rendered into an HTML attribute; controlled instance","1. Enter a payload designed to break out of an attribute context | 2. Save | 3. Inspect rendered HTML source","Input=\ onmouseover=\""alert(1)""","The value is attribute-encoded so it cannot escape the attribute boundary and no event handler is injected","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-008","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0028","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Content Security","Security response headers are present","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Application reachable over HTTPS; proxy or dev tools available","1. Request the application home page over HTTPS | 2. Inspect response headers for CSP, X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options, and HSTS","URL=https://o2.openmrs.org","Recommended security headers are present, mitigating clickjacking, MIME sniffing, and enforcing HTTPS","Automatable","REQ-SEC-009","Security","Standards"
"TC-SEC-0029","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Transport Security","HTTP requests are redirected to HTTPS","Security","Sanity","P1","High","High","Application deployed with TLS and HTTP-to-HTTPS redirect configured","1. Issue a plain HTTP request to the login URL | 2. Observe the redirect | 3. Confirm the final URL uses HTTPS","URL=http://app.example.org/login","The request is redirected with a 301/302 to the HTTPS equivalent and credentials are never sent over plaintext HTTP","Automatable","REQ-SEC-009","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0030","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Transport Security","TLS configuration disallows weak protocols and ciphers","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Access to the TLS endpoint; design-only configuration review","1. Review the negotiated TLS version and cipher suites | 2. Confirm TLS 1.2 or higher only | 3. Confirm deprecated protocols are disabled","Endpoint=app.example.org:443","Only TLS 1.2+ with strong cipher suites is offered; SSLv3, TLS 1.0 and 1.1 and weak ciphers are disabled","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-009","Security","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0031","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","PHI Exposure","Patient identifiers are not exposed in URL query strings","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in clinician viewing a patient chart","1. Open a patient chart | 2. Inspect the browser address bar and any AJAX request URLs | 3. Check whether PHI such as name, MRN, or SSN appears as a query parameter","Patient=Demo-PT-1001","Patient PHI is not transmitted in URL query strings; opaque UUIDs are used and no sensitive demographic data leaks via URLs or referrers","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-010","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0032","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","PHI Exposure","Server logs do not record PHI or credentials","Database","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Access to application and server logs in a controlled environment; ability to generate activity","1. Perform a login and a patient search | 2. Inspect application logs and access logs | 3. Search logs for passwords, tokens, MRN, SSN, and full names","Search=clinician1; Patient=Demo-PT-1001","Logs contain no plaintext passwords, session tokens, or PHI; sensitive values are masked or omitted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-010","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0033","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","PHI Exposure","Browser back button does not expose PHI after logout","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","User has viewed a patient chart and then logged out","1. Log in and open a patient chart | 2. Log out | 3. Press the browser Back button | 4. Observe the page content","Patient=Demo-PT-1001","Cached PHI is not served after logout; the user is redirected to login and no patient data is rendered","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-010","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0034","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","PHI Exposure","Cache-control headers prevent caching of PHI pages","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in user; proxy or dev tools available","1. Open a page containing PHI | 2. Inspect response headers for Cache-Control and Pragma","Page=patient dashboard","PHI-bearing responses carry no-store/no-cache directives so sensitive content is not retained by browsers or intermediaries","Automatable","REQ-SEC-010","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0035","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Password Storage","Stored password is hashed and salted, never plaintext","Database","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Read access to the user credential store in a controlled non-production environment","1. Create a user with a known password | 2. Query the stored credential record | 3. Inspect the stored value and any salt column","Username=hashtest; Password=Test@Pass123","The stored value is a one-way salted hash (not reversible, not the plaintext), with a per-user salt and a strong algorithm","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-011","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0036","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Password Storage","Two users with identical passwords have different stored hashes","Database","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Read access to the credential store in a controlled environment","1. Create user A and user B with the same password | 2. Query both stored hashes | 3. Compare them","UserA/UserB Password=Test@Pass123","The two stored hashes differ, confirming a unique per-user salt prevents hash correlation and rainbow-table attacks","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-011","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0037","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","CSRF Protection","State-changing request without a valid CSRF token is rejected","Security","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in user with a valid session; controlled non-production instance; proxy available","1. Capture a legitimate state-changing POST and note its anti-CSRF token | 2. Replay the request with the token removed or altered | 3. Observe the response","POST save patient note without CSRF token","The request is rejected and no state change occurs, confirming CSRF protection on state-changing endpoints","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-012","Security","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0038","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","CSRF Protection","CSRF token is unique per session and not predictable","Security","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Two separate authenticated sessions available","1. Capture the CSRF token from session 1 | 2. Capture the token from session 2 | 3. Compare values and assess randomness","Two sessions of clinician1","Tokens differ between sessions and show sufficient entropy, so a token cannot be guessed or reused across sessions","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-012","Security","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0039","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Error Handling","Server errors do not leak stack traces or internals","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Ability to trigger an error condition on a controlled instance","1. Submit a malformed request that triggers a server error | 2. Inspect the error response shown to the user","Malformed=invalid JSON body to a REST endpoint","A generic error message is shown with no stack trace, framework version, SQL, or file path disclosure","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-013","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0040","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Error Handling","404 and 500 pages do not reveal technology fingerprint","Negative","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Application reachable; ability to request a non-existent path","1. Request a non-existent URL | 2. Inspect the 404 response body and headers | 3. Trigger a 500 and inspect","URL=/nonexistent-xyz","Error pages are generic and Server/X-Powered-By headers do not disclose exact framework or version details","Automatable","REQ-SEC-013","Security","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0041","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Audit","Successful login is recorded in the security audit log","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Audit logging enabled; access to audit records","1. Log in successfully as a clinician | 2. Query the audit log for the login event","Username=clinician1","An audit entry records the successful login with user identity, timestamp, and source, supporting accountability","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-014","Security; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0042","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Audit","Failed login attempts are audited","Functional","Regression","P2","High","High","Audit logging enabled; access to audit records","1. Submit a failed login | 2. Query the audit log for the failed-login event","Username=clinician1; WrongPassword=Bad000","An audit entry records the failed attempt with username, timestamp, and outcome, enabling intrusion detection","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-014","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0043","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Audit","Patient record access is logged for PHI accountability","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging for record access enabled; access to audit records","1. Log in as a clinician | 2. Open a patient chart | 3. Query the audit log for a record-access event","Username=clinician1; Patient=Demo-PT-1001","An audit entry captures who accessed which patient record and when, satisfying HIPAA accountability for PHI access","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-014","Security; Audit; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0044","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Audit","Privilege and role changes are audited","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Admin can modify roles; audit logging enabled","1. As admin, change a user's role or privilege | 2. Query the audit log for the change event","Admin grants Add Observations to Receptionist","An audit entry records the privilege change including actor, target, before/after, and timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-014","Security; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0045","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Audit","Audit log entries are tamper-evident and read-only to clinical users","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as a non-admin clinical user","1. Attempt to delete or modify an existing audit log entry through the UI or API","Username=clinician1; Action=delete audit row","The clinical user cannot alter or delete audit records; modification is denied and the attempt itself is logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-014","Security; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0046","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Data At Rest","Database backups containing PHI are encrypted","Database","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Access to backup configuration in a controlled environment; encryption-at-rest policy defined","1. Review backup storage configuration | 2. Confirm encryption-at-rest is enabled for database and file backups | 3. Verify key management is documented","Backup target=encrypted volume","Backups containing PHI are encrypted at rest with managed keys, meeting the data-at-rest protection requirement","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-015","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0047","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Data At Rest","Sensitive configuration secrets are not stored in plaintext","Database","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Access to deployment configuration in a controlled environment","1. Inspect configuration files and environment for database passwords and API keys | 2. Confirm secrets are externalized and protected","Config=runtime properties","Secrets are not committed in plaintext; they are stored in a secret manager or protected store, not in readable config","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-015","Security","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0048","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","API Security","Unauthenticated REST request is rejected","API","Sanity","P1","Critical","High","REST endpoint available; no credentials supplied","1. Issue a GET to a protected REST resource with no auth header or session | 2. Inspect the status code","GET /ws/rest/v1/patient?q=Test (no auth)","The API responds with 401 Unauthorized and returns no patient data","Automatable","REQ-SEC-006","Security; API; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0049","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","API Security","Expired or revoked token is rejected","API","Regression","P2","High","High","An expired or revoked API token is available","1. Issue a protected REST request using the expired/revoked token | 2. Inspect the response","Token=expired-jwt-or-session","The API rejects the request with 401 and the stale credential cannot access any resource","Automatable","REQ-SEC-004","Security; API","Standards"
"TC-SEC-0050","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","API Security","SMART on FHIR scope limits returned resources","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","High","SMART on FHIR app authorized with a narrow scope (e.g., patient/Observation.read only)","1. Authorize the app with patient/Observation.read scope | 2. Request an Observation resource | 3. Request a MedicationRequest resource","Scope=patient/Observation.read","Observation read succeeds while the out-of-scope MedicationRequest is denied, enforcing least-privilege scopes","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-005","Security; Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-SEC-0051","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","API Security","FHIR Patient.read enforces compartment authorization","FHIR","Integration","P1","Critical","High","SMART app authorized for patient context A; resource B belongs to another patient","1. Launch in patient context A | 2. Request Patient/A | 3. Request Patient/B outside the authorized compartment","Context=Patient/A; Target=Patient/B","Patient/A is returned; Patient/B is denied, confirming the FHIR compartment boundary is enforced","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-006","Security; Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-SEC-0052","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","API Security","FHIR server requires TLS for all requests","FHIR","Regression","P2","High","Medium","HAPI FHIR endpoint configured for TLS","1. Attempt a FHIR request over plain HTTP | 2. Attempt the same over HTTPS","Endpoint=/fhir/Patient","Plain HTTP is refused or redirected to HTTPS; only encrypted FHIR traffic is accepted","Automatable","REQ-SEC-009","Security; Standards-FHIR","Standards"
"TC-SEC-0053","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Interface Security","HL7 inbound interface authenticates the sending application","HL7","Integration","P2","High","High","An HL7 v2 MLLP interface configured to require sender authentication/allowlist","1. Send an ADT message from an unlisted sending application | 2. Send the same from an allowlisted sender","MSH sending app=UNKNOWN_APP vs ALLOWED_APP","Messages from unauthorized senders are rejected with an appropriate ACK error while allowlisted senders are accepted","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-005","Security; Standards-HL7","Standards"
"TC-SEC-0054","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Interface Security","HL7 PHI in transit is protected by TLS or VPN","HL7","Regression","P2","High","Medium","HL7 channel configuration available for review","1. Review the HL7 transport configuration | 2. Confirm MLLP runs over TLS or a secured tunnel","Channel=ADT inbound","HL7 messages carrying PHI traverse an encrypted channel, never plaintext MLLP over an untrusted network","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-009","Security; Standards-HL7; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-SEC-0055","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authorization","Privilege combinations evaluated across roles","Pairwise","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Multiple roles and resource actions defined; test matrix prepared","1. For each role-action pair in the pairwise set, log in with the role | 2. Attempt the action | 3. Record allow/deny | 4. Compare with the access matrix","Pairs: {Clerk,ViewChart}; {Clerk,EditObs}; {Nurse,ViewChart}; {Nurse,EditObs}; {Admin,ManageUsers}","Each role-action outcome matches the documented access-control matrix with no unexpected allow results","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-005","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0056","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authentication","MFA challenge required when enabled","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","High","MFA enabled for the account on the omiiCARE platform","1. Enter valid username and password | 2. Submit | 3. Observe the MFA challenge | 4. Enter a valid one-time code","Username=mfauser; Password=Test@Pass123; OTP=valid","After primary credentials the user is prompted for the second factor and is only granted access after a valid code","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-001","Security","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0057","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authentication","Invalid MFA code is rejected and limited","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","MFA enabled; user passed primary authentication","1. Complete primary authentication | 2. Enter an incorrect OTP repeatedly","Username=mfauser; OTP=000000","Invalid codes are rejected, attempts are rate-limited, and access is not granted without a valid second factor","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-001","Security","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0058","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Input Validation","File upload restricts type and scans content","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in user with attachment upload privilege; controlled instance","1. Upload an allowed image file | 2. Upload a disallowed executable file | 3. Upload a file with a spoofed extension","good=scan.png; bad=payload.exe; spoof=payload.exe renamed to .png","Allowed types succeed; disallowed and spoofed files are rejected based on content-type validation, preventing malicious upload","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-007","Security; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0059","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","API Security","Rate limiting throttles excessive requests","API","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","API rate-limit policy configured on the platform","1. Send requests within the allowed rate | 2. Exceed the configured request rate within the window | 3. Observe responses","Limit=100 req/min","Requests within the limit succeed; requests exceeding the limit receive 429 Too Many Requests, mitigating brute-force and abuse","Automatable","REQ-SEC-003","Security; API","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0060","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authorization","Forced browsing to admin pages is blocked for non-admins","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in as a non-admin clinical user","1. Log in as the non-admin user | 2. Directly navigate to an administration URL","URL=/admin/manageUsers.page; Username=clinician1","The admin page is not rendered; the user receives an authorization error and cannot view or alter admin settings","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-005","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0061","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Session Management","Cookie without SameSite is flagged in design review","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Cookie policy matrix defined for Lax, Strict, and None contexts","1. For each SameSite configuration, inspect cookie behavior on cross-site navigation | 2. Compare against the policy matrix","Cases: Lax; Strict; None+Secure; None-without-Secure","Each configuration matches the intended policy; SameSite=None is only permitted with Secure, mitigating CSRF and leakage","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-004","Security","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0062","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Exploratory","Time-boxed exploratory probe of authentication and session flows","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Controlled non-production instance; tester with valid low-privilege account; intercepting proxy","1. Explore login, password reset, and session handling for inconsistent error messages, weak token handling, and parameter tampering for 60 minutes | 2. Record observations and reproducible issues","Account=clinician1; Proxy enabled","Findings are documented with reproduction steps; any weakness in auth, session, or error handling is logged for triage","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-001","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0063","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Password Recovery","Password reset does not confirm account existence","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Self-service password reset enabled","1. Request a reset for a known existing email | 2. Request a reset for a non-existent email | 3. Compare the on-screen responses","existing=clinician1@example.org; missing=nobody@example.org","Both requests return the same neutral confirmation message, preventing account enumeration via the reset flow","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-001","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0064","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Password Recovery","Reset token is single-use and time-limited","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","High","A valid reset token was issued","1. Use the reset token to set a new password | 2. Attempt to reuse the same token | 3. Wait past expiry and attempt an unused token","Token=reset-abc123; Expiry=30 min","The token works once, is rejected on reuse, and an expired token is refused, limiting the reset window","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-001","Security","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0065","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Accessibility Security","Login error messaging is accessible without leaking detail","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Screen reader available; user on the login page","1. Submit invalid credentials | 2. Verify the error is announced by the screen reader and associated with the form","Username=clinician1; Password=wrong","The generic error is programmatically associated and announced to assistive tech while still not revealing which field was wrong","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-001","Security; Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-SEC-0066","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Authorization IDOR","Bulk export endpoint enforces per-record authorization","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","High","FHIR bulk data export configured; user with scoped access","1. Initiate a bulk export as a scoped user | 2. Inspect the exported resource set","Scope=group-A patients only","The export contains only records within the user's authorized scope; no out-of-scope patient resources are included","Manual-Only","REQ-SEC-006","Security; Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-SEC-0067","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Input Validation","Numeric vital-sign field rejects out-of-range and non-numeric input","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in clinician on an observation form; allowed range defined for a vital","1. Enter a value below the minimum | 2. Enter the minimum | 3. Enter the maximum | 4. Enter above the maximum | 5. Enter a non-numeric value","Field=Heart Rate; Range=20-300; values=19,20,300,301,abc","Below-min, above-max, and non-numeric values are rejected; min and max are accepted, protecting data integrity and patient safety","Automatable","REQ-SEC-007","Security; Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-SEC-0068","Security (functional/readiness, design-only)","Audit","Audit records include sufficient detail for forensic review","Database","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Audit logging enabled; access to audit storage","1. Perform a sensitive action | 2. Inspect the resulting audit record fields","Action=view patient chart","Each audit record includes actor identity, action, target object, timestamp, and source address, supporting forensic reconstruction","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SEC-014","Security; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-A11Y-0001","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Keyboard Navigation","Navigate the OpenMRS Home dashboard apps grid using only the keyboard","Functional","Smoke","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician on the OpenMRS Reference Application Home page; mouse physically disconnected or unused","1. Press Tab from the top of the page | 2. Continue pressing Tab to move across header, search, and app tiles | 3. Press Enter on the Active Visits app tile | 4. Use Shift+Tab to move backward","Browser=Chrome 124; User=clinician-qa; App tile=Active Visits","Every interactive element (links, search, app tiles) receives focus in a logical order, each focused element is operable with Enter/Space, and activating the Active Visits tile opens that page without requiring a mouse","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-001","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0002","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Keyboard Navigation","Operate Patient Registration multi-step form using keyboard only","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk on the Register a Patient screen","1. Tab into the Given name field and type | 2. Tab to Family name and type | 3. Tab to Next/Continue control and press Enter | 4. Tab through gender radio group and select with arrow keys | 5. Tab to birthdate fields and enter values | 6. Tab to Confirm and press Enter","Given=Asha; Family=Rao; Gender=Female; DOB=10-Mar-1992","All registration steps can be completed in sequence with keyboard only, radio groups respond to arrow keys, and the patient record is created without mouse interaction","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-001","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0003","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Keyboard Navigation","Verify no keyboard trap inside the patient search autocomplete dropdown","Negative","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient search widget present on the Find Patient Record page","1. Tab focus into the patient search input | 2. Type three characters to trigger the autocomplete list | 3. Press Down arrow to enter the suggestion list | 4. Attempt to Tab and Shift+Tab out of the suggestion list | 5. Press Escape","Search term=Tes; Suggestions appear for synthetic patients","Focus can move into and out of the autocomplete list freely via Tab/Shift+Tab/Escape; focus is never trapped and the user can always reach the next control (WCAG 2.1.2)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-002","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0004","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Keyboard Navigation","Verify no keyboard trap in modal dialogs (Start Visit / Delete confirmation)","Negative","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician on a patient dashboard with the Start Visit modal available","1. Open the Start Visit modal via keyboard | 2. Tab through all controls in the modal | 3. Confirm focus cycles within the modal and does not escape behind it | 4. Press Escape | 5. Confirm focus returns to the triggering control","Patient=QA-Synthetic-001; Modal=Start Visit","Focus is contained within the open modal while it is active (focus trap by design), Escape closes the modal, and focus returns to the element that opened it without becoming stranded","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-002","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0005","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Focus Order","Verify logical focus order matches visual reading order on the patient dashboard","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician viewing a patient dashboard with multiple widgets (visits, diagnoses, vitals)","1. Place focus at page start | 2. Tab through the page recording the order of focused elements | 3. Compare focus order with the left-to-right, top-to-bottom visual layout","Patient=QA-Synthetic-002","Focus order follows a meaningful sequence consistent with the visual/reading order; no focus jumps to off-screen or visually-later elements before earlier ones (WCAG 2.4.3)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0006","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Visible Focus","Verify a visible focus indicator is present on all interactive controls","Functional","Smoke","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; default OpenMRS RefApp theme active","1. Tab through header links, buttons, form fields, and app tiles | 2. Observe each focused element for a visible focus ring or outline | 3. Note any control where the focus indicator is missing or hidden","Pages=Home, Registration, Patient Dashboard","Every focusable control shows a clearly visible focus indicator with sufficient contrast against its background; no control receives focus invisibly (WCAG 2.4.7)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-004","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0007","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Visible Focus","Boundary: focus indicator remains visible against the dark header background","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; OpenMRS top navigation header rendered with its dark background","1. Tab to the Home link in the header | 2. Tab to the user account menu in the header | 3. Tab to the logout control | 4. Inspect focus ring contrast against the dark header at each stop","Header controls=Home, Account menu, Logout","The focus indicator on dark-header controls has a contrast ratio of at least 3:1 against adjacent colors and stays perceptible at every header control","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-004","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0008","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Skip Links","Verify a Skip to main content link is present and functional","Functional","Sanity","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician on any OpenMRS RefApp page with repeated header navigation","1. Load the page and press Tab once from the very top | 2. Observe whether a Skip to main content link appears | 3. Activate it with Enter | 4. Press Tab again and confirm focus lands in main content","Page=Patient Dashboard","A Skip to main content (bypass) link is the first focusable element, becomes visible on focus, and moves focus past the repeated navigation directly into main content (WCAG 2.4.1)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-005","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0009","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Skip Links","Negative: absence of bypass mechanism on a page with large repeated navigation","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician on a page that lacks a skip link but has extensive repeated header/sidebar navigation","1. Load the page | 2. Tab from the top and count how many tab stops are required to reach main content | 3. Verify whether any bypass mechanism (skip link, landmark, heading nav) exists","Page=Admin landing page","If no skip link, ARIA landmarks (main, navigation) or a heading structure must provide an alternate bypass; total absence of any bypass mechanism is a WCAG 2.4.1 failure to be reported","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-005","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0010","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","ARIA Roles","Verify ARIA landmark roles partition the page (banner, navigation, main, contentinfo)","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; accessibility inspection tool (axe DevTools or browser a11y tree) available","1. Open the patient dashboard | 2. Inspect the accessibility tree for landmark roles | 3. Confirm banner, navigation, main, and contentinfo (or equivalent HTML5 landmarks) are present and unique where required","Page=Patient Dashboard; Tool=axe DevTools","Page exposes correct, non-duplicated landmark roles allowing screen-reader users to jump between regions; main landmark wraps the primary content (WCAG 1.3.1)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0011","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","ARIA Roles","Verify form controls expose correct roles and states in the accessibility tree","Accessibility","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk on the Register a Patient screen; a11y tree inspector available","1. Inspect the gender radio group in the a11y tree | 2. Confirm role=radiogroup with radio children and aria-checked states | 3. Inspect the Unknown checkbox role and aria-checked | 4. Inspect Next button role","Form=Registration demographics step","Radio group exposes role radiogroup/radio with correct aria-checked, checkboxes expose checkbox role with state, and buttons expose button role; states update as values change (WCAG 4.1.2)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0012","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Form Labels","Verify every visible registration field has a programmatically associated label","Accessibility","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk on the Register a Patient demographics step","1. Inspect each input (Given name, Middle name, Family name) in the a11y tree | 2. Confirm each has an accessible name from a label, aria-label, or aria-labelledby | 3. Click each label text and confirm focus moves to its field","Fields=Given, Middle, Family name","Every form field has a programmatically determinable label; clicking a label focuses its control; no field is announced as unlabeled (WCAG 1.3.1, 3.3.2, 4.1.2)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-007","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0013","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Form Labels","Negative: placeholder-only field with no persistent label is flagged","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician on a form where a field uses only placeholder text as its visible cue","1. Inspect the field in the a11y tree | 2. Check whether an accessible name exists when the placeholder is cleared | 3. Enter a value and confirm the label/name remains available","Field=Search term using placeholder only","A field relying solely on placeholder text (which disappears on input and is not a label) must be reported as a labeling failure; an accessible name must persist independent of placeholder (WCAG 3.3.2)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-007","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0014","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Error Association","Verify validation errors are programmatically associated with their fields","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk on the Register a Patient screen","1. Leave the required Given name field empty | 2. Attempt to proceed to the next step | 3. Inspect the error message element | 4. Confirm the field references the error via aria-describedby and is marked aria-invalid","Given name=empty (required)","On validation failure the field is marked aria-invalid=true and links its error message via aria-describedby so screen readers announce the specific error when the field is focused (WCAG 3.3.1, 3.3.3)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-008","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0015","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Error Association","Screen reader announces error summary when registration submission fails","Accessibility","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk; NVDA or VoiceOver running on the Register a Patient screen","1. Submit the form with multiple required fields empty | 2. Listen for the error summary announcement | 3. Navigate to the summary and follow a link to the first errored field","Empty fields=Given name, Family name, DOB","An error summary region (role=alert or aria-live=assertive) is announced automatically on failed submit, and each listed error links to its field (WCAG 3.3.1, 4.1.3)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-008","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0016","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Screen Reader","Verify screen reader announces dynamic Active Visits updates via live region","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; NVDA running; Active Visits list visible and updating","1. Open the Active Visits page with a screen reader active | 2. Have a synthetic patient checked in by a second clerk | 3. Listen for an announcement when the list updates","Patient=QA-Synthetic-003 check-in","The newly added active visit is announced through an aria-live polite region without the user needing to refresh or move focus (WCAG 4.1.3)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-009","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0017","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Screen Reader","Verify screen reader announces successful patient creation confirmation","Accessibility","Sanity","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Registration Clerk; VoiceOver active; completing patient registration","1. Complete all registration steps with valid data | 2. Confirm the final step | 3. Listen for the success confirmation announcement","Given=Maya; Family=Quinn; DOB=05-Jul-1988","The Created Patient Record confirmation is conveyed to assistive technology via a status/alert live region so non-visual users know the action succeeded (WCAG 4.1.3)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-009","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0018","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Color Contrast","Verify body text meets 4.5:1 contrast against its background","Accessibility","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; contrast analysis tool (axe or Colour Contrast Analyser) available","1. Open the patient dashboard | 2. Sample foreground and background colors of body text in vitals and diagnoses widgets | 3. Compute contrast ratios","Sample text=diagnosis names, vitals values","All normal-size body text has a contrast ratio of at least 4.5:1 against its background (WCAG 1.4.3); any value below the threshold is reported as a failure","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-010","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0019","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Color Contrast","Boundary: large text (>=18.66px bold / 24px) meets 3:1 threshold exactly","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; contrast tool available; page contains heading-size text","1. Identify large-text headings (patient name banner, section headings) | 2. Sample foreground/background colors | 3. Compute ratios and compare against the 3:1 large-text threshold","Sample=Patient name banner heading","Large-scale text meets at least 3:1 contrast; values at exactly 3:1 pass and values just below (e.g. 2.9:1) are flagged as boundary failures (WCAG 1.4.3)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-010","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0020","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Color Contrast","Verify UI component and graphical object contrast meets 3:1 (icons, borders, focus)","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; contrast tool available","1. Sample the contrast of form field borders against the page background | 2. Sample required-field indicator icons | 3. Sample the active state of toggles/checkboxes","Components=field borders, checkbox outline, required marker","Active UI components and meaningful graphical objects have at least 3:1 contrast against adjacent colors so their boundaries/state are perceivable (WCAG 1.4.11)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-010","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0021","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Use of Color","Negative: required-field and error states must not rely on color alone","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Registration Clerk; simulate grayscale/color-blindness view","1. View the registration form in grayscale | 2. Identify required fields | 3. Trigger validation errors | 4. Confirm required status and error status are conveyed by text/icon/asterisk, not color only","Form=Registration; mode=grayscale","Required and error states are distinguishable without color (asterisk, icon, or text label present); information conveyed by color alone is a WCAG 1.4.1 failure","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-011","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0022","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Icon Buttons","Verify the Logout icon control has an accessible name","Accessibility","Smoke","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; a11y tree inspector and screen reader available","1. Locate the logout icon control in the header/account menu | 2. Inspect its accessible name in the a11y tree | 3. Navigate to it with a screen reader and listen to the announcement","Control=Logout icon","The logout icon button exposes a clear accessible name such as Log out (via aria-label or visually hidden text) so it is announced meaningfully, not as button or blank (WCAG 4.1.2, 2.4.4)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-012","Accessibility; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0023","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Icon Buttons","Verify navigation/sidebar toggle icon button exposes name and expanded state","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician on a page with a collapsible navigation toggle","1. Locate the menu/sidebar toggle icon button | 2. Inspect accessible name and aria-expanded | 3. Activate it and confirm aria-expanded toggles true/false","Control=Nav toggle","The toggle has an accessible name (e.g. Toggle navigation) and exposes aria-expanded reflecting the current open/closed state, updating on activation (WCAG 4.1.2)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-012","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0024","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Icon Buttons","Negative: icon-only edit/delete buttons in a list lack distinguishing accessible names","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician viewing a list with repeated row-level icon actions (edit, delete)","1. Inspect the edit and delete icon buttons across multiple rows | 2. Confirm each has a unique, descriptive accessible name including row context","List=Allergies list with edit/delete per row","Each row-level icon button has a distinct accessible name (e.g. Delete allergy Penicillin) so screen-reader users can distinguish identical icons across rows; generic or empty names are reported as failures (WCAG 2.4.4, 4.1.2)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-012","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0025","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Data Tables","Verify data tables use proper header cells and scope associations","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician viewing a tabular widget (e.g. lab results or visit history)","1. Inspect the table markup/a11y tree | 2. Confirm column and row headers use th with appropriate scope | 3. Navigate cells with a screen reader and confirm headers are announced","Table=Lab results table","Table column/row headers are marked as header cells with correct scope so each data cell is announced with its associated header context (WCAG 1.3.1)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0026","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Data Tables","Negative: layout achieved with table markup but missing header semantics","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician viewing a grid that visually looks like a table","1. Inspect the grid markup | 2. Determine if it is a data table lacking th headers or a layout table misusing semantics | 3. Verify screen-reader navigation does not announce phantom or missing headers","Grid=Visit summary grid","A data table without header semantics (or a layout table exposing table semantics) is flagged; data tables must declare headers and layout structures must not falsely expose table roles (WCAG 1.3.1)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0027","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Reflow / Zoom","Verify content reflows without horizontal scrolling at 400% zoom (320px width)","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician on the patient dashboard at 1280px base width","1. Set browser zoom to 400% (equivalent to 320 CSS px viewport) | 2. Review the patient dashboard | 3. Scroll and confirm no loss of content or two-dimensional scrolling for primary content","Zoom=400%; Page=Patient Dashboard","Content reflows into a single column with only vertical scrolling; no content or functionality is lost and no horizontal scrolling is required for blocks of text (WCAG 1.4.10)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-014","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0028","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Reflow / Zoom","Verify text remains readable and functional at 200% zoom","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician on the Register a Patient screen at default zoom","1. Set browser zoom to 200% | 2. Review form labels, fields, and buttons | 3. Complete a registration step at this zoom level","Zoom=200%; Form=Registration","At 200% zoom all text is readable, controls remain operable and do not overlap or clip, and the registration step can be completed (WCAG 1.4.4)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-014","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0029","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Text Spacing","Verify content adapts when user text-spacing overrides are applied","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; a text-spacing bookmarklet/extension applying WCAG 1.4.12 metrics","1. Apply line-height 1.5x, paragraph spacing 2x, letter spacing 0.12em, word spacing 0.16em | 2. Review the patient dashboard | 3. Confirm no clipped or overlapping text or lost content","Page=Patient Dashboard; spacing per WCAG 1.4.12","With user text-spacing applied, no content is clipped, truncated, or overlapped and all information remains available (WCAG 1.4.12)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-014","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0030","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Time Limits","Verify session timeout warning is announced and extendable before logout","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician with an idle-session timeout configured in the OpenMRS RefApp","1. Remain idle until the pre-timeout warning appears | 2. Confirm a screen reader announces the warning | 3. Use the keyboard to extend the session before expiry","Idle timeout=configured; warning lead time present","Before the session expires the user receives a perceivable, screen-reader-announced warning and can extend the time limit via keyboard, satisfying time-limit accommodation (WCAG 2.2.1)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-015","Accessibility; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0031","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Time Limits","Negative: session expires without warning while clinician completes a form","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician entering a long encounter form; short idle timeout configured","1. Begin filling a long encounter/observation form | 2. Pause long enough to approach the timeout | 3. Observe whether any warning precedes data loss","Form=Encounter note; idle pause near timeout","A timeout that silently discards entered clinical data without warning or recovery is a WCAG 2.2.1 failure and a patient-safety/data-integrity risk; the system must warn and preserve data","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-015","Accessibility; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0032","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","State Transition","Validate Start Visit modal focus state transitions (closed->open->closed)","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician on a patient dashboard; Start Visit control available","1. State Closed: focus on Start Visit trigger | 2. Activate to transition to Open: focus moves into modal, background inert | 3. Confirm focus trapped while Open | 4. Press Escape to transition to Closed | 5. Confirm focus returns to trigger","Modal=Start Visit","Each state transition manages focus correctly: opening moves focus into the dialog and makes background inert, closing returns focus to the trigger; no orphaned focus in any state (WCAG 2.4.3, 4.1.2)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-002","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0033","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","State Transition","Validate aria-expanded transitions on the account dropdown menu","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; account/user menu in header","1. State Collapsed: inspect aria-expanded=false | 2. Activate menu via keyboard: aria-expanded=true and focus enters menu | 3. Arrow through items | 4. Escape: aria-expanded=false and focus returns to trigger","Menu=Account dropdown","aria-expanded accurately reflects collapsed/expanded states across transitions, menu items are reachable by keyboard, and Escape restores both state and focus (WCAG 4.1.2)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0034","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Decision Table","Decision table for form-field accessibility name resolution sources","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; a11y tree inspector available; test fields configured with varying labeling","1. Field with label only -> expect name from label | 2. Field with aria-label only -> name from aria-label | 3. Field with aria-labelledby -> name from referenced element | 4. Field with label + aria-label -> aria-label wins | 5. Field with none -> no accessible name (fail)","Variants: label-only; aria-label-only; aria-labelledby; label+aria-label; none","Accessible name is computed per the ARIA name-computation precedence for each combination; the none case yields an empty name and is reported as a labeling failure (WCAG 4.1.2)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-007","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-A11Y-0035","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Decision Table","Decision table for contrast pass/fail across text size and weight","Decision Table","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; contrast tool; sample texts of varied size/weight","1. Normal text 4.5:1 -> pass | 2. Normal text 4.4:1 -> fail | 3. Large text 3.0:1 -> pass | 4. Large text 2.9:1 -> fail | 5. Bold 14pt (large) at 3.1:1 -> pass","Combinations of size/weight/ratio","Each size/weight/ratio combination is classified pass or fail strictly per WCAG 1.4.3 thresholds; boundary values just under threshold fail and at threshold pass","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-010","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-A11Y-0036","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Pairwise","Pairwise screen-reader x browser coverage for registration flow announcements","Pairwise","System","P2","High","Medium","Test matrix of assistive tech and browsers prepared; synthetic registration data ready","1. NVDA + Chrome: complete registration, verify announcements | 2. JAWS + Edge: repeat | 3. VoiceOver + Safari: repeat | 4. NVDA + Firefox: repeat | 5. Compare label, error, and success announcements across pairs","Pairs: NVDA/Chrome; JAWS/Edge; VoiceOver/Safari; NVDA/Firefox","Field labels, validation errors, and success confirmations are announced correctly and consistently across each AT/browser pair; any pair-specific gap is documented (WCAG 4.1.2, 4.1.3)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-009","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0037","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Pairwise","Pairwise OS x zoom x input-method coverage for dashboard operability","Pairwise","System","P3","Medium","Low","Multiple OS/zoom/input combinations available","1. Windows + 200% zoom + keyboard | 2. macOS + 400% zoom + keyboard | 3. Windows + 100% + switch device | 4. macOS + 200% + keyboard | 5. Verify operability and reflow in each","Pairs across OS, zoom, input method","Dashboard remains operable and content reflows correctly across the sampled OS/zoom/input combinations with no loss of functionality (WCAG 1.4.10, 2.1.1)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-014","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-A11Y-0038","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Exploratory","Exploratory keyboard-only session across core clinician workflows","Exploratory","System","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; mouse unplugged; 60-minute timebox","1. Without a mouse, attempt find patient, start visit, record vitals, add diagnosis, and logout | 2. Note any control unreachable or non-operable by keyboard | 3. Record focus, trap, or announcement issues encountered","Workflows: search, visit, vitals, diagnosis, logout","All core clinician tasks are completable using the keyboard alone; any blocking interaction is logged as a defect with WCAG mapping (WCAG 2.1.1)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-001","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0039","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Exploratory","Exploratory screen-reader walkthrough of patient dashboard semantics","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; NVDA active; 45-minute timebox","1. Using virtual cursor, traverse headings, landmarks, lists, and tables | 2. Confirm heading hierarchy is logical | 3. Note any unlabeled controls, redundant announcements, or missing structure","Page=Patient Dashboard","Heading and landmark structure supports efficient screen-reader navigation; semantic gaps and verbose or missing announcements are documented (WCAG 1.3.1, 2.4.6)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-009","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0040","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Headings","Verify heading levels are properly nested without skips","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; a11y tree or HeadingsMap tool available","1. Open the patient dashboard | 2. Extract the heading outline | 3. Confirm a single h1 and no skipped levels (e.g. h2 to h4)","Page=Patient Dashboard","Headings form a logical hierarchy with one top-level h1 and no skipped levels, enabling structural navigation (WCAG 1.3.1, 2.4.6)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0041","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Page Title","Verify each page has a unique, descriptive document title","Functional","Sanity","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician navigating between Home, Registration, and Patient Dashboard","1. Visit each page | 2. Read the browser tab/document title | 3. Confirm it describes the page and patient context where relevant","Pages=Home, Registration, Dashboard","Each page has a unique, descriptive title that identifies its purpose (and patient context where applicable) for orientation (WCAG 2.4.2)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-006","Accessibility; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0042","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Language","Verify the page declares a valid language attribute","Accessibility","Sanity","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; ability to inspect the html element","1. Inspect the html element on multiple pages | 2. Confirm a valid lang attribute is set | 3. If locale is switched, confirm lang updates accordingly","lang=en; alt locale=es","The page programmatically declares its human language via a valid lang attribute so assistive tech uses correct pronunciation; it reflects the active locale (WCAG 3.1.1)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0043","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Images","Verify informative images have appropriate alt text and decorative images are hidden","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; a11y tree inspector","1. Inspect the OpenMRS logo and any informative icons | 2. Confirm informative images expose meaningful alt text | 3. Confirm purely decorative images use empty alt or are hidden from AT","Images=Logo, status icons","Informative images convey their meaning through accessible text and decorative images are hidden from assistive technology to avoid noise (WCAG 1.1.1)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0044","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Target Size","Verify interactive targets meet minimum size and spacing for touch use","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician on a touch device or with target-size inspection","1. Measure tap targets of row-level icon buttons | 2. Confirm each meets the recommended minimum size and spacing | 3. Attempt activation on touch without mis-taps","Targets=row icon buttons; device=tablet","Interactive targets are large enough and spaced to be reliably activated by touch, reducing mis-activation in clinical use (WCAG 2.5.5/2.5.8 best practice)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-012","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-A11Y-0045","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Login Accessibility","Verify the OpenMRS login form is fully keyboard and screen-reader accessible","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","On the OpenMRS RefApp login page; not yet authenticated; screen reader available","1. Tab to Username, type | 2. Tab to Password, type | 3. Tab to session Location select and choose | 4. Tab to Login and press Enter | 5. Confirm labels and any error are announced","Username=clinician-qa; Password=synthetic; Location=Outpatient Clinic","Login fields have associated labels, are reachable and operable by keyboard, errors are announced, and login completes without a mouse (WCAG 1.3.1, 2.1.1, 3.3.2)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-007","Accessibility; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0046","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Login Accessibility","Negative: login error announced and does not leak which credential was wrong","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","On the OpenMRS login page; screen reader active","1. Enter an invalid username/password combination | 2. Submit | 3. Listen for the error announcement | 4. Read the error text","Username=clinician-qa; Password=wrong-synthetic","The authentication error is announced via a live region and uses a generic message (does not reveal whether username or password was incorrect), balancing accessibility with security (WCAG 4.1.3)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-008","Accessibility; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0047","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Boundary Inputs","Boundary: accessible-name announcement for very long patient name in banner","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient with a maximal-length name registered; screen reader active","1. Open the dashboard of the patient with a long name | 2. Navigate to the patient name banner with a screen reader | 3. Confirm the full name is announced and visually not truncated in a way that loses information","Name=Aaaaaaaaaa Bbbbbbbbbb Cccccccccc (max length)","The full patient name is programmatically available and announced even at maximum length; any visual truncation still exposes the complete name to AT (WCAG 1.3.1)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0048","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","FHIR Accessibility","Verify FHIR Patient.name rendering preserves accessible structure for assistive tech","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","Resource Adapter Layer fetching Patient from a FHIR R4 endpoint; rendered in the patient banner","1. Retrieve a FHIR Patient resource | 2. Render name from name.given and name.family | 3. Inspect the rendered banner accessible name | 4. Confirm given+family compose a single coherent announced name","FHIR Patient.name.given=[Maya]; family=Quinn","FHIR name parts are composed into a coherent accessible name in the UI so screen-reader users hear the full name; no part is dropped or announced out of order (WCAG 1.3.1; FHIR R4)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility; Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-A11Y-0049","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","FHIR Accessibility","Verify coded clinical data (CodeableConcept) displays human-readable text, not raw codes","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","Resource Adapter Layer rendering a Condition/Observation with CodeableConcept; screen reader active","1. Retrieve a Condition with a coded diagnosis | 2. Render it in the diagnoses widget | 3. Confirm the display/text is shown and announced rather than the raw code | 4. Verify the code system is not read aloud to the user","Condition.code.text=Type 2 diabetes mellitus; system=SNOMED CT","The human-readable display text of coded concepts is presented and announced; raw codes and system URIs are not surfaced to end users as the primary content (WCAG 1.3.1; FHIR R4)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility; Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-A11Y-0050","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","HL7 Accessibility","Verify HL7 v2-sourced patient data renders with accessible labels in the adapter UI","HL7","Integration","P4","Low","Low","Resource Adapter Layer ingesting an HL7 v2 ADT message mapped to the patient banner","1. Ingest an ADT^A01 message with PID name fields | 2. Map PID-5 to the displayed name | 3. Inspect the rendered field for an associated label and accessible name","HL7 PID-5=Quinn^Maya","Patient data sourced from HL7 v2 segments is displayed with proper labels and accessible names in the UI, identical to native data, so assistive tech announces it correctly (WCAG 1.3.1; HL7 v2)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility; Standards-HL7; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-A11Y-0051","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Security Overlay","Security: focus is moved to logout confirmation and session cannot be operated post-logout via stale focus","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; screen reader active","1. Activate logout via keyboard | 2. Confirm focus moves to the login page or confirmation | 3. Press Back and attempt to operate a previously focused PHI control | 4. Confirm protected content is not operable without re-auth","Action=Logout then Back navigation","After logout focus moves to a safe post-logout context and previously focused PHI controls are not operable from cached pages without re-authentication (WCAG 2.4.3; security)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-012","Accessibility; Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0052","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","API Accessibility Support","API: REST patient response includes display fields needed to build accessible names","API","Integration","P4","Low","Low","Authorized API client with access to the OpenMRS REST patient endpoint","1. Call the patient REST endpoint for a synthetic patient | 2. Inspect the JSON for display/preferredName fields | 3. Confirm fields needed to construct an accessible UI name are present and non-empty","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/patient/{uuid}; patient=synthetic","The API returns the display/name fields the UI needs to compose an accessible, human-readable name; missing display data that would force code-only rendering is reported (supports WCAG 1.3.1)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility; Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0053","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Motion / Animation","Verify auto-updating content can be paused and respects reduced-motion preference","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; Active Visits auto-refreshing; OS prefers-reduced-motion enabled","1. Enable prefers-reduced-motion at the OS level | 2. Open a page with auto-updating or animated content | 3. Confirm non-essential motion is reduced/stopped and updates can be paused","Setting=prefers-reduced-motion: reduce","Non-essential animation/auto-update respects the reduced-motion preference and offers a pause/stop mechanism, preventing distraction and vestibular issues (WCAG 2.2.2, 2.3.3)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-015","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-A11Y-0054","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Adapter Parity","Pairwise: accessible-name parity for patient banner across source systems","Pairwise","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","Resource Adapter Layer configured against OpenMRS, OpenEMR, HAPI FHIR, and omiiCARE backends","1. Render the patient banner from each backend | 2. Inspect the accessible name in each | 3. Compare label association and announced name across the four sources","Backends=OpenMRS, OpenEMR, HAPI FHIR, omiiCARE","The patient banner exposes an equivalent, correctly labeled accessible name regardless of source system; any backend producing an unlabeled or inconsistent name is flagged (WCAG 1.3.1, 4.1.2)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility; Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-A11Y-0055","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Consistent Navigation","Verify navigation and component identification are consistent across pages","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician navigating multiple RefApp pages","1. Note the order and labels of header navigation on Home | 2. Navigate to Registration and Patient Dashboard | 3. Compare navigation order, labels, and icon meanings across pages","Pages=Home, Registration, Dashboard","Repeated navigation appears in a consistent relative order and components with the same function share consistent labels/icons across pages (WCAG 3.2.3, 3.2.4)","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y-005","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0056","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Error Prevention","Verify reversible confirmation for destructive clinical actions is keyboard/AT accessible","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; a deletable clinical item (allergy/diagnosis) present; screen reader active","1. Trigger delete on a clinical item via keyboard | 2. Confirm a confirmation dialog appears and is announced | 3. Cancel via Escape and confirm no deletion | 4. Repeat and confirm via keyboard","Item=Allergy Penicillin (synthetic)","Destructive clinical actions present an accessible, announced confirmation that is operable and cancelable by keyboard, preventing accidental data loss (WCAG 3.3.4, 2.1.1)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-008","Accessibility; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0057","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Database Integrity","Database: stored accessibility-relevant display name is non-null and trimmed for affected patients","Database","Integration","P4","Low","Low","Read access to a non-production OpenMRS database with synthetic data","1. Query person_name for synthetic patients | 2. Confirm given_name and family_name are non-null and non-empty | 3. Verify no leading/trailing whitespace that would distort announced names","Table=person_name; patients=synthetic set","Stored name fields used to build accessible UI names are non-null, non-empty, and trimmed so rendered accessible names are correct; anomalies are reported as data-integrity issues (supports WCAG 1.3.1)","Automatable","REQ-A11Y-013","Accessibility; Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y-0058","Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)","Audit","Verify accessibility-affecting setting changes (locale/theme) are audit-logged","Database","Regression","P4","Low","Low","Logged in as Admin with audit logging enabled","1. Change the system or user locale affecting lang/text direction | 2. Save | 3. Inspect the audit log for the change record with user, timestamp, old/new value","Setting=default locale en->es","Changes to accessibility-affecting configuration are recorded in the audit trail with actor and before/after values for regulatory traceability (Audit; supports WCAG 3.1.1)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y-006","Accessibility; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0001","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Page Response Time","Patient dashboard page load meets P95 response-time SLA under nominal load","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Performance test environment provisioned to production-equivalent spec; OpenMRS RefApp deployed with seeded dataset of 50,000 patients; JMeter/Gatling load harness configured; monitoring (APM) active","1. Configure load script to open Patient Dashboard for randomized existing patient IDs | 2. Ramp to 50 concurrent virtual users over 2 minutes | 3. Sustain steady state for 10 minutes | 4. Capture server-side and client-side response times | 5. Compute P50, P95, P99 latency","Patients=50000; ConcurrentUsers=50; PatientID pool=synthetic IDs 1001-51000; SLA target P95<=2000ms","Patient Dashboard P95 response time is <=2000ms and P99 <=3500ms; zero HTTP 5xx errors; results recorded against REQ-PERF-001","Automatable","REQ-PERF-001","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0002","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","API Response Time","REST patient search API meets latency budget at nominal throughput","API","System","P1","Critical","High","OpenMRS REST module enabled; 50,000 patients seeded; API auth token provisioned for performance service account; load harness configured against /ws/rest/v1/patient","1. Issue GET /ws/rest/v1/patient?q=<term> at 30 requests/sec | 2. Sustain for 10 minutes | 3. Record per-request latency and status codes | 4. Compute percentiles","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/patient?q=Smith; RPS=30; Duration=10m; SLA P95<=800ms","API P95 latency <=800ms, P99 <=1500ms, error rate <0.1%; criterion traced to REQ-PERF-002","Automatable","REQ-PERF-002","Clinical; Standards-FHIR","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0003","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Concurrent Users","System sustains target concurrent clinical user load without functional break","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Production-equivalent env; realistic mixed workflow script (login, search, open dashboard, enter vitals); 200 named test accounts provisioned","1. Ramp from 0 to 200 concurrent users over 10 minutes | 2. Each user executes mixed clinical workflow loop | 3. Sustain 30 minutes | 4. Monitor error rate, latency and throughput | 5. Validate sampled workflows complete functionally","ConcurrentUsers=200; RampUp=10m; Steady=30m; Workflow=login+search+dashboard+vitals","All workflows complete with functional correctness; aggregate error rate <0.5%; P95 transaction latency within per-transaction SLA; no deadlocks; traced to REQ-PERF-003","Automatable","REQ-PERF-003","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0004","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Concurrent Users","Concurrent-user threshold boundary: behavior at exactly rated capacity","Boundary","System","P1","High","High","Rated concurrent capacity defined as 200 users in NFR; load harness configured for precise user counts","1. Run load at 199 users for 10 minutes and record metrics | 2. Run load at exactly 200 users for 10 minutes | 3. Compare latency, error rate, resource utilization at each point","UserCounts=199,200; Duration=10m each; SLA P95<=2000ms","At 200 users (rated capacity) all SLAs are still met; metrics at 199 and 200 differ within expected linear range; no SLA breach at the boundary; traced to REQ-PERF-003","Automatable","REQ-PERF-003","Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0005","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Concurrent Users","Overload beyond rated capacity triggers graceful degradation not failure","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Rated capacity 200; rate limiting / connection pool limits configured per design; monitoring active","1. Ramp load to 300 users (150% of rated capacity) | 2. Sustain 10 minutes | 3. Observe rejection behavior, queueing, and error responses | 4. After test, return to 200 users and verify recovery","UserCounts=300 (overload); RecoveryUsers=200","System sheds excess load gracefully (e.g. HTTP 429/503 with retry semantics or queueing) rather than crashing; no data corruption; system recovers to nominal SLA within 5 minutes once load drops; traced to REQ-PERF-009","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-009","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0006","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Search Pagination","Patient list pagination latency stays within budget under high data volume","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","100,000 patients seeded; paginated patient list/search UI available; load harness configured","1. Execute search returning large result set | 2. Page through results requesting page sizes per criteria | 3. Measure time-to-first-page and subsequent page latency | 4. Record percentiles across 1000 paging operations","Patients=100000; PageSizes=10,25,50; Pages traversed=20","Each page request returns within P95<=1200ms regardless of page depth; deep pages do not show linear latency growth (keyset/indexed paging); traced to REQ-PERF-004","Automatable","REQ-PERF-004","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0007","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Search Pagination","Deep pagination boundary at maximum page offset","Boundary","System","P2","Medium","Medium","100,000 result-set query available; max supported page size and offset documented in design","1. Request the last page of a 100,000-row result at max page size | 2. Request one page beyond the last valid page | 3. Measure latency and validate response","ResultSet=100000; PageSize=50; LastPage=2000; OffsetBeyond=2001","Last valid page returns within latency budget; request beyond last page returns empty result set with success status (no error, no timeout); traced to REQ-PERF-004","Automatable","REQ-PERF-004","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0008","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Search Pagination","Search with zero matches returns quickly (negative-result performance)","Negative","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Large patient dataset seeded; search endpoint available","1. Execute search for a term guaranteed to match no records | 2. Measure response time | 3. Repeat 100 times under light concurrency","SearchTerm=ZZZQX-NOMATCH-9999; Iterations=100","Empty result returned with P95<=600ms; no full table scan observed in DB plan; traced to REQ-PERF-004","Automatable","REQ-PERF-004","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0009","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Report Generation","Standard clinical report generates within defined time budget","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","Reporting module configured; dataset of 50,000 patients with encounters seeded; report definition for patient encounter summary available","1. Trigger report generation for a 1-month date range | 2. Measure end-to-end generation time | 3. Repeat for 5 runs and average | 4. Validate output row count correctness","Report=Encounter Summary; DateRange=30 days; Runs=5; SLA<=30s","Report completes within <=30s for the defined range with correct row counts; no timeout; traced to REQ-PERF-005","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-005","Clinical; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0010","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Report Generation","Large-range report generation boundary and timeout handling","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Reporting configured; 12 months of seeded encounter data; configured report timeout threshold documented","1. Generate report for maximum supported range (12 months) | 2. Measure time | 3. Generate report for a range exceeding supported limit | 4. Observe handling","Report=Encounter Summary; MaxRange=12 months; ExcessRange=24 months","Max-range report completes within configured upper bound; excess-range request is either chunked/queued or rejected with a clear message rather than hanging or OOM; traced to REQ-PERF-005","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-005","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0011","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Report Generation","Concurrent report generation does not starve interactive clinical traffic","Decision Table","System","P1","High","High","Reporting + interactive workflows on same env; resource isolation/queue policy defined","1. Establish interactive baseline at 100 users | 2. Concurrently trigger 5 heavy reports | 3. Measure interactive latency during report execution | 4. Vary combinations of report count (0,5,10) vs interactive load (100,200) per decision table | 5. Record SLA pass/fail per cell","InteractiveUsers={100,200}; ConcurrentReports={0,5,10}; Interactive SLA P95<=2000ms","Interactive workflow SLA holds (P95<=2000ms) across decision-table combinations within rated capacity; reports may queue but interactive traffic is prioritized; traced to REQ-PERF-005 and REQ-PERF-009","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-005","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0012","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","DB Query Budget","Patient dashboard load stays within database query-count budget (N+1 guard)","Database","System","P1","High","High","DB query logging / APM SQL capture enabled; OpenMRS dashboard instrumented; single-user trace mode","1. Enable SQL statement capture | 2. Load a patient dashboard for one patient | 3. Count distinct SQL statements executed and total DB time | 4. Compare against query budget","QueryBudget<=40 statements per dashboard load; DBTime<=400ms","Dashboard load executes <=40 SQL statements with no N+1 explosion; total DB time <=400ms; any per-row repeated query is flagged; traced to REQ-PERF-006","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-006","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0013","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","DB Query Budget","Slow-query threshold: no single query exceeds budget under load","Database","System","P1","High","High","DB slow-query log enabled with threshold; load harness configured; representative workload script","1. Run mixed workload at rated capacity for 15 minutes | 2. Collect slow-query log entries above threshold | 3. Identify queries lacking index usage | 4. Capture execution plans for top offenders","SlowQueryThreshold=500ms; Workload=mixed; Duration=15m","No query exceeds 500ms during sustained rated load; all hot-path queries use indexes (no full scans on large tables); traced to REQ-PERF-006","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-006","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0014","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","DB Connection Pool","Connection pool exhaustion boundary under peak concurrency","Boundary","System","P1","Critical","High","DB connection pool max size configured per design; load harness can drive peak concurrency; pool metrics exposed","1. Drive concurrency to saturate the connection pool | 2. Monitor active vs idle vs waiting connections | 3. Push 10% beyond configured pool max | 4. Observe wait-timeout behavior","PoolMax=50; PeakConcurrency to saturate; Overshoot=+10%","At pool saturation, requests queue within configured wait timeout and succeed; beyond capacity, requests fail fast with a clear error rather than hanging indefinitely; no connection leak after test; traced to REQ-PERF-006","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-006","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0015","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Soak/Stability","24-hour soak test shows no memory leak or latency drift","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Dedicated soak environment; sustained moderate load script; heap/GC and resource monitoring with retention >24h","1. Apply 40% of rated load continuously for 24 hours | 2. Sample heap usage, GC frequency, latency hourly | 3. Plot trend lines | 4. Compare hour-1 vs hour-24 metrics","Load=40% rated; Duration=24h; SampleInterval=1h","No upward drift in heap baseline after GC across 24h (no leak); P95 latency at hour-24 within 10% of hour-1; no resource exhaustion; traced to REQ-PERF-007","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-007","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0016","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Soak/Stability","Endurance stability: error rate remains flat over extended run","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","Soak environment; long-duration script; error logging aggregated","1. Run 8-hour endurance test at 60% rated load | 2. Aggregate error counts per hour | 3. Detect any cumulative error growth or connection leak | 4. Verify thread counts stable","Load=60% rated; Duration=8h","Hourly error rate stays flat (no cumulative growth); thread and handle counts remain bounded; traced to REQ-PERF-007","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-007","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0017","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Resource Utilization","CPU utilization stays below threshold at rated load","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","Production-equivalent sizing; OS/container CPU metrics collected; rated load script ready","1. Apply rated load (200 users) for 20 minutes | 2. Sample CPU per app and DB node | 3. Compute sustained average and peak CPU | 4. Compare to thresholds","RatedUsers=200; CPUThreshold sustained<=70%; peak<=85%","Sustained CPU <=70% with headroom; peaks <=85%; no sustained saturation; traced to REQ-PERF-008","Automatable","REQ-PERF-008","Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0018","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Resource Utilization","Memory and GC pressure stay within thresholds at rated load","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","JVM heap and GC metrics exposed; rated load script ready; container memory limits set","1. Apply rated load for 20 minutes | 2. Sample heap used, GC pause time, GC frequency | 3. Verify no near-limit memory pressure or long GC pauses","RatedUsers=200; HeapThreshold<=75%; MaxGCPause<=200ms","Heap usage stays <=75% of limit; no GC pause >200ms; no OutOfMemory; traced to REQ-PERF-008","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-008","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0019","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Resource Utilization","Resource threshold pairwise coverage across node/load/cache combinations","Pairwise","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Multiple env configurations available (app nodes, load levels, cache on/off); test matrix tool used to derive pairwise set","1. Generate pairwise combinations of AppNodes{1,2}, Load{nominal,peak}, Cache{on,off} | 2. Execute each selected combination for 10 minutes | 3. Record CPU, memory, latency per run | 4. Validate thresholds per run","Factors=AppNodes{1,2},Load{nominal,peak},Cache{on,off}; pairwise-reduced set","Each pairwise combination meets resource and latency thresholds; cache-off + peak is the worst case and still bounded; traced to REQ-PERF-008","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-008","Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-PERF-0020","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Graceful Degradation","Dependency slowdown (DB latency injection) degrades gracefully","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Fault-injection capability to add DB latency; circuit-breaker/timeout config per design; monitoring active","1. Baseline at nominal load (state: Normal) | 2. Inject 500ms DB latency (state: Degraded) | 3. Observe timeouts, retries, user-facing behavior | 4. Remove latency injection (state: Recovering) | 5. Confirm return to Normal","InjectedDBLatency=500ms; Load=nominal","System transitions Normal->Degraded with bounded user impact (timeouts surface clean errors, no cascading crash), then Recovering->Normal once fault clears within 2 minutes; traced to REQ-PERF-009","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-009","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0021","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Graceful Degradation","Downstream service unavailable falls back without functional break","Negative","Integration","P1","Critical","High","A non-critical downstream integration (e.g. lab results feed) can be disabled; fallback design defined","1. Establish nominal load | 2. Make downstream service unreachable | 3. Exercise workflows depending on it | 4. Verify fallback or clear unavailability messaging | 5. Restore service","Downstream=Lab feed; State=unreachable","Core clinical workflows continue; dependent feature shows graceful unavailable state, not a crash or hang; no PHI loss; recovery automatic on restore; traced to REQ-PERF-009","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-009","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-PERF-0022","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","No Functional Break Under Load","Vitals entry remains functionally correct under sustained load","Functional","E2E","P1","Critical","High","Rated load running; vitals entry workflow scripted; data verification queries prepared","1. Under 80% rated load, submit 500 vitals entries with known values | 2. After test, query persisted observations | 3. Compare submitted vs stored values | 4. Check for partial writes or duplicates","Load=80% rated; VitalsRecords=500; Fields=BP,Pulse,Temp,SpO2","All 500 vitals persisted exactly with no data loss, duplication, or value corruption under load; traced to REQ-PERF-010","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-010","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0023","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","No Functional Break Under Load","Concurrent order entry maintains data integrity (no lost updates)","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Order entry workflow available; concurrency harness can target same and different patients; DB integrity checks ready","1. Drive concurrent order submissions for overlapping patients | 2. Include simultaneous edits to same encounter | 3. After run, verify no lost updates, no orphan records, referential integrity intact","ConcurrentOrders=200; OverlapPatients=20","No lost updates or race-induced corruption; optimistic/locking behavior preserves integrity; all FK constraints satisfied; traced to REQ-PERF-010","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-010","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0024","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","FHIR API Performance","FHIR Patient read endpoint meets latency SLA under load","FHIR","System","P2","High","Medium","FHIR2 module enabled (or HAPI FHIR adapter); 50,000 Patient resources available; load harness targeting /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient","1. Issue GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient/<id> at 25 RPS | 2. Sustain 10 minutes | 3. Validate FHIR response conformance and latency | 4. Compute percentiles","Endpoint=/ws/fhir2/R4/Patient/{id}; RPS=25; SLA P95<=900ms","FHIR read P95<=900ms with valid R4 Patient resources; error rate <0.1%; traced to REQ-PERF-011","Automatable","REQ-PERF-011","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0025","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","FHIR API Performance","FHIR search bundle pagination performance under volume","FHIR","System","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR endpoint with large Observation dataset; _count and pagination links supported","1. Execute GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Observation?patient=<id>&_count=50 | 2. Follow next-link pages | 3. Measure per-page latency and bundle correctness across deep pages","Endpoint=/ws/fhir2/R4/Observation; _count=50; PatientObs=5000","Each FHIR search page returns within P95<=1500ms with correct next/self links and total handling; no degradation on deep pages; traced to REQ-PERF-011","Automatable","REQ-PERF-011","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PERF-0026","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","FHIR API Performance","FHIR Bundle transaction throughput and atomicity under load","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR transaction endpoint available; bundle payloads prepared; concurrency harness ready","1. POST transaction Bundles at 10 RPS for 10 minutes | 2. Each bundle creates Patient+Encounter+Observation | 3. Verify atomic commit and latency | 4. Check for partial commits on any error","Endpoint=/ws/fhir2/R4 (transaction); RPS=10; BundleEntries=3","Transaction bundles commit atomically within P95<=2000ms; no partial commits; throughput sustained; traced to REQ-PERF-011","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-011","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PERF-0027","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","HL7 Interface Performance","HL7 v2 ADT message ingestion throughput meets criteria","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 listener/interface engine configured (or omiiCARE adapter); MLLP feeder available; message backlog generator ready","1. Feed ADT^A01 messages at 50 msgs/sec for 10 minutes | 2. Measure end-to-end processing latency and ACK turnaround | 3. Verify no message loss and queue depth stays bounded","MessageType=ADT^A01; Rate=50/sec; Duration=10m","All messages processed with ACK within P95<=1000ms; queue depth bounded; zero message loss; traced to REQ-PERF-012","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-012","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PERF-0028","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","HL7 Interface Performance","HL7 burst-load boundary and backpressure handling","HL7","System","P2","High","Medium","HL7 interface configured with queue depth limits; burst generator available","1. Send a sudden burst at 3x nominal rate for 2 minutes | 2. Observe queue depth, NACK/backpressure behavior | 3. Return to nominal | 4. Verify backlog drains without loss","NominalRate=50/sec; BurstRate=150/sec; BurstDuration=2m","Burst is absorbed via queueing/backpressure with no message loss; backlog drains to zero after burst; no NACK storm or crash; traced to REQ-PERF-012","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-012","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PERF-0029","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Caching","Cache hit improves response time and reduces DB load (positive case)","Performance","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Caching layer enabled for reference/concept data; cache metrics exposed; load harness ready","1. Warm cache via initial requests | 2. Run repeated reads of cacheable data under load | 3. Measure cache hit ratio and latency vs cold baseline | 4. Confirm DB query reduction","CacheableData=Concept dictionary; Load=nominal","Cache hit ratio >=90% in steady state; cached-path latency markedly lower than cold; DB query volume reduced; traced to REQ-PERF-013","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-013","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0030","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Caching","Cold cache / cache stampede behavior under concurrent miss","Negative","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Caching enabled; ability to flush cache; concurrency harness ready","1. Flush cache | 2. Simultaneously fire many requests for the same uncached key | 3. Observe whether a stampede of DB queries occurs | 4. Measure latency spike and recovery","Concurrency=100 same-key; CacheState=cold","Cache miss is coalesced (single-flight) or limited; no thundering-herd DB overload; latency spike bounded and recovers; traced to REQ-PERF-013","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-013","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PERF-0031","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Login/Auth Performance","Authentication and session creation latency under login storm","Security","System","P2","High","Medium","Auth subsystem configured; many test accounts available; load harness can simulate simultaneous logins","1. Simulate a morning login storm of 200 logins within 60 seconds | 2. Measure auth latency and success rate | 3. Verify session tokens issued correctly | 4. Confirm no auth bypass or lockout misfire","LoginStorm=200 logins/60s; Accounts=synthetic","All logins authenticate within P95<=1500ms; 100% correct success/failure decisions; no spurious lockouts; no auth bypass under load; traced to REQ-PERF-014","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-014","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0032","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Security Under Load","Rate limiting / throttling prevents abuse without harming legit traffic","Security","System","P2","High","Medium","Rate limiting configured per design; harness can generate abusive and legitimate traffic concurrently","1. Generate abusive request flood from one client identity | 2. Concurrently run legitimate user traffic | 3. Verify abuser is throttled (429) while legit traffic stays within SLA","AbuserRate=500/sec; LegitLoad=nominal","Abusive client receives throttling responses; legitimate traffic SLA unaffected; no global outage from one bad actor; traced to REQ-PERF-014","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-014","Security","Platform"
"TC-PERF-0033","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Audit Logging Performance","Audit log write does not breach latency budget on PHI access under load","Database","System","P1","High","High","HIPAA audit logging enabled for PHI access; load harness exercising patient record views; audit store monitored","1. Drive PHI-access workflows at rated load for 15 minutes | 2. Verify every access produces an audit record | 3. Measure added latency from audit write | 4. Confirm no audit records dropped","Load=rated; Workflow=patient record view; AuditOverheadBudget<=50ms","Audit logging adds <=50ms overhead; zero audit records lost under load; access latency still within SLA; traced to REQ-PERF-015","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-015","Audit; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0034","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Network/Payload","Large clinical payload (bulk observation) handling within budget","Boundary","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Endpoint accepting bulk observation submission; payload size limits documented","1. Submit increasing payload sizes up to documented max | 2. Submit one payload just over the max | 3. Measure latency at max and observe rejection behavior over max","MaxPayload=5MB; Over=6MB; Observations per payload up to 1000","At max payload, request succeeds within budget; over-max is rejected cleanly with a clear 413-style error rather than timeout/crash; traced to REQ-PERF-002","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-002","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0035","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Scalability","Horizontal scale-out maintains SLA (decision table of nodes vs load)","Decision Table","System","P2","High","Medium","Cluster can run with 1, 2, 3 app nodes behind load balancer; shared DB; load harness configurable","1. For each node count, run load levels {nominal, peak, overload} | 2. Record SLA pass/fail per cell of node x load matrix | 3. Confirm scale-out restores SLA where single node fails","Nodes={1,2,3}; Load={nominal,peak,overload}","SLA pass/fail matrix shows adding nodes recovers SLA at peak/overload; near-linear throughput scaling within tested range; traced to REQ-PERF-016","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-016","Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-PERF-0036","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Cold Start","Application cold-start and readiness time within boot SLA","Functional","System","P3","Medium","Low","Ability to restart app node; readiness probe defined; timing instrumentation","1. Stop app node | 2. Start node and timestamp until readiness probe passes | 3. Issue first real request and measure first-request latency | 4. Repeat 3 times","BootSLA<=120s; FirstRequestBudget<=3000ms","Node reaches ready state within <=120s; first post-boot request completes within <=3000ms (warm-up allowance); traced to REQ-PERF-017","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-017","Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-PERF-0037","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Failover","Node failover under load preserves in-flight criteria and recovers SLA","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Multi-node cluster with load balancer; session/failover design defined; load running","1. Run nominal load across cluster (state: Healthy) | 2. Kill one app node mid-load (state: Degraded) | 3. Observe LB redistribution and in-flight request handling | 4. Confirm SLA recovery (state: Recovered)","Nodes=2; KillNode=1; Load=nominal","On node loss, traffic redistributes; in-flight requests fail over or surface clean retryable errors (no PHI corruption); SLA recovers within 60s; traced to REQ-PERF-016","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-016","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PERF-0038","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Exploratory","Exploratory performance hot-spot hunt across clinical workflows","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","APM/profiler attached; seeded realistic data; tester familiar with clinical workflows; time-boxed charter","1. Time-box 90 minutes | 2. Exercise diverse workflows (registration, encounter, orders, reports, search) while watching APM traces | 3. Note any operation exceeding perceived-instant threshold | 4. Capture worst traces and resource spikes | 5. Log candidate bottlenecks","Charter=Find latency hot-spots; TimeBox=90m","Documented list of slowest operations with traces and reproducible steps; at least the top hot-spots identified for follow-up; no critical workflow silently exceeds budget; traced to REQ-PERF-001","Manual-Only","REQ-PERF-001","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0039","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Accessibility Under Load","Assistive-tech-driven workflow remains responsive under nominal load","Accessibility","System","P3","Medium","Low","Screen-reader/keyboard-only test path defined; background nominal load applied; accessibility tooling ready","1. Apply nominal background load | 2. Complete a keyboard-only patient search and dashboard open with screen reader | 3. Measure perceived responsiveness and focus-update latency | 4. Confirm no UI freeze blocking AT","BackgroundLoad=nominal; Path=keyboard+screen-reader","Accessible workflow stays responsive under load with focus and live-region updates within perceptible budget; no long-task freeze; traced to REQ-PERF-001","Manual-Only","REQ-PERF-001","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0040","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Capacity Planning","Throughput ceiling discovery (stress to breaking point) for capacity model","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Stress environment isolated from shared systems; monitoring with high retention; staged ramp script","1. Ramp load in stages beyond rated capacity until SLA breaches | 2. Record the user count and throughput at first SLA breach (knee) and at saturation | 3. Identify the limiting resource (CPU/DB/pool) | 4. Document capacity headroom vs rated","StartUsers=200; Ramp step=+50; Until SLA breach","Knee point and max throughput identified with the bottleneck resource named; rated capacity confirmed to have documented headroom margin; traced to REQ-PERF-016","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-016","Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-PERF-0041","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Pairwise Workflow Mix","Pairwise mixed-workload combinations meet aggregate SLA","Pairwise","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Multiple workflow types scriptable; pairwise tool to derive mix combinations; load harness","1. Derive pairwise set across WorkflowMix{search-heavy,write-heavy,report-heavy}, Cache{on,off}, DataVolume{50k,100k} | 2. Run each selected combo at nominal load | 3. Validate aggregate SLA per combo","Factors=Mix{search,write,report},Cache{on,off},Volume{50k,100k}; pairwise set","Each pairwise workload combination meets aggregate SLA; worst-case combo identified and still within criteria or flagged; traced to REQ-PERF-003","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-003","Clinical","Platform"
"TC-PERF-0042","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","Data Volume Scaling","Response time degradation across growing data volumes stays sub-linear","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Datasets seeded at 10k, 50k, 100k, 500k patients on comparable envs; same query workload","1. Run identical search/dashboard workload against each dataset size | 2. Record P95 latency per size | 3. Plot latency vs volume | 4. Verify growth is sub-linear (indexed access)","Volumes={10k,50k,100k,500k}; Workload=search+dashboard","Latency growth is sub-linear across volumes (no full-scan blowup); 500k dataset still within or near SLA with documented margin; traced to REQ-PERF-004","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF-004","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF-0043","Performance Readiness (criteria/design)","API Error-Path Performance","Malformed/unauthorized API requests are rejected fast under load","Negative","System","P3","Medium","Medium","REST/FHIR endpoints available; harness can send malformed and unauthorized requests; monitoring active","1. Under nominal load, inject 10% malformed and 10% unauthorized requests | 2. Measure rejection latency and ensure they do not consume disproportionate resources | 3. Confirm valid-request SLA unaffected","MalformedPct=10; UnauthorizedPct=10; Load=nominal","Invalid requests are rejected quickly (4xx) without heavy processing; they do not degrade valid-request SLA; no resource amplification from bad input; traced to REQ-PERF-002","Automatable","REQ-PERF-002","Security; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-NOTIF-0001","Notifications & Alerts","Appointment Reminders","Generate appointment reminder for a scheduled visit within reminder window","Functional","Smoke","P1","High","High","Logged in as Scheduler; patient has a future appointment scheduled and an active opt-in for reminders; reminder lead time configured to 24h","1. Open the patient appointment record | 2. Confirm appointment time is within the 24h reminder window | 3. Trigger the reminder scheduler job | 4. Inspect the notification queue for the patient","Patient=Jane Synthetic; Appt=02-Jul-2026 10:00; ReminderLead=24h; Channel=SMS","A single reminder notification is created in the queue for the patient with correct appointment date/time, channel SMS, and status Pending","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-001","Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0002","Notifications & Alerts","Appointment Reminders","Suppress reminder when appointment is cancelled before send","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Reminder is queued in Pending state for a future appointment; logged in as Scheduler","1. Confirm a Pending reminder exists for the appointment | 2. Cancel the appointment | 3. Re-run the reminder scheduler | 4. Inspect the reminder state","Appt status: Scheduled -> Cancelled; Reminder=Pending","Reminder transitions from Pending to Cancelled/Suppressed and is not delivered to the patient","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0003","Notifications & Alerts","Appointment Reminders","Reminder lead-time boundary at exactly the configured window edge","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Reminder lead time configured to exactly 24h; appointment exists; logged in as Scheduler","1. Set appointment to exactly 24h00m00s from current time | 2. Run scheduler | 3. Set a second appointment to 24h00m01s | 4. Run scheduler | 5. Compare which appointments queued a reminder","ApptA=now+24h00m00s; ApptB=now+24h00m01s; Lead=24h","Appointment at exactly 24h is included in the reminder batch; appointment just outside the window is not, per inclusive boundary rule","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-002","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0004","Notifications & Alerts","Appointment Reminders","No duplicate reminder created when scheduler runs twice","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","An appointment is eligible for a reminder; reminder scheduler idempotency enabled","1. Run reminder scheduler once | 2. Confirm one Pending reminder exists | 3. Run scheduler again without state change | 4. Inspect queue count for the appointment","Appt=02-Jul-2026 10:00; Channel=Email","Exactly one reminder exists; the second run does not create a duplicate notification","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-003","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0005","Notifications & Alerts","Critical Result Alerts","Critical lab result triggers high-priority clinician alert","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Lab Tech; ordering provider on record; critical-result thresholds configured for Potassium","1. Enter a lab result above the critical-high threshold | 2. Save the result | 3. Open the ordering provider notification inbox | 4. Verify alert content","Patient=Synthetic A; Test=Potassium; Value=7.2 mmol/L; CriticalHigh=>6.0","A critical-result alert is generated for the ordering provider with priority Critical, the abnormal value, and reference range, in real time","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-004","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0006","Notifications & Alerts","Critical Result Alerts","Critical alert escalates when not acknowledged within SLA","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Critical-result alert delivered to primary provider; escalation SLA configured to 15 minutes; backup provider defined","1. Deliver a critical alert to the primary provider | 2. Do not acknowledge | 3. Advance time beyond the 15-minute SLA | 4. Run escalation job | 5. Inspect alert routing","Test=Troponin; Value=High; SLA=15m; Backup=On-call MD","Unacknowledged alert escalates from primary provider to the backup/on-call provider and is logged with an escalation timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-005","Patient Safety; Clinical; Audit","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0007","Notifications & Alerts","Critical Result Alerts","Acknowledgement state transition from New to Acknowledged","State Transition","Regression","P1","High","High","A critical alert exists in New state in the provider inbox; logged in as that provider","1. Open the New critical alert | 2. Click Acknowledge | 3. Confirm acknowledgement | 4. Inspect alert state and audit log","Alert=Critical-Potassium; Provider=Dr Synthetic","Alert transitions New -> Acknowledged, escalation timer is stopped, and an audit entry records the acknowledging user and timestamp","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-006","Patient Safety; Audit","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0008","Notifications & Alerts","Critical Result Alerts","Invalid state transition from Acknowledged back to New is rejected","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","An alert is already in Acknowledged state; logged in as provider","1. Open the Acknowledged alert | 2. Attempt to set the alert back to New via UI/API | 3. Inspect the response and the alert state","Alert state=Acknowledged","The system rejects the illegal transition; alert remains Acknowledged and an error is returned; no audit corruption occurs","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-006","Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0009","Notifications & Alerts","Allergy Alerts","Drug-allergy alert fires when ordering a contraindicated medication","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; patient has a documented penicillin allergy; CDS allergy checking enabled","1. Open the patient order entry | 2. Order Amoxicillin | 3. Observe the interaction/allergy check | 4. Read the alert details","Patient=Synthetic B; Allergy=Penicillin (severe); Order=Amoxicillin 500mg","A drug-allergy alert is presented before order confirmation, naming the allergen, severity, and the conflicting medication","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-007","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0010","Notifications & Alerts","Interaction Alerts","Drug-drug interaction alert with override reason capture","Decision Table","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Provider; patient already on Warfarin; interaction checking enabled","1. Order Aspirin for the patient | 2. Observe interaction alert | 3. Choose to override | 4. Attempt to proceed without an override reason | 5. Enter a valid override reason and proceed","Patient on Warfarin; New order=Aspirin; Severity=Major","Interaction alert appears; override is blocked until a reason is entered; with a valid reason the order proceeds and the override reason is stored and auditable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-008","Patient Safety; Clinical; Audit","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0011","Notifications & Alerts","Alert Fatigue / Dedup","Duplicate identical allergy alert is suppressed within dedup window","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patient with penicillin allergy; same contraindicated drug ordered twice in one session; dedup window configured","1. Order Amoxicillin and trigger the allergy alert | 2. Dismiss/acknowledge the alert | 3. Re-order the same Amoxicillin in the same session within the dedup window | 4. Observe alerting behavior","Drug=Amoxicillin; DedupWindow=session/60m","The second identical alert is deduplicated/suppressed or shown as already-acknowledged rather than presented as a brand-new interruptive alert","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-009","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0012","Notifications & Alerts","Alert Fatigue / Dedup","Distinct alerts for different drugs are not collapsed by dedup logic","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patient with multiple allergies; dedup enabled","1. Order Drug A and trigger an allergy alert | 2. Order Drug B with a different allergen conflict | 3. Verify both alerts are surfaced","DrugA=Amoxicillin (penicillin); DrugB=Sulfamethoxazole (sulfa)","Both distinct allergy alerts are presented; dedup does not incorrectly suppress the second, clinically different alert","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-009","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0013","Notifications & Alerts","System Messages","Display in-app system maintenance banner to all logged-in users","Functional","Sanity","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as System Administrator; a system message broadcast feature is available","1. Create a system message with start/end window | 2. Activate the broadcast | 3. Log in as a clinical user | 4. Verify the banner is shown","Message=""Scheduled maintenance 22:00-23:00""; Audience=All","All active users see the system message banner during the active window; the banner is dismissible and does not block clinical workflow","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-010","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-NOTIF-0014","Notifications & Alerts","In-App Alerts","OpenMRS alert is delivered to a specific user role inbox","Functional","Smoke","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Administrator on OpenMRS RefApp; target user account exists","1. Navigate to the Manage Alerts admin screen | 2. Create an alert addressed to a specific user | 3. Save the alert | 4. Log in as the target user | 5. Open the alert/notification area","Recipient=clerk1; Text=""Please review pending tasks""","The targeted user sees the alert in their notification area; non-targeted users do not see it","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-011","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-NOTIF-0015","Notifications & Alerts","In-App Alerts","Mark OpenMRS alert as read removes it from active alert list","State Transition","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as a user who has at least one unread alert in OpenMRS","1. Open the alert list | 2. Confirm the alert shows as unread | 3. Mark the alert as read | 4. Refresh the alert list","Alert text=""Task assigned""","The alert is marked read for that user and no longer appears in the active/unread alert list; state persists across sessions","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-011","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-NOTIF-0016","Notifications & Alerts","Delivery Channels","Email delivery of appointment reminder succeeds with valid address","Functional","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Patient opted in to email reminders with a valid email; SMTP/email gateway configured","1. Queue an email reminder for the patient | 2. Trigger the delivery worker | 3. Inspect delivery status and gateway response | 4. Verify message content","Email=jane.synthetic@example.test; Channel=Email","Email reminder is sent, delivery status is Delivered/Sent, and the message contains correct appointment details","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-012","Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0017","Notifications & Alerts","Delivery Channels","SMS delivery to invalid phone number is handled with failure status","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Patient opted in to SMS reminders but has a malformed phone number; SMS gateway configured","1. Queue an SMS reminder | 2. Trigger delivery | 3. Inspect gateway response and reminder status | 4. Verify error handling","Phone=+1-000; Channel=SMS","Delivery fails gracefully with status Failed and a captured gateway error; the failure is logged and does not crash the worker","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-013","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0018","Notifications & Alerts","Delivery Failure Handling","Failed delivery is retried per backoff policy up to max attempts","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Delivery worker configured with retries=3 and exponential backoff; gateway returns transient failure","1. Queue a notification | 2. Force a transient gateway error | 3. Allow the worker to retry | 4. Count attempts and inspect timing | 5. Observe terminal state after max attempts","Retries=3; Backoff=exp; Error=503 transient","Notification is retried up to exactly 3 times with increasing delays; after the final failed attempt it moves to a terminal Failed/Dead-letter state","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-013","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0019","Notifications & Alerts","Delivery Failure Handling","Channel fallback from SMS to email on persistent SMS failure","Decision Table","System","P2","High","Medium","Patient opted in to SMS with email as fallback; SMS gateway down","1. Queue reminder with channel preference SMS then Email | 2. Force SMS to fail all retries | 3. Observe fallback routing | 4. Verify final delivery channel","Primary=SMS; Fallback=Email","After SMS exhausts retries, the system falls back to Email and the reminder is delivered via Email with the fallback recorded","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-014","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0020","Notifications & Alerts","Opt-In / Opt-Out","Patient opts out of SMS reminders and no SMS is sent","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Patient currently opted in to SMS reminders; logged in as patient or registration staff updating consent","1. Open patient communication preferences | 2. Set SMS reminders to Opt-Out | 3. Save preferences | 4. Queue an appointment reminder | 5. Inspect delivery channels","Patient=Synthetic C; SMS=Opt-Out; Email=Opt-In","No SMS is sent after opt-out; only the remaining opted-in channels are used; the consent change is timestamped and auditable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-015","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0021","Notifications & Alerts","Opt-In / Opt-Out","Opt-out does not suppress mandatory critical safety alerts to clinicians","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Patient has opted out of marketing/reminder communications; a critical clinical alert is generated for clinicians","1. Confirm patient opt-out status for reminders | 2. Generate a critical-result alert tied to that patient | 3. Verify clinician alerting","Patient opt-out=reminders; Alert=Critical lab to provider","Patient-facing reminder opt-out does NOT suppress clinician-directed critical safety alerts; the provider still receives the critical alert","Manual-Only","REQ-NOTIF-015","Patient Safety; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0022","Notifications & Alerts","Opt-In / Opt-Out","Opt-out preference persists across sessions and is not overwritten by defaults","Database","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patient previously set SMS Opt-Out; database access available to verify persisted preference","1. Verify SMS preference is Opt-Out in the preference store | 2. Log out and back in | 3. Re-open preferences | 4. Query the persisted preference record","DB table: communication_preference; patient_id=synthetic","The persisted opt-out value is unchanged after re-login; default seeding logic does not overwrite an explicit patient choice","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-015","PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0023","Notifications & Alerts","FHIR Communication","Create FHIR Communication resource for a delivered notification","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR endpoint available via the Resource Adapter Layer; OAuth token with write scope","1. POST a Communication resource representing a sent reminder | 2. Capture the resource id | 3. GET the resource | 4. Validate required fields","status=completed; category=notification; payload=appt reminder; recipient=Patient/123","The Communication resource is created with HTTP 201, a server-assigned id, status completed, and valid recipient/payload references per FHIR R4","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-016","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-NOTIF-0024","Notifications & Alerts","FHIR CommunicationRequest","Validate FHIR CommunicationRequest for a queued reminder","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR endpoint available; reminder queued as a CommunicationRequest","1. GET the CommunicationRequest for the queued reminder | 2. Validate status and intent | 3. Validate occurrence timing and recipient","status=active; intent=order; occurrenceDateTime=appt time","CommunicationRequest validates against FHIR R4: status active, intent present, occurrence timing matches the appointment, recipient references the patient","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-016","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-NOTIF-0025","Notifications & Alerts","FHIR Validation","Reject FHIR Communication with missing required status element","Negative","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR endpoint with validation enabled","1. POST a Communication resource omitting the required status element | 2. Inspect the response","Communication without status field","Server returns HTTP 400/422 with an OperationOutcome indicating the missing required status; the invalid resource is not persisted","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-017","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-NOTIF-0026","Notifications & Alerts","HL7 Messaging","Generate HL7 v2 result message that triggers critical-result notification","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 v2 interface configured to receive ORU^R01 result messages; critical thresholds mapped","1. Send an ORU^R01 message with an abnormal flag for a critical analyte | 2. Process the message | 3. Verify a critical-result alert is generated","MSH/OBX with abnormal flag=HH; analyte=Potassium 7.2","The ORU^R01 with abnormal flag HH is parsed and triggers a critical-result notification to the ordering provider","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-018","Standards-HL7; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-NOTIF-0027","Notifications & Alerts","HL7 Messaging","Malformed HL7 message segment is rejected and ACK reflects error","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 v2 interface configured","1. Send an ORU message with a malformed/missing required OBX segment | 2. Process the message | 3. Inspect the ACK","ORU with corrupted OBX segment","The interface returns an application error ACK (AE/AR); no spurious alert is generated; the error is logged for review","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-018","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-NOTIF-0028","Notifications & Alerts","Notification API","Retrieve unacknowledged alerts via API for a provider","API","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","REST API available; valid auth token for a provider with pending alerts","1. Call GET /notifications?status=unacknowledged with the provider token | 2. Inspect the response payload | 3. Verify pagination and counts","Token=provider; status=unacknowledged","API returns 200 with the provider's unacknowledged alerts, correct total count, and pagination metadata; no other provider's alerts are leaked","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-019","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0029","Notifications & Alerts","Notification API","Acknowledge alert via API updates state and is idempotent","API","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","REST API available; an unacknowledged alert id known; valid provider token","1. POST acknowledge for the alert id | 2. Verify state becomes Acknowledged | 3. POST acknowledge again for the same id | 4. Inspect response","alert_id=NA-1001; token=provider","First acknowledge returns 200 and sets Acknowledged; second call is idempotent (200/409 without corrupting state); audit records a single acknowledgement","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-006","Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0030","Notifications & Alerts","Notification API Security","Provider cannot acknowledge another provider's alert (authorization)","Security","Integration","P1","Critical","High","REST API available; alert belongs to Provider A; valid token for Provider B","1. As Provider B, call acknowledge on Provider A's alert id | 2. Inspect the response and the alert state","alert_id owned by Provider A; token=Provider B","API returns 403 Forbidden (or 404); the alert remains owned by and unacknowledged for Provider A; the attempt is logged","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-020","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0031","Notifications & Alerts","Notification API Security","Unauthenticated request to notifications endpoint is rejected","Security","Integration","P1","High","High","REST API available; no auth token supplied","1. Call GET /notifications without an Authorization header | 2. Inspect the response","No token","API returns 401 Unauthorized; no notification data including PHI is returned in the body","Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-020","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0032","Notifications & Alerts","Audit / Compliance","Audit log captures who acknowledged a critical alert and when","Database","System","P1","High","High","Audit logging enabled; a critical alert has been acknowledged by a provider","1. Acknowledge a critical alert as a provider | 2. Query the audit log/table | 3. Verify the recorded fields","Provider=Dr Synthetic; alert=Critical-Troponin","Audit log contains an immutable entry with user id, alert id, action Acknowledge, and UTC timestamp; entries cannot be edited via the UI","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-021","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0033","Notifications & Alerts","PHI / Privacy","SMS reminder content does not expose sensitive clinical details","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patient opted in to SMS reminders; message templates configured","1. Queue an SMS appointment reminder | 2. Inspect the rendered SMS body","Template=appt reminder; Patient=Synthetic D","SMS body contains only minimum-necessary info (e.g., generic appointment time/location) and does not disclose diagnosis, test names, or other PHI beyond what is necessary","Manual-Only","REQ-NOTIF-022","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0034","Notifications & Alerts","Accessibility","Critical alert dialog is keyboard accessible and screen-reader announced","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Critical alert UI available; keyboard-only and screen reader (e.g., NVDA) configured","1. Trigger a critical alert dialog | 2. Navigate the dialog using only the keyboard | 3. Confirm focus is trapped within the dialog | 4. Verify the screen reader announces the alert role and content","CDS critical alert modal","Dialog is fully operable by keyboard, focus is trapped and returned on close, and the alert is announced with an appropriate ARIA alert/role per WCAG 2.1 AA","Manual-Only","REQ-NOTIF-023","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0035","Notifications & Alerts","Accessibility","Alert severity is not conveyed by color alone","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Notification list UI showing alerts of varying severity","1. Open the notification list with critical, high, and low alerts | 2. Inspect how severity is indicated","Alerts of mixed severity","Severity is conveyed via text/label or icon in addition to color, satisfying WCAG use-of-color requirements for color-blind users","Manual-Only","REQ-NOTIF-023","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0036","Notifications & Alerts","Delivery Channels","Pairwise coverage of channel x opt-in x patient-contact validity","Pairwise","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Patients configured with combinations of channel, opt-in status, and contact-info validity","1. For each pairwise combination, queue a reminder | 2. Trigger delivery | 3. Record delivery outcome | 4. Compare against expected","Channels={SMS,Email,In-App}; OptIn={Yes,No}; Contact={Valid,Invalid}","Each pairwise combination yields the expected outcome: delivered only when opted-in and contact valid; suppressed when opted-out; failed/handled when contact invalid","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-024","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0037","Notifications & Alerts","Alert Fatigue / Dedup","Decision table for alert routing by severity and acknowledgement SLA","Decision Table","System","P2","High","Medium","Alert engine configured with severity-based routing and SLA rules","1. Generate alerts across severities | 2. Vary acknowledgement within/after SLA | 3. Observe routing, escalation, and dedup per rule | 4. Compare to the decision table","Severity={Critical,High,Low}; Ack={Within SLA,After SLA}","Each rule combination produces the documented outcome: critical+after-SLA escalates, low+acknowledged closes, duplicates dedup; no rule yields an undefined result","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-005","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0038","Notifications & Alerts","Reminders","Boundary on max notification message length for SMS segment","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","SMS template configurable; gateway enforces segment limits","1. Render an SMS reminder at exactly 160 characters | 2. Render one at 161 characters | 3. Inspect segmentation and delivery","Body lengths: 160 and 161 chars","160-char message sends as a single segment; 161 chars either splits into multi-part per gateway rules or is rejected per configured policy without truncating critical info","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-012","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0039","Notifications & Alerts","Reminders","Time zone correctness of reminder send time across DST boundary","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Patient and facility in a time zone observing DST; appointment scheduled near a DST change","1. Schedule an appointment local time near the DST transition | 2. Queue the reminder | 3. Compute the scheduled send time | 4. Verify against expected local time","TZ=America/New_York; Appt near DST change; Lead=24h","Reminder is scheduled and displayed in the correct local time accounting for the DST shift; no off-by-one-hour error in send or displayed appointment time","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-002","Data Integrity; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0040","Notifications & Alerts","Exploratory","Exploratory session on high-volume critical alerts and inbox behavior","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Test environment seeded with a large volume of alerts for one provider","1. Generate a burst of 200+ alerts for a single provider | 2. Explore inbox loading, sorting, filtering, and acknowledgement | 3. Probe for performance lag, ordering errors, lost acknowledgements | 4. Note any defects","200+ mixed-severity alerts; single provider inbox","Inbox remains responsive; critical alerts are prioritized/visible; acknowledgements are not lost under load; any anomalies are documented with reproduction steps","Manual-Only","REQ-NOTIF-025","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0041","Notifications & Alerts","Critical Result Alerts","Acknowledgement requires authenticated active session (no auto-ack)","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A critical alert is in New state; session may be expired","1. Let the provider session expire | 2. Attempt to acknowledge the alert | 3. Inspect behavior","Expired session token","Acknowledgement is rejected and the user is prompted to re-authenticate; the alert remains New so it is not silently lost","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-006","Security; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0042","Notifications & Alerts","Delivery Failure Handling","Dead-letter notification is visible for manual review and resend","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","A notification has reached terminal Failed/Dead-letter state; logged in as Notification Admin","1. Open the dead-letter/failed notifications view | 2. Locate the failed notification | 3. Inspect failure reason | 4. Trigger a manual resend","Failed reminder id; reason=gateway error","Failed notification is listed with its failure reason; admin can manually resend, and a successful resend updates the status with an audit trail","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-014","Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0043","Notifications & Alerts","Opt-In / Opt-Out","Double opt-in confirmation required before activating SMS reminders","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Patient requests SMS reminders; double opt-in policy enabled","1. Patient requests SMS reminders | 2. System sends a confirmation request | 3a. Patient confirms -> verify activation | 3b. Patient does not confirm -> verify not activated","Confirm=Yes/No; Channel=SMS","SMS reminders are activated only after explicit confirmation; without confirmation the channel stays inactive and no marketing reminders are sent","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-015","Regulatory/Compliance; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF-0044","Notifications & Alerts","In-App Alerts","Concurrent acknowledgement of the same shared alert by two users","State Transition","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","An alert is addressed to a role/queue shared by two users; both logged in","1. User A opens the shared alert | 2. User B opens the same alert | 3. Both attempt to acknowledge near-simultaneously | 4. Inspect final state and audit","Shared alert; Users A and B","The alert is acknowledged exactly once with a consistent final state; the audit log records the actual acknowledging user without duplicate or conflicting entries","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF-006","Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0001","Billing & Insurance","Charge Capture","Capture a billable service charge from a completed encounter","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Billing Clerk; a completed clinical encounter exists for patient with at least one billable service order","1. Open the patient billing dashboard | 2. Select the completed encounter | 3. Click Capture Charges | 4. Confirm the service line item appears | 5. Click Save","Patient=Jane Synthetic; Encounter=ENC-1001; Service=Office Visit Level 3","The service is added as a billable line item with status Captured and is linked to the source encounter","Automatable","REQ-BILL-001","Billing; Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0002","Billing & Insurance","Charge Capture","Reject charge capture when encounter is not finalized","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Billing Clerk; an encounter exists in Draft/In-Progress state","1. Open the patient billing dashboard | 2. Select the in-progress encounter | 3. Click Capture Charges","Patient=Jane Synthetic; Encounter=ENC-1002 status=In-Progress","System blocks charge capture and displays a validation message that only finalized encounters can be charged; no line item is created","Automatable","REQ-BILL-001","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0003","Billing & Insurance","Charge Capture","Prevent duplicate charge capture for the same encounter service","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in as Billing Clerk; charges already captured for encounter ENC-1001","1. Open encounter ENC-1001 | 2. Click Capture Charges again | 3. Attempt to re-save the same service line","Patient=Jane Synthetic; Encounter=ENC-1001; Service=Office Visit Level 3","System detects duplicate and prevents a second identical billable line, displaying a duplicate-charge warning","Automatable","REQ-BILL-002","Billing; Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0004","Billing & Insurance","Charge Capture","Capture multiple distinct services on one encounter","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Billing Clerk; encounter has 3 distinct billable services","1. Open the encounter | 2. Click Capture Charges | 3. Verify all 3 services listed | 4. Save","Encounter=ENC-1003; Services=Consult, ECG, Venipuncture","All three services are captured as separate line items each with its own price and code","Automatable","REQ-BILL-002","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0005","Billing & Insurance","Charge Capture","Charge capture writes an audit log entry with user and timestamp","Database","Regression","P2","High","High","DB access available; Billing Clerk session active","1. Capture a charge for encounter ENC-1004 | 2. Query the billing audit table | 3. Inspect the latest row","Encounter=ENC-1004; User=clerk01","An audit record exists capturing user id, action=CHARGE_CAPTURE, entity id, and UTC timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-BILL-018","Audit; Billing; Security","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0006","Billing & Insurance","Service Pricing","Apply current active price from the chargemaster to a captured service","Functional","Sanity","P1","Critical","High","Chargemaster has an active price for service code 99213; Billing Clerk logged in","1. Capture service 99213 | 2. Observe the unit price | 3. Compare to chargemaster active price","Service=99213; ChargemasterPrice=120.00 USD","The line item unit price equals the active chargemaster price of 120.00 and currency USD","Automatable","REQ-BILL-003","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0007","Billing & Insurance","Service Pricing","Use effective-dated price matching the date of service","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","High","Chargemaster has two price rows for 99213: effective until 31-Dec-2025=100.00 and from 01-Jan-2026=120.00","1. Capture 99213 on a service date of 15-Dec-2025 | 2. Capture 99213 on a service date of 15-Jan-2026 | 3. Compare applied prices","DOS1=15-Dec-2025; DOS2=15-Jan-2026","First charge uses 100.00 and second uses 120.00 based on the effective-dated price selection","Automatable","REQ-BILL-003","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0008","Billing & Insurance","Service Pricing","Reject charge when no active price exists for the service code","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Service code 88888 has no chargemaster entry; Billing Clerk logged in","1. Attempt to capture service 88888 | 2. Save","Service=88888 (no price)","System blocks save and reports that no active price is configured for the service code","Automatable","REQ-BILL-003","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0009","Billing & Insurance","Service Pricing","Boundary: price of exactly 0.00 for a no-charge service","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Service code Z0000 configured with price 0.00 (no-charge); Billing Clerk logged in","1. Capture service Z0000 | 2. Verify line total","Service=Z0000; Price=0.00","Service is captured with a 0.00 line total and does not error; line is flagged as no-charge","Automatable","REQ-BILL-003","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0010","Billing & Insurance","Service Pricing","Boundary: maximum allowed price value precision and rounding","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Chargemaster supports 2-decimal currency; Billing Clerk logged in","1. Configure price 99999999.999 | 2. Save chargemaster entry | 3. Capture and view line total","Price=99999999.999","Price is rounded/validated to 2 decimals (99999999.99 or rejection per config) with no silent truncation error","Partially-Automatable","REQ-BILL-003","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0011","Billing & Insurance","Invoice Generation","Generate an invoice from captured charges","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Patient has 3 captured charges not yet invoiced; Billing Clerk logged in","1. Open patient billing dashboard | 2. Select the 3 captured charges | 3. Click Generate Invoice | 4. Confirm","Patient=Jane Synthetic; Charges=3","An invoice is created with a unique invoice number, all 3 line items, computed subtotal, and status Open","Automatable","REQ-BILL-004","Billing; Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0012","Billing & Insurance","Invoice Generation","Invoice subtotal equals sum of line items","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Invoice INV-2001 generated with lines 120.00, 45.00, 30.00","1. Open invoice INV-2001 | 2. Read the subtotal field | 3. Sum line items manually","Lines=120.00+45.00+30.00","Subtotal shown is exactly 195.00 matching the arithmetic sum of line items","Automatable","REQ-BILL-004","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-BILL-0013","Billing & Insurance","Invoice Generation","Prevent generating an invoice with zero line items","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","No charges selected; Billing Clerk logged in","1. Open billing dashboard | 2. Click Generate Invoice without selecting charges","Selected charges=0","System blocks invoice creation and prompts to select at least one charge","Automatable","REQ-BILL-004","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
