"TC-ENC-0046","Encounters & Clinical Forms","API","Void an encounter via REST DELETE with a reason and verify state","API","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Valid REST credentials with void privilege; existing encounter uuid","1. DELETE /ws/rest/v1/encounter/{uuid}?reason=test | 2. GET the encounter with voided included","API=REST void; reason=test","The encounter is marked voided with the supplied reason; default GET no longer returns it as active","Automatable","REQ-ENC-062","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ENC-0047","Encounters & Clinical Forms","FHIR","Retrieve an encounter as a FHIR Encounter resource and validate required elements","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; an existing encounter mapped to FHIR","1. GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Encounter/{id} | 2. Validate resourceType, status, class, subject and period","FHIR=Encounter read","A valid FHIR R4 Encounter is returned with status, class, subject reference and period populated","Automatable","REQ-ENC-070","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ENC-0048","Encounters & Clinical Forms","FHIR","FHIR Encounter status maps correctly across the encounter lifecycle","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; encounters in in-progress and finished states","1. GET a FHIR Encounter for an open visit encounter | 2. GET a FHIR Encounter after the visit is closed | 3. Compare status codes","FHIR status=in-progress->finished","Status reflects the lifecycle (e.g., in-progress for active, finished for closed) per the mapping","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ENC-071","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ENC-0049","Encounters & Clinical Forms","FHIR","Form observations are retrievable as FHIR Observation resources linked to the Encounter","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint; encounter with obs created via a form","1. GET /Observation?encounter={encounterId} | 2. Validate each Observation has code, value and encounter reference","FHIR=Observation search by encounter","Observations are returned with LOINC/SNOMED-style coding where mapped, values, and a reference back to the Encounter","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ENC-072","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ENC-0050","Encounters & Clinical Forms","FHIR","Obs group maps to a FHIR Observation with hasMember components","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint; encounter containing a nested obs group","1. GET the grouping Observation | 2. Inspect hasMember/component references to member observations","FHIR=Observation hasMember","The grouping Observation references its member Observations, preserving the obs group hierarchy","Manual-Only","REQ-ENC-072","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ENC-0051","Encounters & Clinical Forms","HL7","Inbound HL7 ORU/observation message creates an encounter with observations","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 inbound channel configured; valid patient identifier mapping","1. Submit an HL7 message with PV1 (visit), OBR and OBX segments | 2. Process the message | 3. Verify the resulting encounter and obs","HL7=ORU with OBX rows","An encounter is created with obs mapped from OBX segments and the provider mapped from the message","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ENC-080","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ENC-0052","Encounters & Clinical Forms","HL7","HL7 message with an unmappable observation code is queued/errored rather than silently dropped","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 inbound channel configured; error queue available","1. Submit an HL7 message containing an OBX code with no concept mapping | 2. Process | 3. Inspect the error queue","HL7 OBX code=UNMAPPED","The message is flagged to the error queue with a clear reason; no partial/silent obs loss occurs","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ENC-081","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ENC-0053","Encounters & Clinical Forms","Database","Saved encounter persists encounter_datetime, type, location and creator correctly","Database","Regression","P2","High","Medium","DB read access; an encounter just saved via the UI","1. Save an encounter | 2. Query the encounter table by uuid | 3. Verify encounter_type, encounter_datetime, location_id, creator and date_created","DB=encounter row","All key columns match the UI inputs; creator and date_created reflect the acting user and save time","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ENC-090","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
