"TC-IDENT-0035","Patient Identifiers & MPI","Duplicate Prevention","Decision table for duplicate scoring by name/DOB/gender/identifier match combinations","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","High","Duplicate detection rules defined for demographic and identifier overlap","1. Create candidate pairs varying name, DOB, gender, and identifier match | 2. Run detection | 3. Record duplicate flag","Rules: id-match=high; name+DOB+gender=high; name only=low","Each combination yields the expected duplicate likelihood; identifier match always flags high","Partially-Automatable","REQ-IDENT-008","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Standards"
