"TC-SCHED2-0011","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Slot Generation","Slot generation honors a configurable buffer/gap between appointments","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Service type with 30 min duration and 10 min buffer configured","1. Configure 10 min buffer | 2. Generate slots for a 09:00-11:00 window | 3. Inspect slot start times","Duration=30; Buffer=10; Window=09:00-11:00","Slots start at 09:00, 09:40, 10:20 reflecting duration+buffer; partial trailing slot is not offered","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-021","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0012","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Slot Generation","Boundary: availability window shorter than one slot duration yields zero slots","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Service type 30 min; availability window 09:00-09:20","1. Generate slots for the 20-minute window | 2. Inspect offered slots","Duration=30; Window=09:00-09:20","No bookable slots are offered because the window cannot fit a full appointment","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-020","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0013","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Slot Generation","Slot generation excludes already-booked and held slots","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Provider has a booked appointment 09:30-10:00 and a held slot 10:30-11:00","1. Open booking for that provider/day | 2. Inspect available slots","Booked=09:30-10:00; Held=10:30-11:00","Booked and held slots are not offered as available; remaining free slots are shown","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-022","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0014","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Slot Generation","Concurrent slot hold race: two users holding the same slot","Negative","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Two scheduler sessions open the same provider/day; one free slot at 10:00","1. User A selects 10:00 and begins booking | 2. User B selects 10:00 simultaneously | 3. Both submit","Slot=10:00; Users=A,B","Only one booking succeeds; the second user receives a slot-taken/conflict error and the slot is not double-booked","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-022","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0015","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Overbooking Rules","Decision table: overbooking allowed by role, slot capacity, and appointment priority","Decision Table","Regression","P1","High","High","Overbooking policy configured with capacity per slot and role permissions","1. For each rule row apply role, current slot count vs capacity, and priority | 2. Attempt booking | 3. Record outcome","Role={Scheduler,Admin}; SlotFull={yes,no}; Priority={routine,urgent}","Outcomes match the decision table: Admin+full+urgent=allow with override note; Scheduler+full+routine=block; not-full=allow for all; each override is audit-logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-030","Patient Safety; Audit; Security","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0016","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Overbooking Rules","Overbook beyond max capacity is hard-blocked even for admin","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Slot capacity max 2; slot already has 2 booked; admin user","1. Open the full slot | 2. Attempt to book a third appointment as admin | 3. Submit","Capacity=2; Existing=2; Role=Admin","Booking is blocked at the absolute max capacity with a clear message; no third appointment is created","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-030","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0017","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Overbooking Rules","Overbooking override requires reason and is audit-logged","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Admin with override privilege; slot at soft capacity","1. Attempt overbook | 2. Leave override reason blank and submit | 3. Provide reason and submit | 4. Check audit log","Reason1=blank; Reason2=""Urgent referral""","Blank reason is rejected; with reason the overbook succeeds and an audit entry records user, timestamp, reason, and slot","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-031","Audit; Security; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0018","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Waitlist","Add patient to waitlist when no slots available and verify ordering","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Service fully booked for the requested day; patient registered","1. Attempt to book a full day | 2. Choose Add to Waitlist | 3. Add a second patient to the same waitlist | 4. View waitlist order","Patient1=WL-A; Patient2=WL-B","Both patients are added; waitlist preserves FIFO order by request time unless priority changes it","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-040","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0019","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Waitlist","Waitlist auto-offer triggers on cancellation of a booked slot","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","Medium","One waitlisted patient WL-A; a booked appointment exists in the same service/day","1. Cancel the booked appointment | 2. Observe waitlist processing | 3. Check WL-A notification/offer state","Waitlisted=WL-A; Cancelled appt freed","WL-A transitions from Waitlisted to Offered; an offer/notification is generated for the freed slot","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-041","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0020","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Waitlist","Waitlist offer expiry returns slot to pool and advances to next patient","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","WL-A in Offered state with a configured offer expiry; WL-B next in line","1. Let the offer to WL-A expire without acceptance | 2. Observe state change | 3. Check WL-B","OfferExpiry=15 min; Next=WL-B","WL-A offer transitions to Expired; slot is re-offered to WL-B; slot is not lost","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-041","Data Integrity; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0021","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Waitlist","Remove patient from waitlist and verify they receive no further offers","Negative","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Patient WL-A on waitlist","1. Remove WL-A from waitlist | 2. Free a matching slot via cancellation | 3. Verify offers","Patient=WL-A","WL-A no longer appears on the waitlist and receives no offer when a slot frees; next eligible patient is offered instead","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-040","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0022","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Recurring Series","Create a weekly recurring appointment series and verify all occurrences generated","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Provider availability covers the chosen weekday for the series range","1. Open booking | 2. Choose recurring weekly | 3. Set start date, count 6 | 4. Save | 5. View calendar across 6 weeks","Pattern=Weekly; Count=6; Day=Tuesday","Six occurrences are created on consecutive Tuesdays; all share a series ID and individual appointment IDs","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-050","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0023","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Recurring Series","Recurring series skips occurrences that fall on provider time-off","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Weekly Tuesday series; provider has time-off on one Tuesday in the range","1. Create the 6-occurrence weekly series | 2. Provider has time-off on occurrence 3 | 3. Generate series | 4. Inspect occurrence 3","Series=6 weekly; TimeOff=occurrence 3","Occurrence 3 is flagged as conflicted/skipped or rescheduled per policy; the user is warned rather than silently double-booking","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-051","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0024","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Recurring Series","Edit single occurrence in a series without affecting other occurrences","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","A weekly series of 6 occurrences exists","1. Open occurrence 4 | 2. Choose Edit this occurrence only | 3. Change time to 14:00 | 4. Save | 5. Inspect other occurrences","EditScope=this occurrence; NewTime=14:00","Only occurrence 4 changes to 14:00; occurrences 1-3 and 5-6 retain original time; occurrence 4 marked as an exception in the series","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-052","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0025","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Recurring Series","Edit entire series from a given occurrence forward (this and following)","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","A weekly series of 6 occurrences exists","1. Open occurrence 3 | 2. Choose This and following | 3. Change provider | 4. Save | 5. Inspect occurrences","EditScope=this and following; NewProvider=Dr Lee","Occurrences 3-6 update to Dr Lee; occurrences 1-2 unchanged; series integrity preserved","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-052","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0026","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Recurring Series","Cancel entire recurring series and verify cascade","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A weekly series of 6 occurrences, none yet checked-in","1. Open the series | 2. Choose Cancel series | 3. Provide reason | 4. Confirm | 5. Inspect all occurrences","CancelScope=series; Reason=""Patient request""","All future occurrences move to Cancelled with reason; past/checked-in occurrences are not retroactively altered; cancellation is audit-logged","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-053","Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0027","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Recurring Series","Boundary: recurring series with count exceeding configured max occurrences","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Max occurrences per series configured at 52","1. Create weekly series with count 53 | 2. Save | 3. Create with count 52 | 4. Save","Count1=53; Count2=52; Max=52","Count 53 is rejected with a max-occurrence message; count 52 is accepted","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-051","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0028","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Reschedule Cascade","Reschedule an appointment and verify original slot is freed","State Transition","Regression","P1","High","High","A booked appointment at 10:00 exists; an open slot at 11:00 exists","1. Open the 10:00 appointment | 2. Reschedule to 11:00 | 3. Save | 4. Inspect 10:00 and 11:00 slots","From=10:00; To=11:00","Appointment moves to 11:00; the 10:00 slot becomes available again; appointment retains history of the change","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-060","Data Integrity; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0029","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Reschedule Cascade","Reschedule into a conflicting/occupied slot is blocked","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Two appointments: A at 10:00, B at 11:00; B occupies its slot fully","1. Open appointment A | 2. Attempt to reschedule A into 11:00 where B sits at capacity | 3. Submit","ApptA=10:00; ApptB=11:00 full","Reschedule is blocked due to conflict; A remains at 10:00; conflict reason shown","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-061","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0030","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Reschedule Cascade","Reschedule of a series occurrence updates dependent reminders","Integration","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","An appointment with a scheduled 24h reminder","1. Reschedule the appointment to a new date | 2. Inspect the linked reminder schedule","Reminder=24h before; Reschedule=+2 days","The 24h reminder is recomputed against the new date/time; the stale reminder is cancelled and not sent for the old time","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-062","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0031","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Reschedule Cascade","Reschedule past the appointment start time is rejected","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","An appointment scheduled in the past relative to now","1. Open a past-due appointment | 2. Attempt to reschedule to another past time | 3. Submit","NewTime=yesterday 09:00","Rescheduling to a time in the past is rejected with validation; only future times are allowed","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-061","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0032","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Reminders","Reminder is scheduled at the configured lead time on booking","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Reminder policy 24h before via SMS; patient has a valid phone","1. Book an appointment 3 days out | 2. Inspect scheduled reminders","LeadTime=24h; Channel=SMS","A single SMS reminder is scheduled for 24h before the appointment to the patient phone","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-070","Clinical","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0033","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Reminders","Reminder is not sent for a cancelled appointment","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Appointment with a pending 24h reminder","1. Cancel the appointment before the reminder fires | 2. Wait until reminder time | 3. Inspect outbound messages","Reminder pending; Cancel before fire","No reminder is sent for the cancelled appointment; reminder job is voided","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-071","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0034","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Reminders","Pairwise: reminder channel x patient contact-preference x consent","Pairwise","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patients with varied contact preferences and consent flags","1. For each combination of channel, preference, and consent send/schedule a reminder | 2. Record delivery decision","Channel={SMS,Email,Voice}; Pref={SMS,Email,None}; Consent={yes,no}","Reminders are sent only on consented and preferred channels; consent=no suppresses all channels; mismatches fall back per policy or are suppressed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-072","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0035","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Reminders","Reminder content contains no PHI beyond minimum necessary","Security","Regression","P1","High","High","Reminder template configured; appointment booked","1. Trigger a reminder | 2. Inspect message content for SMS and email","Template=default","Reminder includes appointment date/time and clinic but excludes diagnosis, reason-for-visit, and other sensitive PHI per minimum-necessary","Manual-Only","REQ-SCHED2-073","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Security","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0036","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Check-In / Check-Out","Check in a patient and verify status and arrival timestamp","State Transition","Sanity","P1","High","Medium","A Scheduled appointment for today exists","1. Open today schedule | 2. Select the appointment | 3. Click Check In | 4. Inspect status and timestamp","Appt=today Scheduled","Status transitions Scheduled to CheckedIn; arrival timestamp recorded; appointment appears in the arrived/waiting list","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-080","Clinical; Audit","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0037","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Check-In / Check-Out","Invalid state transition: check out an appointment that was never checked in","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","A Scheduled appointment that has not been checked in","1. Open the Scheduled appointment | 2. Attempt Check Out directly | 3. Observe","Appt status=Scheduled","Check Out is rejected or disabled because the appointment is not in a CheckedIn/InProgress state; status unchanged","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-081","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0038","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Check-In / Check-Out","Full state machine traversal: Scheduled to CheckedIn to InProgress to Completed","State Transition","Regression","P1","High","Medium","A Scheduled appointment for today","1. Check In | 2. Move to InProgress (start encounter) | 3. Complete the visit/check out | 4. Inspect each transition and timestamps","Appt=today","Each transition succeeds in order with timestamps; final status Completed; no skipped or reversed states without explicit allowance","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-080","Clinical; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0039","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Check-In / Check-Out","Check-in links/creates a visit and encounter for the patient","Integration","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Patient has no active visit; appointment scheduled today","1. Check in the appointment | 2. Inspect patient dashboard for a visit | 3. Verify appointment-visit link","Appt=today; ActiveVisit=none","Check-in creates or links an active visit; the appointment references the visit; encounter datetime aligns with check-in","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-082","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-SCHED2-0040","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","No-Show","Mark appointment as no-show after grace period and verify status","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","A Scheduled appointment whose start time has passed by more than the grace period","1. Open the past-start appointment | 2. Mark No-Show | 3. Inspect status and metrics","GracePeriod=15 min; Start passed","Status transitions to Missed/NoShow; the slot is freed per policy; no-show is reflected in patient and provider metrics","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-090","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0041","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","No-Show","Cannot mark no-show before appointment start time","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","A Scheduled appointment with a future start time","1. Open a future appointment | 2. Attempt to mark No-Show | 3. Observe","Start=future","No-Show action is disabled or rejected because the appointment has not started; status unchanged","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-091","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0042","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","No-Show","Repeated no-shows trigger configured flag/alert on patient","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","No-show threshold configured at 3 within 90 days","1. Mark 2 no-shows for a patient | 2. Verify no flag | 3. Mark a 3rd within 90 days | 4. Inspect patient flag","Threshold=3/90d","No flag at 2; at the 3rd no-show within window a high-no-show flag/alert is raised on the patient record","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-092","Clinical","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0043","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Conflict Decision Table","Decision table for booking conflicts across provider, room, patient, and equipment","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Provider, room, and equipment resources configured for a service","1. For each rule apply provider-busy, room-busy, patient-double-booked, equipment-busy as yes/no | 2. Attempt booking | 3. Record allow/block and reason","ProviderBusy/RoomBusy/PatientDouble/EquipBusy={yes,no} combos","Booking is blocked when any required resource is busy with the correct precedence and reason; allowed only when all required resources are free; outcomes match the table exactly","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-100","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0044","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Conflict Decision Table","Patient double-booking across two services at the same time is blocked","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Patient has an appointment 10:00-10:30 in service A","1. Attempt to book the same patient 10:15-10:45 in service B | 2. Submit","Existing=A 10:00-10:30; New=B 10:15-10:45","Overlapping patient booking is blocked with a patient-conflict message; no overlapping appointment is created","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-101","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0045","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Conflict Decision Table","Adjacent non-overlapping bookings for same patient are allowed (boundary)","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Patient has an appointment 10:00-10:30","1. Book the same patient 10:30-11:00 | 2. Submit","Existing=10:00-10:30; New=10:30-11:00","Back-to-back adjacent appointment is allowed because there is no time overlap at the boundary","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-101","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0046","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","FHIR","Create an appointment via FHIR Appointment resource and verify persistence","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; patient and practitioner FHIR resources exist","1. POST a FHIR Appointment with status booked, participants patient and practitioner, start/end | 2. GET the created resource | 3. Cross-check in UI","Resource=Appointment; status=booked","201 Created with a resource id; GET returns the appointment with correct status, participants, and period; visible in the scheduling UI","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-110","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0047","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","FHIR","FHIR Appointment with invalid status value is rejected","Negative","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled","1. POST a FHIR Appointment with status ""confirmedish"" (invalid) | 2. Observe response","status=confirmedish (invalid)","Server returns 4xx with an OperationOutcome indicating an invalid status code; no resource is created","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-111","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0048","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","FHIR","FHIR Appointment $find/slot search returns only free slots","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR Slot and Schedule resources populated for a provider","1. GET /Slot?schedule=X&status=free&start=ge<today> | 2. Inspect returned slots","status=free; schedule=X","Only Slot resources with status free are returned; busy/busy-tentative slots are excluded; period bounds respected","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-112","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0049","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","FHIR","FHIR Appointment cancel via PATCH status transitions consistently with UI","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","An existing FHIR Appointment in booked status","1. PATCH status to cancelled with cancellationReason | 2. GET resource | 3. Verify UI status","PATCH status=cancelled","Resource status becomes cancelled with reason; the scheduling UI reflects the cancellation; freed slot becomes available","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-113","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0050","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","HL7","Inbound HL7 SIU^S12 (new appointment) creates a scheduled appointment","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 v2 interface engine connected; provider and patient mappable","1. Send SIU^S12 with SCH, PID, AIS, AIP segments | 2. ACK received | 3. Verify appointment created","Message=SIU^S12","AA ACK returned; an appointment is created matching SCH start/duration, AIS service, and AIP provider; patient resolved via PID","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-120","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0051","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","HL7","Inbound HL7 SIU^S15 (cancel) cancels the matching appointment","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","An appointment previously created via SIU^S12 with a known placer/filler id","1. Send SIU^S15 referencing the same appointment id | 2. ACK received | 3. Verify status","Message=SIU^S15; AppointmentID match","AA ACK returned; the matching appointment transitions to Cancelled; slot freed; no duplicate created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-121","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0052","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","HL7","HL7 SIU with unknown patient identifier is rejected with AE/AR ACK","Negative","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","HL7 interface connected","1. Send SIU^S12 with a PID identifier not present in the system | 2. Inspect ACK","PID id=UNKNOWN-999","An AE or AR ACK is returned with an error indicating unresolved patient; no appointment is created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-122","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0053","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","HL7","HL7 SIU^S13 (reschedule) updates appointment time idempotently","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","An appointment exists from a prior SIU message","1. Send SIU^S13 with a new start time | 2. Send the identical S13 again | 3. Inspect appointment","Message=SIU^S13; NewStart","First S13 updates the appointment time; the duplicate retransmission does not create a second change or duplicate appointment (idempotent)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-121","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0054","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","API","Booking API enforces optimistic concurrency (version/ETag) on update","API","Integration","P1","High","High","An appointment with a known version/ETag retrieved by two clients","1. Client A and B GET the appointment (same ETag) | 2. A updates (ETag advances) | 3. B updates using stale ETag","ETag stale on B","Client B update is rejected with a 409/precondition-failed; no lost update; B must re-fetch and retry","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-130","Data Integrity; Security","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0055","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","API","Booking API rejects malformed and out-of-range datetime payloads","Negative","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Scheduling API reachable with valid auth","1. POST with start after end | 2. POST with invalid ISO datetime | 3. POST with timezone-less datetime where tz required","start>end; bad ISO; no tz","Each malformed request returns 4xx with a descriptive validation error; no appointment is created","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-131","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0056","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","API","Booking API pagination and filter by date range and provider","API","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Multiple appointments exist across providers and dates","1. GET appointments?provider=X&date=ge..&date=le..&_count=20 | 2. Follow next page link","Filter=provider X, date range","Only matching appointments returned, correctly paginated with stable ordering; no duplicates or omissions across pages","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-132","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0057","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Security","Authorization: scheduler from clinic A cannot book/view appointments of clinic B","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Multi-location setup; scheduler scoped to clinic A","1. Log in as clinic A scheduler | 2. Attempt to view clinic B schedule via UI and API | 3. Attempt to book in clinic B","User scope=Clinic A","Access to clinic B schedule and booking is denied (403) in both UI and API; attempt is audit-logged","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-140","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0058","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Security","IDOR: directly accessing another patient appointment id is blocked","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Two patients with appointments; low-privilege user","1. As a user without rights, GET /appointment/{otherPatientApptId} directly | 2. Observe","ApptID=other patient","Server returns 403/404 without leaking appointment details; no PHI disclosed; attempt audit-logged","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-141","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0059","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Security","Audit log captures every booking, reschedule, cancel, and override with actor and timestamp","Security","Regression","P1","High","High","Audit logging enabled","1. Perform book, reschedule, cancel, and overbook-override actions | 2. Inspect audit log","Actions=book,reschedule,cancel,override","Each action produces an immutable audit entry with actor, action, target appointment, before/after, reason where applicable, and timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-142","Audit; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0060","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Database","Unique constraint prevents two confirmed appointments in the same exclusive slot at DB level","Database","Integration","P1","Critical","High","DB access to appointment tables; an exclusive (capacity 1) slot","1. Insert appointment A into the slot | 2. Concurrently/directly insert appointment B into the same exclusive slot | 3. Inspect constraint behavior","Slot capacity=1","DB unique/exclusion constraint rejects the second insert; only one confirmed appointment persists for the exclusive slot","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-150","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0061","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Database","Cancelling an appointment soft-deletes (voids) rather than hard-deletes the row","Database","Regression","P2","High","Medium","DB access; a booked appointment","1. Cancel the appointment via UI | 2. Query the appointment row | 3. Inspect void/cancel flags","Action=cancel","Row is retained with cancelled/voided status, reason, and timestamp; it is not physically removed, preserving auditability","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-151","Data Integrity; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SCHED2-0062","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Database","Reschedule preserves referential integrity to encounter/visit links","Database","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","An appointment linked to a visit is rescheduled","1. Reschedule the linked appointment | 2. Query foreign keys to visit/encounter | 3. Verify integrity","Appt linked to visit","Foreign-key references remain valid after reschedule; no orphaned or dangling links; history of change is queryable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-152","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-SCHED2-0063","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Accessibility","Scheduling calendar grid is fully keyboard navigable","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Scheduling calendar open; keyboard only","1. Tab into the calendar | 2. Navigate days/slots with arrow keys | 3. Activate a slot with Enter | 4. Open and dismiss booking dialog with keyboard","Keyboard only","All slots and controls are reachable and operable by keyboard; focus order is logical; dialog traps and restores focus; no keyboard trap","Manual-Only","REQ-SCHED2-160","Accessibility; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0064","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Accessibility","Screen reader announces slot availability, status, and conflict errors","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Screen reader enabled (e.g., NVDA/VoiceOver); booking flow open","1. Navigate slots with a screen reader | 2. Select a slot | 3. Trigger a conflict | 4. Listen to announcements","Screen reader on","Slot availability and status are announced; conflict/validation errors are announced via live region with actionable text","Manual-Only","REQ-SCHED2-161","Accessibility; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0065","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Time Zone & DST","Booking displays consistent local clinic time across user timezones","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Clinic timezone fixed; two users in different browser timezones","1. User in tz+0 books 14:00 clinic-local slot | 2. User in tz+5 views the same appointment | 3. Compare displayed times","ClinicTZ fixed; Users tz+0, tz+5","Both users see the appointment at the correct clinic-local time (with optional tz indicator); the underlying instant is consistent; no off-by-tz errors","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-012","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0066","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Time Zone & DST","DST fall-back duplicated hour does not create overlapping bookable slots","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Clinic observes DST; date is a fall-back day with a repeated 01:00-02:00 hour","1. Generate slots across the repeated hour | 2. Attempt to book in the duplicated hour | 3. Inspect for duplicates","Date=DST fall-back","The repeated hour is handled deterministically; no two distinct bookable slots collide on the same wall-clock label without disambiguation","Manual-Only","REQ-SCHED2-012","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0067","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Exploratory","Exploratory: rapid create/cancel/reschedule churn for slot-state consistency","Exploratory","System","P2","High","Medium","A provider day with several open slots; tester with booking rights","1. Rapidly book, cancel, and reschedule across slots in varied order | 2. Refresh the calendar | 3. Reconcile slot states against expected","Ad-hoc churn sequence","Slot availability remains consistent with the net of actions; no phantom-held, double-counted, or stuck slots; UI matches backend on refresh","Manual-Only","REQ-SCHED2-170","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0068","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Exploratory","Exploratory: booking near provider availability edges and lunch breaks","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Provider with a lunch break block 12:00-13:00 inside availability","1. Probe booking at 11:45, 12:00, 12:30, 12:55, 13:00 | 2. Observe which are allowed","Lunch=12:00-13:00; Duration=30","Slots straddling or inside the lunch break are not offered; edges (e.g., 11:30 ending at 12:00 and 13:00 start) behave per duration; no slot bleeds into the break","Manual-Only","REQ-SCHED2-170","Data Integrity; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0069","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Cancellation Policy","Late cancellation within policy window flags fee/penalty per decision table","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Cancellation policy: free if >24h, fee if <24h, no fee for clinic-initiated","1. Cancel >24h before as patient | 2. Cancel <24h before as patient | 3. Cancel <24h as clinic-initiated | 4. Inspect fee flag","Window=24h; Initiator={patient,clinic}","No fee when >24h or clinic-initiated; a late-cancellation fee/penalty flag is set only for patient-initiated cancel <24h, matching the table","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-180","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0070","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Reschedule Cascade","Reschedule cascade for a group/block appointment updates all linked participants","Integration","System","P2","High","Medium","A group appointment with 3 patients linked to one slot/provider","1. Reschedule the group appointment to a new time | 2. Inspect each linked participant appointment | 3. Verify reminders","Group size=3; Reschedule=+1 day","All 3 participant appointments move together to the new time; original slot freed; reminders recomputed for each participant; no participant left behind","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-062","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0071","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Slot Generation","Pairwise: slot generation across duration x buffer x window-length x capacity","Pairwise","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Configurable slot parameters available","1. Apply pairwise combinations of duration, buffer, window length, and per-slot capacity | 2. Generate slots | 3. Verify counts and start times","Dur={15,30}; Buffer={0,10}; Window={60,120}; Cap={1,2}","For each combination the generated slot count, start times, and capacity match the expected formula; no partial or overlapping slots produced","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-021","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0072","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Check-In / Check-Out","Patient self check-in via kiosk verifies identity before status change","Functional","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Self check-in kiosk enabled; patient has appointment today","1. Patient enters identifiers at kiosk | 2. System verifies DOB + last name | 3. On match, check in | 4. On mismatch, deny","Verify=DOB+LastName","Correct identity match transitions to CheckedIn; mismatched identifiers are denied without revealing appointment details; failed attempts are limited and logged","Manual-Only","REQ-SCHED2-082","PHI/Privacy; Security; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0073","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","No-Show","No-show on one occurrence of a recurring series does not affect future occurrences","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","A weekly series; occurrence 2 start time has passed","1. Mark occurrence 2 as No-Show | 2. Inspect occurrences 3-6","Series=6 weekly; NoShow=occ 2","Only occurrence 2 is Missed/NoShow; future occurrences remain Scheduled and are unaffected","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-090","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0074","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Waitlist","Pairwise: waitlist matching across service-type x provider-preference x time-window","Pairwise","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Waitlist entries with varied preferences","1. For each combination of service-type, provider preference (any/specific), and acceptable time window, free a matching/non-matching slot | 2. Observe offers","ServiceType varied; ProviderPref={any,specific}; Window varied","Offers go only to waitlist entries whose preferences match the freed slot; non-matching entries are skipped; matching precedence respected","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-041","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0075","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","FHIR","FHIR Appointment participant required/optional status enforced","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","FHIR endpoint enabled","1. POST Appointment with a required participant whose status is needs-action | 2. Attempt to set overall status booked | 3. Observe","participant.required=required; status=needs-action","Overall booked status is consistent with participant statuses per FHIR rules; conflicting combinations are rejected with OperationOutcome","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-111","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SCHED2-0076","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Security","Reminder/notification webhook endpoint validates signature and rejects spoofed callbacks","Security","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Outbound reminder delivery uses a webhook callback for status","1. Send a delivery-status callback with a valid signature | 2. Send one with an invalid/absent signature | 3. Inspect handling","Signature={valid,invalid,absent}","Valid signature updates delivery status; invalid/absent signature is rejected (401) and not applied; rejection is logged","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-143","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-SCHED2-0077","Appointment Scheduling (deep)","Overbooking Rules","Boundary: book exactly at soft capacity threshold without triggering override","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Soft capacity 3, hard capacity 5; slot has 2 booked","1. Book a 3rd appointment (reaches soft capacity) | 2. Verify no override prompt | 3. Book a 4th (exceeds soft) | 4. Observe override prompt","Soft=3; Hard=5; Existing=2","3rd booking succeeds without override; the 4th (beyond soft capacity) requires an override with reason","Automatable","REQ-SCHED2-031","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0001","Consent & Privacy","Consent Capture","Capture a new active treatment consent for a patient","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Privacy officer logged in with consent management privilege; target patient exists","1. Open the patient record | 2. Open the Consent panel | 3. Select scope Treatment | 4. Set status Active | 5. Set effective date to today | 6. Record patient signature method | 7. Save","Patient=Synthea-Test-001; Scope=Treatment; Status=Active; Method=Wet signature","Consent is saved with a unique id, status Active, scope Treatment, recorded actor, and a timestamped creation audit entry","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-001","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0002","Consent & Privacy","Consent Capture","Capture consent with multiple scopes in a single record","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Consent officer logged in; patient exists","1. Open Consent panel | 2. Add scope Treatment | 3. Add scope Research | 4. Add scope Disclosure to family | 5. Save | 6. Reopen record","Scopes=Treatment,Research,DisclosureFamily","All three scopes persist independently and are each individually evaluable for authorization decisions","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-001","PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0003","Consent & Privacy","Consent Capture","Reject consent capture without a required scope","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Consent officer logged in; patient exists","1. Open Consent panel | 2. Leave scope unselected | 3. Set status Active | 4. Save","Scope=(none); Status=Active","Save is blocked with a validation error indicating scope is mandatory; no partial record is persisted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-001","Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0004","Consent & Privacy","Consent Capture","Reject consent with effective date after expiry date","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Consent officer logged in; patient exists","1. Open Consent panel | 2. Set effective date 2026-08-01 | 3. Set expiry date 2026-07-01 | 4. Save","Effective=2026-08-01; Expiry=2026-07-01","Validation error: expiry must be on or after effective date; record not saved","Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-002","Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0005","Consent & Privacy","Consent Capture","Boundary: expiry date equal to effective date","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Consent officer logged in; patient exists","1. Open Consent panel | 2. Set effective date 2026-07-01 | 3. Set expiry date 2026-07-01 | 4. Save | 5. Evaluate authorization at 2026-07-01T12:00","Effective=2026-07-01; Expiry=2026-07-01","Consent is accepted; it is considered active for the single calendar day per inclusive boundary rule","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-002","Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0006","Consent & Privacy","Consent Capture","Boundary: maximum future expiry horizon enforcement","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Consent officer logged in; policy max horizon = 10 years","1. Open Consent panel | 2. Set expiry to today + 10 years | 3. Save | 4. Repeat with today + 10 years + 1 day","MaxHorizon=10y","Expiry at exactly the max horizon saves; expiry beyond the max horizon is rejected with a policy validation error","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-002","Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0007","Consent & Privacy","Consent Capture","Capture consent on behalf of a minor by a verified guardian","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Consent officer logged in; minor patient with linked guardian relationship exists","1. Open minor patient record | 2. Open Consent panel | 3. Select grantor = guardian relationship | 4. Verify guardian identity attestation | 5. Save","Patient=Minor-007; Grantor=Guardian-Mother","Consent records the guardian as the consenting actor with relationship captured; patient is referenced as the subject","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-003","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0008","Consent & Privacy","Consent Capture","Block self-consent capture for a minor below age of capacity","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Consent officer logged in; minor patient (age 9) exists","1. Open minor record | 2. Attempt consent with grantor = patient self | 3. Save","Patient=Minor-009; Age=9; Grantor=Self","System blocks self-consent for a patient under the configured age of capacity and requires a guardian grantor","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-003","Patient Safety; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0009","Consent & Privacy","Consent Scope","Decision table: authorization by scope and requesting purpose","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Patient has consent scoped to Treatment only (active); requester role and purpose vary","1. Request access purpose=Treatment | 2. Request purpose=Research | 3. Request purpose=Marketing | 4. Record each decision","Scope=Treatment; Purposes=Treatment,Research,Marketing","Treatment purpose is permitted; Research and Marketing are denied because they fall outside the granted scope","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-004","PHI/Privacy; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0010","Consent & Privacy","Consent Scope","Pairwise: scope x actor-role x data-category access matrix","Pairwise","System","P1","High","High","Multiple consent scopes configured; varying actor roles and data categories","1. Iterate combinations of scope {Treatment,Research}, role {Clinician,Researcher,Billing} and category {Clinical,Demographics,Financial} | 2. Evaluate each | 3. Log outcome","Pairwise set across scope/role/category","Each combination yields the policy-correct permit or deny with no combination producing an undefined or default-allow result","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-004","Security; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0011","Consent & Privacy","Consent Scope","Deny access to a category explicitly excluded by consent provision","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Patient consent permits Clinical but explicitly excludes Mental Health notes","1. Authenticate as treating clinician | 2. Request mental health note | 3. Observe decision and audit","Permit=Clinical; Except=MentalHealth","Mental health note access is denied by the except provision while general clinical access is allowed; denial is audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-005","PHI/Privacy; Security; Audit","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0012","Consent & Privacy","Consent Expiry","State transition: Active consent transitions to Expired at expiry","State Transition","System","P1","High","High","Consent active with expiry = today at 23:59","1. Verify access permitted before expiry | 2. Advance system clock past expiry | 3. Re-evaluate access | 4. Inspect consent status","Expiry=today 23:59","Status auto-transitions to Expired; subsequent access requiring that consent is denied; the transition is audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-006","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0013","Consent & Privacy","Consent Expiry","Boundary: access exactly at the expiry instant","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Consent active with precise expiry datetime","1. Request access one second before expiry | 2. Request at the exact expiry second | 3. Request one second after","Expiry=2026-07-01T17:00:00","Pre-expiry permitted; at-instant follows the documented inclusive/exclusive rule consistently; post-expiry denied","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-006","PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0014","Consent & Privacy","Consent Expiry","Expired consent cannot be silently used after renewal lapse","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A previously active consent has expired; no renewal recorded","1. Attempt treatment data access relying on the expired consent | 2. Observe result","Consent=Expired","Access is denied and the requester is informed consent has lapsed; no fallback to the expired grant occurs","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-006","PHI/Privacy; Security","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0015","Consent & Privacy","Consent Revoke","Revoke an active consent and confirm immediate effect","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Patient has an active treatment consent; officer logged in","1. Open the active consent | 2. Select Revoke | 3. Enter revocation reason | 4. Confirm | 5. Immediately re-evaluate access","Reason=PatientRequest","Status becomes Revoked with reason and timestamp; access depending on it is denied on the very next request","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-007","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0016","Consent & Privacy","Consent Revoke","State transition: Active to Revoked to no reactivation","State Transition","System","P2","High","Medium","An active consent exists","1. Revoke the consent | 2. Attempt to set status back to Active | 3. Observe","Status path=Active->Revoked->Active?","Reactivation of a revoked consent is blocked; a new consent record must be created instead, preserving the revoked record immutably","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-007","Data Integrity; Audit","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0017","Consent & Privacy","Consent Revoke","Reject revocation without a recorded reason","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Active consent exists; officer logged in","1. Open consent | 2. Select Revoke | 3. Leave reason blank | 4. Confirm","Reason=(empty)","Revocation is blocked with a validation message requiring a reason for the audit trail","Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-007","Audit; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0018","Consent & Privacy","Consent Revoke","Partial revocation removes one scope while retaining others","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Consent with scopes Treatment and Research is active","1. Open consent | 2. Revoke only the Research scope | 3. Save | 4. Re-evaluate both scopes","Revoke=Research; Keep=Treatment","Research access is denied while Treatment access continues; the scope-level revocation is individually audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-007","PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity; Audit","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0019","Consent & Privacy","Break-Glass","Break-glass emergency access grants temporary override with reason","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Clinician without standing access; patient under emergency; break-glass enabled","1. Attempt access and be denied | 2. Invoke Break-Glass | 3. Enter clinical justification | 4. Acknowledge override warning | 5. Access record","Reason=EmergencyCardiacArrest","Temporary access is granted, a high-visibility override banner is shown, and a break-glass audit event is written with actor, patient, reason and time","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-008","Patient Safety; PHI/Privacy; Audit; Security","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0020","Consent & Privacy","Break-Glass","Break-glass without justification is rejected","Negative","System","P1","High","High","Break-glass enabled; clinician denied normal access","1. Invoke Break-Glass | 2. Leave justification blank | 3. Confirm","Reason=(empty)","Override is refused; justification is mandatory and no access is granted until provided","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-008","Security; Audit; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0021","Consent & Privacy","Break-Glass","State transition: break-glass session expires and access reverts","State Transition","System","P2","High","High","Active break-glass session with a fixed TTL","1. Establish break-glass access | 2. Wait until TTL elapses | 3. Attempt continued access | 4. Inspect status","TTL=60 minutes","After TTL the elevated access ends and the clinician is denied again unless re-invoked; expiry is audited","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-008","Security; Audit; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0022","Consent & Privacy","Break-Glass","Break-glass event triggers mandatory post-hoc review flag","Functional","Integration","P2","High","High","A break-glass access occurred","1. Complete a break-glass access | 2. Open the privacy review queue | 3. Locate the event","Event=break-glass","The access appears in the privacy officer review queue flagged for mandatory post-hoc justification review","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-009","Regulatory/Compliance; Audit; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0023","Consent & Privacy","Break-Glass","Decision table: break-glass eligibility by role and patient state","Decision Table","System","P2","High","High","Break-glass policy configured by role and emergency flag","1. Evaluate role {Physician,Nurse,Clerk} x patientEmergency {true,false} | 2. Attempt override per cell | 3. Record","Roles x EmergencyFlag matrix","Clinical roles may break-glass; non-clinical roles such as Clerk are never eligible regardless of emergency flag","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-008","Security; Patient Safety; Audit","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0024","Consent & Privacy","Minimum Necessary","Minimum-necessary returns only fields required for the stated purpose","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Billing clerk requesting data for claims purpose","1. Authenticate as billing clerk | 2. Request patient record for purpose=Billing | 3. Inspect returned fields","Purpose=Billing","Only billing-relevant fields (demographics, coverage, charges) are returned; clinical notes and sensitive observations are withheld","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-010","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Security","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0025","Consent & Privacy","Minimum Necessary","Negative: clinician cannot over-fetch beyond purpose scope","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","Clinician requests data citing a narrow purpose","1. Request with purpose=Referral | 2. Attempt to expand response to full chart | 3. Observe","Purpose=Referral","Response is constrained to referral-relevant elements; attempts to widen the dataset beyond purpose are rejected and logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-010","PHI/Privacy; Security","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0026","Consent & Privacy","Minimum Necessary","Pairwise: purpose x dataset-projection coverage","Pairwise","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Multiple purposes and dataset projections configured","1. Iterate purpose {Treatment,Billing,Research,Audit} x projection {Full,Demographics,DeIdentified} | 2. Evaluate returned projection","Pairwise purpose/projection","Each purpose maps to its least-privilege projection; Research receives DeIdentified by default unless explicit consent broadens it","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-010","PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0027","Consent & Privacy","Disclosure Log","Every PHI disclosure writes an accounting-of-disclosures entry","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Patient with consented disclosure to an external provider","1. Perform an authorized disclosure to an external provider | 2. Open accounting of disclosures | 3. Inspect the entry","Recipient=ExternalClinicA","An entry records recipient, date, purpose, data categories, and the disclosing actor, satisfying accounting-of-disclosures requirements","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-011","Regulatory/Compliance; Audit; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0028","Consent & Privacy","Disclosure Log","Disclosure log entries are immutable and tamper-evident","Security","System","P1","High","High","At least one disclosure entry exists; admin access available","1. Attempt to edit a disclosure entry via UI | 2. Attempt direct datastore update | 3. Verify integrity hash/chain","Entry=DISC-001","Edits are blocked; any out-of-band tampering is detected via integrity controls and surfaced as an alert","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-011","Audit; Security; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0029","Consent & Privacy","Disclosure Log","Patient-facing accounting of disclosures excludes treatment-internal access","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Patient requests an accounting of disclosures report","1. Generate the patient accounting report | 2. Inspect included and excluded events","ReportType=AccountingOfDisclosures","Report includes external and non-TPO disclosures and correctly excludes routine internal treatment access per regulation","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-011","Regulatory/Compliance; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0030","Consent & Privacy","Disclosure Log","Database: disclosure record retention meets minimum period","Database","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Disclosure records older than the retention floor exist","1. Query disclosure table for oldest entries | 2. Verify retention age | 3. Run purge job | 4. Re-query","RetentionFloor=6 years","Records younger than the retention floor are never purged; the purge job only removes entries beyond the regulatory window","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-012","Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity; Database","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0031","Consent & Privacy","Restricted Records","Restricted patient record is hidden from normal search results","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Patient flagged as restricted/VIP; standard clinician without override logged in","1. Search for the restricted patient by name | 2. Inspect search results","Patient=VIP-Restricted-030","The restricted patient does not appear in normal results, or appears masked without record access, per the restriction policy","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-013","PHI/Privacy; Security","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0032","Consent & Privacy","Restricted Records","Authorized care-team member can access a restricted record","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","Patient flagged restricted; clinician is on the assigned care team","1. Authenticate as assigned care-team clinician | 2. Open the restricted record","Patient=VIP-Restricted-030; Role=CareTeam","Care-team member is granted access, and the access is written to the audit log with the restriction context","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-013","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Security","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0033","Consent & Privacy","Restricted Records","Negative: non-care-team access to restricted record is denied and alerted","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Patient flagged restricted; clinician not on care team","1. Attempt to open the restricted record | 2. Observe denial | 3. Check privacy alerting","Patient=VIP-Restricted-030; Role=Unrelated","Access is denied; a privacy alert is raised to the security/privacy team identifying the attempting actor","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-013","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0034","Consent & Privacy","Restricted Records","State transition: applying and lifting a record restriction","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patient record currently unrestricted; privacy officer logged in","1. Apply restriction flag | 2. Confirm masked behavior | 3. Lift restriction with reason | 4. Confirm normal behavior","Flag=Restricted->Unrestricted","Restriction applies and lifts correctly; both transitions are audited with actor and reason and take effect on next access","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-013","PHI/Privacy; Audit","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0035","Consent & Privacy","FHIR Consent","Create a FHIR Consent resource and validate against profile","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","High","FHIR R4 endpoint reachable; create privilege; patient resource exists","1. POST a Consent resource with status active and category, scope, patient, dateTime | 2. Read it back | 3. Validate against the profile","status=active; scope=patient-privacy","Consent is created with 201, returns a logical id, echoes status active, and validates against the FHIR Consent profile","Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-014","Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0036","Consent & Privacy","FHIR Consent","Reject FHIR Consent missing the mandatory status element","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR endpoint reachable; create privilege","1. POST a Consent resource omitting status | 2. Observe response","status=(missing)","Server returns 400 or 422 with an OperationOutcome indicating the required status element is missing; nothing is persisted","Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-014","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0037","Consent & Privacy","FHIR Consent","FHIR Consent provision deny rule blocks a category read","FHIR","System","P1","High","High","A Consent resource with a deny provision on category=psychotherapy exists","1. Attempt to read a psychotherapy note via FHIR | 2. Observe enforcement","provision.type=deny; category=psychotherapy","The read is denied or the resource is filtered out consistent with the deny provision; a permitted category remains readable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-015","Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy; Security","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0038","Consent & Privacy","FHIR Consent","FHIR Consent provision period boundary controls access window","FHIR","System","P2","High","Medium","Consent with provision.period start and end configured","1. Request access before period.start | 2. Within the period | 3. After period.end","period.start/end set","Access is denied outside the provision period and permitted within it, matching the period boundaries inclusively per spec","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-015","Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0039","Consent & Privacy","FHIR Consent","Search FHIR Consent by patient and status","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Multiple Consent resources exist for several patients","1. GET Consent?patient=Patient/123&status=active | 2. Inspect the bundle","patient=123; status=active","Only active consents for the specified patient are returned in a searchset bundle with correct total and self link","Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-014","Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0040","Consent & Privacy","FHIR Consent","Update FHIR Consent status to inactive reflects revocation","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","An active FHIR Consent resource exists","1. PUT the Consent with status=inactive | 2. Read it back | 3. Re-evaluate enforcement","status active->inactive","Resource version increments, status is inactive, and enforcement now denies access previously granted by that consent","Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-007","Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0041","Consent & Privacy","Authorization Checks","Authorization denies access when no consent exists for required scope","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Patient has no consent for the Research scope; researcher logged in","1. Authenticate as researcher | 2. Request research data | 3. Observe decision","Scope=Research; Consent=none","Access is denied because absence of consent defaults to deny (opt-in), and the denial is audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-016","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0042","Consent & Privacy","Authorization Checks","Conflicting consents resolve to the most restrictive outcome","Decision Table","System","P1","High","High","Two consents exist: one permits, one denies the same category","1. Configure permit consent | 2. Configure deny consent for same category | 3. Request access | 4. Record decision","Permit + Deny on same category","Conflict resolves to deny (most-restrictive precedence); decision rationale is captured in the audit trail","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-016","Security; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0043","Consent & Privacy","Authorization Checks","Authorization decision latency stays within SLA under load","Boundary","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Consent decision service deployed; load harness available","1. Drive concurrent consent-evaluation requests | 2. Measure p95 latency | 3. Verify no decisions error out","Concurrency=100; SLA p95<300ms","p95 decision latency stays within SLA and no request returns a default-allow due to timeout or error","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-016","Security; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0044","Consent & Privacy","Authorization Checks","API: consent enforcement on REST PHI endpoint","API","Integration","P1","High","High","REST API reachable; bearer token for a researcher; patient lacks research consent","1. Call GET /patient/{id}/observations with researcher token | 2. Inspect status and body","Token=ResearcherJWT","API returns 403 with a privacy-policy error and leaks no PHI in the body or error message","Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-016","Security; PHI/Privacy; Standards-FHIR","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0045","Consent & Privacy","Authorization Checks","Fail-closed when consent service is unavailable","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Consent decision service is down or unreachable","1. Take the consent service offline | 2. Request PHI requiring a consent decision | 3. Observe behavior","ConsentService=DOWN","System fails closed and denies access rather than defaulting to allow; the outage and denials are logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-017","Security; Patient Safety; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0046","Consent & Privacy","Audit","Audit log captures every consent grant, change and revocation","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging enabled; consent operations performed","1. Capture a consent | 2. Modify it | 3. Revoke it | 4. Open the audit log and filter by patient","Patient=Synthea-Test-001","Three distinct audit entries exist with actor, action, before/after where applicable, timestamp and source, in order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-018","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0047","Consent & Privacy","Audit","Audit entries cannot be deleted by an application user","Security","System","P1","High","High","Audit entries exist; admin and standard accounts available","1. Attempt to delete an audit entry as admin | 2. Attempt as standard user | 3. Verify persistence","Roles=Admin,User","No application role can delete audit entries; deletion attempts are themselves logged","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-018","Audit; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
