"TC-CONSENT-0049","Consent & Privacy","Audit","Read access to sensitive records is audited even when permitted","Security","System","P2","High","High","Sensitive record access permitted by consent; audit enabled","1. Authorized clinician reads a sensitive record | 2. Open audit log | 3. Locate the read event","Record=MentalHealthNote","Even permitted reads of sensitive categories generate an audit read event with actor, patient, time and category","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-018","Audit; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0050","Consent & Privacy","Consent Capture","Exploratory: probe consent UI for inconsistent state on rapid edits","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Consent officer logged in; patient with an existing consent","1. Rapidly toggle scopes and status | 2. Use browser back during save | 3. Open the record in two tabs and edit both | 4. Observe consistency","Concurrent edits; rapid toggles","No orphaned, duplicated or partially-saved consents result; concurrent edits are resolved deterministically with a clear conflict message","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-001","Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0051","Consent & Privacy","Restricted Records","Accessibility: restriction and consent banners are screen-reader announced","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Screen reader active; restricted patient record","1. Navigate to the restricted record with a screen reader | 2. Trigger the restriction warning | 3. Listen for announcement","ScreenReader=NVDA","The restriction/consent warning is exposed as an ARIA alert and announced; focus moves to the dialog and is trapped","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-020","Accessibility; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
