"TC-CONSENT-0053","Consent & Privacy","Consent Scope","Database: consent-scope referential integrity on patient merge","Database","System","P2","High","Medium","Two patient records each with consents; a merge is performed","1. Record consents on both patients | 2. Merge the duplicate into the surviving record | 3. Query consents for the survivor","Merge=Patient-A into Patient-B","All consents reassociate to the surviving patient without orphaned rows; conflicting scopes resolve most-restrictive and the merge is audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-021","Data Integrity; Database; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Platform"
"TC-CONSENT-0054","Consent & Privacy","Authorization Checks","Pairwise: consent-status x record-restriction x role decisions","Pairwise","System","P2","High","High","Consent statuses, restriction flags and roles configured","1. Iterate status {Active,Expired,Revoked} x restriction {On,Off} x role {CareTeam,Other} | 2. Evaluate access per cell","Pairwise status/restriction/role","Each cell yields the correct permit/deny; only Active consent with care-team role on a restricted record permits access","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-016","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0055","Consent & Privacy","Minimum Necessary","Boundary: bulk export caps returned records to authorized count","Boundary","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Researcher authorized for a cohort of N consented patients","1. Request a bulk export | 2. Include one extra non-consented patient id | 3. Inspect output count","Cohort=50 consented + 1 non-consented","Export contains exactly the consented records; the non-consented patient is excluded and the exclusion is logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-CONSENT-010","PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity; Security","Standards"
"TC-CONSENT-0056","Consent & Privacy","Disclosure Log","Self-disclosure (patient requesting own data) is logged but not consent-gated","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Patient portal identity verified; right-of-access request","1. Patient requests their own record via portal | 2. Observe access | 3. Inspect disclosure/access log","Requester=Patient self","Patient receives their own data under right-of-access without third-party consent gating; the access is still recorded in the log","Manual-Only","REQ-CONSENT-022","Regulatory/Compliance; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Platform"
