"TC-RESTAPI-0049","REST API (deep, per resource)","Query Params","Search term shorter than minimum length is rejected","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Default search minimum character setting in effect","1. GET /patient?q=a | 2. Inspect status","q=a (1 char)","HTTP 400 (or 200 with empty results) per the configured minimum search length; no expensive unbounded scan is performed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-014","Performance; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0050","REST API (deep, per resource)","Voided/Retired","includeAll=true exposes voided records to authorized users only","Security","Regression","P2","High","High","A voided patient and two users: one with and one without data-management privilege","1. As privileged user GET /patient/{uuid}?includeAll=true | 2. As basic user repeat","includeAll=true","Privileged user sees voided=true record; basic user receives 404 or is denied; voided data is not exposed without authorization","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-003","PHI/Privacy; Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0051","REST API (deep, per resource)","Error Codes","Unauthenticated request returns 401 with no PHI","Security","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","No valid session cookie or Basic credentials","1. GET /ws/rest/v1/patient/{uuid} without authentication | 2. Inspect status and body","no Authorization header","HTTP 401 Unauthorized; response body contains no patient PHI, only an authentication error","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-015","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0052","REST API (deep, per resource)","Error Codes","Authenticated but unprivileged request returns 403","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","A user lacking Get Patients / manage privileges","1. Authenticate as the restricted user | 2. GET a protected resource (e.g. /user) | 3. Inspect status","restricted role","HTTP 403 Forbidden; the action is denied and no protected data is returned","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-015","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0053","REST API (deep, per resource)","Error Codes","Nonexistent uuid returns 404","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Low","Valid session","1. GET /ws/rest/v1/patient/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000 | 2. Inspect status","unknown uuid","HTTP 404 Not Found with a clear error message; no stack trace or internal path leaked","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-015","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0054","REST API (deep, per resource)","Error Codes","Malformed JSON body returns 400 not 500","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Valid session","1. POST /patient with a truncated/invalid JSON body | 2. Inspect status","body: {person:{names: (broken)","HTTP 400 with a parse error; the server does not return 500 or expose a stack trace","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-015","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0055","REST API (deep, per resource)","Error Codes","Unsupported HTTP method returns 405","Negative","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Valid session","1. Send PUT /ws/rest/v1/patient (collection) | 2. Inspect status and Allow header","PUT on collection","HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed with an Allow header listing permitted methods","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-015","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0056","REST API (deep, per resource)","Content Negotiation","Accept application/json returns JSON; unsupported type returns 406","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Valid session","1. GET /patient/{uuid} with Accept: application/json | 2. Repeat with Accept: application/xml | 3. Repeat with Accept: text/csv","Accept: json | xml | csv","JSON request returns 200 application/json; unsupported media types return 406 Not Acceptable (or the documented supported set), never silently mis-typed content","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-016","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0057","REST API (deep, per resource)","Content Negotiation","POST with wrong Content-Type returns 415","Negative","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Valid session","1. POST /patient with body but Content-Type: text/plain | 2. Inspect status","Content-Type: text/plain","HTTP 415 Unsupported Media Type; the JSON body is not parsed under the wrong content type","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-016","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0058","REST API (deep, per resource)","API","Lost-update: two clients update same person concurrently","API","Regression","P2","High","High","An existing person and two sessions reading the same version","1. Both clients GET /person/{uuid} | 2. Client A POST a gender change | 3. Client B POST an address change using its stale snapshot | 4. GET final state","two concurrent updates","Last write does not silently clobber unrelated fields; either both changes merge correctly or the stale write is rejected; no field is lost without detection","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-017","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0059","REST API (deep, per resource)","API","Conditional GET with If-None-Match / ETag returns 304 when unchanged","API","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","A resource that returns an ETag (or Last-Modified) header","1. GET resource and capture ETag | 2. GET again with If-None-Match set to that ETag | 3. Modify resource | 4. GET with the old If-None-Match","ETag header value","If supported, step 2 returns 304 Not Modified with no body; after modification step 4 returns 200 with the new representation and a new ETag","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-017","Performance; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-RESTAPI-0060","REST API (deep, per resource)","API","Conditional update with If-Match precondition fails on stale ETag (412)","API","Regression","P2","High","High","A resource supporting optimistic concurrency via ETag/If-Match","1. GET resource and capture ETag | 2. Update the resource out-of-band | 3. POST update with the original (now stale) If-Match | 4. Inspect status","stale If-Match","Update is rejected with HTTP 412 Precondition Failed; the stale client is forced to refetch, preventing a lost update","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-017","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-RESTAPI-0061","REST API (deep, per resource)","Security","SQL injection in q parameter is neutralized","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Valid session","1. GET /patient?q=' OR '1'='1 | 2. GET /patient?q=test'; DROP TABLE person;-- | 3. Inspect results and DB integrity","q='' OR ''1''=''1 ; q with DROP TABLE","Inputs are parameterized/escaped; no unintended rows returned and no schema change; query is treated as a literal search term","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-018","Security; PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0062","REST API (deep, per resource)","Security","Stored XSS payload in person name is not executed on read","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Valid session","1. POST /person with givenName containing a script payload | 2. GET /person/{uuid} | 3. Inspect raw JSON","givenName=<script>alert(1)</script>","The payload is stored/returned as data only; the API does not render it; consuming clients receive properly encoded JSON with no executable markup interpreted server-side","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-018","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0063","REST API (deep, per resource)","Security","Direct object reference to another patient is access-controlled","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","A user whose role restricts patients to one location; a patient in another location","1. Authenticate as the restricted user | 2. GET /patient/{otherLocationPatientUuid} | 3. Inspect status","cross-location patient uuid","Access is denied (403 or 404) per location-based access control; the user cannot read a patient outside their authorized scope (no IDOR)","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-018","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0064","REST API (deep, per resource)","Security","Session fixation: logout invalidates the session token","Security","Regression","P2","High","High","An authenticated session with a known JSESSIONID","1. GET /session to confirm authenticated | 2. DELETE /session (logout) | 3. Reuse the old token on GET /patient/{uuid}","old JSESSIONID after logout","After logout the old token is invalid; reuse returns 401; no PHI is served on the invalidated session","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-018","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0065","REST API (deep, per resource)","Security","Rate limiting / brute-force protection on /session","Security","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","A known username","1. POST repeated Basic auth attempts with wrong passwords | 2. Observe lockout/throttle behavior","20 rapid failed logins","After a threshold the account is locked or requests throttled; no credential enumeration via differing error messages","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-018","Security","Platform"
"TC-RESTAPI-0066","REST API (deep, per resource)","Database","Voided record retains row with audit columns set","Database","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","DB read access; a patient voided via API","1. Void patient via DELETE | 2. Query patient table directly for the uuid","SELECT voided, voided_by, date_voided, void_reason","Row persists with voided=1, voided_by, date_voided and void_reason populated; soft-delete semantics confirmed at the data layer","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-019","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0067","REST API (deep, per resource)","Database","Obs value stored in correct typed column per datatype","Database","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","DB read access; numeric, coded and text obs created via API","1. Create obs of each datatype | 2. Query obs table for value_numeric, value_coded, value_text","one obs per datatype","Numeric value in value_numeric, coded answer in value_coded, free text in value_text; no type is stored in the wrong column","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-019","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0068","REST API (deep, per resource)","Database","Referential integrity: encounter rows reference valid patient and visit","Database","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","DB read access","1. Create encounter via API | 2. Query encounter table foreign keys patient_id and visit_id","encounter FK columns","Foreign keys resolve to existing, non-purged patient and visit rows; no orphaned encounter is created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-019","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0069","REST API (deep, per resource)","FHIR","Read a FHIR R4 Patient via /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient/{id}","FHIR","Sanity","P1","High","Medium","A patient exists; FHIR2 module enabled","1. GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient/{uuid} with Accept: application/fhir+json | 2. Validate the resource","Accept: application/fhir+json","HTTP 200; a valid FHIR R4 Patient resourceType with id, name, gender and birthDate conforming to the R4 schema","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-020","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0070","REST API (deep, per resource)","FHIR","FHIR Patient search by identifier returns a Bundle","FHIR","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A patient with a known identifier; FHIR2 enabled","1. GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient?identifier=1000X | 2. Validate the response","identifier=1000X","HTTP 200; a searchset Bundle with total and entry array; the matching Patient is present with correct identifier system and value","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-020","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0071","REST API (deep, per resource)","FHIR","FHIR read of unknown id returns OperationOutcome 404","FHIR","Regression","P2","Medium","Low","FHIR2 enabled","1. GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient/nonexistent | 2. Inspect status and body","id=nonexistent","HTTP 404 with a FHIR OperationOutcome resource describing the not-found error (standards-conformant error envelope)","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-020","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0072","REST API (deep, per resource)","FHIR","FHIR Observation maps OpenMRS obs with LOINC code and value","FHIR","Regression","P2","High","Medium","An obs on a LOINC-mapped concept; FHIR2 enabled","1. GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Observation/{uuid} | 2. Validate code and value","obs on LOINC-mapped concept","HTTP 200; Observation has code.coding with the LOINC system URI and code, a valueQuantity (or valueCodeableConcept) and a subject reference to the Patient","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-020","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0073","REST API (deep, per resource)","FHIR","FHIR _count and pagination links on a search Bundle","FHIR","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Several FHIR Patients exist; FHIR2 enabled","1. GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient?_count=2 | 2. Follow the Bundle link rel=next","_count=2","Each Bundle page contains at most 2 entries and includes self and next links; following next yields the subsequent non-overlapping page","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-020","Standards-FHIR","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0074","REST API (deep, per resource)","FHIR","Create a FHIR Patient via POST returns 201 with Location","FHIR","Regression","P2","High","Medium","FHIR2 enabled; write privileges","1. POST /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient with a valid R4 Patient body | 2. Inspect status, Location header and body","valid R4 Patient JSON","HTTP 201 Created with a Location header pointing to the new resource and the persisted Patient echoed with a server-assigned id","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-020","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0075","REST API (deep, per resource)","FHIR","FHIR conditional create with If-None-Exist avoids duplicate","FHIR","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","A FHIR Patient with identifier 1000X already exists","1. POST /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient with If-None-Exist: identifier=1000X | 2. Inspect status","If-None-Exist: identifier=1000X","If supported, server returns 200 referencing the existing resource rather than creating a duplicate; otherwise documents the behavior; no duplicate Patient is created","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-020","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-RESTAPI-0076","REST API (deep, per resource)","HL7","Submit an HL7 v2 ADT^A04 message via the HL7 endpoint","HL7","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 inbound processing enabled; an identifier source mapped","1. POST an ADT^A04 (register patient) message to the HL7 inbound queue | 2. Process the queue | 3. GET the resulting patient","ADT^A04 with PID containing name, DOB, MRN","Message is accepted and processed without error; a patient is created/updated reflecting the PID demographics; an ACK is generated","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-021","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0077","REST API (deep, per resource)","HL7","Malformed HL7 message is queued as an error with NAK","HL7","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 inbound processing enabled","1. POST an HL7 message missing the required MSH-9 message type | 2. Process the queue | 3. Inspect the error queue","HL7 missing MSH-9","Message fails processing and lands in the HL7 error queue with a descriptive error; a NAK/AR acknowledgment is produced; no partial patient data is committed","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-021","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0078","REST API (deep, per resource)","HL7","ORU^R01 result message creates observations under an encounter","HL7","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 enabled; concepts mapped to OBX codes; an existing patient","1. POST an ORU^R01 with OBX segments | 2. Process the queue | 3. GET the patient encounters","ORU^R01 with two OBX numeric results","An encounter with the OBX-derived observations is created and linked to the correct patient; obs values and units match the OBX fields","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-021","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0079","REST API (deep, per resource)","Paging","totalCount only returned when totalCount=true requested","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","A collection with many matches","1. GET /patient?q=Test&limit=5 | 2. GET /patient?q=Test&limit=5&totalCount=true","totalCount flag","Without the flag the response may omit totalCount for performance; with totalCount=true the accurate grand total is returned alongside the page","Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-014","Performance; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0080","REST API (deep, per resource)","Paging","Stable ordering across pages prevents row skips/duplicates","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","A collection larger than two pages with a deterministic sort","1. Page through the entire collection in limit-sized chunks | 2. Collect all uuids | 3. Check for gaps/dupes","limit=2 across all pages","The concatenation of all pages contains every uuid exactly once with no duplicates or omissions; ordering is stable between requests","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-014","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0081","REST API (deep, per resource)","Exploratory","Explore unexpected behavior with deeply nested custom representations","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Low","Low","An existing patient with rich subresources","1. Request progressively deeper v=custom expansions across person, identifiers, attributes and auditInfo | 2. Observe performance and correctness | 3. Note any field that fails to expand","v=custom with 3+ nesting levels","Deep expansions return correct nested data without server errors; any unsupported nesting is reported clearly rather than returning partial/garbled JSON; response time stays reasonable","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-004","Data Integrity; Performance","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0082","REST API (deep, per resource)","Exploratory","Probe timezone handling of encounterDatetime round-trip","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","An encounter created with an explicit timezone offset","1. POST /encounter with encounterDatetime including a +05:30 offset | 2. GET the encounter from clients in different timezones | 3. Compare instants","encounterDatetime=2026-06-30T23:00:00+05:30","The stored instant is unambiguous and round-trips to the same UTC moment regardless of client timezone; no off-by-one-day shift in the encounter date","Manual-Only","REQ-RESTAPI-006","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-RESTAPI-0083","REST API (deep, per resource)","Accessibility","REST error payloads are machine-parseable for assistive client tooling","Accessibility","Regression","P4","Low","Low","Valid session","1. Trigger 400, 404 and 403 errors | 2. Inspect each error body structure","various error responses","Each error returns a consistent JSON structure (error.message, error.code/detail) enabling assistive and automated clients to surface meaningful, localizable messages rather than opaque HTML","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-015","Accessibility; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-RESTAPI-0084","REST API (deep, per resource)","Audit","Every create/update/void writes audit metadata retrievable via v=full","Audit","Regression","P2","High","High","Privileges to view audit info","1. Create then update then void a person via API | 2. GET /person/{uuid}?v=full at each step | 3. Inspect auditInfo","auditInfo at each lifecycle stage","auditInfo reports creator+dateCreated on create, changedBy+dateChanged on update, and voidedBy+dateVoided+voidReason on void; an immutable audit trail is maintained for compliance","Partially-Automatable","REQ-RESTAPI-022","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-FHIR2-0001","FHIR R4 (deep: search/bundle/operations)","Search Params - Patient","Search Patient by exact family name token","FHIR","Regression","P2","High","Medium","FHIR endpoint /ws/fhir2/R4 reachable; OAuth/basic auth valid; at least one Patient with family=Smith exists","1. Authenticate to FHIR endpoint | 2. GET /Patient?family=Smith | 3. Inspect returned Bundle | 4. Verify each entry resourceType=Patient and name.family matches","family=Smith","HTTP 200; Bundle.type=searchset; every entry.resource.name.family contains Smith (case-insensitive starts-with per R4 string semantics); total reflects match count","Automatable","REQ-FHIR2-001","Standards-FHIR;Clinical;Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
