"TC-SECDEEP-0001","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - IDOR","Direct object reference on patient record by sequential internal patient id","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Two patients P1 and P2 exist; a low-privileged user authenticated who is authorized only for P1","1. Authenticate as the limited user and load P1 via the patient dashboard | 2. Capture the patient REST/UI request containing P1 internal id | 3. Replay the request substituting P2 internal id | 4. Observe the response","P1 uuid=11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111; P2 uuid=22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222","Server returns 403/404 with no P2 PHI; access denial is recorded to the audit log; no demographics leak in error body","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-001","PHI/Privacy; Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0002","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - IDOR","IDOR on clinical observation (obs) resource across patients","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","User authorized for P1 only; an obs belonging to P2 exists with a known uuid","1. Authenticate as the limited user | 2. Issue GET /ws/rest/v1/obs/{P2_obs_uuid} | 3. Inspect response status and body | 4. Repeat via FHIR Observation/{id}","P2_obs_uuid=33333333-3333-3333-3333-333333333333","Both REST and FHIR endpoints deny access (403/404); no observation value, code or concept returned; denial audited","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-001","PHI/Privacy; Clinical; Security; Standards-FHIR","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0003","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - IDOR","Horizontal escalation on encounter resource via REST","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Two clinicians each own distinct encounters; clinician A authenticated","1. As clinician A list own encounters | 2. Note an encounter uuid owned by clinician B for an unauthorized patient | 3. GET /ws/rest/v1/encounter/{B_uuid} | 4. Attempt DELETE on the same uuid","B_encounter_uuid=44444444-4444-4444-4444-444444444444","Read and delete are both denied; no encounter detail disclosed; privilege check enforced server-side not just hidden in UI","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-002","Clinical; PHI/Privacy; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0004","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - Vertical","Privilege escalation by calling admin-only manageUsers endpoint as clinician","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","A clinician account lacking Manage Users privilege is authenticated","1. Authenticate as clinician | 2. Attempt POST /ws/rest/v1/user to create a new admin user | 3. Attempt PUT to grant System Developer role to self | 4. Observe responses","NewUser=tester_priv; Role=System Developer","All privilege-mutating calls return 403; no user created; no role granted; attempt logged","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-003","Security; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0005","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - Force Browse","Forced browsing to admin pages without menu link","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","Non-admin user authenticated","1. Authenticate as non-admin | 2. Navigate directly to /admin and to module management URLs by typing the path | 3. Observe rendering and data exposure","URL=/openmrs/admin/index.htm","Server enforces authorization and redirects/denies; no admin functions or settings shown despite direct URL entry","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-003","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0006","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - FHIR scope","Patient-context FHIR token cannot read other patients (compartment)","FHIR","Integration","P1","Critical","High","SMART patient-launch token issued for patient/Patient.read scoped to P1","1. Present the patient-scoped token | 2. GET /fhir2/R4/Patient/{P1} | 3. GET /fhir2/R4/Patient/{P2} | 4. GET /fhir2/R4/Observation?patient={P2}","Scope=patient/*.read; launch patient=P1","P1 reads succeed; any cross-compartment read to P2 is denied with 403/empty bundle; compartment enforced server-side","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-004","Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy; Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0007","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - Decision Table","Resource access decision table across role x operation","Decision Table","System","P1","High","High","Roles {Anonymous, Clinician, Pharmacist, Admin} and operations {read, write, delete} on Patient/Order","1. For each role authenticate | 2. Attempt each operation on Patient and Order | 3. Record allow/deny | 4. Compare against expected matrix","Matrix: Anonymous=deny all; Clinician=read+write Patient/Order, no delete; Pharmacist=read Patient, write Order(dispense); Admin=all","Every cell matches the authorization matrix; no allow where deny expected; deviations flagged as defects","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-002","Security; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0008","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - Mass assignment","Mass assignment of restricted fields on patient update","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","Clinician authorized to edit demographics for P1","1. Capture legitimate PUT to patient | 2. Inject extra fields such as roles, voided, dateCreated, uuid override | 3. Submit | 4. Read back the record","Injected: {""voided"":true,""auditInfo"":{...},""roles"":[""System Developer""]}","Server ignores/strips unauthorized fields; patient not voided; no role granted; only permitted demographic fields change","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-005","Security; Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0009","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - Provider link","Patient cannot access another patient via portal patient/Patient relationship","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Patient-portal style account (omiiCARE) bound to P1 only","1. Login as patient-portal user | 2. Request own records | 3. Tamper patientId param to P2 | 4. Observe","portalUser=p1.portal; tamper patientId=P2","Only P1 data returned; P2 request denied; binding between account and patient enforced server-side","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-004","PHI/Privacy; Security","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0010","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A02 Cryptographic Failures - TLS","TLS configuration rejects weak protocols and ciphers","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Access to the owned test environment endpoint and a TLS scanner","1. Scan endpoint TLS versions | 2. Attempt TLS 1.0/1.1 handshake | 3. Enumerate cipher suites | 4. Check for export/NULL/RC4/3DES","Target=https://o2.openmrs.org (owned test mirror)","Only TLS 1.2+ negotiated; legacy protocols refused; no weak/export ciphers; forward secrecy ciphers preferred","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-006","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0011","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A02 Cryptographic Failures - HSTS","HSTS enforced and HTTP redirects to HTTPS","Security","Integration","P2","High","High","Owned test environment reachable on port 80 and 443","1. Request http:// base URL | 2. Inspect redirect | 3. Inspect Strict-Transport-Security header on https response | 4. Verify max-age and includeSubDomains","Header expected: Strict-Transport-Security: max-age>=31536000; includeSubDomains","HTTP 301/308 to HTTPS; HSTS present with long max-age and includeSubDomains; no PHI served over cleartext","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-006","Security; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0012","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A02 Cryptographic Failures - At rest","PHI at rest is encrypted (DB/file/backup design verification)","Database","System","P1","Critical","High","Design/config access to DB encryption settings on owned environment","1. Review DB at-rest encryption (TDE/volume) config | 2. Inspect attachment/blob storage encryption | 3. Inspect backup encryption | 4. Confirm key management separation","Tables: patient, person_name, obs; attachment store; nightly backup","PHI columns/files and backups are encrypted at rest; keys managed separately from data; documented per policy","Manual-Only","REQ-SECDEEP-007","PHI/Privacy; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0013","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A02 Cryptographic Failures - Passwords","Password storage uses strong adaptive hashing with per-user salt","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Design/config access to authentication storage on owned environment","1. Review password hash algorithm and parameters | 2. Verify unique salt per user | 3. Confirm no reversible/MD5/SHA1-unsalted | 4. Verify hash not exposed via any API","Sample users: u1, u2 with identical passwords","Hashes use a strong adaptive algorithm with per-user salt; identical passwords yield different hashes; never returned in any response","Manual-Only","REQ-SECDEEP-007","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0014","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A02 Cryptographic Failures - Transit","No sensitive data in URL query strings or referers","Security","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Authenticated session with PHI views","1. Navigate clinical pages | 2. Inspect URLs and Referer headers | 3. Check for tokens, MRNs, SSNs in query strings | 4. Check server access logs design","Look for ?token=, ?mrn=, ?ssn= patterns","No tokens or PHI in query strings; sensitive identifiers passed in body/headers; referer leakage controlled via Referrer-Policy","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-006","PHI/Privacy; Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0015","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - SQL","SQL injection on patient search name parameter","Database","System","P1","Critical","High","Authenticated user with patient search access","1. Open patient search | 2. Enter SQLi payloads in name field | 3. Submit and observe | 4. Try boolean and time-based variants","Payloads: '' OR ''1''=''1; '' UNION SELECT null--; ''; WAITFOR DELAY ''0:0:5''--","Input treated as literal; no extra rows, no DB error leak, no time delay; parameterized queries confirmed; attempt logged","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-008","Security; Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0016","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - SQL","Blind SQLi on REST query params (q, identifier)","Database","System","P1","Critical","High","Authenticated user; REST patient search endpoint reachable","1. GET /ws/rest/v1/patient?q=<payload> | 2. Use time-based payload | 3. Use boolean-based payload | 4. Compare response timing and counts","payload=test' AND SLEEP(5)-- ; payload=test' AND 1=1--","No measurable injected delay; identical result counts regardless of boolean condition; queries parameterized","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-008","Security; Database","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0017","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - HQL/ORM","ORM/HQL injection via order-by or filter parameters","Database","System","P2","High","Medium","Authenticated user with list/sort endpoints","1. Identify sortable list endpoint | 2. Inject HQL fragments into sort/filter param | 3. Observe errors or data changes | 4. Try nested property traversal","sort=name);--; filter=person.user.password","Injection rejected; no HQL error stack; cannot traverse to restricted properties; allowlist of sortable fields enforced","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-008","Security; Database","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0018","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - LDAP","LDAP injection on directory-backed login","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Environment configured with LDAP/AD authentication backend (owned)","1. At login enter LDAP metacharacters in username | 2. Try filter-breaking payloads | 3. Observe auth result and logs","Payloads: *)(uid=*))(|(uid=* ; admin)(&) ; *","Login fails safely; no auth bypass; LDAP filter properly escaped; no directory enumeration; attempts logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-009","Security; Audit","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0019","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - Command","OS command injection on report/export filename or path params","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","User with report export capability","1. Trigger export with crafted filename | 2. Inject shell metacharacters | 3. Observe server behavior | 4. Check for command execution side effects","filename=rep;id|whoami ; path=../../etc/passwd","No command executed; metacharacters sanitized; no file outside allowed dir; safe error returned","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-010","Security; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0020","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - NoSQL","NoSQL/JSON injection on FHIR search parameters","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR endpoint reachable with search params","1. Send FHIR search with operator-injection in params | 2. Use JSON object where scalar expected | 3. Observe parsing | 4. Confirm no filter bypass","name[$ne]=; _id={""$gt"":""""}","Server validates types; object-injection rejected with 400; no broadened result set; no backend error leak","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-008","Standards-FHIR; Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0021","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - XSS stored","Stored XSS via patient name / address fields rendered on dashboard","Security","System","P1","High","High","Clinician can register/edit a patient; viewer opens dashboard","1. Register patient with script payload in given/family name | 2. Save | 3. Open patient dashboard as another user | 4. Observe execution","givenName=<script>alert(document.cookie)</script>; family=<img src=x onerror=alert(1)>","Payload stored as data and rendered inert (encoded); no script execution; output encoding applied on all PHI fields","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-011","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0022","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - XSS reflected","Reflected XSS via search query echoed in results header","Security","System","P2","High","Medium","Authenticated user with search","1. Submit search term containing markup | 2. Observe results page echo of term | 3. Inspect DOM and CSP behavior","q=<svg/onload=alert(1)>","Search term encoded in output; no script runs; CSP blocks inline as defense in depth","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-011","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0023","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - Header","HTTP header / CRLF injection on parameters reflected into headers","Negative","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Endpoint that sets a header/cookie from user input","1. Send CRLF payload in input reflected to response header | 2. Observe response splitting | 3. Attempt to set rogue Set-Cookie","payload=value%0d%0aSet-Cookie:%20admin=1","CRLF stripped/encoded; no header injection; no response splitting; single intended header only","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-011","Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0024","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A04 Insecure Design - Threat model","Negative-by-default authorization design for new clinical resource","Functional","System","P2","High","High","Design review of a newly added resource endpoint","1. Review default access policy for the new endpoint | 2. Verify it denies unless explicitly granted | 3. Test an unmapped role | 4. Confirm fail-closed","NewResource=careTeam; Role=unmapped","Endpoint denies by default; only explicitly privileged roles allowed; fail-closed on missing policy","Manual-Only","REQ-SECDEEP-012","Security; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0025","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A04 Insecure Design - Abuse case","Account takeover via unbounded password reset flow","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Password reset feature enabled on owned environment","1. Trigger reset for a victim account | 2. Attempt to brute-force the reset token/OTP | 3. Reuse a token | 4. Use an expired token","Token=6-digit OTP; attempts=10000","Tokens are high-entropy, single-use, short-lived, rate-limited and bound to the requesting session; brute force blocked","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-013","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0026","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A04 Insecure Design - Business logic","Prevent ordering high-risk medication without required co-sign workflow","Decision Table","System","P2","High","High","Prescriber and required co-signer roles configured for controlled substances","1. Place a controlled-substance order as prescriber | 2. Attempt to activate without co-sign | 3. Provide co-sign | 4. Verify state","Drug=controlled C-II; co-sign required=true","Order cannot reach Active without co-sign; bypass attempts blocked; safety control cannot be skipped via API","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-012","Patient Safety; Clinical; Security","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0027","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A04 Insecure Design - Enumeration","Username/account enumeration via differential responses","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Login and reset endpoints reachable","1. Submit login for known vs unknown username | 2. Submit reset for known vs unknown email | 3. Compare status, body, timing","known=valid_user; unknown=nouser_zzz","Responses are uniform for known/unknown (same message, status, timing); no account enumeration possible","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-013","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0028","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A05 Security Misconfiguration - Headers","Security response headers present and correct","Security","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Authenticated and anonymous access to owned environment","1. Inspect response headers on app pages and API | 2. Verify CSP, X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options/frame-ancestors, Referrer-Policy | 3. Verify no Server/X-Powered-By version leak","Expected: X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff; CSP set; frame-ancestors restricted","All baseline security headers present and restrictive; no sensitive version/banner disclosure","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-014","Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0029","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A05 Security Misconfiguration - Defaults","Default and demo credentials are disabled in non-demo deployments","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Hardened deployment profile (not the public demo)","1. Attempt login with known default admin/Admin123 | 2. Attempt common module default accounts | 3. Observe","creds=admin/Admin123","Default credentials rejected in hardened profile; forced password change on first admin login; documented","Manual-Only","REQ-SECDEEP-015","Security; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0030","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A05 Security Misconfiguration - Errors","Error pages do not leak stack traces or internals","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Ability to trigger 4xx/5xx on owned environment","1. Force a 500 via malformed request | 2. Force a 404 | 3. Inspect bodies | 4. Check for stack traces, SQL, file paths, framework versions","Malformed JSON body; nonexistent path","Generic error pages returned; no stack trace, SQL, internal path or version disclosed; correlation id only","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-015","Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0031","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A05 Security Misconfiguration - CORS","CORS policy is restrictive and does not reflect arbitrary origins","API","Integration","P2","High","Medium","REST/FHIR API reachable cross-origin","1. Send request with Origin: https://evil.example | 2. Inspect Access-Control-Allow-Origin and -Credentials | 3. Try null origin | 4. Try preflight","Origin=https://evil.example; Origin=null","Arbitrary origins not reflected; ACAO restricted to allowlist; credentials not allowed with wildcard; null origin denied","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-014","Security; API","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0032","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A05 Security Misconfiguration - Methods","Unsafe HTTP methods (TRACE/PUT/OPTIONS) restricted","Negative","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Web/app server reachable","1. Send TRACE request | 2. Send arbitrary PUT to static path | 3. Inspect Allow header on OPTIONS | 4. Observe","Methods: TRACE, PUT, DELETE on static resources","TRACE disabled; no unauthorized PUT/DELETE on static; Allow advertises only required methods","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-014","Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0033","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A05 Security Misconfiguration - Exposed","Sensitive endpoints (actuator/console/swagger) not publicly exposed","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","Knowledge of common management paths","1. Probe /actuator, /h2-console, /env, /swagger, /api-docs, module debug pages | 2. Observe auth requirement | 3. Check data exposure","paths=/actuator/health,/h2-console,/swagger-ui","Management/debug consoles disabled or auth-protected in production; no config/secrets exposed anonymously","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-015","Security","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0034","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - Brute force","Account lockout / throttling after repeated failed logins","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","A valid account exists; lockout policy configured","1. Submit N-1 wrong passwords | 2. Submit Nth wrong password to trip lockout | 3. Attempt correct password while locked | 4. Wait/observe unlock or admin reset","threshold=5 attempts; lockout window per policy","States: Active -> (fails) -> Locked -> (timeout/admin) -> Active; correct password rejected while Locked; events audited","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-016","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0035","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - Session fixation","Session identifier rotates on authentication","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Login flow issues a session cookie","1. Obtain pre-auth session id | 2. Authenticate successfully | 3. Compare post-auth session id | 4. Replay pre-auth id","pre-auth JSESSIONID captured","Session id is regenerated on login; pre-auth id invalidated; fixation prevented","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-016","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0036","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - Cookie flags","Session cookies set with HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite","Security","Integration","P2","High","High","HTTPS session established","1. Authenticate | 2. Inspect Set-Cookie for session cookie | 3. Verify HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite | 4. Verify scope/path","Cookie=JSESSIONID","Session cookie marked HttpOnly, Secure and SameSite=Lax/Strict; not script-accessible; not sent cross-site insecurely","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-016","Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0037","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - Logout","Logout invalidates session server-side (no token reuse)","State Transition","System","P2","High","High","Authenticated session active","1. Authenticate and capture session/token | 2. Logout | 3. Replay the previous session/token on a protected request | 4. Observe","captured session/token","Post-logout the old session/token is rejected (401/redirect); server-side invalidation, not just client cookie clear","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-016","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0038","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - Idle timeout","Idle and absolute session timeout enforced","Boundary","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Configured idle timeout (e.g., 30 min) and absolute lifetime","1. Authenticate | 2. Idle for timeout-1 then act (still valid) | 3. Idle for timeout+1 then act (expired) | 4. Exceed absolute lifetime","idle=30m; absolute=8h","At timeout-1 session valid; at timeout+1 session expired requiring re-auth; absolute lifetime enforced regardless of activity","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-016","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0039","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - MFA","MFA challenge required and cannot be bypassed","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","MFA enabled for the account (owned environment)","1. Enter valid username/password | 2. At MFA step attempt to skip by calling post-auth endpoint directly | 3. Submit wrong OTP repeatedly | 4. Submit replayed OTP","OTP=valid then replay; skip via direct URL","MFA cannot be bypassed by direct navigation; wrong OTP throttled; OTP single-use and time-bound","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-017","Security","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0040","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - Password policy","Password complexity, history and length boundaries enforced","Boundary","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Password change available; policy configured","1. Set password at min length-1 (reject) | 2. At min length (accept) | 3. Reuse a previous password (reject) | 4. Common/breached password (reject)","minLen=8; history=5; common=Password1","Below-min rejected; at-min accepted; reused-within-history rejected; common/breached rejected; messages non-enumerating","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-017","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0041","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - JWT alg","JWT rejects none algorithm and signature stripping","API","Integration","P1","Critical","High","API accepts a bearer JWT (SMART/OAuth on owned env)","1. Capture a valid JWT | 2. Re-sign with alg=none and remove signature | 3. Send to protected API | 4. Observe","alg=none token; stripped signature","Token rejected (401); server enforces expected algorithm; none/unsigned tokens never accepted","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-018","Security; API","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0042","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - JWT tamper","JWT signature validation detects payload tampering","API","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Valid signed JWT available","1. Decode JWT and modify sub/scope/exp claims | 2. Re-encode without valid signature | 3. Send to API | 4. Observe","modify scope to system/*.*; modify exp to future","Tampered token rejected; signature mismatch detected; no elevated scope honored","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-018","Security; API","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0043","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - JWT expiry","Expired and not-yet-valid JWT are rejected","Boundary","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Ability to mint tokens with controlled exp/nbf on owned env","1. Send token with exp in the past | 2. Send token with nbf in the future | 3. Send token at exact exp boundary | 4. Observe","exp=now-60s; nbf=now+300s","Expired and not-yet-valid tokens rejected; boundary handled consistently; clock skew tolerance documented","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-018","Security; API","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0044","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - OAuth scope","OAuth/SMART scope enforcement limits resource and action","Decision Table","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Tokens issued with varying scopes on owned env","1. With patient/Observation.read attempt Observation read (allow) and write (deny) | 2. With user/MedicationRequest.write attempt write (allow) and Patient.read (deny) | 3. Record matrix","scopes: patient/Observation.read; user/MedicationRequest.write","Each request honored strictly per granted scope; resource and action enforced; out-of-scope denied 403","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-019","Standards-FHIR; Security; API","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0045","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - OAuth redirect","OAuth redirect_uri strictly validated against allowlist","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","OAuth/SMART authorization endpoint on owned env","1. Start authorize with registered redirect_uri (allow) | 2. Use unregistered redirect_uri (deny) | 3. Use open-redirect/path-append variants | 4. Observe","registered=https://app/cb; evil=https://app.attacker/cb","Only exact-registered redirect_uri accepted; variants and unregistered denied; no token/code leak to attacker URL","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-019","Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0046","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - PKCE","Authorization code requires PKCE and code is single-use","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","Public SMART client using auth code + PKCE","1. Complete authorize obtaining code | 2. Exchange code with wrong code_verifier (deny) | 3. Exchange with correct verifier (allow) | 4. Replay the code a second time (deny)","code_verifier valid/invalid; reused code","Wrong verifier rejected; correct verifier succeeds once; code replay rejected; PKCE required for public clients","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-019","Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0047","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A08 Integrity - Audit immutability","Audit/log records cannot be altered or deleted by users","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging enabled; a clinical action recorded","1. Perform an auditable action | 2. Attempt to update the audit record via API/UI | 3. Attempt to delete it | 4. Verify","target audit/log entry id","Audit entries are append-only; update/delete denied even for admins via app; tamper attempts themselves logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-020","Audit; Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0048","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A08 Integrity - Signed updates","Software/module updates verified for integrity before load","Functional","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Module/plugin install mechanism on owned env","1. Attempt to install an unsigned/modified module | 2. Attempt with tampered checksum | 3. Observe load behavior","module=tampered.omod","Unsigned/tampered modules rejected; integrity (signature/checksum) verified prior to activation","Manual-Only","REQ-SECDEEP-021","Security; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0049","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A08 Integrity - Deserialization","Insecure deserialization of untrusted input rejected","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","Endpoint accepting serialized/object payloads","1. Submit crafted serialized payload | 2. Submit unexpected type/gadget chain marker | 3. Observe","payload=java serialized gadget marker","Untrusted deserialization blocked; only expected DTO shapes parsed; no remote code execution; safe 400","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-021","Security; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0050","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A08 Integrity - Optimistic lock","Concurrent edit integrity uses version/ETag (lost update prevention)","State Transition","System","P2","High","Medium","Two clients editing the same patient/obs","1. Client A GET resource with ETag/version | 2. Client B updates the resource | 3. Client A updates using stale ETag (If-Match) | 4. Observe","stale ETag from A","Stale update rejected (412 Precondition Failed / conflict); no silent lost update; integrity preserved","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-021","Data Integrity; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0051","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A09 Logging - Auth events","Authentication successes and failures are logged with context","Audit","System","P2","High","High","Audit/log subsystem enabled","1. Perform successful login | 2. Perform failed login | 3. Perform privilege-denied action | 4. Inspect logs","users: u_success, u_fail","Each event logged with timestamp, user, source IP, action and outcome; no password/PHI in log payload","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-022","Audit; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0052","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A09 Logging - PHI access","PHI read access generates an access/disclosure audit entry","Audit","System","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging of record access enabled (HIPAA)","1. Open a patient chart as clinician | 2. View an encounter and lab result | 3. Inspect audit trail","patient P1; encounter; lab obs","Each PHI access is recorded with who/what/when/patient; supports HIPAA accounting of disclosures; no gaps","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-022","Audit; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0053","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A09 Logging - No sensitive data","Logs do not contain passwords, tokens or full PHI","Negative","System","P2","High","High","Access to application/server logs on owned env","1. Trigger login, token exchange, patient search | 2. Inspect logs for secrets | 3. Search for password, bearer, SSN patterns","grep: password=, Authorization: Bearer, SSN","No credentials, tokens or unmasked PHI in logs; sensitive values masked/omitted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-022","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0054","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A09 Logging - Alerting","Monitoring alerts on brute force and anomalous access","Functional","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Monitoring/alerting integrated on owned env","1. Simulate burst of failed logins | 2. Simulate bulk PHI export | 3. Verify alert generation/threshold","20 failed logins in 1 min; 500-record export","Alerts raised for brute force and bulk-access anomalies within defined thresholds; routed to security responders","Manual-Only","REQ-SECDEEP-023","Audit; Security","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0055","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A09 Logging - Tamper detection","Log tampering/gaps are detectable (integrity controls)","Database","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Centralized/append-only logging with integrity controls","1. Review log integrity mechanism (hash chain/WORM) | 2. Simulate deletion of a log line in copy | 3. Verify detection","log integrity config","Tampering or gaps detectable via integrity controls; logs forwarded off-host; chain-of-custody preserved","Manual-Only","REQ-SECDEEP-023","Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0056","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A10 SSRF - FHIR reference","SSRF via external/contained reference resolution blocked","FHIR","Integration","P1","Critical","High","FHIR endpoint that may resolve references/$validate against profiles","1. POST resource with reference URL to internal metadata (169.254.169.254) | 2. POST profile/canonical URL to internal host | 3. Observe outbound fetch","ref=http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/","Server does not fetch internal/cloud-metadata URLs; outbound resolution disabled or allowlisted; SSRF blocked","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-024","Standards-FHIR; Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0057","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A10 SSRF - Webhook/import","SSRF via document import / webhook URL field","Negative","System","P2","High","High","Feature that fetches a user-supplied URL (import, image, webhook)","1. Supply URL pointing to internal IP ranges | 2. Supply file:// and gopher:// schemes | 3. Supply DNS-rebinding host | 4. Observe","urls: http://127.0.0.1:8080/, file:///etc/passwd, http://[::1]/","Internal IPs, non-http schemes and rebinding blocked; allowlist + scheme/host validation enforced; no internal access","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-024","Security","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0058","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A10 SSRF - Redirect","SSRF protection survives HTTP redirect to internal host","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","URL-fetching feature that follows redirects","1. Supply external URL that 302-redirects to 127.0.0.1 | 2. Observe whether redirect target is re-validated | 3. Confirm block","external -> 302 -> http://127.0.0.1:22","Redirect targets are re-validated against allowlist; internal redirect target blocked; no follow to internal host","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-024","Security","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0059","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","CSRF","State-changing POST requires anti-CSRF token","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Authenticated session in a cookie-based UI flow","1. Capture a state-changing request (e.g., void patient) | 2. Replay without CSRF token | 3. Replay with wrong token | 4. Replay with valid token","action=void patient; token variations","Requests without/with invalid CSRF token rejected; only valid same-session token accepted; SameSite as defense in depth","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-025","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0060","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","CSRF","CSRF token is per-session/per-request and not predictable","Security","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Authenticated UI session","1. Obtain CSRF tokens across multiple requests/sessions | 2. Assess entropy and reuse | 3. Attempt token from session A in session B","tokens t1..tn","Tokens are unpredictable and bound to the session; cross-session token rejected; not reusable after logout","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-025","Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0061","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","Clickjacking","Framing protection prevents UI redress on clinical actions","Security","Integration","P2","High","Medium","App pages reachable; CSP/frame headers configured","1. Embed a clinical action page in an iframe on attacker page | 2. Observe frame-ancestors/X-Frame-Options enforcement | 3. Attempt overlay click","iframe src=clinical action URL","Sensitive pages refuse framing via frame-ancestors 'self'/DENY; clickjacking prevented","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-014","Security; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0062","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","Rate Limiting","API rate limiting on authentication endpoint","Boundary","Integration","P2","High","High","Auth/token endpoint reachable on owned env","1. Send requests just below limit (allowed) | 2. Exceed the limit (throttled) | 3. Inspect 429 and Retry-After | 4. Confirm reset after window","limit=N/min; burst above N","Below limit allowed; above limit returns 429 with Retry-After; counter resets after window; per-account+IP scoping","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-026","Security; API","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0063","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","Rate Limiting","Rate limiting on patient search / bulk read prevents scraping","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Authenticated low-priv user; search/export endpoints","1. Issue rapid sequential searches | 2. Attempt large-page bulk reads | 3. Observe throttling and pagination caps","page size=100000; rapid loop","Excessive requests throttled; max page size capped; mass-scrape mitigated; events logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-026","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0064","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","Rate Limiting - Pairwise","Throttling behavior across auth-state x endpoint-class pairs","Pairwise","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Endpoints classed {auth, read, write, export}; auth-states {anon, user, admin}","1. For selected pairwise combinations issue load above threshold | 2. Record throttle response | 3. Compare to policy","pairs: anon-auth, user-read, admin-export, anon-write","Each tested pair throttled per its policy; no pair is unbounded; responses consistent (429 + Retry-After)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-026","Security; API","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0065","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - Patient list","Patient list/search does not return restricted/embargoed patients","Negative","System","P2","High","High","A restricted/VIP patient flagged; clinician without break-glass","1. Search for the restricted patient by name | 2. Attempt direct open | 3. Verify break-glass requirement","restricted patient flag=true","Restricted patient hidden from normal results; access requires break-glass with justification; access audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-002","PHI/Privacy; Security; Audit","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0066","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - Break-glass","Break-glass access requires justification and heightened audit","State Transition","System","P2","High","High","Break-glass workflow enabled","1. Trigger break-glass on a restricted chart | 2. Attempt without justification (deny) | 3. Provide justification (allow, time-boxed) | 4. Verify expiry and audit","justification text; window=4h","Without justification denied; with justification access granted, time-boxed, and logged with elevated detail; auto-expires","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-002","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0067","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - Pairwise","Injection payload x input-field pairwise coverage","Pairwise","System","P2","High","Medium","Authenticated user; multiple input surfaces","1. Apply payload classes {SQLi, XSS, LDAPi, CMDi} across fields {name, identifier, note, search} as pairwise set | 2. Submit | 3. Record handling","pairwise matrix of payload x field","Every tested pair is neutralized (encoded/parameterized/rejected); no execution or data leak in any pair","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-008","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0068","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A02 Cryptographic Failures - FHIR transit","FHIR API refuses cleartext and enforces TLS","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","High","FHIR base URL on owned env","1. Attempt http:// FHIR call | 2. Inspect redirect/refusal | 3. Confirm https-only capability statement security","fhir base over http","Cleartext FHIR rejected/redirected; CapabilityStatement.security advertises TLS/OAuth; no PHI over http","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-006","Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy; Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0069","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","HL7 Interface - AuthZ","HL7v2 inbound interface authenticates/authorizes sending app","HL7","Integration","P2","High","High","HL7v2 MLLP listener configured on owned env","1. Send ADT^A01 from an unregistered sending facility | 2. Send from a registered facility | 3. Observe ACK/NAK","MSH sending app=ROGUE vs REGISTERED","Unregistered sender rejected (AR/AE NAK); only registered facilities accepted; rejection logged; no patient created from rogue feed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-027","Standards-HL7; Security; Audit","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0070","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","HL7 Interface - Injection","HL7v2 segment/escape injection does not corrupt parsing","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7v2 inbound processing on owned env","1. Send message with embedded delimiters/escape sequences in PID fields | 2. Send oversized field | 3. Observe parsing and stored data","PID-5 with | ^ ~ \\ & and overlong value","Delimiters/escapes handled safely; no segment injection or field bleed; oversized rejected with NAK; data stored intact","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-027","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity; Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0071","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A05 Misconfiguration - FHIR metadata","Unauthenticated FHIR access limited to metadata only","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR endpoint on owned env","1. GET /fhir2/R4/metadata anonymously (allowed) | 2. GET /fhir2/R4/Patient anonymously (deny) | 3. GET /fhir2/R4/Observation anonymously (deny)","no auth header","CapabilityStatement may be public; all PHI resources require auth; anonymous resource reads denied 401","Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-015","Standards-FHIR; Security; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0072","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - Token storage","Bearer tokens not cached/exposed in browser storage or history","Security","System","P3","Medium","Medium","SMART app session in browser","1. Inspect localStorage/sessionStorage for raw long-lived tokens | 2. Inspect browser history/URLs for tokens | 3. Check cache headers on token responses","token responses","Tokens not persisted insecurely; token endpoints Cache-Control: no-store; no tokens in URL/history","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-018","Security","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0073","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A04 Insecure Design - Rate of consent","Consent state gates data sharing/export operations","Decision Table","System","P2","High","High","Patient consent flags configured (share, research, export)","1. With consent=denied attempt export/share (deny) | 2. With consent=granted attempt (allow) | 3. Revoke consent then attempt (deny) | 4. Verify audit","consent: denied/granted/revoked","Operations strictly follow current consent state; revocation immediately blocks; each decision audited; fail-closed on unknown","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-012","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0074","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - Location scope","User restricted to a location cannot access other location's patients","Negative","System","P2","High","High","User assigned to Location L1; patient belongs to Location L2","1. Authenticate as L1 user | 2. Search/open an L2-only patient | 3. Attempt via REST with explicit location filter override","L1 user; patient at L2","L2 patient not accessible to L1 user; location-based scoping enforced server-side; override attempt denied and logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-002","PHI/Privacy; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0075","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A03 Injection - XXE","XML/FHIR XML parsing blocks external entity (XXE) injection","API","Integration","P2","High","High","Endpoint accepting XML (FHIR XML or HL7 CDA) on owned env","1. POST XML with external entity referencing file:///etc/passwd | 2. POST with billion-laughs entity expansion | 3. Observe","XML DOCTYPE with SYSTEM entity; nested entity bomb","External entities not resolved; no local file disclosure; entity expansion limited; parser hardened (DTD disabled)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-010","Security; Standards-FHIR","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0076","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A05 Misconfiguration - Verbose API","API does not over-return fields (excessive data exposure)","API","System","P2","High","Medium","Authenticated user with limited need-to-know","1. Request a patient resource | 2. Inspect returned fields for unnecessary sensitive data | 3. Compare default vs custom representation","representation=default vs full","Default representation limits sensitive fields; no internal-only fields (audit metadata, internal ids beyond uuid) over-exposed; least disclosure","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-015","PHI/Privacy; Security; API","OpenMRS"
"TC-SECDEEP-0077","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A07 Auth Failures - Concurrent sessions","Concurrent session policy and remote session revocation","State Transition","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Policy for concurrent sessions configured; same account on two devices","1. Login on device A and device B | 2. Apply policy (limit or list) | 3. Revoke device A session centrally | 4. Act on device A","account on A and B","Policy enforced (limit or visibility); revoked session immediately invalid; user can terminate remote sessions; events audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-016","Security; Audit","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0078","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A08 Integrity - Provenance","FHIR Provenance/AuditEvent recorded for create/update of clinical data","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR write enabled; Provenance/AuditEvent supported on owned env","1. Create an Observation via FHIR | 2. Update it | 3. Query Provenance/AuditEvent for the resource | 4. Verify actor and target","Observation create+update","Provenance/AuditEvent generated capturing actor, action, timestamp and target version; supports integrity and traceability","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-020","Standards-FHIR; Audit; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0079","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A02 Cryptographic Failures - Key rotation","Encryption key and secret rotation supported without data loss","Functional","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Key management/rotation procedure on owned env","1. Review key rotation procedure for at-rest keys and signing keys | 2. Rotate a signing key (JWKS) | 3. Verify old tokens validate during overlap then expire | 4. Verify data still readable","JWKS kid old/new","Rotation supported with overlap window; old kid honored until expiry then retired; at-rest data re-keyed without loss; documented","Manual-Only","REQ-SECDEEP-007","Security; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0080","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A09 Logging - Clock/timezone","Audit timestamps are accurate, synchronized and timezone-consistent","Exploratory","System","P3","Low","Medium","NTP-synchronized hosts; audit enabled","1. Perform actions across hosts | 2. Compare audit timestamps and timezone handling | 3. Check for drift | 4. Verify UTC storage","actions on host1 and host2","Timestamps synchronized (NTP), stored in UTC/with offset, consistent across components; no drift undermining audit ordering","Manual-Only","REQ-SECDEEP-022","Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-SECDEEP-0081","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A01 Broken Access Control - GraphQL/batch","Batch/bundle request enforces per-entry authorization","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","High","FHIR transaction bundle supported on owned env","1. Submit a transaction bundle mixing authorized and unauthorized resource ops | 2. Observe per-entry handling | 3. Verify no partial unauthorized success","bundle: read P1 (ok) + read P2 (unauthorized)","Each bundle entry independently authorized; unauthorized entries fail; no bypass of per-resource checks via batching","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-001","Standards-FHIR; Security; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-SECDEEP-0082","Security (OWASP deep, design-only)","A05 Misconfiguration - Pairwise","Header/cookie hardening pairwise across endpoint x context","Pairwise","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Endpoints {UI page, REST, FHIR} x contexts {anon, auth}","1. For each pairwise combination inspect security headers and cookie flags | 2. Record presence/correctness | 3. Compare to baseline","pairs: UI-anon, REST-auth, FHIR-anon","All tested endpoint/context pairs carry correct security headers and cookie flags; no pair missing hardening","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SECDEEP-014","Security","Standards"
"TC-A11Y2-0001","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.1.1 Alt Text","Patient photo on dashboard exposes meaningful text alternative","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged-in clinician; patient with an uploaded photo on the dashboard","1. Open the patient dashboard for a patient with a photo | 2. Inspect the patient image element with a screen reader and DOM inspector | 3. Read the accessible name announced","Patient=SYNTH-A11Y-001; Photo=present","Image exposes a non-empty alt attribute conveying purpose (e.g. patient name/identity), not the file name or empty alt; screen reader announces it","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-001","Accessibility; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0002","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.1.1 Alt Text","Decorative iconography is hidden from assistive technology","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged-in user on any list view containing decorative icons","1. Open a screen with decorative-only icons (e.g. spacer/separator glyphs) | 2. Inspect each decorative icon node | 3. Verify it is hidden from AT","Screen=Patient dashboard widgets","Decorative icons use empty alt='' or aria-hidden=true and are not announced by screen readers","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-001","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0003","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.1.1 Alt Text","Informational status icon conveys state via text not color/shape alone","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Order list with icons representing active/completed/cancelled states","1. Open the orders list showing status icons | 2. Inspect each status icon's accessible name | 3. Cross-check icon state against announced text","States=Active,Completed,Cancelled,Discontinued","Each status icon exposes a text alternative matching its state; no state is conveyed by icon shape/color only","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-001","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0004","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.1.1 Alt Text","Chart/graph image provides equivalent data text alternative","Accessibility","System","P2","High","Medium","Patient with vitals trend graph rendered as image/canvas","1. Open the vitals graph widget | 2. Inspect the graph container for text alternative or adjacent data table | 3. Verify equivalent information is available to AT","Vitals=BP trend over 6 visits","Graph exposes a text alternative or an accessible data table conveying the same trend information","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-001","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0005","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.1.1 Alt Text","Negative: image button with no accessible name fails","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Any toolbar with image-only buttons","1. Identify image-only action buttons (e.g. print, export) | 2. Inspect each for alt/aria-label/title | 3. Flag any with empty accessible name","Buttons=Print,Export,Delete","Defect raised if any image-only control has no accessible name; control is unusable to screen reader users","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-001","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0006","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.1.1 Alt Text","CAPTCHA or barcode image offers text/audio alternative","Accessibility","System","P3","Medium","Low","A screen presenting a non-text challenge or scannable code","1. Open a screen presenting a barcode/QR or challenge image | 2. Inspect for descriptive text alternative | 3. Confirm purpose is conveyed without forcing visual recognition","Element=Patient ID barcode","Non-text content has a text alternative describing its purpose; no security info leaked beyond intended use","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-001","Accessibility; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0007","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.3.1 Info & Relationships","Registration form fields are programmatically associated with labels","Accessibility","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Registration form open","1. Open patient registration form | 2. For each input inspect for/id or aria-labelledby association | 3. Verify clicking label focuses the field","Fields=Given,Family,Gender,DOB","Every input has a programmatically associated label; label click moves focus to its control","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-002","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0008","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.3.1 Info & Relationships","Data table uses proper header cells and scope","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A clinical data table (e.g. encounters list) is displayed","1. Open a tabular list view | 2. Inspect that column/row headers use th with scope | 3. Navigate the table with a screen reader by cell","Table=Recent encounters","Headers use th with correct scope (col/row); screen reader announces row/column headers per cell","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-002","Accessibility; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0009","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.3.1 Info & Relationships","Required fields are conveyed programmatically not only visually","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Form with required fields marked with asterisk","1. Inspect required fields for aria-required or required attribute | 2. Verify the required state is announced | 3. Confirm asterisk meaning is also in text","Fields=Given*,Family*,Gender*","Required state is exposed via aria-required/required; not conveyed by red asterisk color alone","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-002","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0010","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.3.1 Info & Relationships","Grouped radio/checkbox controls use fieldset/legend or group role","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Form containing a grouped choice (e.g. Gender radios)","1. Inspect grouped controls for fieldset/legend or role=group with label | 2. Navigate with screen reader | 3. Verify group purpose is announced","Group=Gender (M/F/Other/Unknown)","Radio/checkbox group is wrapped in fieldset/legend or labeled group; the group purpose is announced once","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-002","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0011","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.3.1 Info & Relationships","Heading structure is hierarchical with no skipped levels","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Patient dashboard loaded","1. Extract heading outline (h1..h6) of the page | 2. Verify a single h1 and logical nesting | 3. Flag any skipped heading levels","Page=Patient dashboard","Headings form a logical hierarchy; no level is skipped (e.g. h2 to h4) and exactly one h1 exists","Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-002","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0012","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.3.1 Info & Relationships","Reading/DOM order matches visual order for multi-column layout","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","A multi-column dashboard layout","1. Disable CSS positioning or read DOM source order | 2. Compare to visual reading order | 3. Verify meaning is preserved","Layout=Two-column dashboard","DOM order yields a meaningful sequence matching the intended visual reading order","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-002","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0013","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.3 Contrast","Body text meets 4.5:1 contrast against background","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Any text-heavy page loaded","1. Sample primary body text foreground/background colors | 2. Compute contrast ratio | 3. Compare against 4.5:1 threshold","Text=Encounter notes body; FG/BG sampled","Normal text contrast ratio is at least 4.5:1; boundary values just below fail","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0014","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.3 Contrast","Large text meets 3:1 contrast threshold","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Page with large headings (>=18.66px bold or >=24px)","1. Identify large-text elements | 2. Sample colors and compute ratio | 3. Compare against 3:1 threshold","Heading=Section title 24px","Large text contrast ratio is at least 3:1; values below the boundary are flagged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0015","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.3 Contrast","Placeholder-as-label text meets contrast and persistence","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Form using placeholder text in inputs","1. Sample placeholder text contrast | 2. Verify ratio meets 4.5:1 | 3. Confirm placeholder is not the only label","Field=Search placeholder","Placeholder text meets 4.5:1 and is not relied upon as the sole label; defect if low contrast","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0016","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.3 Contrast","Disabled and error text contrast evaluated across states","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Form supporting normal/disabled/error states","1. Capture text colors in normal, disabled, and error states | 2. Compute contrast per state | 3. Apply pass/fail per WCAG (disabled exempt, error not)","States=Normal,Disabled,Error","Error and normal text meet 4.5:1; disabled controls are exempt but evaluated and documented","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0017","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.10 Reflow","Content reflows at 320 CSS px without horizontal scroll","Accessibility","System","P2","High","Medium","Patient dashboard accessible in a resizable browser","1. Set viewport to 320 CSS px width (or 400% zoom at 1280px) | 2. Load the dashboard | 3. Scan for two-dimensional scrolling","Viewport=320px width","Content reflows to single column; no horizontal scrolling required except for data tables/maps exceptions","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-004","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0018","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.10 Reflow","Wide data table allows scrolling exception without content loss","Boundary","System","P3","Medium","Medium","A wide data table is shown at narrow viewport","1. Reduce viewport to 320px with a wide table present | 2. Verify table allows horizontal scroll as permitted exception | 3. Confirm no other content is lost or clipped","Table=Lab results matrix","Wide table may scroll horizontally as an allowed exception; surrounding content reflows without loss","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-004","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0019","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.10 Reflow","Sticky header/footer does not obscure content at 400% zoom","Negative","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Page with sticky header at high zoom","1. Zoom to 400% | 2. Scroll through content | 3. Verify sticky elements do not hide form fields or actions","Zoom=400%","Sticky elements do not permanently obscure interactive content; all fields remain reachable","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-004","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0020","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.11 Non-text Contrast","Form input borders meet 3:1 against adjacent colors","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Form with bordered inputs","1. Sample input border color vs adjacent background | 2. Compute contrast | 3. Compare against 3:1","Field=Text input default border","Input boundaries have at least 3:1 contrast so field extent is perceivable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-005","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0021","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.11 Non-text Contrast","Focus indicator color meets 3:1 non-text contrast","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Keyboard focus visible on controls","1. Tab to a control | 2. Sample focus indicator vs unfocused/background | 3. Compute contrast against 3:1","Control=Primary button","Focus indicator has at least 3:1 contrast against adjacent colors","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-005","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0022","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.11 Non-text Contrast","Toggle/checkbox graphical state meets 3:1 contrast","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Controls with on/off graphical states","1. Capture checkbox/toggle in checked and unchecked states | 2. Sample the indicator graphics | 3. Verify each state meets 3:1","States=Checked,Unchecked,Indeterminate","Graphical control states meet 3:1 so checked/unchecked is distinguishable without relying on color","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-005","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0023","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.11 Non-text Contrast","Chart series rely on more than color and meet contrast","Negative","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Multi-series clinical chart displayed","1. Inspect chart series differentiation | 2. Verify patterns/labels beyond color | 3. Sample series-vs-background contrast","Chart=Multi-series vitals","Series are distinguishable by pattern/label not color alone, and meaningful graphics meet 3:1","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-005","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0024","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.1.1 Keyboard","Full registration flow operable by keyboard only","Functional","E2E","P1","Critical","High","Registration accessible to logged-in registrar","1. Navigate to registration using keyboard only | 2. Complete all fields via Tab/typing/arrow keys | 3. Submit the form using keyboard","Registrar account; synthetic patient","Entire flow is completable with keyboard only; no step requires a pointer","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-006","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0025","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.1.1 Keyboard","Custom dropdown/autocomplete operable via keyboard","Functional","Regression","P2","High","High","A typeahead control (e.g. concept search) present","1. Focus the autocomplete with Tab | 2. Type to filter and use arrow keys to navigate options | 3. Select with Enter and dismiss with Escape","Control=Concept search","Options open, navigate, select, and dismiss using keyboard alone with correct value committed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-006","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0026","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.1.1 Keyboard","Negative: no keyboard trap in modal or widget","Negative","Regression","P1","Critical","High","A modal dialog can be opened","1. Open a modal with keyboard | 2. Tab through all elements | 3. Verify focus can leave via Tab/Shift+Tab/Escape without trapping","Modal=Confirm dialog","Focus is never trapped; user can move out of the component using standard keys","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0027","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.1.1 Keyboard","Drag-only interactions provide keyboard alternative","Negative","System","P3","Medium","Medium","A UI with drag-reorder or slider","1. Identify any drag-based interaction | 2. Attempt the same operation via keyboard | 3. Verify an equivalent keyboard path exists","Control=Reorderable list / slider","Drag operations have keyboard-operable equivalents; defect if action is pointer-only","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0028","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.1.1 Keyboard","Date picker fully operable by keyboard","Pairwise","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A date field with a calendar popup","1. Focus the date field | 2. Open the picker via keyboard | 3. Navigate months/days with arrows and select with Enter across browser/OS pairs","Pairs=Chrome/Win,Firefox/Linux,Safari/Mac","Date can be entered and selected by keyboard across tested browser/OS pairings","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0029","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.4.3 Focus Order","Tab order follows logical sequence on registration form","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Registration form open","1. Place focus at top of form | 2. Press Tab repeatedly recording focus order | 3. Compare order to visual/logical sequence","Form=Registration","Focus moves in a logical, meaningful order that preserves operability and meaning","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-007","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0030","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.4.3 Focus Order","Modal open moves focus into dialog and restores on close","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","High","A modal triggered from a button","1. Activate the trigger | 2. Verify focus moves into the modal | 3. Close the modal and verify focus returns to the trigger","Modal=Edit demographics","On open focus enters dialog; on close focus returns to the invoking control","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-007","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0031","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.4.3 Focus Order","Negative: positive tabindex values do not disrupt order","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Page audited for tabindex usage","1. Scan DOM for tabindex>0 | 2. Tab through page | 3. Verify no jarring jumps caused by manual tabindex","Attribute=tabindex","No tabindex>0 disrupts natural order; sequence remains logical","Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-007","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0032","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.4.3 Focus Order","Skip-to-content link is first focusable and functional","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Any page with primary navigation","1. Load page and press Tab once | 2. Verify a skip link receives focus | 3. Activate it and confirm focus jumps to main content","Link=Skip to content","Skip link is the first focusable element and moves focus to main content when activated","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-007","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0033","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.4.7 Focus Visible","Visible focus indicator present on all interactive controls","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Page with links, buttons, and inputs","1. Tab through each interactive control | 2. Observe focus indicator presence | 3. Flag any control with no visible focus","Controls=Links,Buttons,Inputs","Every focusable control shows a clearly visible focus indicator; none rely on default removal","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-008","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0034","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.4.7 Focus Visible","Negative: outline:none without replacement is a defect","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","CSS audit for focus suppression","1. Search styles for outline:none | 2. Tab to affected controls | 3. Verify a replacement focus style exists","CSS=outline:none usages","Any outline removal is paired with a visible alternative; otherwise defect raised","Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-008","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0035","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.4.7 Focus Visible","Focus visible on custom widget options during navigation","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","A listbox/menu widget present","1. Open the widget | 2. Arrow through options | 3. Verify the active option shows a visible focus/selection state at each step","Widget=Concept listbox","Active option is visibly indicated at every navigation step; focus never disappears","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-008","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0036","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 3.3.1 Error Identification","Validation errors identify the field and describe the problem in text","Negative","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Registration form open","1. Submit form with a missing required field | 2. Observe error messaging | 3. Verify error identifies field and describes the issue in text","Leave Family name blank","Error is identified in text, names the field, and is programmatically associated; not color-only","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-009","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0037","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 3.3.1 Error Identification","Invalid date format produces a specific actionable error","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Form with a date field","1. Enter an invalid/boundary date (e.g. 31/02/2026 or future DOB) | 2. Submit | 3. Read the error text and association","DOB=31/02/2026; DOB=2099-01-01","Specific error explains the constraint and is tied to the date field via aria-describedby","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-009","Accessibility; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0038","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 3.3.1 Error Identification","Error summary links navigate to offending fields","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Form returning multiple errors","1. Submit form with multiple errors | 2. Verify an error summary lists each error | 3. Activate a summary link and confirm focus moves to the field","Errors=Given,Gender missing","Summary lists all errors; activating a link moves focus to the corresponding field","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-009","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0039","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 3.3.1 Error Identification","Negative: error conveyed by red border only fails","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Form with color-based error styling","1. Trigger a validation error | 2. View under grayscale/simulated color blindness | 3. Verify a text error exists beyond color","Filter=Grayscale","Error remains identifiable without color; defect if only a red border indicates the error","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-009","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0040","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 3.3.2 Labels & Instructions","All inputs have visible labels or accessible names","Accessibility","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Any data entry form open","1. Inspect each input for a visible label or accessible name | 2. Verify instructions for formatted fields | 3. Flag any unlabeled input","Form=Vitals entry","Every input has a persistent visible label or accessible name and any required format instruction","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-010","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0041","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 3.3.2 Labels & Instructions","Format hints provided before input is needed","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Form field with specific format requirement","1. Locate a field needing a format (e.g. phone, identifier) | 2. Verify hint text is present before entry | 3. Confirm hint is associated to the field","Field=Phone (format hint)","Format instruction is shown before/at the field and programmatically associated via aria-describedby","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-010","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0042","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 3.3.2 Labels & Instructions","Label persists when value entered (no disappearing placeholder label)","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Form using floating/placeholder labels","1. Focus a field that uses placeholder as label | 2. Type a value | 3. Verify the label remains visible/accessible","Field=Search","Label remains perceivable after entry; placeholder-only labels that vanish are a defect","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-010","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0043","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.2 Name/Role/Value","Custom toggle exposes correct role and state to AT","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","High","A custom toggle/switch control present","1. Inspect the control for role (switch/checkbox) | 2. Toggle it | 3. Verify name, role, and aria-checked/pressed update","Control=Active/Inactive switch","Control exposes correct role, accessible name, and current value/state that updates on change","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-011","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0044","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.2 Name/Role/Value","Custom combobox exposes ARIA combobox pattern correctly","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","High","A custom autocomplete/combobox present","1. Inspect for role=combobox, aria-expanded, aria-controls, aria-activedescendant | 2. Open/close and select | 3. Verify states update per interaction","Control=Concept combobox","Combobox roles and states (expanded/collapsed, active option) update correctly across interactions","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-011","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0045","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.2 Name/Role/Value","Modal dialog exposes role=dialog with accessible name","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A modal dialog can be opened","1. Open the modal | 2. Inspect for role=dialog/alertdialog and aria-modal | 3. Verify aria-labelledby provides the title","Modal=Edit demographics","Dialog has role=dialog, aria-modal, and an accessible name from its title","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-011","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0046","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.2 Name/Role/Value","Negative: div-based button lacks role and keyboard semantics","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","UI containing clickable div/span acting as button","1. Identify clickable non-semantic elements | 2. Inspect role and tabindex | 3. Attempt keyboard activation","Element=div onclick handler","Defect if clickable element lacks button role, name, focusability, and Enter/Space activation","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-011","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0047","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.2 Name/Role/Value","Progress/loading control exposes accessible value","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","A long-running action with progress UI","1. Trigger an action with progress indicator | 2. Inspect role=progressbar and aria-valuenow/min/max | 3. Verify values update as progress changes","Action=Bulk export","Progress control exposes role and current/min/max values that update through the lifecycle","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-011","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0048","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.3 Status Messages","Save confirmation announced via live region without focus change","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","High","Editable form that shows a success toast","1. Submit a valid change | 2. Listen with screen reader | 3. Verify the success message is announced via aria-live without moving focus","Action=Save vitals","Success status is announced via role=status/aria-live polite without stealing focus","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-012","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0049","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.3 Status Messages","Error alert announced assertively","Negative","Regression","P2","High","High","Form that can produce a submission error","1. Trigger a submit error (e.g. server validation) | 2. Listen with screen reader | 3. Verify the error is announced assertively via role=alert","Action=Save with conflict","Critical error is announced immediately via role=alert/aria-live assertive","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-012","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0050","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.3 Status Messages","Search result count change announced to AT","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","A live-filtering search present","1. Perform a search that updates result count | 2. Listen for an announcement | 3. Verify the result count is conveyed via live region","Search=Patient name filter","Updated result count is announced via a polite live region without requiring focus move","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-012","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0051","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.3 Status Messages","Negative: status conveyed only by visual toast not announced","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A toast/notification system","1. Trigger a status toast | 2. Verify presence of aria-live container | 3. Confirm AT announces it","Toast=Saved successfully","Defect if visual-only toast has no live region and is silent to screen reader users","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-012","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0052","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.2 Name/Role/Value","FHIR-driven status flags surface accessible state in UI","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","UI rendering a FHIR resource status (e.g. Condition.clinicalStatus)","1. Load a resource with a coded status | 2. Inspect the rendered status control/text | 3. Verify role/value and text alternative reflect the code","Resource=Condition clinicalStatus=active","Coded FHIR status renders with an accessible name/value matching the code, not color-only","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-011","Accessibility; Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-A11Y2-0053","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.1.1 Alt Text","FHIR Media/DocumentReference rendering exposes alternative text","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","UI displaying a FHIR Media or DocumentReference attachment","1. Render an attachment with title/contentType | 2. Inspect the displayed element accessible name | 3. Verify title is used as alt where image","Resource=Media.content.title","Attachment title populates the accessible name; missing title is flagged as a defect","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-001","Accessibility; Standards-FHIR","Standards"
"TC-A11Y2-0054","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 3.3.1 Error Identification","FHIR OperationOutcome diagnostics surfaced as accessible error","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Client surfaces FHIR validation errors to the user","1. Submit a request returning OperationOutcome with issue.diagnostics | 2. Verify the diagnostics text is shown | 3. Confirm it is announced via role=alert","OperationOutcome issue.severity=error","OperationOutcome diagnostics are rendered as accessible, announced error text linked to context","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-009","Accessibility; Standards-FHIR; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-A11Y2-0055","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.3.1 Info & Relationships","HL7-sourced result table preserves header relationships","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Lab results imported via HL7 ORU rendered in a table","1. Render results parsed from an ORU^R01 message | 2. Inspect table headers and units columns | 3. Verify th/scope relationships are intact","Message=ORU^R01 OBX segments","HL7-derived result grid uses proper header cells so screen readers announce test/unit/value relationships","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-002","Accessibility; Standards-HL7; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-A11Y2-0056","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.2 Name/Role/Value","Accessibility tree snapshot validated via DOM/AT API","Database","System","P3","Medium","Low","Test harness can read the accessibility tree","1. Capture accessibility tree for a form | 2. Compare names/roles/values to expected baseline | 3. Diff against stored snapshot","Snapshot=Registration a11y tree","Accessibility tree matches the approved baseline; regressions in name/role/value are detected","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-011","Accessibility; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-A11Y2-0057","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.3 Status Messages","Platform notification center messages exposed to AT","Functional","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Portable platform notification widget present","1. Generate a notification | 2. Open the notification center | 3. Verify items have accessible names and unread state is conveyed non-visually","Platform=omiiCARE notifications","Notifications expose accessible names and unread/read state via text/ARIA, not color alone","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-012","Accessibility; Standards-FHIR","Platform"
"TC-A11Y2-0058","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.1.1 Keyboard","Telemedicine call controls operable by keyboard","Functional","System","P2","High","High","A telehealth session UI is available","1. Join a session via keyboard | 2. Tab to mute/camera/end controls | 3. Operate each via keyboard","Platform=Telehealth controls","Mute, camera, and end-call controls are reachable and operable by keyboard with accessible names","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-006","Accessibility; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-A11Y2-0059","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.3 Contrast","Theme variants evaluated for contrast across light/dark/high-contrast","Pairwise","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Application supports multiple themes","1. Switch among light, dark, and high-contrast themes | 2. Sample key text/control colors per theme | 3. Verify each combination meets thresholds","Themes=Light,Dark,HighContrast","All supported theme combinations meet contrast thresholds; failing pairs are documented","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-003","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-A11Y2-0060","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.2 Name/Role/Value","Security: ARIA does not leak PHI to AT beyond visible content","Security","Regression","P2","High","High","Forms with aria-label/aria-describedby on PHI fields","1. Inspect ARIA attributes on PHI-bearing controls | 2. Verify no extra PHI is embedded beyond what is visible | 3. Confirm masked fields are not exposed in accessible name","Field=SSN (masked)","Accessible names/descriptions do not expose masked or hidden PHI beyond intended visible content","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-013","Accessibility; PHI/Privacy; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0061","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 4.1.2 Name/Role/Value","API: rendered control reflects coded value from REST response","API","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Client renders controls from OpenMRS REST data","1. Fetch a resource via REST that drives a control's value | 2. Render the control | 3. Verify accessible value matches the API value","Endpoint=/ws/rest patient","Control accessible value matches the coded value returned by the API; mismatches flagged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-A11Y2-011","Accessibility; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0062","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 2.4.3 Focus Order","Pairwise focus order across browser and screen reader combinations","Pairwise","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Multiple browser/AT combinations available","1. Tab through a key form in each browser/AT pair | 2. Record focus order | 3. Compare consistency across pairs","Pairs=Chrome/NVDA,Firefox/Orca,Safari/VoiceOver","Focus order remains logical and consistent across tested browser and screen reader pairings","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-007","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0063","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 1.4.10 Reflow","Exploratory reflow stress across nested modals and tables at 320px","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Complex screen with nested modal and table","1. Open a modal containing a table at 320px | 2. Explore scrolling and overflow | 3. Probe for clipped content or lost actions","Viewport=320px; nested modal","No essential content or action is lost; only permitted table scrolling occurs; issues logged","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-004","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-A11Y2-0064","Accessibility (per WCAG 2.1 AA SC)","SC 3.3.2 Labels & Instructions","Usability: clinician completes labeled allergy entry under screen reader","Usability","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Screen reader user with clinician role; allergy form","1. Navigate to allergy entry with screen reader | 2. Complete coded allergen, reaction, severity via labels | 3. Save and confirm announcement","Allergen=synthetic; Severity=Mild","Clinician completes the labeled form entirely via AT and receives an announced save confirmation","Manual-Only","REQ-A11Y2-010","Accessibility; Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF2-0001","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Page SLO p95","Validate patient dashboard render p95 under nominal load","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Owned perf environment with production-like data set (>=250k patients); load tool (JMeter/k6) configured; APM (e.g. New Relic/Grafana) capturing percentiles","1. Warm caches with a 5-min ramp | 2. Drive 50 concurrent virtual users opening the patient dashboard | 3. Sustain steady state for 15 min | 4. Capture server-side and end-to-end latency percentiles","VUs=50; Think time=5s; Target=patientDashboard.page; Steady=15min","p50<=800ms AND p95<=2000ms AND p99<=3500ms for dashboard render; no errors; results recorded in APM","Automatable","REQ-PERF2-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF2-0002","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Page SLO p99","Validate login page p99 latency budget is not exceeded under load","Boundary","System","P1","High","High","Owned perf environment; auth service reachable; percentile capture enabled","1. Ramp to 100 concurrent login attempts over 2 min | 2. Sustain for 10 min | 3. Record p50/p95/p99 for the authenticate call | 4. Compare against SLO budget","VUs=100; Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/session; Steady=10min","p99 for authenticate <=1500ms; p95<=900ms; no auth timeouts; lockout logic unaffected","Automatable","REQ-PERF2-001","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF2-0003","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","API SLO","Measure REST patient search API latency percentiles at volume","API","System","P1","High","High","Owned env with >=250k patients indexed; REST API token; percentile capture","1. Issue patient search GET with common surname query | 2. Drive 75 req/s for 10 min | 3. Capture latency distribution | 4. Verify result count stability","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/patient?q=Smith&limit=10; Rate=75rps","p95<=1200ms AND p99<=2500ms; result set deterministic; no 5xx; no connection pool exhaustion","Automatable","REQ-PERF2-002","PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
