"TC-PERF2-0047","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Audit Write Overhead","Audit logging overhead under PHI-access load","Security","System","P2","High","High","Owned env; audit/PHI access logging enabled; load tool","1. Run PHI-access heavy load with audit on | 2. Repeat with audit off (lab only) | 3. Compare latency and throughput | 4. Verify no audit entries dropped","Workload=PHI read; Audit=on/off","Audit overhead quantified and acceptable (e.g. <10% latency add); zero audit entries dropped under load; audit writes durable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF2-020","Audit; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-PERF2-0048","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Accessibility Under Load","Assistive-tech responsiveness during high server load","Accessibility","System","P3","Medium","Low","Owned env; screen reader (NVDA/VoiceOver) test station; ability to apply backend load","1. Apply heavy backend load | 2. Navigate key clinical screens with screen reader | 3. Measure focus/announcement timing | 4. Verify no missing live-region updates","Load=peak; AT=NVDA; Screens=chart/orders","Under load, focus order and ARIA live announcements remain timely; no spinner traps; status updates announced; WCAG operability holds","Manual-Only","REQ-PERF2-021","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-PERF2-0049","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Security Under Load","Auth/rate-limit controls must hold under load (no bypass)","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Owned env; rate limiting + authz configured; load tool","1. Drive heavy authenticated + unauthenticated mixed load | 2. Attempt authz-protected calls without rights at high rate | 3. Verify rate limits and authz still enforced | 4. Check for race-condition bypass","Mixed auth/unauth; authz-violating calls at rate","No authz bypass under load; rate limiting enforced consistently; no TOCTOU bypass; 401/403 returned reliably","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF2-022","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Platform"
"TC-PERF2-0050","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Exploratory Hotspot","Exploratory profiling to discover unknown performance hotspots","Exploratory","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Owned env; profiler/flame-graph tooling; representative load","1. Run representative load with continuous profiler | 2. Capture flame graphs and DB hot queries | 3. Explore top CPU/IO consumers | 4. Log unexpected hotspots and hypotheses","Profiler=async-profiler; Load=mixed","At least 3 prioritized hotspots identified with evidence; each given a remediation hypothesis; no critical finding left unlogged","Manual-Only","REQ-PERF2-023","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PERF2-0051","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Cold Start","Cold-start / post-restart latency and warm-up time","State Transition","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Owned env; ability to restart app node; warm-up metrics","1. Restart application node | 2. Immediately drive nominal load | 3. Measure latency from cold to warm | 4. Time until p95 reaches steady SLO","Action=restart; Load=nominal immediately after","Cold-start latency bounded; system transitions Cold->Warming->Steady; p95 reaches SLO within agreed warm-up window; no errors during warm-up","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF2-024","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PERF2-0052","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Rolling Deploy","Zero-downtime during rolling deploy under load","State Transition","System","P1","High","High","Owned env multi-node; rolling deploy pipeline; steady load","1. Apply steady clinical load | 2. Execute rolling deploy node-by-node | 3. Monitor error rate and latency during cutover | 4. Verify in-flight requests drained","Nodes=N; Deploy=rolling; Load=steady","No error spike beyond threshold during deploy; in-flight requests drained, not killed; latency stays within SLO; zero failed clinical transactions","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF2-025","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PERF2-0053","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Throttling Decision Table","Per-tenant/per-user throttling decision table","Decision Table","System","P2","High","Medium","Owned env; throttling policy by tenant/user/endpoint configurable","1. Enumerate tenant-tier x endpoint-class x rate combinations | 2. Drive each past its limit | 3. Record throttle response | 4. Build table","Tier{free,std,premium} x Endpoint{read,write,report}","Each cell throttles at its configured limit; 429 with Retry-After returned; clinical-critical endpoints not over-throttled; table complete","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF2-026","Security; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-PERF2-0054","Performance & Load (criteria, deep)","Bulk Import Load","Bulk patient/data import throughput without interactive impact","Database","System","P2","High","High","Owned env; bulk import tool; off-peak and on-peak windows","1. Run a large bulk import (e.g. 100k records) | 2. Measure import throughput and DB load | 3. Run once isolated, once with interactive load | 4. Compare interactive p95","Records=100k; Modes=isolated/with-interactive","Import throughput documented; with interactive load running, clinical p95 stays within SLO (import throttled/batched); no lock contention stalls","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PERF2-027","Data Integrity; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-MOBILE-0001","Responsive / Mobile Web","Breakpoints","Verify layout reflow at the 768px tablet breakpoint boundary","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","RefApp home page reachable; browser devtools available","1. Open the home page at viewport width 769px | 2. Note multi-column app tile layout | 3. Resize viewport to exactly 768px | 4. Resize to 767px | 5. Compare layouts at each step","Widths=769,768,767 px","At >=768px the desktop/tablet grid renders; at <768px the layout collapses to the mobile single/stacked column without overlap or clipping at the boundary","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-001","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0002","Responsive / Mobile Web","Breakpoints","Validate app tile grid columns across standard device widths","Pairwise","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","RefApp home page reachable","1. Load home page at 320px | 2. Reload at 375px | 3. Reload at 414px | 4. Reload at 768px | 5. Reload at 1024px | 6. Record column count and tile wrapping at each width","Widths=320,375,414,768,1024 px","Tile columns increase monotonically with width; tiles never overflow the viewport; no half-clipped tile at any tested width","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-001","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0003","Responsive / Mobile Web","Breakpoints","Verify extreme narrow viewport (280px) does not break core navigation","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in user on home page","1. Set viewport to 280px (Galaxy Fold cover) | 2. Load home page | 3. Attempt to open the main menu | 4. Tap a primary app tile","Width=280 px","Content remains readable and tappable; menu opens; navigation succeeds without horizontal scroll or content cutoff","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-001","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0004","Responsive / Mobile Web","No Horizontal Scroll","Confirm no horizontal scrollbar on patient dashboard at 360px","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Patient with active visit exists; clinician logged in","1. Open patient dashboard at 360px width | 2. Scroll vertically end to end | 3. Attempt horizontal swipe/drag | 4. Inspect document.scrollWidth vs window.innerWidth","Width=360 px; Patient=SYN-PT-1001","No horizontal scroll occurs; scrollWidth <= innerWidth; all dashboard widgets fit within the viewport","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-002","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0005","Responsive / Mobile Web","No Horizontal Scroll","Detect horizontal overflow caused by long unbroken patient identifier","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Patient with a long identifier/name exists","1. Open patient header at 360px for a patient with a 40-char identifier | 2. Observe header rendering | 3. Check for horizontal scroll","Width=360 px; Identifier=ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789ABCD","Long identifier wraps or truncates with ellipsis; no horizontal scroll is introduced by the long token","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-002","Data Integrity; Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0006","Responsive / Mobile Web","No Horizontal Scroll","Wide data table degrades gracefully on mobile","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patient with many encounters/obs exists","1. Open an encounter list/obs table at 375px | 2. Observe table rendering | 3. Attempt to view all columns","Width=375 px","Table either becomes horizontally scrollable within its own container (not the page) or stacks into cards; the page body itself has no horizontal scroll","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-002","Clinical; Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0007","Responsive / Mobile Web","Collapsible Navbar","Verify navbar collapses into hamburger menu below breakpoint","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in user; RefApp navbar present","1. Load any page at 1200px and confirm expanded nav links | 2. Resize to 600px | 3. Observe the navbar | 4. Confirm a hamburger/toggle control appears","Widths=1200,600 px","Above breakpoint nav links are inline; below breakpoint links collapse into a hamburger toggle control that is visible and tappable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0008","Responsive / Mobile Web","Collapsible Navbar","Toggle collapsible navbar open and closed (state transition)","State Transition","Regression","P1","High","High","Page loaded at 480px with hamburger visible","1. Observe collapsed state (menu hidden) | 2. Tap hamburger -> menu expands | 3. Tap hamburger again -> menu collapses | 4. Tap a menu item -> navigation occurs and menu collapses","Width=480 px","States transition Collapsed->Expanded->Collapsed correctly; selecting an item navigates and auto-collapses the menu","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0009","Responsive / Mobile Web","Collapsible Navbar","Navbar menu closes when tapping outside the menu","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Hamburger menu expanded at mobile width","1. Open the hamburger menu | 2. Tap on the page area outside the menu | 3. Observe menu state","Width=414 px","Tapping outside collapses the open menu; no orphaned/half-open menu state remains","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0010","Responsive / Mobile Web","Collapsible Navbar","Keyboard accessibility of collapsed navbar toggle","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile width; external keyboard or tab navigation available","1. Tab to the hamburger toggle | 2. Activate with Enter and Space | 3. Tab into the expanded menu items | 4. Activate a menu item with Enter","Width=480 px","Toggle is focusable and operable via Enter/Space; aria-expanded reflects open/closed; menu items are reachable and operable by keyboard","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0011","Responsive / Mobile Web","Collapsible Navbar","Screen reader announces navbar toggle state","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile width; screen reader (VoiceOver/TalkBack) active","1. Focus the hamburger toggle with screen reader | 2. Listen to the announced role and state | 3. Expand the menu | 4. Listen to updated state announcement","Width=414 px","Toggle is announced as a button with expandable state; aria-expanded toggles true/false and is announced on change","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-003","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0012","Responsive / Mobile Web","Touch Targets","Verify primary action buttons meet 44x44 CSS px minimum touch target","Accessibility","Regression","P1","High","High","Mobile width; patient dashboard with action buttons","1. Open dashboard at 375px | 2. Measure computed hit area of Save/Start Visit/primary buttons | 3. Compare against 44x44 CSS px","Width=375 px; Target>=44x44 CSS px","All primary interactive controls have a touch target of at least 44x44 CSS px (WCAG 2.5.5 / Apple HIG)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-004","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0013","Responsive / Mobile Web","Touch Targets","Boundary check of adjacent touch targets spacing","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile width; list with closely packed row actions","1. Open a list with edit/delete row icons at 360px | 2. Measure spacing between adjacent targets | 3. Tap each repeatedly to check mis-taps","Width=360 px; Min spacing>=8px","Adjacent targets have adequate spacing (>=8px) so repeated taps hit the intended control without accidental activation of neighbors","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-004","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0014","Responsive / Mobile Web","Touch Targets","Negative: tiny icon-only control fails minimum target size","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Mobile width; page containing small icon controls","1. Identify icon-only controls (close X, info) at 375px | 2. Measure hit area | 3. Flag any below 44x44 CSS px","Width=375 px","Any control below 44x44 CSS px is reported as a defect; test fails if such controls exist on primary clinical flows","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-004","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0015","Responsive / Mobile Web","Orientation","Layout adapts correctly on portrait to landscape rotation","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile device/emulator; patient dashboard open","1. Open dashboard in portrait | 2. Rotate device to landscape | 3. Observe reflow | 4. Rotate back to portrait","Device=375x667 <-> 667x375","Layout reflows on rotation without content loss, overlap, or horizontal scroll; scroll position and entered form data are preserved","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-005","Accessibility; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0016","Responsive / Mobile Web","Orientation","Form in-progress data persists across orientation change","State Transition","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Clinician entering a clinical form on mobile","1. Begin entering a vitals/clinical form in portrait | 2. Fill several fields | 3. Rotate to landscape mid-entry | 4. Verify entered values remain","Form=Vitals; Pulse=72; Temp=37.0","All entered field values persist after rotation; no field is reset or lost; focus does not jump unexpectedly","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-005","Patient Safety; Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0017","Responsive / Mobile Web","Orientation","Landscape on small-height device keeps action bar reachable","Boundary","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Small device in landscape (e.g., 667x375)","1. Open a long clinical form in landscape | 2. Scroll to bottom | 3. Locate Save/Cancel actions","Device=667x375","Action bar is reachable (sticky or scrollable into view); the on-screen keyboard does not permanently hide the submit action","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-005","Patient Safety; Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0018","Responsive / Mobile Web","Viewport Meta","Verify viewport meta tag is present and correctly configured","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","Access to page HTML source","1. Load the app on mobile | 2. View page source | 3. Inspect the meta name=viewport tag content","Expected: width=device-width, initial-scale=1","A viewport meta tag exists with width=device-width and initial-scale=1 so the page renders at device width rather than a zoomed-out desktop layout","Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0019","Responsive / Mobile Web","Viewport Meta","Negative: pinch-zoom must not be disabled (no user-scalable=no)","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Access to page HTML source; mobile device","1. Inspect viewport meta tag | 2. Check for user-scalable=no or maximum-scale=1 | 3. On device, attempt pinch-zoom on text","Expected: pinch-zoom allowed","Viewport meta does not disable user scaling; users can pinch-zoom content to at least 200% (WCAG 1.4.4); test fails if user-scalable=no is present","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-006","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0020","Responsive / Mobile Web","Forms on Small Screens","Login form usable and fully visible at 320px","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logout state; mobile width 320px","1. Open login page at 320px | 2. Confirm username, password, login fields visible | 3. Enter credentials | 4. Submit","Width=320 px; User=syn_clerk; Pass=Valid#123","All login fields and the submit button are visible and usable without horizontal scroll; login succeeds","Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-007","Security; Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0021","Responsive / Mobile Web","Forms on Small Screens","Correct mobile keyboard type for numeric vitals fields","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinician on a vitals form on a real mobile device","1. Open vitals form on mobile | 2. Focus a numeric field (pulse) | 3. Observe the on-screen keyboard | 4. Focus a date/time field","Field=Pulse (numeric)","Numeric fields invoke a numeric keypad (inputmode/type appropriate); date fields invoke a date picker; reduces entry errors on mobile","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-007","Clinical; Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0022","Responsive / Mobile Web","Forms on Small Screens","On-screen keyboard does not obscure the focused input","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile device; long clinical form","1. Focus an input near the bottom of a long form | 2. Observe scroll behavior when keyboard appears | 3. Type a value","Device=375x667","The focused input scrolls into view above the on-screen keyboard and remains visible while typing","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-007","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0023","Responsive / Mobile Web","Forms on Small Screens","Negative: required-field validation visible without horizontal scroll on mobile","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile width; registration/clinical form with required fields","1. Open form at 360px | 2. Submit with required fields empty | 3. Observe validation messages","Width=360 px","Inline validation messages render fully within the viewport, are associated with their fields, and do not cause horizontal scroll or overlap","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-007","Data Integrity; Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0024","Responsive / Mobile Web","Forms on Small Screens","Patient registration multi-section form navigable on mobile","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Registration privilege; mobile width","1. Start patient registration at 375px | 2. Complete demographics section | 3. Advance to contact/address section | 4. Complete and submit","Width=375 px; Name=Syn Test; Gender=F; DOB=1990-01-01","Each form section is navigable, fields are reachable, section navigation works, and the patient is created successfully","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-007","PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0025","Responsive / Mobile Web","Forms on Small Screens","Date of birth / date picker usable on touch screen","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Mobile device; form with a date field","1. Open a form with a DOB field on mobile | 2. Tap the date field | 3. Select a date via the picker | 4. Confirm value","Date=1985-06-15","Date picker opens on tap, supports touch selection, and the selected date is recorded in the expected format","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-007","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0026","Responsive / Mobile Web","Mobile Navigation","Breadcrumb / back navigation works on mobile flows","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in; multi-level navigation available","1. Navigate Home -> Find Patient -> Patient Dashboard on mobile | 2. Use back/breadcrumb to return | 3. Verify each level","Width=414 px","Back/breadcrumb navigation returns to the correct prior context without losing state or producing a broken/blank page","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-008","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0027","Responsive / Mobile Web","Mobile Navigation","Sticky header/action bar remains accessible while scrolling","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Mobile width; long-content page","1. Open a long page at 375px | 2. Scroll down significantly | 3. Observe header/action bar | 4. Trigger a header action","Width=375 px","Sticky elements (header or primary actions) remain reachable while scrolling; they do not overlap or hide content needed for the action","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-008","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0028","Responsive / Mobile Web","Mobile Navigation","Active visit context banner visible and not truncated on mobile","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patient with active visit; clinician logged in","1. Open patient with active visit at 360px | 2. Observe the active visit banner/context | 3. Verify key context (visit type, location, start)","Width=360 px; Patient=SYN-PT-1002","Active visit context is visible and key details are legible (wrapped/truncated gracefully); clinician can identify the visit before charting","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-008","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0029","Responsive / Mobile Web","Performance on Mobile","Home page first contentful paint within target on throttled mobile","Performance","System","P2","High","Medium","Network throttling (Fast 3G) and CPU 4x slowdown configured","1. Clear cache | 2. Throttle to Fast 3G + 4x CPU | 3. Load home page | 4. Record FCP and TTI from devtools/Lighthouse","Throttle=Fast 3G, CPU 4x","FCP is within the agreed mobile budget (e.g., <3s) and the page becomes interactive without long main-thread blocking; record actual values","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-009","Performance","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0030","Responsive / Mobile Web","Performance on Mobile","Mobile bundle/asset transfer size within budget","Performance","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Devtools network tab available","1. Load home page on a cold cache mobile profile | 2. Record total transfer size and number of requests | 3. Identify largest assets","Profile=Mobile cold cache","Total initial transfer size is within the defined performance budget; no single oversized uncompressed asset dominates load","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-009","Performance","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0031","Responsive / Mobile Web","Performance on Mobile","Images served responsively / not oversized for mobile","Performance","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Devtools available; pages with images/logos","1. Load pages with imagery at 375px | 2. Inspect rendered vs intrinsic image dimensions | 3. Check srcset/sizes usage","Width=375 px","Images are not served at dimensions far larger than rendered; responsive image techniques (srcset) or appropriately sized assets are used","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-009","Performance","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0032","Responsive / Mobile Web","Performance on Mobile","Layout stability (no excessive content shift) on mobile load","Performance","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Lighthouse/devtools CLS measurement available","1. Load patient dashboard on mobile profile | 2. Observe content as it loads | 3. Measure Cumulative Layout Shift","Profile=Moto G / Fast 3G","CLS is within acceptable threshold (<0.1); content does not jump such that a tap lands on the wrong control","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-009","Performance; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0033","Responsive / Mobile Web","Accessibility","Text reflows at 320px without loss of content (WCAG 1.4.10)","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile width; content-heavy clinical page","1. Open a content page at 320px CSS width (or 400% zoom on 1280px) | 2. Read all content | 3. Check for two-dimensional scrolling","Width=320 px / 400% zoom","All content and functionality remain available with only vertical scrolling; no information or function is lost (WCAG 1.4.10 Reflow)","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-010","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0034","Responsive / Mobile Web","Accessibility","Text spacing override does not clip content on mobile","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Mobile width; ability to inject text-spacing CSS","1. Apply WCAG 1.4.12 text-spacing overrides at 375px | 2. Review forms and lists | 3. Check for clipped/overlapping text","Width=375 px","With increased line/letter/word/paragraph spacing, no content is clipped or overlapped and all functions remain usable","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-010","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0035","Responsive / Mobile Web","Accessibility","Focus order remains logical in collapsed mobile layout","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile width; keyboard available","1. Tab through the page at 480px | 2. Track focus order through nav, content, actions | 3. Confirm focus visible","Width=480 px","Focus order follows a logical reading sequence in the reflowed layout; focus indicator is visible on every interactive element","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-010","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0036","Responsive / Mobile Web","Accessibility","Color contrast holds for mobile-specific UI elements","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Mobile width; contrast analyzer","1. Inspect hamburger icon, mobile menu items, badges at 375px | 2. Measure contrast ratios | 3. Compare against 4.5:1 (text) / 3:1 (UI)","Width=375 px","Text meets >=4.5:1 and UI/icon components meet >=3:1 contrast in mobile presentation (WCAG 1.4.3 / 1.4.11)","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-010","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0037","Responsive / Mobile Web","Forms on Small Screens","Decision table: form submit state by network and validation on mobile","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile device; clinical form","1. Combine conditions: ValidInput {Y,N} x Online {Y,N} | 2. Attempt submit for each combination | 3. Record outcome","Combos: (Y,Y),(Y,N),(N,Y),(N,N)","(Y,Y)=saved; (Y,N)=blocked or queued with clear offline message; (N,Y)=validation error shown; (N,N)=validation error takes precedence, no data loss","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-007","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0038","Responsive / Mobile Web","Mobile Navigation","Pairwise: navigation entry across device x orientation x auth-role","Pairwise","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Test accounts for clerk and clinician roles","1. Combine Device{phone,tablet} x Orientation{portrait,landscape} x Role{clerk,clinician} | 2. Log in and open primary landing per combo | 3. Verify role-appropriate nav items","Pairwise set of 4-6 combos","For each combination the correct role-scoped navigation renders responsively with no broken layout or missing privileged items","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-008","Security; Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0039","Responsive / Mobile Web","Exploratory","Exploratory: rapid resize stress of patient dashboard","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Patient dashboard open; resizable browser","1. Rapidly resize window between 320px and 1280px repeatedly | 2. Observe for flicker, stuck states, or overlap | 3. Interact mid-resize","Range=320-1280 px","Layout recovers cleanly to the correct breakpoint after rapid resizing; no stuck overlays, orphaned menus, or unclickable regions remain","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-001","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0040","Responsive / Mobile Web","Exploratory","Exploratory: interrupt mobile form entry with incoming call / app switch","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Real mobile device; clinical form in progress","1. Begin entering a clinical form | 2. Switch to another app / simulate call | 3. Return to the browser after delay | 4. Inspect form state","Device=physical phone","On returning, the form session and entered data are preserved (or the user is clearly warned of session expiry); no silent data loss","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-005","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0041","Responsive / Mobile Web","Security","Session timeout warning is visible and actionable on mobile","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Configured idle session timeout; mobile width","1. Log in on mobile and remain idle near timeout | 2. Observe the timeout/warning UI at 375px | 3. Attempt to extend session","Width=375 px; Idle near timeout","Timeout warning renders fully within the mobile viewport and its extend/continue action is tappable; session security is enforced","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-011","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0042","Responsive / Mobile Web","Security","Sensitive fields are masked and not autofilled insecurely on mobile","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Login/credential form on mobile","1. Open login on mobile | 2. Confirm password field masks input | 3. Check autocomplete handling for credentials | 4. Verify no PHI cached in URL","Width=375 px","Password input is masked; credential autocomplete behaves per policy; no PHI/credentials are exposed in query strings or visible plaintext","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-011","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0043","Responsive / Mobile Web","Security","Negative: deep link to patient on mobile enforces authentication","Negative","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Valid patient dashboard URL captured; unauthenticated mobile session","1. Open a direct patient dashboard URL on mobile while logged out | 2. Observe behavior","URL=/patientDashboard?patientId=SYN-PT-1001","Unauthenticated access is blocked and redirected to login; no PHI is rendered before authentication regardless of mobile layout","Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-011","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0044","Responsive / Mobile Web","API","REST API returns same patient data regardless of mobile client","API","Integration","P2","Medium","Low","Valid API session token","1. Call GET patient resource via REST from a mobile user-agent | 2. Call the same endpoint from desktop UA | 3. Compare payloads","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/patient/{uuid}","API response content is identical across user agents; responsiveness is purely client-side; no server-side data divergence by device","Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-012","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0045","Responsive / Mobile Web","FHIR","FHIR Patient read consumed by mobile client renders correctly","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Low","FHIR module enabled; valid token","1. GET Patient/{id} from the FHIR R4 endpoint | 2. Render key fields (name, gender, birthDate, identifier) in the mobile view | 3. Verify mapping","Endpoint=/ws/fhir2/R4/Patient/{id}","FHIR Patient resource fields map correctly to the mobile UI; name/gender/birthDate/identifier display accurately and fit the mobile layout","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-013","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0046","Responsive / Mobile Web","FHIR","FHIR Bundle pagination usable within mobile list view","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","FHIR endpoint with paginated results","1. Request a searchset Bundle (e.g., Observation) with _count | 2. Render first page in a mobile list | 3. Follow next link | 4. Verify continuity","Endpoint=/ws/fhir2/R4/Observation?_count=10","Each Bundle page renders within the mobile viewport without horizontal scroll; next/prev links work and no records are duplicated or skipped","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-013","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-MOBILE-0047","Responsive / Mobile Web","HL7","HL7 ADT-driven patient appears correctly in mobile patient search","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","HL7 inbound interface configured (Platform); ADT^A04 feed","1. Send a synthetic ADT^A04 registration message | 2. Wait for ingestion | 3. Search the patient in the mobile UI | 4. Verify demographics","Msg=ADT^A04; Name=SYN^TEST; MRN=SYN9001","The HL7-registered patient is findable in mobile search and demographics match the message; mobile presentation is correct and complete","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-014","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-MOBILE-0048","Responsive / Mobile Web","Database","Audit log records mobile-originated PHI access","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Audit/logging enabled; DB read access","1. Access a patient record from a mobile session | 2. Query the audit/log store for the access event | 3. Verify user, patient, timestamp, and access type","Patient=SYN-PT-1001","An audit record is persisted for the mobile PHI access with correct actor, target, action, and timestamp; mobile access is not exempt from auditing","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-015","Audit; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0049","Responsive / Mobile Web","Breakpoints","Decision table: layout mode by viewport width band","Decision Table","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Home page reachable","1. For width bands <576, 576-767, 768-991, >=992 load the page | 2. Record layout mode | 3. Verify expected columns/nav per band","Bands: xs,sm,md,lg","Each width band maps to its expected layout mode (mobile stacked / tablet / desktop) consistently per the design grid with no unexpected jumps","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-001","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0050","Responsive / Mobile Web","Touch Targets","Swipe/scroll gesture does not accidentally trigger destructive action","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Mobile device; list with swipeable/row actions","1. On a list at 375px perform vertical scroll over rows with delete actions | 2. Perform horizontal swipe near a delete icon | 3. Observe outcomes","Width=375 px","Normal scrolling never triggers a destructive action; any swipe-to-delete requires confirmation; no accidental data deletion occurs","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-004","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-MOBILE-0051","Responsive / Mobile Web","Forms on Small Screens","Long picklist / concept search usable on small screen","Usability","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinical form with a searchable concept/coded field on mobile","1. Open a coded field (e.g., diagnosis) at 375px | 2. Type to search | 3. Scroll the result list | 4. Select an item","Width=375 px; Search=Hypertension","The search dropdown fits the viewport, is scrollable, results are tappable, and the selected concept is captured correctly","Partially-Automatable","REQ-MOBILE-007","Clinical; Accessibility","OpenMRS"
