"TC-MOBILE-0053","Responsive / Mobile Web","Performance on Mobile","State transition: offline to online while using mobile web app","State Transition","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Mobile device; app loaded; network toggle available","1. Use the app online | 2. Disable network | 3. Attempt an action | 4. Re-enable network | 5. Retry the action","Network toggle on/off","Offline state shows a clear non-blocking message; on reconnect, normal operation resumes and no duplicate/lost submissions occur","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-009","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-MOBILE-0054","Responsive / Mobile Web","Accessibility","Touch target and reflow validated on RTL locale at mobile width","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","RTL locale configured (if supported); mobile width","1. Switch UI to an RTL locale | 2. Load home and a form at 375px | 3. Verify mirrored layout, reflow, and touch targets","Width=375 px; Locale=ar","RTL layout mirrors correctly, reflows without horizontal scroll, and touch targets/menus remain usable; no clipped or misaligned controls","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-010","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-MOBILE-0055","Responsive / Mobile Web","Security","Negative: screenshot/clipboard of PHI handled per policy on mobile","Security","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Mobile device; PHI displayed; org policy defined","1. Display a patient record on mobile | 2. Attempt to copy PHI to clipboard | 3. Observe any policy controls or warnings","Patient=SYN-PT-1001","Clipboard/screenshot handling aligns with the documented policy (warned or restricted where required); no unexpected PHI leakage path is enabled by the mobile UI","Manual-Only","REQ-MOBILE-011","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
