"TC-COMPAT-0023","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Timezone","Verify FHIR resource instant fields carry timezone offset across clients","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR API access; OAuth token","1. GET Observation via FHIR R4 from client A | 2. Inspect effectiveDateTime offset | 3. GET same from client B different TZ | 4. Compare instant value","Endpoint=/ws/fhir2/R4/Observation; Header=Accept: application/fhir+json","FHIR instant/dateTime fields include correct timezone offset; identical absolute instant regardless of client TZ","Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-012","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-COMPAT-0024","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Cookie & Session","Verify session cookie attributes Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite across browsers","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","HTTPS environment; clinician account; devtools access","1. Log in via Chrome | 2. Inspect session cookie attributes in devtools | 3. Repeat in Firefox and Edge | 4. Verify Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite present","Browser=Chrome,Firefox,Edge; URL=https","Session cookie has Secure, HttpOnly and appropriate SameSite in all browsers; not readable by JS; not sent over HTTP","Partially-Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-013","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0025","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Cookie & Session","Verify session persistence across browser tab and window in same browser","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinician account","1. Log in tab 1 | 2. Open app in tab 2 same browser | 3. Verify shared session | 4. Log out tab 1 | 5. Refresh tab 2","Browser=Chrome; Tabs=2","Session shared across tabs; logout in one tab invalidates session in other on next request; consistent state transition","Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-014","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0026","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Cookie & Session","Verify session isolation between normal and private/incognito window","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Clinician account; second account","1. Log in as user A in normal window | 2. Open incognito window | 3. Log in as user B | 4. Verify sessions isolated | 5. Confirm no cookie leakage","Browser=Chrome incognito; UserA, UserB","Sessions fully isolated; user B context never reflects user A; no PHI cross-contamination between contexts","Partially-Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-013","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
