"TC-COMPAT-0038","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Rendering Engine","Verify CSS Grid/Flexbox layout parity Blink vs Gecko vs WebKit","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinician account; pixel-diff tooling","1. Capture dashboard screenshot in Chrome (Blink) | 2. Capture in Firefox (Gecko) | 3. Capture in Safari (WebKit) | 4. Pixel-diff key components","Engines=Blink,Gecko,WebKit","Layout parity within tolerance across engines; no engine-specific grid/flex collapse; differences only in expected font rendering","Partially-Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-019","Data Integrity; Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0039","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Rendering Engine","Verify date/time input control behavior differs gracefully across engines","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinician account; form with date input","1. Open native HTML date input in Chrome | 2. Open in Firefox | 3. Open in Safari (WebKit historically limited) | 4. Verify valid entry in each","Field=DOB; Engines=Blink,Gecko,WebKit","Date entry succeeds in all engines via native or polyfill control; invalid input rejected; no engine left without usable picker","Partially-Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-019","Clinical; Usability","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0040","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","JS Compatibility","Verify no unhandled console errors across browser matrix on critical pages","Negative","Regression","P1","High","Medium","Clinician account; devtools access","1. Open login, dashboard, registration, form pages | 2. Monitor console in Chrome | 3. Repeat across Firefox, Edge, Safari | 4. Log any errors","Pages=login,dashboard,registration,form","No uncaught JS exceptions or 404 asset errors in console on any browser; warnings triaged; critical paths clean","Partially-Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-020","Data Integrity; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0041","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","JS Compatibility","Verify graceful degradation when JavaScript is disabled","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Browser with JS disabled","1. Disable JavaScript | 2. Load application | 3. Observe behavior | 4. Verify informative noscript message","Browser=Firefox; Setting=JS disabled","Application shows a clear noscript notice requiring JavaScript; no blank page or silent failure; no PHI leak in static HTML","Manual-Only","REQ-COMPAT-020","Security; Usability","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0042","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Network & Caching","Verify static asset caching headers consistent across browsers","API","Integration","P3","Low","Low","Devtools network access","1. Load app fresh in Chrome | 2. Inspect cache-control/etag on assets | 3. Reload and verify 304s | 4. Repeat in Firefox","Browsers=Chrome,Firefox","Cache headers honored consistently; cacheable assets return 304 on revalidation; no stale PHI cached inappropriately","Partially-Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-021","Security; Performance","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0043","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Network & Caching","Verify back/forward cache (bfcache) does not expose stale PHI after logout","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Clinician account; patient with PHI","1. Open patient PHI page | 2. Log out | 3. Press browser Back | 4. Verify PHI not shown from bfcache | 5. Repeat across browsers","Browsers=Chrome,Firefox,Safari","Back after logout does not render cached PHI; page forces re-auth or shows blocked state; no PHI exposure via bfcache","Partially-Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-022","PHI/Privacy; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0044","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","FHIR Client","Verify FHIR API content negotiation across HTTP clients/browsers","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR API enabled; OAuth token","1. Request Patient with Accept application/fhir+json | 2. Request with application/json | 3. Request XML if supported | 4. Verify correct content-type response","Endpoint=/ws/fhir2/R4/Patient; Accept variants","Server honors content negotiation; returns valid FHIR R4 resource with matching content-type; consistent across client tools","Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-012","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-COMPAT-0045","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","SMART on FHIR","Verify SMART app launch in embedded iframe across browsers (cookie/storage)","Security","Integration","P2","High","High","SMART on FHIR app registered; clinician account","1. Launch SMART app in EHR context in Chrome | 2. Verify OAuth handshake and token | 3. Repeat in Safari (ITP storage partitioning) | 4. Confirm app loads","App=SMART sample; Browsers=Chrome,Safari","SMART app launches and authorizes in all browsers; storage partitioning/ITP does not break token exchange; scopes enforced","Manual-Only","REQ-COMPAT-023","Standards-FHIR; Security; PHI/Privacy","Standards"
"TC-COMPAT-0046","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","HL7 Interop","Verify HL7 v2 message ingestion unaffected by client browser/OS","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","HL7 interface engine endpoint; integration account","1. Send HL7 v2 ADT message from integration client on Windows | 2. Send equivalent from Linux client | 3. Verify patient updated identically | 4. Check encoding (MSH-18)","Message=ADT^A01; Encoding=UTF-8; OS=Windows,Linux","HL7 ingestion is client-OS independent; character encoding per MSH-18 preserved; resulting record identical regardless of source OS","Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-024","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-COMPAT-0047","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Database Consistency","Verify data written via one browser is consistent when read via another","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Clinician account; two browsers; DB read access","1. Create encounter with obs in Chrome | 2. Query backing record via API/DB | 3. Read same encounter in Firefox UI | 4. Compare values","Browsers=Chrome,Firefox; Encounter=vitals","Persisted data identical regardless of authoring browser; no browser-introduced encoding or rounding differences; referential integrity intact","Partially-Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-025","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0048","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Print & Media","Verify print stylesheet renders patient summary correctly across browsers","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Clinician account; patient with data","1. Open patient summary | 2. Invoke print preview in Chrome | 3. Repeat in Firefox, Edge, Safari | 4. Verify print layout, page breaks, no nav chrome","Browsers=Chrome,Firefox,Edge,Safari; Media=print","Print preview applies print stylesheet; PHI legible; nav/buttons hidden; clean page breaks; consistent across browsers","Manual-Only","REQ-COMPAT-026","Clinical; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-COMPAT-0049","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Platform Portability","Verify Resource Adapter Layer maps fields identically when SUT swapped to OpenEMR/HAPI","Pairwise","System","P2","High","Medium","Resource Adapter Layer configured; OpenEMR/HAPI FHIR targets available","1. Run patient read via adapter against OpenMRS | 2. Against HAPI FHIR | 3. Against OpenEMR | 4. Compare normalized field mapping output","Targets=OpenMRS,HAPI FHIR,OpenEMR; Resource=Patient","Adapter normalizes equivalent fields across target systems; no field drops or mismaps; portability contract upheld","Partially-Automatable","REQ-COMPAT-027","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-COMPAT-0050","Cross-Browser & Compatibility","Accessibility AT","Verify screen reader announces dashboard landmarks across browser/AT pairs","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Screen reader installed; clinician account","1. Navigate dashboard with NVDA+Firefox | 2. With JAWS+Chrome | 3. With VoiceOver+Safari | 4. Verify landmark and heading announcements","Pairs=NVDA-Firefox; JAWS-Chrome; VoiceOver-Safari","Landmarks, headings and controls announced consistently across AT/browser pairs; meets WCAG 4.1.2 name/role/value","Manual-Only","REQ-COMPAT-028","Accessibility; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-USAB-0001","Usability & UX","Consistency","Verify primary action button label and placement are consistent across registration, encounter and order forms","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged-in clinician with access to registration, clinical form and order entry","1. Open patient registration form and note the save/submit control label and position | 2. Open a clinical encounter form and note the save control | 3. Open an order entry form and note the save control | 4. Compare label wording, casing and screen position across all three","Forms=Registration, Vitals encounter, Drug order","Primary save control uses consistent label wording, casing, color and bottom-right (or consistent) placement across all three forms; no synonyms like Save vs Submit vs Confirm for the same action","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0002","Usability & UX","Consistency","Verify date format is rendered consistently across dashboard, encounters list and reports","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Patient with multiple encounters and at least one report available","1. Open patient dashboard and note date format of recent encounters | 2. Open the visits/encounters list and note date format | 3. Open a report containing dates and note format | 4. Compare formats for order, separators and locale","Locale=en; Patient with >=3 encounters","All surfaces render dates in the same locale-aware format (order, separator, 12/24h); no mixed dd/mm vs mm/dd within the same locale","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0003","Usability & UX","Consistency","Verify terminology for the same concept is identical across navigation, page title and breadcrumb","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Any navigable module page available","1. Navigate to a module via the main menu and note the menu label | 2. Observe the page heading/title on the loaded page | 3. Observe the breadcrumb trail entry for that page | 4. Compare all three labels","Module=Patient Dashboard","Menu label, page title and breadcrumb use the same canonical term for the module; no drift such as Visits vs Encounters vs Consultations for one concept","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0004","Usability & UX","Error Prevention","Verify confirmation prompt appears before deleting a saved encounter (destructive action)","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Clinician with a saved encounter and delete permission","1. Open a patient with a saved encounter | 2. Choose to delete/void the encounter | 3. Observe the interstitial confirmation | 4. Cancel and verify encounter persists | 5. Confirm and verify encounter is voided","Encounter=Vitals; Action=Void","A confirmation dialog with clear consequence text and an explicit reason field appears before voiding; Cancel preserves the encounter; Confirm voids it and records who/when/why","Automatable","REQ-USAB-002","Patient Safety; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0005","Usability & UX","Error Prevention","Verify destructive confirmation requires a void reason and rejects empty reason","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Clinician voiding a clinical record requiring a reason","1. Initiate void of an observation or encounter | 2. Leave the reason field blank | 3. Attempt to confirm | 4. Observe validation | 5. Enter a valid reason and confirm","Reason='' then Reason='Entered in error'","With blank reason the confirm is blocked and an inline message requests a reason; with a valid reason the void completes and the reason is stored in audit","Automatable","REQ-USAB-002","Patient Safety; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0006","Usability & UX","Error Prevention","Verify unsaved-changes guard warns before navigating away from a partially completed form","State Transition","System","P2","High","High","Clinician with a clinical form partially filled and not saved","1. Open a clinical form and enter data in several fields | 2. Without saving, click a navigation link or browser back | 3. Observe the leave-confirmation prompt | 4. Choose Stay and verify data intact | 5. Repeat and choose Leave","Form=Vitals; Pulse=80 entered, not saved","A leave-confirmation warns that unsaved changes will be lost; Stay returns to the form with all entered data intact; Leave discards and navigates away","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-003","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0007","Usability & UX","Error Prevention","Verify decision-table behavior for save/cancel/navigate combinations on a dirty form","Decision Table","System","P2","High","Medium","Clinician on a clinical form","1. For each row apply the form state and user action | 2. Observe whether a guard prompt appears and the final state | 3. Verify data retention matches expected","Rules: Clean+Navigate=no prompt,leave; Dirty+Navigate=prompt; Dirty+Save=no prompt,persist; Dirty+Cancel=prompt then discard; Clean+Cancel=close no prompt","Each combination matches the decision table: prompts appear only when the form is dirty and the action loses data; clean states navigate without interruption; saved data persists","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-003","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0008","Usability & UX","Error Prevention","Verify duplicate-submission protection when clinician double-clicks Save on an order","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Clinician submitting a drug order","1. Fill a drug order form | 2. Rapidly double-click the Save control | 3. Observe the network and resulting orders | 4. Check the orders list for duplicates","Order=Paracetamol 500mg; double-click within 300ms","Only one order is created; the control disables or debounces after first click and shows a progress state; no duplicate order appears in the list","Automatable","REQ-USAB-004","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0009","Usability & UX","Error Recovery","Verify form repopulates entered data after a server-side validation error","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Clinician submitting a form that triggers server validation failure","1. Fill a registration form including several fields | 2. Enter one value that fails server validation | 3. Submit | 4. Observe the returned form","Field with invalid value=Phone 'abc'; other fields valid","Server rejects submission but all previously entered valid fields remain populated; only the offending field is flagged; no full re-entry required","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-005","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0010","Usability & UX","Error Recovery","Verify graceful recovery and retry when a save fails due to transient network error","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","Clinician saving a clinical form with simulated network interruption","1. Fill a clinical form | 2. Simulate a network drop and attempt to save | 3. Observe the error state | 4. Restore network and use the offered retry | 5. Verify single save","Form=Vitals; Network=offline then online","A clear, non-technical error is shown with a retry option; entered data is preserved; retry succeeds and creates exactly one record without duplication","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-005","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0011","Usability & UX","Helpful Messages","Verify validation messages are specific, actionable and field-anchored","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinician on registration with multiple required fields","1. Submit the registration form with several invalid/empty fields | 2. Observe each validation message | 3. Verify message text names the field and the correction needed | 4. Verify focus moves to the first error","Given name='' ; DOB future date; Phone='12'","Each message is specific (names field and rule, e.g. 'Date of birth cannot be in the future'), appears adjacent to its field, and focus lands on the first invalid field","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-006","Data Integrity; Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0012","Usability & UX","Helpful Messages","Verify system errors avoid raw stack traces and present a user-safe message with reference id","Security","System","P2","High","High","Ability to trigger a server error condition","1. Trigger a server-side error (e.g. malformed request) | 2. Observe the displayed error | 3. Inspect for stack traces, SQL or class names | 4. Note any support reference id","Trigger=invalid encounter payload","User sees a friendly message with a correlation/reference id; no stack trace, SQL, internal class names or server paths are exposed in the UI","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-006","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0013","Usability & UX","Helpful Messages","Verify success confirmation is shown after saving an encounter and auto-dismisses appropriately","Functional","Sanity","P3","Low","Low","Clinician saving a valid encounter","1. Save a valid clinical encounter | 2. Observe the success toast/banner | 3. Verify wording confirms what was saved | 4. Verify it is dismissible and screen-reader announced","Encounter=Vitals saved","A success message confirms the specific action (e.g. 'Vitals encounter saved'), is announced to assistive tech via a live region, and can be dismissed or auto-dismisses without blocking work","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-006","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0014","Usability & UX","Navigation Efficiency","Verify clinician can reach order entry from patient search within a minimal click path","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinician logged in at the home/search screen","1. From home, search a patient | 2. Open the patient | 3. Navigate to order entry | 4. Count clicks and page loads from search result to order form","Patient=Synthetic Test One","Order entry is reachable in a small, predictable number of steps from the patient result with no dead-ends; each step has a clear affordance and the active patient context is preserved","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-007","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0015","Usability & UX","Navigation Efficiency","Verify breadcrumb allows direct return to a prior level without losing patient context","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinician three levels deep within a patient context","1. Navigate patient > dashboard > encounter detail | 2. Click an intermediate breadcrumb level | 3. Verify the prior page loads | 4. Verify the same patient remains active","Patient with encounter detail open","Breadcrumb navigates directly to the chosen ancestor level; the active patient context is retained; no full re-search required","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-007","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0016","Usability & UX","Navigation Efficiency","Verify active patient context banner persists across module navigation","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Clinician with an active patient selected","1. Select an active patient | 2. Navigate across dashboard, orders, results and visits | 3. On each page observe the patient identity banner | 4. Verify name, identifier and key demographics remain visible and correct","Patient=Synthetic Test One; ID=10001","The patient identity banner remains pinned and correct across all modules, preventing wrong-patient actions; switching patients clearly updates the banner everywhere","Automatable","REQ-USAB-007","Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0017","Usability & UX","Navigation Efficiency","Verify back navigation after deep linking returns to a sensible location not a blank state","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","User arrives at a deep-linked encounter URL","1. Open a deep link directly to an encounter detail | 2. Use in-app back/up navigation | 3. Observe destination | 4. Verify no blank or error page results","Deep link to encounter UUID","Back/up navigation lands on a meaningful parent (patient dashboard) rather than a blank page or browser error; context is reconstructed correctly","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-007","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0018","Usability & UX","Learnability","Verify field-level help/tooltips are available for non-obvious clinical inputs","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Clinician on a clinical form with coded fields","1. Open a clinical form containing a coded or specialized field | 2. Hover/focus the help affordance | 3. Read the help text | 4. Verify it explains expected input and units","Field=Temperature unit selector","Help text is available via hover and keyboard focus, explains expected input, units and constraints, and is announced to assistive technology","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-008","Accessibility; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0019","Usability & UX","Learnability","Verify first-time user can complete patient registration using only visible affordances","Exploratory","UAT","P2","Medium","Medium","New clinician account with registration access and no prior training","1. As a first-time user, attempt to register a patient using only on-screen cues | 2. Note any step requiring outside knowledge | 3. Record confusion points and dead-ends | 4. Capture time and error count","Persona=untrained clinician; synthetic patient","User completes registration relying on labels, placeholders and inline help; no step requires undocumented knowledge; confusion points are logged for triage","Manual-Only","REQ-USAB-008","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0020","Usability & UX","Learnability","Verify consistent iconography meaning across modules aids recognition","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Multiple modules using shared icons","1. Identify icons used for edit, delete/void, print and add across modules | 2. Verify each icon has consistent meaning everywhere | 3. Verify each icon has an accessible name/tooltip","Icons=edit, void, print, add","Each icon carries the same meaning across modules and exposes an accessible name; no icon is reused for conflicting actions","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-008","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0021","Usability & UX","Confirmation On Destructive Actions","Verify voiding a patient identifier requires explicit double confirmation","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Admin with permission to void identifiers","1. Open patient identifiers | 2. Choose to void an identifier | 3. Observe primary confirmation | 4. Observe any secondary type-to-confirm or reason requirement | 5. Confirm and verify audit","Identifier=OpenMRS ID; Reason='Duplicate'","Voiding a patient identifier requires explicit confirmation with a reason; the action is audit-logged with actor, timestamp and reason; cancel aborts with no change","Automatable","REQ-USAB-002","Patient Safety; PHI/Privacy; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0022","Usability & UX","Confirmation On Destructive Actions","Verify retiring a concept/metadata shows impact warning before proceeding","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","Admin retiring a concept used by existing forms","1. Open a concept referenced by active forms | 2. Choose retire | 3. Observe whether dependencies/impact are communicated | 4. Confirm and verify retire state","Concept=in-use observation concept","Before retiring, the UI warns the metadata is in use and confirmation is required; after retiring it is marked retired (not hard-deleted) preserving historical data integrity","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-002","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0023","Usability & UX","Confirmation On Destructive Actions","Verify discard-draft confirmation when closing a new order without saving","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinician with a new unsaved order draft","1. Begin a new order and enter details | 2. Click close/cancel without saving | 3. Observe discard confirmation | 4. Choose Keep editing then Discard","Order draft=Amoxicillin","Closing an unsaved order prompts a discard confirmation; Keep editing returns to the draft intact; Discard closes without creating an order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-002","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0024","Usability & UX","Undo","Verify a voided observation can be unvoided restoring original values and audit chain","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Admin/clinician with unvoid permission and a voided observation","1. Void an observation with a reason | 2. Locate the voided record | 3. Perform unvoid | 4. Verify the observation is restored with original values | 5. Verify audit shows void then unvoid","Obs=Pulse 80; Void reason='Error'","Unvoid restores the original observation values; the audit trail retains both void and unvoid events with actor/timestamp; no data is silently lost","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-009","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0025","Usability & UX","Undo","Verify undo window/affordance after a non-destructive bulk action where supported","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","User performs a reversible action that offers undo","1. Perform an action that surfaces an undo affordance (e.g. dismiss a notification or remove a list item) | 2. Invoke undo within the offered window | 3. Verify prior state is restored","Action=remove item from a working list","Undo restores the prior state within the offered window; after the window closes the action is final and any persistence is consistent; clear messaging on undo availability","Manual-Only","REQ-USAB-009","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-USAB-0026","Usability & UX","Keyboard Shortcuts","Verify keyboard-only completion of a clinical form without a mouse","Accessibility","System","P1","High","High","Clinician on a clinical form; keyboard only","1. Using Tab/Shift+Tab navigate all fields in logical order | 2. Enter values using keyboard only | 3. Operate dropdowns and date pickers via keyboard | 4. Submit via keyboard | 5. Verify save","Form=Vitals; keyboard only","All fields are reachable and operable by keyboard in a logical order; dropdowns/date pickers are keyboard-operable; form submits successfully without a mouse","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-010","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0027","Usability & UX","Keyboard Shortcuts","Verify visible focus indicator is present on all interactive controls","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Any page with interactive controls","1. Tab through controls on a representative form and dashboard | 2. Observe focus indicator on each control | 3. Verify contrast of the focus ring | 4. Confirm no focus is lost or hidden","Pages=dashboard, clinical form","Every interactive control shows a clearly visible, sufficient-contrast focus indicator; focus is never invisible or trapped; tab order matches visual order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-010","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0028","Usability & UX","Keyboard Shortcuts","Verify modal dialogs trap focus and restore focus to trigger on close","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A modal (e.g. confirmation dialog) is invokable","1. Open a modal via keyboard | 2. Tab through and verify focus stays within the modal | 3. Press Escape to close | 4. Verify focus returns to the invoking control","Modal=void confirmation","Focus is trapped within the open modal; Escape closes it; on close focus returns to the control that opened it; background is inert","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-010","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-USAB-0029","Usability & UX","Empty States","Verify patient with no encounters shows a helpful empty state with a primary action","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Newly registered patient with no encounters","1. Open a patient with zero encounters | 2. Observe the encounters/visits area | 3. Verify empty-state messaging | 4. Verify a clear next-step action is offered","Patient=freshly registered, no data","An informative empty state explains there are no encounters yet and offers a primary action (e.g. Start a visit) rather than a blank or broken region","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-011","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0030","Usability & UX","Empty States","Verify patient search with no matches shows guidance rather than a blank grid","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Search available; query that matches nothing","1. Search a patient with a query guaranteed to return no results | 2. Observe the result area | 3. Verify no-results messaging and suggestions","Query='zzqx-no-match'","A no-results message is shown with guidance (broaden search, check spelling, register new) instead of a blank or error grid","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-011","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0031","Usability & UX","Empty States","Verify report with no data in range communicates empty range, not failure","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Report module with a date range producing no rows","1. Run a report for a range known to have no data | 2. Observe the output | 3. Verify it distinguishes empty-result from error","Report=Encounters; range=future window","The report clearly states no data for the selected criteria and remains distinct from an error state; filters remain adjustable without reload errors","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-011","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0032","Usability & UX","Loading States","Verify long-running search shows a loading indicator and disables duplicate submission","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Search likely to take noticeable time","1. Initiate a search expected to take time | 2. Observe loading indicator | 3. Attempt to resubmit during load | 4. Verify result rendering","Query=common surname returning many results","A loading indicator is shown during the query; resubmission is prevented or queued sensibly; results render without flicker once loaded","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-012","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0033","Usability & UX","Loading States","Verify skeleton/placeholder prevents layout shift while dashboard widgets load","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Patient dashboard with multiple async widgets","1. Open a patient dashboard | 2. Observe widgets loading | 3. Watch for content jumping/layout shift | 4. Verify final layout stability","Dashboard with vitals, allergies, problems widgets","Loading placeholders reserve space so content does not jump; cumulative layout shift is minimal; each widget resolves to data or its own empty/error state","Manual-Only","REQ-USAB-012","Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0034","Usability & UX","Loading States","Verify slow API response surfaces timeout messaging instead of indefinite spinner","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Ability to simulate a slow/timed-out backend call","1. Trigger a data load with simulated backend delay beyond timeout | 2. Observe behavior past the timeout | 3. Verify messaging and retry | 4. Verify spinner does not hang forever","Backend delay > client timeout","After the timeout a clear message with retry is shown; the spinner does not persist indefinitely; no partial/corrupt data is displayed as complete","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-012","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0035","Usability & UX","Error States","Verify error region is screen-reader announced and programmatically associated with fields","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Form with validation; screen reader active","1. Submit a form with errors using a screen reader | 2. Verify errors are announced | 3. Verify aria-describedby/aria-invalid links message to field | 4. Navigate to first error","Screen reader=NVDA/VoiceOver; invalid fields present","Validation errors are announced via a live region, fields expose aria-invalid, and messages are programmatically associated so assistive tech users can locate and fix them","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-013","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-USAB-0036","Usability & UX","Error States","Verify partial failure in a multi-section save communicates which section failed","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Form with multiple sections where one section can fail server-side","1. Submit a multi-section form where one section fails validation | 2. Observe the error presentation | 3. Verify the failing section is identified | 4. Verify successful sections state","Sections=Demographics OK, Contact invalid","The UI clearly identifies which section failed and why, preserves valid sections, and avoids implying the whole save failed when only one part did","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-013","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0037","Usability & UX","Consistency","Verify locale switch consistently applies to labels, dates and numbers without mixed language","Pairwise","System","P2","Medium","Medium","System supporting multiple locales; user can switch locale","1. For each locale x surface pair, switch locale | 2. Inspect labels, date and number formats | 3. Verify no mixed-language leakage | 4. Verify RTL handling where applicable","Pairs: (es, dashboard),(fr, form),(ar, report),(en, search)","Each locale applies consistently to labels, dates and numbers across surfaces; no untranslated strings leak; RTL locales render with correct direction","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-001","Accessibility","Platform"
"TC-USAB-0038","Usability & UX","Error Prevention","Verify high-risk numeric field warns on out-of-range value before save (soft stop)","Boundary","Regression","P1","High","High","Clinician entering vitals with configured ranges","1. Enter a vitals value just outside a plausible range | 2. Attempt to save | 3. Observe out-of-range warning | 4. Confirm or correct | 5. Repeat at the boundary and just inside","BP systolic=300; then 250; then 249","Out-of-range entries trigger a soft warning prompting confirmation or correction; boundary values behave per configured thresholds; clinician can confirm intentional extremes with an explicit action","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-004","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0039","Usability & UX","Error Prevention","Verify wrong-patient prevention prompt when active patient differs from order target","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Two patients open in workflow; order being placed","1. For each rule set active patient and order target | 2. Place an order | 3. Observe whether a mismatch warning appears | 4. Verify final order target","Rules: same patient=no warn; switched-tab patient=warn; stale-context patient=warn+block","When the order target does not match the displayed active patient, the system warns and requires reconfirmation, preventing wrong-patient orders; matching context proceeds normally","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-004","Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0040","Usability & UX","Helpful Messages","Verify session-timeout warning gives advance notice and preserves work on extend","State Transition","System","P2","High","High","Session timeout configured; user idle on a filled form","1. Fill a form and remain idle until near timeout | 2. Observe pre-timeout warning | 3. Choose Extend session | 4. Verify form data preserved | 5. Let session expire and verify safe handling","Idle to near session limit; form partially filled","A pre-timeout warning appears with a countdown and Extend option; extending preserves entered data; on expiry the user is safely logged out without silently losing unsaved PHI to an unauthenticated state","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-006","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0041","Usability & UX","Accessibility","Verify color is not the sole means of conveying status (alerts, required fields, results)","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Pages using color-coded status (e.g. abnormal results, required fields)","1. Identify color-coded indicators (abnormal result, required field, alert severity) | 2. Verify each has a non-color cue (icon, text, pattern) | 3. Simulate color blindness | 4. Verify distinguishability","Indicators=abnormal flag, required asterisk, alert level","Status is conveyed by text/icon/shape in addition to color; indicators remain distinguishable under color-vision deficiency simulation; meets WCAG use-of-color guidance","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-013","Accessibility; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-USAB-0042","Usability & UX","Accessibility","Verify text reflows and remains usable at 200 percent zoom without loss of content","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Browser zoom configurable; representative pages","1. Set browser zoom to 200 percent | 2. Load a clinical form and dashboard | 3. Verify content reflows without horizontal scrolling loss or clipping | 4. Verify controls remain operable","Zoom=200%; viewport standard","At 200 percent zoom content reflows, no information or controls are lost or clipped, and the workflow remains operable, per WCAG reflow criteria","Manual-Only","REQ-USAB-013","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-USAB-0043","Usability & UX","FHIR","Verify FHIR OperationOutcome errors are surfaced to users as readable, actionable messages","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR API integration returning OperationOutcome on error","1. Trigger a FHIR write that fails (e.g. invalid Patient resource) | 2. Capture the OperationOutcome response | 3. Verify the UI translates issue.diagnostics/severity into a user-readable message | 4. Verify no raw JSON shown to clinician","Invalid Patient.birthDate; Accept=application/fhir+json","FHIR OperationOutcome severity and diagnostics are mapped to a clear, actionable user message; raw resource JSON is not surfaced to clinical users; correlation is logged for support","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-014","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-USAB-0044","Usability & UX","HL7","Verify failed HL7 v2 message ingestion produces an operator-friendly error queue entry","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 v2 inbound interface with an error/dead-letter queue","1. Send a malformed HL7 v2 ADT message | 2. Observe the interface engine/error queue | 3. Verify the failed message is queued with a human-readable reason | 4. Verify reprocess affordance","ADT^A01 with missing required MSH field","The malformed message lands in an error queue with a readable failure reason and segment/field pointer; an operator can review and reprocess; no silent data loss","Manual-Only","REQ-USAB-014","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-USAB-0045","Usability & UX","Database","Verify UI-confirmed void is reflected as a soft-delete (voided flag) not a hard delete in the data store","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Backend/data access available; clinician voids a record via UI","1. Void an observation via the UI with reason | 2. Inspect the underlying record state | 3. Verify voided flag, void reason, voided_by and date_voided are set | 4. Verify row is not physically removed","Obs voided via UI; reason='Entered in error'","The record persists with voided=true and populated void metadata rather than being physically deleted, preserving auditability and supporting later unvoid","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-009","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0046","Usability & UX","Navigation Efficiency","Verify deep-link/bookmark to a patient dashboard prompts login then returns to target","API","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Unauthenticated user; valid deep link to a patient dashboard","1. While logged out, open a bookmarked patient dashboard URL | 2. Observe redirect to login | 3. Authenticate | 4. Verify redirect back to the originally requested patient dashboard","Deep link=patient dashboard URL; valid credentials","Unauthenticated access redirects to login and, after successful auth, returns the user to the originally requested page with the correct patient context, avoiding re-navigation","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-007","Security; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-USAB-0047","Usability & UX","Exploratory","Charter-based exploratory session on alert fatigue and interruptive dialog density in clinical workflow","Exploratory","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Clinician access to ordering, prescribing and documentation flows","1. Charter: explore how many interruptive warnings/confirmations a clinician encounters in a typical order-to-document flow | 2. Record each interruption, its value and dismissibility | 3. Note redundant or low-value prompts | 4. Summarize fatigue risk","Flow=admit, order meds, document, sign","Findings document the count and value of interruptive prompts; low-value or redundant confirmations that risk alert fatigue and reflexive dismissal are identified for tuning while preserving high-value safety stops","Manual-Only","REQ-USAB-015","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-USAB-0048","Usability & UX","Helpful Messages","Verify permission-denied actions show a clear authorization message rather than failing silently","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","User lacking permission for a restricted action","1. As a user without the required privilege, attempt a restricted action (e.g. void encounter) | 2. Observe the response | 3. Verify a clear authorization message | 4. Verify no partial state change","Role=read-only clinician; action=void encounter","The action is blocked with a clear 'you do not have permission' message; no partial change occurs; the attempt is auditable and the control may be hidden/disabled to prevent dead-clicks","Partially-Automatable","REQ-USAB-006","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0001","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Outpatient Journey","Complete outpatient flow register to checkout with single visit context","Functional","E2E","P1","Critical","High","Registration clerk, clinician, lab tech, pharmacist and cashier accounts exist; outpatient location configured","1. Register new patient as clerk | 2. Check in patient and start outpatient visit | 3. Clinician records vitals encounter | 4. Clinician records diagnosis | 5. Clinician orders a lab test | 6. Lab tech enters result | 7. Clinician reviews result and prescribes drug | 8. Pharmacist dispenses | 9. Cashier bills and patient checks out (visit ended)","Patient=Synthetic Jane Doe DOB 1990-01-01; Diagnosis=Malaria; Lab=Malaria smear; Drug=Artemether-Lumefantrine","Single visit threads all encounters; each encounter carries same visit UUID, correct provider, datetime; visit ends at checkout; dashboard reflects full chronology","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-001","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0002","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Outpatient Journey","Check-in blocked when patient has unresolved active visit at another location","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Patient already has an open active visit at Location A","1. Search the patient | 2. Attempt to start a new visit at Location B | 3. Observe system response","Patient with open visit at Outpatient-A; New location=Outpatient-B","System prevents or warns about a second concurrent active visit; clerk is guided to close or transfer the existing visit; no orphan duplicate visit created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-002","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0003","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Outpatient Journey","Vitals-to-diagnosis handoff preserves visit and provider context","Integration","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Active outpatient visit with a recorded vitals encounter exists","1. Open patient with active visit | 2. Confirm vitals encounter present | 3. Start a visit-note/diagnosis encounter | 4. Save diagnosis | 5. Inspect both encounters","Vitals: BP=130/85, Pulse=88; Diagnosis=Hypertension (confirmed)","Both encounters share the same visit; diagnosis encounter records ordering provider; chronology ordered by encounter datetime","Automatable","REQ-E2E2-003","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0004","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Outpatient Journey","Order lab then result then clinician review state transitions","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Active visit; lab order types configured; lab tech account exists","1. Clinician places lab order (state=ORDERED) | 2. Lab receives specimen (state=IN_PROGRESS) | 3. Lab enters result (state=COMPLETED) | 4. Clinician reviews and acknowledges | 5. Attempt illegal transition COMPLETED back to ORDERED","Lab=CBC; Result=WBC 11.2","Order traverses ORDERED to IN_PROGRESS to COMPLETED; review records reviewer and timestamp; illegal backward transition is rejected","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-004","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0005","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Outpatient Journey","Prescribe drug with active allergy triggers interaction alert before dispense","Negative","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Patient has documented penicillin allergy; clinician on active visit","1. Open patient dashboard, confirm allergy listed | 2. Order amoxicillin | 3. Observe allergy alert | 4. Attempt to override without reason | 5. Provide override reason and proceed","Allergy=Penicillin (severe); Drug=Amoxicillin 500mg","Allergy alert is raised before order is finalized; override requires documented reason captured in audit; order not silently saved","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-005","Patient Safety; Clinical; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0006","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Outpatient Journey","Dispense quantity must not exceed prescribed quantity boundary","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Active prescription for 30 tablets exists; pharmacist account","1. Open dispensing queue | 2. Select prescription | 3. Dispense exactly 30 | 4. New prescription 30, attempt dispense 31 | 5. Attempt dispense 0","Prescribed=30 tablets; Dispense values=30, 31, 0","Dispense of 30 succeeds; 31 rejected (exceeds prescribed); 0 rejected (non-positive); remaining balance accurate","Automatable","REQ-E2E2-006","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0007","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Outpatient Journey","Billing aggregates all chargeable items from the visit","Functional","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Visit with consultation, lab order, and dispensed drug; cashier role; billing module enabled","1. End clinical activity | 2. Open billing for the visit | 3. Verify line items | 4. Apply payment | 5. Generate receipt","Items=Consultation, CBC, Drug dispense","Bill contains all chargeable items with correct unit prices and totals; payment recorded; receipt generated with visit reference","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-007","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0008","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Outpatient Journey","Checkout closes visit and finalizes encounter datetimes","State Transition","System","P2","High","Medium","Active visit with multiple encounters; bill settled","1. Confirm visit active | 2. Trigger checkout/end visit | 3. Verify visit stop datetime set | 4. Attempt to add encounter to closed visit","Visit start=09:00; checkout=11:30","Visit transitions ACTIVE to ENDED with stop datetime; adding encounter to ended visit is blocked or requires reopening with audit","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-008","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0009","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Inpatient Journey","Admit patient from outpatient visit and assign ward bed","Functional","E2E","P1","Critical","High","Inpatient program/bed management configured; clinician with admit privilege","1. From active outpatient visit, initiate admission | 2. Select ward and bed | 3. Confirm admission encounter | 4. Verify visit type changes to inpatient | 5. Verify bed marked occupied","Ward=Medical Ward A; Bed=A-12","Admission encounter recorded; visit reflects inpatient context; bed status occupied; patient appears in ward census","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-009","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0010","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Inpatient Journey","Bed double-assignment prevented (concurrency)","Negative","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Bed A-12 available; two clinicians attempting assignment simultaneously","1. Clinician 1 selects bed A-12 | 2. Clinician 2 selects bed A-12 | 3. Both submit near-simultaneously","Bed=A-12; two concurrent admit requests","Only one assignment succeeds; the second receives a conflict/already-occupied error; no two patients share one bed","Manual-Only","REQ-E2E2-010","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0011","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Inpatient Journey","Inpatient medication order with scheduled administration times","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","Admitted patient on ward; drug order types configured","1. Open admitted patient | 2. Order scheduled drug (e.g., q8h) | 3. Verify administration schedule generated | 4. Nurse records one administration | 5. Verify MAR reflects given dose","Drug=Ceftriaxone 1g IV q8h","Order creates schedule; nurse administration recorded against scheduled time; MAR shows given/pending statuses accurately","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-011","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0012","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Inpatient Journey","Ward transfer preserves orders and active visit","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Admitted patient with active orders in Ward A","1. Open patient | 2. Initiate transfer to Ward B | 3. Select new bed | 4. Verify old bed freed and new bed occupied | 5. Verify active orders persist","From=Ward A bed A-12; To=Ward B bed B-03","Transfer encounter recorded; old bed released, new bed occupied; active orders remain active under same visit","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-012","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0013","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Inpatient Journey","Discharge requires resolution of active orders and bed release","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Admitted patient with one active drug order and an open lab order","1. Initiate discharge with active orders present | 2. Observe discharge gating | 3. Discontinue/complete active orders | 4. Complete discharge | 5. Verify bed released","Active drug order + open lab order","Discharge gated while critical orders open (or warns per config); after resolution discharge completes; bed released; discharge encounter recorded","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-013","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0014","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Inpatient Journey","Discharge summary generated with diagnoses and discharge meds","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","Patient ready for discharge with diagnoses and continuing meds","1. Open discharge workflow | 2. Generate discharge summary | 3. Verify diagnoses included | 4. Verify discharge medications listed | 5. Finalize and lock summary","Diagnosis=Community-acquired pneumonia; Discharge med=Amoxicillin 7 days","Discharge summary contains diagnoses, discharge meds, follow-up; finalized summary is immutable/audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-014","Clinical; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0015","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Inpatient Journey","Length-of-stay boundary at same-day admit and discharge","Boundary","System","P3","Medium","Low","Patient admitted and discharged same calendar day","1. Admit at 08:00 | 2. Discharge at 14:00 same day | 3. Inspect LOS computation","Admit 2026-07-01 08:00; Discharge 2026-07-01 14:00","LOS computed correctly (e.g., 0 days or 1 day per business rule), no negative or null LOS","Automatable","REQ-E2E2-015","Data Integrity; Billing","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0016","End-to-End Patient Journeys","ER Triage Journey","ER triage assigns acuity level and routes to treatment","Functional","E2E","P1","Critical","High","Emergency location configured; triage nurse and ER clinician accounts","1. Register/quick-register arriving patient | 2. Start emergency visit | 3. Record triage vitals and acuity | 4. Route to ER clinician queue | 5. Clinician opens and treats","Acuity=ESI Level 2; Complaint=Chest pain","Triage encounter records acuity; patient appears in ER queue ordered by acuity; clinician can open and treat under same visit","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-016","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0017","End-to-End Patient Journeys","ER Triage Journey","Triage queue ordering by acuity then arrival time","Decision Table","System","P2","High","Medium","Multiple ER patients with varying acuity and arrival times","1. Triage patient X ESI-3 at 09:00 | 2. Triage patient Y ESI-1 at 09:05 | 3. Triage patient Z ESI-3 at 08:55 | 4. View ER queue order","X ESI3 09:00; Y ESI1 09:05; Z ESI3 08:55","Queue order: Y (ESI1) first, then Z (ESI3 earlier), then X; acuity dominates, arrival breaks ties","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-017","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0018","End-to-End Patient Journeys","ER Triage Journey","Unidentified emergency patient registered with John/Jane Doe placeholder","Functional","System","P2","High","Medium","Unconscious unidentified patient arriving; emergency registration enabled","1. Quick-register without full demographics | 2. System assigns temporary identifier | 3. Start emergency visit | 4. Later merge/update with real identity","Name=Unknown Male; DOB=estimated","Temporary identity created with unique placeholder ID; care proceeds; later identity reconciliation merges records without data loss","Manual-Only","REQ-E2E2-018","Patient Safety; PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0019","End-to-End Patient Journeys","ER Triage Journey","ER to inpatient admission conversion within same visit","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","Medium","ER patient treated, decision to admit made","1. Treat ER patient | 2. Initiate admit from ER | 3. Assign ward bed | 4. Verify visit continuity","ER complaint=Acute abdomen; Ward=Surgical","Visit continues uninterrupted; admission encounter added; ER and inpatient encounters share single visit; no duplicate visit","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-019","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0020","End-to-End Patient Journeys","ER Triage Journey","Left-without-being-seen (LWBS) disposition closes visit","State Transition","System","P3","Medium","Medium","ER patient triaged but leaves before clinician seen","1. Triage patient | 2. Mark disposition LWBS | 3. Close emergency visit | 4. Verify reporting flag","Disposition=LWBS","Visit closed with LWBS disposition; no treatment encounters; patient counted in LWBS metric for reporting","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-020","Clinical; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0021","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Referral Journey","Outbound referral generated with reason and target facility","Functional","E2E","P2","High","Medium","Clinician on active visit; referral target facilities configured","1. Open patient with active visit | 2. Create outbound referral | 3. Select target facility and specialty | 4. Add reason and attachments | 5. Submit referral","Target=District Hospital Cardiology; Reason=Suspected MI for cath","Referral created with reason, target, attachments; status SUBMITTED; referral appears in tracking list","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-021","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0022","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Referral Journey","Referral lifecycle state transitions submitted to accepted to completed","State Transition","System","P2","High","Medium","Outbound referral in SUBMITTED state","1. Receiving facility marks ACCEPTED | 2. Patient seen, mark IN_PROGRESS | 3. Outcome returned, mark COMPLETED | 4. Attempt to re-open COMPLETED referral","Referral states: SUBMITTED to ACCEPTED to IN_PROGRESS to COMPLETED","Each valid transition recorded with actor and timestamp; reopening completed referral blocked or audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-022","Clinical; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0023","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Referral Journey","Referral rejection returns patient to originating provider queue","Negative","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Referral submitted to facility lacking capacity","1. Receiving facility marks REJECTED with reason | 2. Originating provider notified | 3. Provider re-routes to alternate facility","Rejection reason=No cath lab availability","Rejection captured with reason; originator notified; patient re-routable; original referral retains audit trail","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-023","Clinical; Audit","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0024","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Referral Journey","FHIR ServiceRequest represents outbound referral correctly","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; referral created","1. Create referral | 2. GET ServiceRequest resource | 3. Validate intent, status, subject, requester, performerType | 4. Validate reasonCode coding","ServiceRequest.intent=order; status=active","ServiceRequest validates against R4; subject references Patient; requester references Practitioner; reasonCode uses standard coding system","Automatable","REQ-E2E2-024","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-E2E2-0025","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Cross-Module Integrity","Visit-encounter referential integrity after encounter void","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Visit with three encounters; data manager access","1. Void one encounter with reason | 2. Verify encounter marked voided not deleted | 3. Verify visit still references remaining encounters | 4. Verify obs of voided encounter also voided","Void reason=Entered in error","Voided encounter retains row with voided flag, reason, voidedBy; child obs voided; visit integrity preserved; no hard delete","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-025","Data Integrity; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0026","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Cross-Module Integrity","Lab result auto-flags critical value and notifies ordering provider","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Lab order placed; critical value ranges configured; notifications enabled","1. Lab enters a critical-range result | 2. System flags critical | 3. Ordering provider notified | 4. Provider acknowledges","Test=Potassium; Result=6.8 mmol/L (critical high)","Result flagged critical; ordering provider receives notification; acknowledgement recorded with timestamp; unacknowledged criticals escalate","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-026","Patient Safety; Clinical; Audit","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0027","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Cross-Module Integrity","Result entry rejected for cancelled/discontinued order","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Lab order placed then discontinued by clinician","1. Place lab order | 2. Clinician discontinues order | 3. Lab tech attempts to enter result | 4. Observe","Order=Lipid panel; status=Discontinued","Result entry blocked or warns that order is discontinued; no result attaches to a cancelled order silently","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-027","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0028","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Cross-Module Integrity","Pairwise visit type, location, provider role, order type combinations","Pairwise","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Multiple visit types, locations, provider roles, and order types configured","1. Execute pairwise matrix of (visit type x location x provider role x order type) | 2. For each combo place an order | 3. Verify acceptance/denial per RBAC and config","Visit={OPD,IPD,ER}; Location={A,B}; Role={Clinician,Nurse}; Order={Drug,Lab}","Each pairwise combination behaves per configuration; unauthorized role/order combos denied; authorized combos succeed; no crashes","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-028","Clinical; Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0029","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Cross-Module Integrity","Duplicate diagnosis on same visit deduped or warned","Boundary","System","P3","Medium","Low","Active visit with one diagnosis recorded","1. Record diagnosis Hypertension | 2. Record same diagnosis again on same visit | 3. Observe","Diagnosis=Hypertension x2","System warns of duplicate or dedupes; does not silently store identical conflicting confirmed diagnoses without indication","Automatable","REQ-E2E2-029","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0030","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Cross-Module Integrity","Backdated encounter cannot precede visit start datetime","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Active visit started at 10:00","1. Add encounter dated 09:00 (before visit start) | 2. Add encounter dated 10:30 (within) | 3. Add encounter dated in future","Visit start=10:00; encounter times=09:00, 10:30, future","Encounter before visit start rejected or adjusts visit start per rule; future-dated encounter blocked; within-visit accepted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-030","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-E2E2-0031","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Cross-Module Integrity","Concurrent edits to same encounter by two clinicians","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Encounter open for edit by two users","1. User A opens encounter for edit | 2. User B opens same encounter | 3. User A saves | 4. User B saves stale copy","Two concurrent editors; same encounter","Optimistic locking or last-write detection prevents silent overwrite; User B warned of stale data; no lost update","Manual-Only","REQ-E2E2-031","Data Integrity; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-E2E2-0032","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Standards Interop","FHIR Encounter reflects visit lifecycle status mapping","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 enabled; active then ended visit","1. Start visit; GET Encounter status | 2. End visit; GET Encounter status again | 3. Validate status mapping","Visit active then ended","Active visit maps to Encounter.status=in-progress; ended maps to finished; class and period populated correctly","Automatable","REQ-E2E2-032","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-E2E2-0033","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Standards Interop","HL7 v2 ADT-A04 register, A01 admit, A03 discharge sequence","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 inbound/outbound interface configured","1. Register patient, capture ADT^A04 | 2. Admit, capture ADT^A01 | 3. Discharge, capture ADT^A03 | 4. Validate PID, PV1 segments and message sequence","ADT messages for one patient journey","Each event emits correct ADT trigger; PID identifiers consistent; PV1 patient class transitions O to I; message control IDs unique","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-033","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-E2E2-0034","End-to-End Patient Journeys","Standards Interop","HL7 v2 ORM/OML lab order and ORU result round-trip","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Lab interface configured; LIS simulator available","1. Place lab order; capture outbound OML^O21 | 2. LIS returns ORU^R01 result | 3. System ingests ORU | 4. Verify result attached to original order","Lab=Glucose; result=Glucose 95 mg/dL","Outbound order maps OBR correctly; inbound ORU matched via placer order number; result attaches to correct order/patient","Partially-Automatable","REQ-E2E2-034","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
