"TC-INTEG-0011","Integration (cross-module & external)","Appointment to Visit","Checked-in appointment creates/links an active visit","Functional","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Appointment scheduling enabled; scheduled appointment exists for today","1. Open today appointment for patient | 2. Mark patient Checked-In | 3. Verify an active visit is created or linked | 4. Confirm clinician can document on it","Appt=SYN-A-9001","Check-in transitions appointment status and surfaces an active visit; documentation can proceed against that visit","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-006","Clinical;Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INTEG-0012","Integration (cross-module & external)","Appointment State Transition","Appointment lifecycle state transitions are consistent across modules","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Appointment exists; statuses: Scheduled, CheckedIn, Completed, Missed, Cancelled","1. Drive appointment Scheduled->CheckedIn->Completed | 2. Attempt invalid transition Completed->CheckedIn | 3. Attempt Cancelled->Completed | 4. Record allowed vs blocked","Valid: Scheduled->CheckedIn->Completed; Invalid: Completed->CheckedIn, Cancelled->Completed","Valid transitions succeed and reflect in calendar and visit; invalid transitions are blocked with a clear error; state never corrupts","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-006","Data Integrity;Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-INTEG-0013","Integration (cross-module & external)","FHIR Outbound","New OpenMRS patient is retrievable via FHIR R4 Patient resource","FHIR","Integration","P1","Critical","High","FHIR2 module enabled; /ws/fhir2/R4 reachable; valid auth","1. Register a patient in OpenMRS UI | 2. Note generated identifier | 3. GET /Patient?identifier=<id> via FHIR | 4. Validate resource fields","Patient name=Test Synthetic; DOB=1990-01-01","FHIR Patient returned with matching name, gender, birthDate and identifier; resource validates against R4 Patient profile","Automatable","REQ-INTEG-007","Standards-FHIR;PHI/Privacy;Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INTEG-0014","Integration (cross-module & external)","FHIR Outbound","Vitals encounter surfaces as FHIR Observation resources","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR2 enabled; patient with a saved vitals encounter","1. Save vitals (BP, pulse, temp) | 2. GET /Observation?patient=<id>&category=vital-signs | 3. Inspect returned Observations","BP=120/80; Pulse=72; Temp=37.0","Observations returned with correct LOINC codes, values, units (UCUM) and effectiveDateTime; linked to patient and encounter","Automatable","REQ-INTEG-007","Standards-FHIR;Clinical;Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INTEG-0015","Integration (cross-module & external)","FHIR Inbound","Create patient via FHIR POST appears in OpenMRS registry","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","High","FHIR2 enabled; auth user with create privilege","1. POST a valid R4 Patient bundle/resource to /Patient | 2. Capture returned id | 3. Search the patient in OpenMRS UI | 4. Verify demographics","Resource: name=Inbound Synthetic; gender=female","HTTP 201 with Location; patient is searchable in OpenMRS with matching demographics and FHIR-sourced identifier","Automatable","REQ-INTEG-008","Standards-FHIR;PHI/Privacy;Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INTEG-0016","Integration (cross-module & external)","FHIR Inbound","Reject malformed FHIR resource with OperationOutcome","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR2 endpoint reachable; valid auth","1. POST a Patient resource missing required fields/invalid datatype | 2. Inspect response status and body","Resource: birthDate=not-a-date","HTTP 4xx with OperationOutcome describing the validation error; no partial patient created in OpenMRS","Automatable","REQ-INTEG-008","Standards-FHIR;Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INTEG-0017","Integration (cross-module & external)","FHIR Inbound","Conditional create via If-None-Exist prevents duplicate patient","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR2 enabled; patient with known identifier exists","1. POST Patient with header If-None-Exist=identifier=<existing> | 2. Observe response | 3. Confirm no duplicate created","If-None-Exist=identifier|EXIST-100","Server returns 200 referencing existing resource (or 412 per policy); no duplicate patient is created; behavior documented","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-008","Standards-FHIR;Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-INTEG-0018","Integration (cross-module & external)","HL7 Inbound","Inbound ADT^A01 admit message creates/updates patient and visit","HL7","Integration","P1","Critical","High","HL7 listener/queue configured; sender allowed","1. Submit a valid ADT^A01 message to the inbound interface | 2. Allow processing | 3. Verify patient exists/updated | 4. Verify visit/admission created","MSH...PID...PV1 admit; MRN=HL7-2001","Message accepted (ACK AA); patient created/matched; admission visit recorded with correct location and datetime","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-009","Standards-HL7;Clinical;Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-INTEG-0019","Integration (cross-module & external)","HL7 Inbound","Inbound ORU^R01 result message records observations","HL7","Integration","P1","High","High","HL7 listener configured; patient with matching MRN exists","1. Submit ORU^R01 with OBX result segments | 2. Allow processing | 3. View results on patient dashboard","OBX: glucose=95 mg/dL; MRN=HL7-2001","ACK AA returned; observations stored with correct value, units and observation datetime; linked to patient","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-009","Standards-HL7;Clinical;Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-INTEG-0020","Integration (cross-module & external)","HL7 Inbound","Malformed HL7 message is rejected with negative ACK and queued for review","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","HL7 listener configured; error/dead-letter queue available","1. Submit HL7 message with bad MSH/segment ordering | 2. Observe ACK | 3. Inspect error queue","MSH missing required field 9 (message type)","ACK AE/AR returned; message routed to error queue with reason; no partial clinical data persisted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-009","Standards-HL7;Data Integrity;Audit","Standards"
"TC-INTEG-0021","Integration (cross-module & external)","HL7 Inbound","Unknown MRN in inbound result triggers patient-matching exception","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","HL7 listener configured; matching policy = no auto-create on result","1. Submit ORU^R01 with MRN not present | 2. Observe processing outcome","MRN=DOES-NOT-EXIST","Message is held/errored with unmatched-patient reason; no orphan observation created; alert raised for reconciliation","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-010","Standards-HL7;Patient Safety;Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-INTEG-0022","Integration (cross-module & external)","HL7 Outbound","Registration event emits outbound ADT^A04 to subscribed system","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Outbound HL7 channel configured to a stub receiver","1. Register a new patient | 2. Capture outbound message at stub receiver | 3. Validate segments","Patient=Outbound Synthetic","An ADT^A04 message is emitted with correct PID demographics and MRN; receiver returns ACK AA; emission logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-011","Standards-HL7;PHI/Privacy;Audit","Standards"
"TC-INTEG-0023","Integration (cross-module & external)","WireMock Insurance Stub","Eligibility check succeeds against WireMock insurance stub","API","Integration","P1","High","High","WireMock running with eligibility stub; payer connector configured to stub URL","1. Trigger insurance eligibility for a patient with coverage | 2. WireMock returns active coverage | 3. Verify result surfaced in billing/registration","Member=INS-555; Payer=ACME-HMO","Connector parses stub response; coverage shows Active with plan details; result stored against patient coverage","Automatable","REQ-INTEG-012","Billing;Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INTEG-0024","Integration (cross-module & external)","WireMock Insurance Stub","Eligibility returns inactive coverage and blocks billing path","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","WireMock stub configured to return inactive coverage","1. Trigger eligibility for member with inactive plan | 2. Stub returns coverage=inactive | 3. Verify downstream handling","Member=INS-INACTIVE","System marks coverage Inactive; self-pay/alternate path is offered; no claim auto-submitted on inactive coverage","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-012","Billing;Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INTEG-0025","Integration (cross-module & external)","WireMock Insurance Stub","Eligibility connector handles 500 from payer stub gracefully","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","WireMock stub set to return HTTP 500 for eligibility","1. Trigger eligibility | 2. Stub returns 500 | 3. Observe connector behavior and user message","Stub: status=500","Connector surfaces a transient error (not a crash); request is retried per policy or queued; user sees a non-PHI-leaking error","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-013","Billing;Security","Platform"
"TC-INTEG-0026","Integration (cross-module & external)","WireMock Insurance Stub","Eligibility connector honors timeout when stub delays response","Boundary","Integration","P2","High","High","WireMock stub configured with fixed delay exceeding connector timeout","1. Set stub delay > configured timeout | 2. Trigger eligibility | 3. Measure connector behavior at boundary","Timeout=5s; Stub delay=8s","Connector aborts at timeout, returns timeout error and does not hang the UI thread; request logged for retry","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-013","Billing;Performance;Security","Platform"
"TC-INTEG-0027","Integration (cross-module & external)","WireMock Lab Stub","Outbound lab order reaches WireMock LIS stub with correct payload","API","Integration","P1","High","High","WireMock LIS stub running; lab interface configured to stub","1. Place a lab order routed to external LIS | 2. Capture request at WireMock | 3. Validate payload fields","Order=CBC; Patient=SYN-1003","WireMock receives the order with correct patient id, test code, priority and ordering provider; request matches stub mapping","Automatable","REQ-INTEG-014","Clinical;Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INTEG-0028","Integration (cross-module & external)","WireMock Lab Stub","Asynchronous result callback from LIS stub updates the order","API","Integration","P2","High","High","WireMock configured to POST result callback; order placed and pending","1. Place external lab order | 2. WireMock posts result callback for the order | 3. Verify order/result state updates","Result: WBC=7.0; status=final","Result callback is matched to the correct order via accession; order moves to Completed; result visible on dashboard","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INTEG-014","Clinical;Data Integrity","Platform"
