"TC-REGR-0071","Regression Pack (high-value)","Orders","Pairwise order attribute combinations validation","Pairwise","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Drug ordering form available","1. Apply paired combos of route, frequency, PRN, duration-unit | 2. Save each","Route={oral,IV}; Freq={BID,TID}; PRN={Y,N}; Unit={days,weeks}","Each valid combination saves; incompatible combos (e.g. PRN with fixed duration conflict) flagged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-REGR-010","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-REGR-0072","Regression Pack (high-value)","Authentication","Password change invalidates other active sessions","Security","Regression","P2","High","High","User logged in on two clients","1. Change password on client A | 2. Perform action on client B","Two sessions","Other sessions are invalidated or require re-auth after password change; no stale access","Manual-Only","REQ-REGR-017","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-REGR-0073","Regression Pack (high-value)","Authentication","Login rejects valid username with trailing whitespace mismatch","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Valid account exists","1. Enter username with trailing space | 2. Enter correct password | 3. Submit","Username='admin '","Behavior is deterministic per spec (trim-and-accept or reject); documented and consistent","Partially-Automatable","REQ-REGR-017","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-REGR-0074","Regression Pack (high-value)","FHIR","Encounter resource references correct subject and participant","FHIR","Regression","P2","High","Medium","FHIR enabled; encounter exists","1. GET Encounter/{id} | 2. Inspect subject and participant references","Encounter with provider","Encounter.subject points to correct Patient; participant references the provider Practitioner","Automatable","REQ-REGR-014","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-REGR-0075","Regression Pack (high-value)","FHIR","MedicationRequest status reflects discontinued order","FHIR","Regression","P2","High","Medium","FHIR enabled; discontinued drug order","1. Discontinue drug order | 2. GET MedicationRequest | 3. Inspect status","Order discontinued","MedicationRequest.status maps to stopped/completed consistent with order state","Partially-Automatable","REQ-REGR-014","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-REGR-0076","Regression Pack (high-value)","HL7","Duplicate inbound message (same control ID) is de-duplicated","HL7","Regression","P2","High","Medium","HL7 inbound with dedup configured","1. Send ADT message | 2. Resend identical message same MSH-10 | 3. Inspect","MSH-10=MSGID001 (twice)","Second identical message is recognized as duplicate and not reprocessed; single patient effect","Partially-Automatable","REQ-REGR-015","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-REGR-0077","Regression Pack (high-value)","Exploratory","Exploratory session on concurrent visit and order edge cases","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Test clinician with patient having active visit and orders","1. Time-boxed exploration of rapid start/stop visit, place/discontinue order, void encounter sequences | 2. Note anomalies","Charter=visit/order edges","Document defects/inconsistencies in state, audit and UI; no data corruption observed","Manual-Only","REQ-REGR-028","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-REGR-0078","Regression Pack (high-value)","Exploratory","Exploratory session on identifier formats and check digits","Exploratory","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Registration with identifier validation","1. Explore identifiers with edge formats, check-digit errors, max length, special chars | 2. Note handling","IDs=edge formats","Invalid check digits/formats rejected; valid edge formats accepted; behavior documented","Manual-Only","REQ-REGR-028","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-REGR-0079","Regression Pack (high-value)","Patient Registration","Prior-defect regression: gender unknown blocked save (Assumption)","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Defect history: U gender once broke save","1. Register patient with gender Unknown | 2. Save","Gender=U","Patient with Unknown gender saves successfully; prior save-blocking defect does not recur","Automatable","REQ-REGR-002","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-REGR-0080","Regression Pack (high-value)","Orders","Prior-defect regression: discontinued order reappearing as active (Assumption)","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","High","Defect history: discontinued order showed active after refresh","1. Discontinue drug order | 2. Refresh dashboard | 3. Re-open patient in new session","Order=discontinued","Order remains discontinued across refresh and sessions; stale active state defect does not recur","Partially-Automatable","REQ-REGR-010","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-REGR-0081","Regression Pack (high-value)","Allergies","Prior-defect regression: severity not persisted on edit (Assumption)","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Defect history: allergy severity dropped on edit","1. Add allergy with severe severity | 2. Edit reaction | 3. Save and reopen","Allergen=Latex; Severity=Severe","Severity persists through edit; previously dropped severity defect does not recur","Automatable","REQ-REGR-008","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-REGR-0082","Regression Pack (high-value)","Reporting","Audit report includes user merge actions","Audit","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patient merges performed; audit reporting available","1. Run audit report filtered to merge events | 2. Verify entries","Event=patient merge","Merge actions appear with actor, survivor/non-survivor IDs and timestamp for compliance review","Partially-Automatable","REQ-REGR-016","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-REGR-0083","Regression Pack (high-value)","Pharmacy","Pairwise dispense scenarios across stock and substitution","Pairwise","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Inventory with brands and generics","1. Apply paired combos of stock-level, substitution-allowed, partial-fill, controlled-substance | 2. Process","Stock={ok,low}; Sub={Y,N}; Partial={Y,N}; Controlled={Y,N}","Each combination produces correct dispense outcome and required approvals; controlled substances require extra auth","Manual-Only","REQ-REGR-012","Patient Safety; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-REGR-0084","Regression Pack (high-value)","Billing","State transition of invoice draft to posted to paid to void","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Billing module active","1. Create draft invoice | 2. Post | 3. Record payment to paid | 4. Attempt void of paid invoice","Invoice lifecycle","Valid transitions persist with timestamps; voiding a paid invoice requires reversal/credit not silent delete","Partially-Automatable","REQ-REGR-019","Billing; Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0001","UAT Scenarios","Registration Clerk Day-in-Life","New walk-in patient: register, verify identity, start visit and route to triage in one flow","Functional","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Registration clerk logged in with registration and visit-start privileges; registration desk location selected","1. Search for the patient by name and DOB and confirm no match exists | 2. Register a new patient with full demographics | 3. Capture a primary identifier | 4. Start an outpatient visit at the desk | 5. Assign the patient to the Triage queue","Name=Maria Tester; DOB=1990-04-12; Gender=F; VisitType=Outpatient","Patient is created once with no duplicate, visit is active, and the patient appears in the Triage queue with correct datetime and location","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-001","Clinical; PHI/Privacy; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0002","UAT Scenarios","Registration Clerk Day-in-Life","Returning patient with forgotten ID card is matched on demographics before a duplicate is created","Negative","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Existing patient record present; registration clerk logged in","1. Search by identifier and get no result | 2. Search by name, DOB and gender | 3. Review potential matches presented | 4. Select the existing record rather than creating new","Name=John Sample; DOB=1975-09-03","The existing record is matched and reused, a duplicate is not created, and the clerk is warned of close matches before any create action","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-002","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0003","UAT Scenarios","Registration Clerk Day-in-Life","Register a newborn with estimated DOB and link to mother record","Boundary","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Mother record exists; clerk has registration privilege","1. Register newborn using estimated age in days | 2. Set gender unknown if not yet assigned | 3. Capture relationship to mother | 4. Save","EstimatedAge=2 days; Gender=Unknown; Relationship=Child of <MotherID>","Newborn is registered with estimated birthdate flag set, relationship to mother is stored, and age displays in days","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-003","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0004","UAT Scenarios","Registration Clerk Day-in-Life","Reject registration when mandatory demographic fields are blank","Negative","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clerk logged in","1. Open new patient registration | 2. Leave given name and birthdate blank | 3. Attempt to save","GivenName=(blank); DOB=(blank)","Save is blocked with field-level validation messages for each missing mandatory field and no record is created","Automatable","REQ-UAT2-001","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0005","UAT Scenarios","Nurse Triage Day-in-Life","Triage nurse records vitals, chief complaint and acuity then routes to clinician queue","Functional","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Nurse logged in; patient in Triage queue with active visit","1. Open the patient from the Triage queue | 2. Start the triage form | 3. Record vitals and chief complaint | 4. Assign acuity level | 5. Save and move to clinician queue","Pulse=88; BP=130/85; Temp=37.2; Acuity=3; Complaint=Cough 3 days","Triage encounter is saved with vitals and acuity, and the patient moves from Triage to the clinician queue","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-004","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0006","UAT Scenarios","Nurse Triage Day-in-Life","Abnormal vital triggers a high-acuity prompt (decision table)","Decision Table","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Nurse logged in; patient in triage with active visit","1. Enter combinations of temperature, systolic BP and SpO2 across normal and critical ranges | 2. Observe acuity recommendation per combination","Temp=39.5/37.0; SBP=85/120; SpO2=88/98","System recommends elevated acuity when any value is in the critical range and normal acuity only when all values are normal, per the decision table","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-005","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0007","UAT Scenarios","Nurse Triage Day-in-Life","Reject impossible vital values at triage","Boundary","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Nurse logged in; active visit","1. Enter a pulse of 0 | 2. Enter a temperature of 50 C | 3. Attempt to save","Pulse=0; Temp=50","Out-of-range physiologic values are rejected with validation messages and the encounter is not saved","Automatable","REQ-UAT2-005","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0008","UAT Scenarios","Clinician Day-in-Life","Clinician completes a full consultation: history, diagnosis, orders and plan in one encounter","Functional","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Clinician logged in; patient in clinician queue with active visit","1. Open the patient | 2. Record history of presenting illness | 3. Add a coded diagnosis | 4. Place a lab order and a drug order | 5. Write a plan note | 6. Sign the encounter","Diagnosis=Acute bronchitis; LabOrder=CBC; Drug=Amoxicillin 500mg","Encounter is signed with diagnosis, orders and note all linked to the visit, and orders appear active in their respective queues","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-006","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0009","UAT Scenarios","Clinician Day-in-Life","Drug order against a documented allergy raises an interaction alert before signing","Negative","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Clinician logged in; patient has a documented penicillin allergy and active visit","1. Open the patient with the penicillin allergy | 2. Order Amoxicillin | 3. Attempt to sign the order","Allergy=Penicillin; Drug=Amoxicillin","An allergy interaction alert is shown requiring acknowledgement or override with reason before the order can proceed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-007","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0010","UAT Scenarios","Clinician Day-in-Life","Allergy override is recorded with reason in the audit trail","Audit","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Clinician logged in; allergy alert raised on a drug order","1. Trigger the allergy alert | 2. Choose to override | 3. Enter an override reason | 4. Sign the order | 5. Review the audit log","OverrideReason=Patient tolerated previously","Override action, reason, user and timestamp are written to the audit trail and the order proceeds","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-007","Audit; Patient Safety; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0011","UAT Scenarios","Clinician Day-in-Life","Unsigned encounter persists as draft across navigation and re-login","State Transition","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician logged in; active visit with a partially entered encounter","1. Enter partial encounter data | 2. Navigate away without signing | 3. Return to the patient | 4. Log out and log back in | 5. Reopen the patient","Diagnosis=Draft only","Draft content is preserved through navigation and re-login until explicitly signed or discarded","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-006","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0012","UAT Scenarios","Clinician Day-in-Life","Amend a signed encounter creates a versioned correction not an overwrite","State Transition","UAT","P1","High","High","Clinician logged in; a signed encounter exists","1. Open the signed encounter | 2. Choose amend | 3. Change the diagnosis | 4. Save the amendment | 5. View encounter history","NewDiagnosis=Pneumonia","Original signed content is retained as a prior version, the amendment is recorded with author and timestamp, and history shows both versions","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-008","Data Integrity; Audit; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0013","UAT Scenarios","Pharmacist Day-in-Life","Pharmacist verifies a new prescription, checks interactions and dispenses","Functional","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Pharmacist logged in; an active drug order is awaiting verification","1. Open the pharmacy verification queue | 2. Select the pending order | 3. Review dose, route and frequency | 4. Check interactions | 5. Verify and dispense","Drug=Amoxicillin 500mg TID; Quantity=21","Order moves from pending to dispensed, quantity is decremented from stock, and a dispense record is created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-009","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0014","UAT Scenarios","Pharmacist Day-in-Life","Pharmacist rejects a prescription with an unsafe pediatric dose (boundary)","Boundary","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Pharmacist logged in; pediatric patient with weight recorded; order pending","1. Open the pending order for a 12 kg child | 2. Review the weight-based dose | 3. Identify the dose exceeds the max mg per kg | 4. Reject with reason back to prescriber","Weight=12kg; OrderedDose=1000mg; MaxPerKg=50mg/kg","The order is flagged as exceeding the safe weight-based maximum and is returned to the prescriber with a documented reason","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-010","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0015","UAT Scenarios","Pharmacist Day-in-Life","Partial dispense leaves the balance open and tracked","State Transition","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Pharmacist logged in; verified order for 30 units; only 20 in stock","1. Open the verified order | 2. Dispense 20 units | 3. Record a partial dispense | 4. Re-open the order later","Ordered=30; Dispensed=20","Order state is partially dispensed, a remaining balance of 10 is tracked, and the order remains actionable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-009","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0016","UAT Scenarios","Pharmacist Day-in-Life","Controlled substance dispense requires second-witness sign-off","Security","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Pharmacist logged in; order for a scheduled controlled substance; witness user available","1. Open the controlled substance order | 2. Attempt to dispense | 3. Provide pharmacist credential | 4. Provide witness credential","Drug=Morphine 10mg; Schedule=II","Dispense is blocked until a valid second witness authenticates, and both identities are recorded on the dispense record","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-011","Security; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0017","UAT Scenarios","Lab Tech Day-in-Life","Lab tech accepts a specimen, runs the test and posts a result against the order","Functional","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Lab tech logged in; a lab order with collected specimen exists","1. Open the lab worklist | 2. Accept the specimen for the order | 3. Enter the numeric result | 4. Validate against the reference range | 5. Release the result","Test=Hemoglobin; Result=9.1 g/dL; Range=12-16","Result is posted to the order, flagged low against the reference range, and the ordering clinician is notified","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-012","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0018","UAT Scenarios","Lab Tech Day-in-Life","Critical lab value triggers mandatory call-back documentation","Decision Table","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Lab tech logged in; result entry open","1. Enter a result within the critical-low band | 2. Enter a result within normal band | 3. Enter a result within critical-high band | 4. Observe call-back requirement per band","Potassium=2.5/4.0/6.5","Critical-low and critical-high results require documented call-back to the clinician before release, while normal results release without call-back","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-013","Patient Safety; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0019","UAT Scenarios","Lab Tech Day-in-Life","Reject result entry on a cancelled or mismatched specimen","Negative","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Lab tech logged in; one order cancelled, one specimen barcode mismatched","1. Scan a specimen for a cancelled order | 2. Attempt to enter a result | 3. Scan a specimen whose ID does not match the order","Order1=Cancelled; SpecimenBarcode=mismatch","Result entry is blocked for cancelled orders and for specimen-order mismatches with a clear error, preventing wrong-patient results","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-012","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0020","UAT Scenarios","Lab Tech Day-in-Life","Amended lab result supersedes prior value and notifies clinician","State Transition","UAT","P1","High","High","Lab tech logged in; a released result exists","1. Open the released result | 2. Amend the value with a correction reason | 3. Release the amendment | 4. View the result history","OldResult=9.1; NewResult=11.0; Reason=Recalibration","Amended result is marked corrected, the prior value is retained in history, and the ordering clinician receives a corrected-result notification","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-013","Patient Safety; Data Integrity; Audit","Standards"
"TC-UAT2-0021","UAT Scenarios","Biller Day-in-Life","Biller generates a claim from completed visit charges and submits","Functional","UAT","P1","High","High","Biller logged in; completed visit with chargeable services posted","1. Open the visit billing summary | 2. Confirm all chargeable services are captured | 3. Map services to billing codes | 4. Generate the claim | 5. Submit","Services=Consult,CBC,Amoxicillin; Payer=NHIF","Claim is generated with correct line items and codes, total matches posted charges, and the claim is queued for submission","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-014","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0022","UAT Scenarios","Biller Day-in-Life","Claim is blocked when a required diagnosis-to-procedure link is missing","Negative","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Biller logged in; visit with a procedure but no supporting diagnosis","1. Open the visit with the unlinked procedure | 2. Attempt to generate the claim","Procedure=X-ray; Diagnosis=(none)","Claim generation is blocked with a message that the procedure requires a supporting diagnosis, preventing a denial","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-014","Billing; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0023","UAT Scenarios","Biller Day-in-Life","Insurance co-pay and patient balance split is calculated correctly (decision table)","Decision Table","UAT","P1","High","High","Biller logged in; patient with active insurance and a defined co-pay rule","1. Apply claims with covered, partially covered and non-covered services | 2. Observe payer portion and patient balance for each","Total=100; Coverage=100%/80%/0%","Payer and patient split is computed per coverage rule for each scenario and the sum always equals the claim total","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-015","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0024","UAT Scenarios","Biller Day-in-Life","Refund on an overpaid invoice posts a negative adjustment and preserves history","State Transition","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Biller logged in; invoice with a recorded overpayment","1. Open the overpaid invoice | 2. Initiate a refund for the overpaid amount | 3. Confirm and post | 4. Review invoice ledger","Overpayment=20.00","A refund adjustment is posted, the running balance returns to zero, and the original payment remains visible in the ledger","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-015","Billing; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0025","UAT Scenarios","Admin Day-in-Life","Admin onboards a new clinician: create user, assign role and scope to location","Functional","UAT","P1","High","High","System admin logged in with user-management privilege","1. Create a new user account | 2. Assign the Clinician role | 3. Restrict the user to a single location | 4. Force password change at first login | 5. Save","User=dr.new; Role=Clinician; Location=OPD-1","User is created with the clinician role, location scope is enforced, and first login forces a password change","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-016","Security; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0026","UAT Scenarios","Admin Day-in-Life","Deactivated user immediately loses access and active session is terminated","State Transition","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Admin logged in; target user currently has an active session","1. Confirm the target user is logged in elsewhere | 2. Deactivate the user account | 3. Have the target user attempt a privileged action","User=dr.leaving","Account is disabled, the next request from the existing session is rejected, and the user cannot re-authenticate","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-016","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0027","UAT Scenarios","Admin Day-in-Life","Role privilege change takes effect on next login without restart","State Transition","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Admin logged in; a role missing the order-entry privilege","1. Add the order-entry privilege to the role | 2. Have a user with that role log out and back in | 3. Attempt order entry","Role=NursePlus; Privilege=Add Orders","After re-login the user can perform order entry, confirming privilege propagation without a system restart","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-017","Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0028","UAT Scenarios","Cross-Role Handoff","Inpatient admission handoff from clinician to ward nurse preserves orders and notes","Integration","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Clinician and ward nurse accounts exist; patient admitted with standing orders","1. Clinician writes admission orders and a handoff note | 2. Patient is admitted to a ward bed | 3. Ward nurse opens the patient on the ward list | 4. Nurse reviews active orders and the handoff note","Ward=Medical-A; Bed=12","Ward nurse sees the active orders, the handoff note and current location, with continuity preserved across the role handoff","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-018","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0029","UAT Scenarios","Cross-Role Handoff","Shift change: outgoing nurse signs off and incoming nurse acknowledges pending tasks","State Transition","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Two nurse accounts; ward with pending medication and observation tasks","1. Outgoing nurse reviews the pending task list | 2. Records a shift handoff summary | 3. Incoming nurse logs in | 4. Acknowledges the handoff and pending tasks","PendingTasks=2 meds,1 obs","Handoff summary is captured, incoming nurse acknowledges, and pending tasks carry forward with no loss across the shift boundary","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-018","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0030","UAT Scenarios","Appointment Lifecycle","Full appointment lifecycle: book, check-in, convert to visit, complete, no-show variant","State Transition","UAT","P1","High","High","Scheduler and clinician accounts; provider with available slots","1. Book an appointment in an open slot | 2. Check the patient in on arrival | 3. Convert the appointment to an active visit | 4. Complete after the encounter | 5. In a parallel case mark a separate appointment as no-show","ApptType=Follow-up; Slot=10:00","Each appointment transitions through valid states only, a no-show is recorded distinctly, and completed appointments link to their visit","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-019","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0031","UAT Scenarios","Appointment Lifecycle","Double-booking the same provider slot is prevented","Negative","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Scheduler logged in; provider slot already booked","1. Open the provider schedule | 2. Attempt to book a second appointment in the occupied slot","Slot=10:00 already booked","Booking is rejected with a slot-conflict message unless overbooking is explicitly permitted for that provider","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-019","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0032","UAT Scenarios","Appointment Lifecycle","Cancellation within the late-cancel window flags a fee per policy (decision table)","Decision Table","UAT","P3","Medium","Medium","Scheduler logged in; cancellation policy configured with a 24-hour window","1. Cancel an appointment more than 24 hours out | 2. Cancel one within 24 hours | 3. Cancel a same-day appointment | 4. Observe fee flag per case","CancelTimes=48h/12h/0h","No fee is flagged outside the window, a late-cancel fee is flagged inside the window, and policy is applied consistently","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-019","Billing; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0033","UAT Scenarios","Referral Workflow","Outbound referral to a specialist creates a referral record with reason and packet","Functional","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician logged in; specialty target configured","1. Open the patient | 2. Create an outbound referral | 3. Select the specialty and reason | 4. Attach the clinical summary | 5. Submit","Specialty=Cardiology; Reason=Murmur","Referral is created with reason, target specialty and an attached summary, and shows as pending acceptance","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-020","Clinical; Standards-FHIR","Standards"
"TC-UAT2-0034","UAT Scenarios","Referral Workflow","Referral status round-trip: accepted, scheduled, completed back to referrer","State Transition","UAT","P2","Medium","Medium","Referral created and pending; specialist account exists","1. Specialist accepts the referral | 2. Schedules the patient | 3. Completes the consult and writes back findings | 4. Referrer reviews the closed-loop status","ReferralID=REF-001","Referral progresses through accepted, scheduled and completed, and findings are returned to the original referrer closing the loop","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-020","Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-UAT2-0035","UAT Scenarios","Program Enrollment","Enroll patient in a chronic care program and record an initial program visit","Functional","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician logged in; a care program is configured","1. Open the patient | 2. Enroll in the chronic care program | 3. Set the enrollment date and initial state | 4. Record the first program encounter","Program=HIV Care; State=Active","Enrollment is created with start date and state, and the initial program encounter is linked to the enrollment","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-021","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0036","UAT Scenarios","Program Enrollment","Program state transitions follow the allowed workflow only","State Transition","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician logged in; patient enrolled with state Active","1. Move the patient from Active to On Treatment | 2. Attempt an invalid jump to a terminal state and back | 3. Move to a valid completion state","States=Active,OnTreatment,Completed","Only configured state transitions are allowed, invalid transitions are blocked, and each state change is dated and audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-021","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0037","UAT Scenarios","Patient Merge","Merge two duplicate patient records preserving all clinical data","Functional","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Admin with merge privilege; two confirmed duplicate records of the same person","1. Identify the two duplicate records | 2. Select the surviving (preferred) record | 3. Review observations, visits and orders to be merged | 4. Confirm the merge","Survivor=PT-100; NonSurvivor=PT-205","Both records are merged into the survivor, no encounters or orders are lost, and the non-survivor identifier resolves to the survivor","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-022","Patient Safety; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0038","UAT Scenarios","Patient Merge","Merge is blocked or warns when records have conflicting active diagnoses","Negative","UAT","P2","High","High","Admin with merge privilege; two records with conflicting active problems","1. Select two records with conflicting active diagnoses | 2. Initiate the merge | 3. Review the conflict warning","Conflict=Pregnant vs Male","A conflict warning is presented requiring explicit reviewer confirmation before the merge proceeds, preventing silent data corruption","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-022","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0039","UAT Scenarios","Consent & Privacy","Patient consent restriction blocks data sharing in an export","Security","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Privacy officer logged in; patient with a recorded sensitive-data restriction","1. Apply a consent restriction on the patient | 2. Run a data export that would include the patient | 3. Inspect the export contents","Restriction=No external sharing","Restricted data is excluded or masked from the export per the consent directive and the suppression is logged","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-023","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0040","UAT Scenarios","Consent & Privacy","Break-the-glass emergency access is logged and reviewable","Security","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Clinician logged in; patient outside the clinician's normal care scope","1. Attempt to open a restricted patient | 2. Invoke break-the-glass with a reason | 3. Access the record | 4. Privacy officer reviews the access log","Reason=Emergency treatment","Access is granted after reason capture, and the break-the-glass event with user, reason and timestamp is written to an immutable audit log","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-023","PHI/Privacy; Security; Audit","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0041","UAT Scenarios","Interop Day-in-Life","Inbound ADT admit message creates a visit reconciled to the correct patient","HL7","UAT","P1","Critical","High","HL7 interface engine connected; patient exists with a known MRN","1. Send an ADT A01 admit message with the patient MRN | 2. Observe patient match | 3. Verify the visit and location created","MessageType=ADT^A01; MRN=PT-100","The admit is matched to the existing patient by MRN, a visit is created at the stated location, and no duplicate patient is generated","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-024","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-UAT2-0042","UAT Scenarios","Interop Day-in-Life","Inbound ORU result message posts to the matching lab order","HL7","UAT","P1","High","High","HL7 interface connected; an outstanding lab order exists with a placer order number","1. Send an ORU R01 result referencing the placer order number | 2. Observe order matching | 3. Verify the result and units","MessageType=ORU^R01; PlacerOrder=ORD-77","The result is attached to the correct order with value, units and reference range, and an unmatched result is routed to an exception queue","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-024","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-UAT2-0043","UAT Scenarios","Interop Day-in-Life","Outbound FHIR encounter is exported with correct references and codes","FHIR","UAT","P2","High","Medium","FHIR API enabled; a signed encounter exists","1. Request the Encounter resource via the FHIR API | 2. Validate subject, participant and period references | 3. Validate diagnosis coding","Resource=Encounter; Patient=PT-100","Encounter resource resolves valid references to Patient and Practitioner, carries the correct period, and uses recognized diagnosis code systems","Automatable","REQ-UAT2-025","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-UAT2-0044","UAT Scenarios","Interop Day-in-Life","FHIR bundle posted with an invalid reference is rejected atomically","FHIR","UAT","P2","High","Medium","FHIR API enabled with transaction bundle support","1. Post a transaction bundle where one entry references a non-existent patient | 2. Observe the response","BundleType=transaction; BadRef=Patient/none","The whole transaction bundle is rejected with an operation outcome, and no partial resources are persisted","Automatable","REQ-UAT2-025","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-UAT2-0045","UAT Scenarios","Telemedicine Day-in-Life","Scheduled video consult: join, document encounter, e-prescribe","E2E","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician and patient enrolled for a tele-visit; appointment booked","1. Clinician joins the video session at appointment time | 2. Confirms patient identity | 3. Documents the encounter | 4. E-prescribes and ends the session","ApptType=Tele; Drug=Loratadine","The tele-encounter is documented and linked to the appointment, the prescription is generated, and session start and end are recorded","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-026","Clinical; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0046","UAT Scenarios","Telemedicine Day-in-Life","Tele-visit join is blocked before identity verification","Negative","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician in a tele-session lobby","1. Attempt to start documentation before verifying patient identity | 2. Observe the guard | 3. Verify identity then proceed","Verify=2-factor patient match","Documentation and prescribing are blocked until patient identity is verified, then proceed normally","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-026","PHI/Privacy; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0047","UAT Scenarios","Maternal & Child","Antenatal visit captures gestational age, fetal heart rate and risk flag","Functional","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician logged in; pregnant patient enrolled in antenatal care","1. Open the antenatal patient | 2. Record gestational age and fetal heart rate | 3. Capture danger signs | 4. Set the risk classification","GA=28 weeks; FHR=140; Risk=High","Antenatal observations are saved, the risk classification is set, and high-risk flags surface on the patient summary","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-027","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0048","UAT Scenarios","Maternal & Child","Pediatric growth measurement plots against age and flags malnutrition (boundary)","Boundary","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician logged in; pediatric patient with prior growth points","1. Record weight and height for the child | 2. Compute weight-for-age | 3. Observe the z-score band at the boundary thresholds","Age=24mo; Weight=8kg","Growth value plots on the chart, the z-score band is computed, and a value at or below the severe threshold flags malnutrition","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-027","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0049","UAT Scenarios","Emergency Department","Unidentified emergency patient registered as John Doe then reconciled later","State Transition","UAT","P1","Critical","High","ED clerk logged in; unidentified critical patient arrives","1. Register an unidentified patient with a temporary alias | 2. Start an emergency visit | 3. Provide care under the alias | 4. Later reconcile to the real identity","Alias=Trauma-Unknown-07","Care is delivered under the temporary identity, and on reconciliation all encounters and orders carry forward to the verified identity without loss","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-028","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0050","UAT Scenarios","Emergency Department","ED order set fires standard panel and the right alerts (pairwise)","Pairwise","UAT","P2","High","Medium","ED clinician logged in; chest-pain order set configured","1. Apply the chest-pain order set across pairwise combinations of patient sex, age band and allergy presence | 2. Observe orders and alerts generated","Combos=sex x agedBand x allergy","Each combination produces the correct order set members and surfaces allergy or age-appropriate alerts without missing or extra orders","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-029","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0051","UAT Scenarios","Discharge Workflow","Discharge a patient: medication reconciliation, summary, follow-up and bed release","E2E","UAT","P1","High","High","Clinician and nurse accounts; admitted patient ready for discharge","1. Reconcile inpatient and home medications | 2. Generate the discharge summary | 3. Schedule a follow-up appointment | 4. Discharge and release the bed","FollowUp=2 weeks","Discharge summary captures reconciled meds and diagnoses, the follow-up is booked, the visit is closed, and the bed is released to available","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-030","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0052","UAT Scenarios","Discharge Workflow","Discharge blocked while critical orders or unresulted labs remain open","Negative","UAT","P2","High","High","Clinician logged in; admitted patient with an open critical lab order","1. Attempt to discharge the patient | 2. Observe the open-orders guard | 3. Resolve or acknowledge the open items | 4. Retry discharge","OpenOrder=Troponin pending","Discharge is blocked or warns while critical open orders exist, requiring resolution or explicit clinician acknowledgement before completion","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-030","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0053","UAT Scenarios","Data Integrity & Recovery","Concurrent edits to the same encounter by two clinicians are reconciled safely","Database","UAT","P2","High","High","Two clinician sessions; same encounter open in both","1. Both users open the same encounter | 2. User A edits and saves | 3. User B edits and attempts to save the stale copy","EncounterID=ENC-55","User B is prevented from silently overwriting User A's change via optimistic locking and is prompted to reload and reconcile","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-031","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0054","UAT Scenarios","Data Integrity & Recovery","Voided observation is retained for audit and excluded from active views","State Transition","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician logged in; an erroneous observation recorded","1. Void the observation with a reason | 2. Confirm it disappears from the active dashboard | 3. Query the audit or void history","VoidReason=Entered in error","Voided observation is hidden from active clinical views but remains recoverable in the audit history with reason, user and timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-031","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0055","UAT Scenarios","Reporting Day-in-Life","Department manager runs a daily activity report scoped to their location only","Security","UAT","P2","Medium","Medium","Manager logged in with location-scoped reporting privilege","1. Open the daily activity report | 2. Run for the current date | 3. Inspect the patient and encounter rows | 4. Attempt to widen the scope to another location","Location=OPD-1; Date=today","Report returns only the manager's location data, totals reconcile to source encounters, and cross-location data is not accessible","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-032","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0056","UAT Scenarios","Reporting Day-in-Life","Aggregate report suppresses small cells to protect privacy","Security","UAT","P3","Medium","Medium","Analyst logged in; aggregate report with small subgroup counts","1. Run an aggregate report containing a subgroup with a count below the suppression threshold | 2. Inspect the small-count cells","Threshold=5","Cells below the small-count threshold are suppressed or masked to prevent re-identification while totals remain","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-032","PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0057","UAT Scenarios","Accessibility in Workflow","Triage nurse completes vitals entry using keyboard only","Accessibility","UAT","P2","Medium","Medium","Nurse logged in; triage form open; keyboard-only operation","1. Tab through all vitals fields in logical order | 2. Enter values without a mouse | 3. Trigger save via keyboard | 4. Confirm focus moves to the confirmation","Input=keyboard-only","All fields are reachable and operable by keyboard in a logical order, focus is visible, and the encounter saves without mouse use","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-033","Accessibility","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0058","UAT Scenarios","Accessibility in Workflow","Critical allergy alert is announced by a screen reader","Accessibility","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician logged in; screen reader active; allergy alert will trigger","1. Trigger the allergy interaction alert | 2. Confirm the screen reader announces the alert text and role | 3. Confirm the alert can be acknowledged via keyboard","Tool=Screen reader","The allergy alert is announced as an alert with its full text and is acknowledgeable by keyboard, ensuring no safety-critical alert is missed","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-033","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0059","UAT Scenarios","Session & Security in Workflow","Idle session timeout protects an open chart at an unattended workstation","Security","UAT","P1","High","High","Clinician logged in with a patient chart open; idle timeout configured","1. Open a patient chart | 2. Leave the workstation idle past the timeout | 3. Return and attempt to interact","IdleTimeout=15 min","The session locks or expires after the configured idle period and re-authentication is required before any further access to PHI","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-034","Security; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0060","UAT Scenarios","Session & Security in Workflow","Wrong-patient guard: order placement on the wrong open chart is interrupted","Negative","UAT","P1","Critical","High","Clinician logged in; two patient charts opened in sequence","1. Open patient A then open patient B | 2. Begin an order intending patient A but on patient B's chart | 3. Observe the patient-confirmation step","PatientA=PT-100; PatientB=PT-205","An active patient indicator and confirmation step make the wrong-patient context evident before the order commits, reducing wrong-patient errors","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-035","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0061","UAT Scenarios","Portability","Same UAT consult flow executes on the adapter against an alternate backend","API","UAT","P3","Medium","Medium","Resource Adapter Layer configured against an alternate FHIR backend; tester credentials valid","1. Run the core consult flow (open patient, diagnosis, order) through the adapter | 2. Verify resources land in the alternate backend | 3. Compare field mapping to the OpenMRS run","Backend=HAPI FHIR","The consult flow completes against the alternate backend with equivalent resources and field mappings, confirming portability of the scenario","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-036","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-UAT2-0062","UAT Scenarios","Exploratory","Day-in-the-life exploratory sweep of the outpatient journey for friction and defects","Exploratory","UAT","P3","Medium","Medium","Full outpatient environment available; charter and time-box defined","1. Time-box a session following one patient end to end | 2. Probe error handling, back-button, refresh and concurrent tabs | 3. Note any data loss, confusing states or safety gaps | 4. Log findings","Charter=Outpatient journey; Box=60 min","Exploratory findings are documented with reproduction notes and severity, surfacing friction and defects not covered by scripted cases","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-037","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-UAT2-0063","UAT Scenarios","Clinician Day-in-Life","Problem list reconciliation: resolve, reactivate and de-duplicate conditions","State Transition","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Clinician logged in; patient with several active and resolved problems","1. Mark an active problem resolved with a date | 2. Reactivate a previously resolved problem | 3. Identify and merge a duplicate condition | 4. Review the resulting problem list","Problems=HTN active,DM resolved","Each transition is dated and reflected on the problem list, duplicates collapse to one entry, and history of state changes is retained","Manual-Only","REQ-UAT2-006","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-UAT2-0064","UAT Scenarios","Biller Day-in-Life","Claim denial is recorded and a corrected resubmission is tracked","State Transition","UAT","P2","High","Medium","Biller logged in; a submitted claim returned as denied","1. Record the denial with the payer reason code | 2. Correct the offending line item | 3. Resubmit as a corrected claim | 4. Track the resubmission status","DenialCode=CO-16","The denial and reason are recorded, the corrected claim links to the original, and the resubmission status is tracked through to adjudication","Partially-Automatable","REQ-UAT2-014","Billing; Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-AUDIT2-0001","Audit & Compliance (deep)","PHI CRUD Audit","Verify an audit record is created when a patient demographic record is created","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Audit logging enabled; registration clerk logged in","1. Register a new synthetic patient | 2. Save the registration | 3. Open the audit/log viewer or query the audit store | 4. Locate the create event","PatientName=Test Synth01; DOB=1990-01-01","An audit entry exists for the create action capturing actor, action=CREATE, target patient UUID, UTC timestamp and source IP","Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-001","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0002","Audit & Compliance (deep)","PHI CRUD Audit","Verify update to PHI captures before and after values in the audit trail","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Existing synthetic patient; auditing of changed fields enabled","1. Open an existing patient | 2. Edit the address field | 3. Save | 4. Inspect the audit entry for the update","Old Address=1 Old St; New Address=2 New Ave","Audit entry records action=UPDATE with the prior and new field values (or a diff) for the changed attribute","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-001","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0003","Audit & Compliance (deep)","PHI CRUD Audit","Verify voiding (soft delete) of a clinical observation is audited as a delete action","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Patient with a saved observation; clinician logged in","1. Open the patient observation | 2. Void the observation with a reason | 3. Query the audit trail","Void Reason=Entered in error","Audit entry records action=DELETE/VOID, the void reason, actor and timestamp; observation marked voided not physically removed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-001","Clinical; Audit; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0004","Audit & Compliance (deep)","PHI CRUD Audit","Verify a read/view of a patient chart generates an access audit event","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Access auditing enabled; clinician logged in","1. Search and open a patient dashboard | 2. View the clinical summary | 3. Query the access audit log","Patient=Synth02","An access (READ) audit event is recorded with actor, patient UUID, view context and timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-002","PHI/Privacy; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0005","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Authentication Audit","Verify successful login is recorded with actor, timestamp and source","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Audit logging enabled","1. Navigate to login | 2. Authenticate with valid credentials | 3. Query the audit log for login events","User=clerk1","Audit entry shows event=LOGIN_SUCCESS with username, UTC timestamp, session id and originating IP","Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-003","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0006","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Authentication Audit","Verify failed login attempts are audited with reason","Negative","Integration","P1","High","High","Audit logging enabled; known user account exists","1. Submit login with a valid username and wrong password | 2. Repeat 3 times | 3. Query audit log","User=clerk1; Password=wrong","Each failure records event=LOGIN_FAILURE with username, reason=bad credentials, timestamp and IP; no password value logged","Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-003","Security; Audit; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0007","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Authentication Audit","Verify logout and session timeout are distinguished in the audit trail","State Transition","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","User logged in; short session timeout configured","1. Log in | 2. Log out explicitly and record event | 3. Log in again | 4. Idle until timeout | 5. Query audit log","Timeout=2 min","Audit distinguishes event=LOGOUT (user initiated) from event=SESSION_TIMEOUT with respective timestamps","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-003","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0008","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Authentication Audit","Verify account lockout after threshold failed logins is audited","Boundary","Integration","P1","High","High","Lockout threshold configured to N attempts","1. Submit N-1 bad logins (no lock) | 2. Submit Nth bad login | 3. Query audit log | 4. Attempt N+1","Threshold=5","At attempt N an event=ACCOUNT_LOCKED is audited; before N no lock event; attempt N+1 records blocked attempt","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-003","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0009","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Export Audit","Verify a data export of PHI generates an audit event with record count","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Export feature available; user with export rights","1. Run a patient list or report export to CSV | 2. Confirm download | 3. Query audit log","Export=PatientList; Format=CSV","Audit entry records event=EXPORT, actor, dataset name, record/row count, destination format and timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-004","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0010","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Export Audit","Verify bulk FHIR Bulk Data export ($export) is logged with request parameters","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","High","FHIR Bulk Data endpoint available; OAuth client authorized","1. Invoke GET [base]/Patient/$export | 2. Poll the status URL | 3. Retrieve NDJSON | 4. Inspect server audit log","_type=Patient,Observation","AuditEvent records the $export request, requesting client, _type/_since params, status polling and the produced file set","Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-004","Standards-FHIR; PHI/Privacy; Audit","Standards"
"TC-AUDIT2-0011","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Config Change Audit","Verify a global property / configuration change is audited","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Admin logged in; configuration auditing enabled","1. Open administration settings | 2. Change a global property value | 3. Save | 4. Query config audit log","Property=session.timeout; Value=15","Audit entry records config change with property name, old value, new value, admin actor and timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-005","Regulatory/Compliance; Audit; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0012","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Config Change Audit","Verify role/privilege assignment changes are audited","Security","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Admin logged in; RBAC auditing enabled","1. Open a user account | 2. Add a clinical role with PHI access | 3. Save | 4. Query the audit log","User=nurse2; Role=Clinician","Audit entry records the privilege grant: target user, role added, granting admin, timestamp; supports access-creep review","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-005","Security; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0013","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Config Change Audit","Verify disabling audit logging is itself audited (anti-tamper control)","Negative","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Admin with rights to toggle auditing","1. Open audit configuration | 2. Attempt to disable audit logging | 3. Save | 4. Re-enable and inspect log","Setting=AuditEnabled=false","An audit event for the audit-config change is recorded before/at disable; the disable action is non-silent and reversible action also logged","Manual-Only","REQ-AUDIT2-005","Regulatory/Compliance; Security; Audit; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0014","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Immutability","Verify audit records cannot be edited through the application UI","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Audit entries exist; admin logged in","1. Open the audit log viewer | 2. Attempt to edit an existing audit entry | 3. Observe available controls","Existing audit entry id","No UI control permits editing an audit record; audit entries are read-only","Manual-Only","REQ-AUDIT2-006","Audit; Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0015","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Immutability","Verify direct UPDATE on the audit table is rejected or detectably violates integrity","Database","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Read access to audit store; test DB","1. Identify an audit row | 2. Attempt SQL UPDATE on its actor field | 3. Re-run tamper/integrity check","UPDATE audit SET actor='x'","UPDATE is denied by DB grants/triggers, or if applied the integrity verification flags the row as tampered","Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-006","Audit; Data Integrity; Security","Platform"
"TC-AUDIT2-0016","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Immutability","Verify deletion of audit records is prevented or generates a higher-order audit","Negative","Database","P1","Critical","High","Audit rows exist; restricted DB account","1. Attempt to DELETE an audit row via UI and via SQL | 2. Observe result | 3. Inspect meta-audit","DELETE FROM audit WHERE id=...","Deletion is blocked; if a privileged purge runs, a meta-audit/retention event records who purged what and when","Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-006","Audit; Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-AUDIT2-0017","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Tamper Evidence","Verify each audit record carries a cryptographic hash chained to the prior record","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Tamper-evident audit configured (hash chaining)","1. Generate three sequential audit events | 2. Read stored hash of each | 3. Recompute hash(record + prev_hash) | 4. Compare","3 sequential events","Each record stores a hash equal to recomputed hash over its content plus previous record hash; chain verifies end to end","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-007","Security; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-AUDIT2-0018","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Tamper Evidence","Verify altering one audit record breaks the hash chain at and after that record","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Hash-chained audit with at least 5 records","1. Capture chain valid baseline | 2. Mutate the content of record 3 in store | 3. Run chain verification","Tampered record index=3","Verification fails starting at record 3; records 1-2 still verify; report pinpoints the first broken link","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-007","Security; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-AUDIT2-0019","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Tamper Evidence","Verify periodic audit integrity job alerts on chain or checksum mismatch","Functional","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Scheduled integrity verification job configured; alerting set","1. Introduce a checksum mismatch | 2. Trigger the integrity job | 3. Inspect alert channel","Mismatch injected","Job detects mismatch and raises an alert/notification to the compliance team with affected record range","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-007","Security; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-AUDIT2-0020","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Retention","Verify audit records are retained for the configured minimum period","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Retention policy configured (e.g., 6 years); date manipulation possible in test","1. Create an audit record dated just under retention age | 2. Run retention/purge job | 3. Verify record still present","Retention=6y; Record age=6y minus 1 day","Record younger than retention boundary is retained after the purge job runs","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-008","Regulatory/Compliance; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-AUDIT2-0021","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Retention","Verify audit records older than retention plus grace are purged with a purge audit entry","Boundary","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Retention configured; purge job available","1. Seed a record dated just beyond retention+grace | 2. Run purge job | 3. Verify removal and meta-audit","Record age=6y+grace+1 day","Over-age record is purged; a purge/meta-audit entry records the purge action, count and operator","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-008","Regulatory/Compliance; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-AUDIT2-0022","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Retention","Verify legal hold suspends purge of audit records under hold","Decision Table","System","P1","High","High","Legal hold feature available; retention purge job","1. Place a legal hold on a patient/audit subset | 2. Age records beyond retention | 3. Run purge | 4. Vary hold on/off and over/under age","Hold=on/off; Age=over/under","Records under active legal hold are never purged regardless of age; only non-held over-age records are purged","Manual-Only","REQ-AUDIT2-008","Regulatory/Compliance; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-AUDIT2-0023","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Access Reports","Verify who-accessed-this-patient report lists all accessors with timestamps","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Multiple users have viewed a target patient; access auditing on","1. Open compliance access report | 2. Filter by target patient | 3. Run report","Patient=Synth03","Report lists every distinct accessor, access action, context and UTC timestamp for the patient; matches recorded access events","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-009","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0024","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Access Reports","Verify what-did-user-access report (who/what/when/where) for a single actor","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Target user has performed multiple PHI actions","1. Open user activity report | 2. Filter by actor and date range | 3. Run","User=nurse2; Range=last 7 days","Report shows what records, what actions, when (timestamp) and where (workstation/IP) for the actor; covers who/what/when/where","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-009","PHI/Privacy; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-AUDIT2-0025","Audit & Compliance (deep)","Access Reports","Verify access report includes the where dimension (IP/workstation/location)","Functional","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Access events capture source location","1. Generate access from two distinct IPs | 2. Run access report | 3. Inspect where column","IP1=10.0.0.5; IP2=10.0.0.9","Report distinguishes access by source IP/workstation/location for each event","Partially-Automatable","REQ-AUDIT2-009","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Security","OpenMRS"
