"TC-NOTIF2-0001","Notifications & Alerts (deep)","Critical Result Alert","Generate critical-result alert when a panic-value lab result is finalized","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Lab order resulted; result value flagged as critical/panic per reference range; ordering provider configured as alert recipient","1. Resulent a lab observation with a value beyond the panic threshold | 2. Finalize the result | 3. Inspect the alert engine queue for the ordering provider | 4. Open the ordering provider in-app inbox","Test=Potassium; Value=7.2 mmol/L; PanicHigh=6.5; Provider=Dr Synthetic","A critical-result alert is generated for the ordering provider with the result value, panic flag, patient context and Pending acknowledgement state","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF2-001","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF2-0002","Notifications & Alerts (deep)","Critical Result Alert","Critical alert not raised for in-range result at exact upper reference boundary","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Reference range configured with PanicHigh=6.5 mmol/L; result entered exactly at the non-critical boundary","1. Result a lab observation at the exact upper normal boundary | 2. Finalize the result | 3. Inspect the alert queue","Test=Potassium; Value=6.5 mmol/L; PanicHigh=6.5 (exclusive)","No critical alert is generated; value at the non-panic boundary is treated as non-critical per range definition","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF2-001","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
