"TC-NOTIF2-0004","Notifications & Alerts (deep)","Critical Result Alert","Critical result alert routed to covering provider when ordering provider is off-shift","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Ordering provider has an active coverage/on-call delegation; critical result finalized outside ordering provider working hours","1. Configure coverage from ordering provider to covering provider | 2. Finalize a critical result outside ordering provider hours | 3. Inspect recipient resolution | 4. Confirm delivery target","OrderingProvider=Dr A (off-shift); CoveringProvider=Dr B; Result=Critical","Alert recipient resolves to the covering provider per the coverage decision table; ordering provider receives an informational copy","Manual-Only","REQ-NOTIF2-002","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF2-0005","Notifications & Alerts (deep)","Critical Result Alert","Unacknowledged critical alert escalates after timeout to supervising clinician","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Critical alert delivered to primary recipient; escalation timeout configured to 15 minutes; supervisor defined as tier-2 recipient","1. Deliver a critical alert to the primary recipient | 2. Do not acknowledge within the timeout | 3. Allow the escalation timer to elapse | 4. Inspect tier-2 recipient inbox and alert state","EscalationTimeout=15m; Tier1=Dr A; Tier2=Charge Nurse","Alert transitions Delivered -> Escalated; a new notification is delivered to the tier-2 supervisor while the original remains open and auditable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-NOTIF2-003","Patient Safety; Audit","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF2-0006","Notifications & Alerts (deep)","Escalation Chain","Multi-tier escalation chain walks all tiers when each tier fails to acknowledge","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Three-tier escalation chain configured Tier1->Tier2->Tier3 with 10m timeouts; no recipient acknowledges","1. Trigger a critical alert at Tier1 | 2. Let Tier1 timeout elapse | 3. Let Tier2 timeout elapse | 4. Inspect final state and recipients","Chain=Dr A->Dr B->Medical Director; Timeout=10m each","Alert escalates sequentially through all three tiers; each tier receives a notification; final unacknowledged state is flagged for manual intervention and fully audited","Manual-Only","REQ-NOTIF2-003","Patient Safety; Audit","Platform"
