"TC-NOTIF2-0008","Notifications & Alerts (deep)","Drug Interaction Alert","Generate drug-drug interaction alert at order entry for a contraindicated pair","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Patient has an active medication on the medication list; clinician ordering a second drug with a known severe interaction","1. Open the patient medication ordering form | 2. Enter a drug that severely interacts with an active medication | 3. Attempt to sign the order | 4. Observe interaction alert","ActiveDrug=Warfarin; NewDrug=Aspirin; Severity=Major","A drug-drug interaction alert is presented at order entry naming both drugs, severity Major, and requiring override reason to proceed","Manual-Only","REQ-NOTIF2-004","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-NOTIF2-0009","Notifications & Alerts (deep)","Drug Interaction Alert","Override of interaction alert requires and records a documented reason","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Interaction alert is displayed during order entry; override reason is mandatory by policy","1. Trigger an interaction alert | 2. Attempt to override without entering a reason | 3. Enter a valid override reason and proceed | 4. Inspect the audit log","Override reason blank then ""Benefit outweighs risk, monitored""","Override is blocked until a reason is supplied; once supplied the order proceeds and the override reason plus user and timestamp are written to the audit log","Manual-Only","REQ-NOTIF2-004","Patient Safety; Audit","Platform"
