"TC-DATAQ-0001","Data Quality & Migration","Duplicate Detection","Detect probable duplicate patients via deterministic match on identifier plus name","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Duplicate-detection job configured; two records share national identifier with name variants","1. Load source dataset containing record A and record B sharing the same national identifier | 2. Run the deterministic duplicate-detection pass keyed on identifier+last name | 3. Open the candidate-duplicate worklist | 4. Inspect the matched pair and match key","A=Maria Tester (NID 900112233); B=Maria Testor (NID 900112233)","The pair A/B is flagged as a probable duplicate with match reason ""identifier+name"" and surfaced on the duplicate worklist for steward review","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-001","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0002","Data Quality & Migration","Duplicate Detection","Probabilistic fuzzy match scores near-duplicate names above threshold","Functional","System","P2","High","High","Probabilistic matching enabled with configurable score threshold of 0.85","1. Load two records with similar demographics but no shared identifier | 2. Run the probabilistic matcher using name, DOB and gender | 3. Review the computed match score | 4. Confirm placement on the worklist relative to threshold","A=Jon Smith DOB 1980-01-02 M; B=John Smyth DOB 1980-01-02 M; Threshold=0.85","The pair scores at or above 0.85 and is flagged as a probable duplicate; the score and contributing fields are displayed","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-001","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0003","Data Quality & Migration","Duplicate Detection","Boundary: match score exactly at threshold is treated as a match","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Probabilistic matcher threshold configured at 0.85 inclusive","1. Construct a record pair engineered to yield score exactly 0.850 | 2. Run the matcher | 3. Inspect classification of the pair","Computed score=0.850; Threshold=0.85 (inclusive)","Pair at score 0.850 is classified as a match (threshold is inclusive); pair at 0.849 would be non-match","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-002","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0004","Data Quality & Migration","Duplicate Detection","Negative: distinct twins with same DOB and surname are not auto-merged","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Two genuine sibling/twin records exist with shared surname and DOB but distinct identifiers","1. Load twin records sharing surname and DOB but differing first name and identifier | 2. Run duplicate detection | 3. Review classification | 4. Attempt any auto-merge action","A=Anna Tester NID 700100 DOB 2015-05-01; B=Anita Tester NID 700101 DOB 2015-05-01","Records are NOT auto-merged; at most flagged for manual review with differing identifier noted; no silent data loss occurs","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-002","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0005","Data Quality & Migration","Duplicate Detection","Decision table for merge eligibility across identifier and demographic agreement","Decision Table","System","P2","High","High","Merge rule engine configured with identifier-match and demographic-match inputs","1. Apply rule combinations: identifier match Y/N x DOB match Y/N x name match Y/N | 2. For each combination run the eligibility evaluation | 3. Record the engine decision (auto-merge / review / no-action)","Combos: (ID=Y,DOB=Y,Name=Y)->auto; (ID=Y,DOB=N,Name=Y)->review; (ID=N,DOB=Y,Name=Y)->review; (ID=N,DOB=N,Name=N)->no-action","Each combination yields the documented decision; no combination with identifier mismatch results in auto-merge","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-002","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0006","Data Quality & Migration","Duplicate Detection","Survivorship rule keeps most-recent non-null value during dedupe consolidation","Functional","Integration","P2","High","High","Survivorship policy: prefer most-recent non-null per field","1. Identify a confirmed duplicate pair where each holds different non-null phone numbers | 2. Run consolidation with survivorship policy | 3. Inspect the surviving golden record","A phone=555-0001 updated 2024-01; B phone=555-0002 updated 2025-06","Golden record retains the most-recent non-null phone 555-0002; superseded value preserved in history/audit","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-003","Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0007","Data Quality & Migration","Completeness Checks","Required-field completeness check flags rows missing mandatory demographics","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Completeness ruleset defines mandatory fields: identifier, name, gender, birthdate","1. Load a batch where some rows lack gender or birthdate | 2. Run the completeness validation pass | 3. Open the completeness report | 4. Inspect flagged rows and reason codes","Row 5 missing gender; Row 9 missing birthdate","Rows 5 and 9 are flagged incomplete with field-level reason codes; completeness percentage is reported per field and overall","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-004","Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0008","Data Quality & Migration","Completeness Checks","Boundary: completeness threshold gate blocks load below configured percentage","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Load gate configured to require >= 95% completeness on mandatory fields","1. Prepare a batch computed to yield 94.9% mandatory completeness | 2. Submit batch to the gated loader | 3. Observe gate decision | 4. Repeat with a batch at exactly 95.0%","Batch1 completeness=94.9%; Batch2 completeness=95.0%; Gate>=95%","Batch1 is rejected by the gate; Batch2 at exactly 95.0% passes the gate (inclusive boundary)","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-004","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0009","Data Quality & Migration","Validity Checks","Validity check rejects birthdate in the future","Negative","System","P1","High","High","Validity ruleset enforces birthdate <= load date","1. Load a record with birthdate set after today | 2. Run validity validation | 3. Inspect error report","Birthdate=2099-01-01; Load date=2026-07-01","Record is flagged invalid with reason ""birthdate in future""; record is quarantined and not promoted to target","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-005","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0010","Data Quality & Migration","Validity Checks","Boundary: age 0 (birthdate equals load date) is accepted as valid","Boundary","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Validity rule accepts birthdate up to and including load date","1. Load a newborn record with birthdate equal to load date | 2. Run validity validation | 3. Inspect result","Birthdate=2026-07-01; Load date=2026-07-01","Record is accepted as valid (age 0 newborn); no future-date error is raised","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-005","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0011","Data Quality & Migration","Validity Checks","Gender code outside allowed value set is rejected","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","Validity rule constrains administrative gender to value set male|female|other|unknown","1. Load a record with gender code outside the value set | 2. Run validity validation | 3. Inspect reason code","Gender=X9; Allowed=male|female|other|unknown","Record flagged invalid with ""gender not in value set""; the offending code is captured in the error report","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-005","Data Integrity; Standards-FHIR","Standards"
"TC-DATAQ-0012","Data Quality & Migration","Validity Checks","Pairwise validation across format, range and code-set rules on demographics","Pairwise","System","P2","High","Medium","Validity engine applies independent rules for format, range and code-set","1. Generate pairwise combinations of {phone format valid/invalid} x {postal range valid/invalid} x {country code valid/invalid} | 2. Load each combination | 3. Capture which rule(s) fire per row","Combos covering each pair of conditions at least once","Each rule fires independently and correctly for its triggering condition; combined invalid rows accumulate multiple reason codes without masking","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-005","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0013","Data Quality & Migration","Consistency Checks","Cross-field consistency: deceased flag true requires death date present","Negative","System","P1","High","High","Consistency rule: dead=true implies deathDate not null and >= birthDate","1. Load a record with dead=true but null death date | 2. Run consistency validation | 3. Load a second record with dead=true and death date before birthdate | 4. Inspect both results","R1 dead=true deathDate=null; R2 dead=true birthDate=1990-01-01 deathDate=1980-01-01","R1 flagged ""death date required when deceased""; R2 flagged ""death date precedes birth date""; both quarantined","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-006","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0014","Data Quality & Migration","Consistency Checks","Referential consistency: encounter visit type matches an existing visit","Database","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Target schema enforces encounter.visit_id FK to visit table","1. Load encounters whose visit_id references a non-existent visit | 2. Run referential consistency check | 3. Inspect orphan report","Encounter E100 visit_id=V999 (no such visit)","Encounter E100 reported as orphaned FK; row is rejected or routed to remediation; no orphan inserted into target","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-007","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DATAQ-0015","Data Quality & Migration","Consistency Checks","Unit-of-measure consistency for vitals across source systems","Functional","System","P2","High","High","Transformation maps source weight units to canonical kg","1. Load source rows with weight in lb and weight in kg | 2. Apply unit normalization transform | 3. Verify canonical stored values and UCUM unit code","Source: 154 lb and 70 kg","154 lb is converted to 69.85 kg (within tolerance) and 70 kg passes through; both stored with UCUM code kg; no double conversion","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-008","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DATAQ-0016","Data Quality & Migration","Row-Count Reconciliation","Source-to-target row-count reconciliation per table after ETL","Database","Integration","P1","Critical","High","ETL completed for patient, encounter, obs tables; reconciliation report available","1. Capture source row counts per table before load | 2. Run the ETL load | 3. Capture target row counts per table | 4. Compare counts accounting for documented filters","Source: patient=10000, encounter=85000, obs=500000","Target counts equal source counts minus documented exclusions for each table; any variance is itemized with reason; zero unexplained delta","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-009","Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0017","Data Quality & Migration","Row-Count Reconciliation","Negative: silent row drop on transform error is detected by reconciliation","Negative","Integration","P1","Critical","High","One transform rule throws on malformed rows that are skipped without logging","1. Seed source with 5 rows that trigger the silent transform exception | 2. Run ETL | 3. Run row-count reconciliation | 4. Compare expected vs actual loaded counts","Source=1000 rows; 5 malformed; expected loaded=1000 (none should be silently dropped)","Reconciliation detects a 5-row shortfall and fails the run; the 5 rows are surfaced in a rejects table rather than silently lost","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-009","Patient Safety; Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0018","Data Quality & Migration","Field Reconciliation","Field-level checksum reconciliation for critical clinical columns","Database","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Reconciliation computes per-column hash/aggregate on source and target","1. Compute aggregate checksum of obs.value_numeric on source | 2. Run ETL | 3. Compute the same aggregate on target | 4. Compare checksums and aggregate sums","Source SUM(value_numeric)=1234567.89","Target aggregate equals source aggregate exactly; any mismatch identifies affected rows for investigation","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-010","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
