"TC-DATAQ-0021","Data Quality & Migration","Transformation Rules","Code-system mapping transforms legacy diagnosis codes to ICD-10","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Mapping table ICD-9 to ICD-10 loaded; unmapped codes routed to exceptions","1. Load encounters with ICD-9 diagnosis codes | 2. Apply the code-system mapping transform | 3. Verify mapped target codes | 4. Inspect unmapped exceptions","ICD-9 250.00 -> ICD-10 E11.9; ICD-9 V99.9 unmapped","Mapped codes are correctly translated to ICD-10; unmapped code V99.9 is routed to the exceptions queue, not dropped or defaulted","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-012","Clinical; Data Integrity; Standards-FHIR","Standards"
"TC-DATAQ-0022","Data Quality & Migration","Transformation Rules","Decision table for null-handling strategy by target field nullability","Decision Table","System","P2","High","Medium","Transform null-policy: NOT NULL target with no default -> reject; nullable -> pass null; coded with default -> apply default","1. For each target field type apply a null source value | 2. Evaluate the transform null-handling decision | 3. Record outcome per field class","Fields: birthdate(NOT NULL,no default); middle_name(nullable); status(coded,default=active)","NOT NULL no-default field rejects null row; nullable field stores null; coded-with-default field applies ""active""; outcomes match the table","Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-011","Data Integrity","Platform"
