"TC-DATAQ-0031","Data Quality & Migration","Rollback","Failed migration run rolls back atomically leaving target unchanged","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Migration wrapped in a transaction or has a defined rollback procedure; snapshot/baseline captured","1. Capture target baseline state | 2. Start migration run | 3. Inject a fatal error midway (e.g., constraint violation) | 4. Observe rollback | 5. Compare target to baseline","Baseline target rows=10000; failure injected after 4000 rows staged","All 4000 partial rows are rolled back; target returns exactly to the 10000-row baseline; no partial/committed data remains","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-016","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DATAQ-0032","Data Quality & Migration","Rollback","State transition of a migration batch: pending to running to committed or rolled-back","State Transition","System","P2","High","High","Batch status model: PENDING, RUNNING, VALIDATING, COMMITTED, ROLLED_BACK, FAILED","1. Create a batch (PENDING) | 2. Start it (RUNNING) | 3. Pass validation (VALIDATING) | 4a. Commit (COMMITTED) | 4b. Alternatively force validation failure to drive ROLLED_BACK | 5. Attempt an illegal transition from COMMITTED back to RUNNING","Batch B1 happy path; Batch B2 validation-fail path","Legal transitions succeed and are audited; illegal transition COMMITTED->RUNNING is rejected; terminal states are immutable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-016","Data Integrity; Audit","Platform"
