"TC-DATAQ-0045","Data Quality & Migration","Security","PHI is masked in migration logs and rejects/exception tables","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Logging policy requires PHI masking; rejects table stores hashed/tokenized identifiers","1. Trigger validation failures that route rows to the rejects table | 2. Inspect migration logs and the rejects table | 3. Search for clear-text identifiers, names and birthdates","Rejected rows containing NID, name, DOB","Logs and rejects table contain masked/tokenized PHI only; no clear-text identifier, name or DOB is exposed; access is audit-logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DATAQ-023","PHI/Privacy; Security; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
