"TC-DEATH-0009","Death & Record Lifecycle","Mark Deceased - Decision Table","Validate Dead flag, date and cause combinations via decision table","Decision Table","Regression","P1","High","High","Clinician; death form available","1. For each rule set Dead/Date/Cause as specified | 2. Attempt Save | 3. Record acceptance or rejection","R1 Dead=Yes,Date=valid,Cause=coded=>Accept; R2 Dead=Yes,Date=empty,Cause=coded=>Reject; R3 Dead=Yes,Date=valid,Cause=empty=>Reject(if required); R4 Dead=No,Date=set,Cause=set=>Date/Cause cleared/ignored; R5 Dead=Yes,Date=future=>Reject","System enforces each decision rule exactly; only valid combinations persist and invalid ones are rejected with appropriate messages","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0010","Death & Record Lifecycle","Reverse Deceased","Reverse an erroneously recorded death by setting Dead back to No","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Clinician with edit privilege; a patient currently flagged deceased","1. Open the deceased patient | 2. Open Mark Patient Deceased action | 3. Toggle Dead to No | 4. Save | 5. Reopen the record","Patient currently dead=true","Patient transitions deceased->living; deceased banner removed; deathDate and causeOfDeath cleared or nulled per config; change is audited","Automatable","REQ-DEATH-003","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0011","Death & Record Lifecycle","Reverse Deceased","Verify death-derived data is reconciled after reversing deceased status","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","High","A patient was reversed from deceased to living (see reverse flow)","1. Reverse the deceased flag to No | 2. Inspect deathDate, causeOfDeath and any deceased indicators | 3. Inspect previously auto-cancelled future appointments","Patient previously dead with cancelled future appointments","Death attributes are cleared; UI no longer shows deceased; previously cancelled appointments are NOT silently auto-restored and require manual review","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-003","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0012","Death & Record Lifecycle","Reverse Deceased - Audit","Confirm both mark-deceased and reverse actions are captured in the audit trail","Audit","Integration","P1","High","High","Auditing/logging enabled; admin with audit access","1. Mark a patient deceased | 2. Reverse the deceased flag | 3. Open the audit/log view or query the change log","Patient marked then reversed by user clinician1","Audit log records both transitions with actor, timestamp, old and new values for dead, deathDate and causeOfDeath","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-009","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0013","Death & Record Lifecycle","Downstream - Appointments","Future scheduled appointments are cancelled or flagged when a patient is marked deceased","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Patient has one or more future appointments scheduled; appointment module enabled","1. Schedule a future appointment for a living patient | 2. Mark the patient deceased | 3. Open the appointment list","Future Appt=2026-08-10; Death Date=2026-07-01","Future appointments are cancelled or clearly flagged as deceased; no active future appointment remains bookable for the patient","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-004","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0014","Death & Record Lifecycle","Downstream - Appointments","Block new appointment scheduling for a deceased patient","Negative","Integration","P1","High","High","Patient is flagged deceased; scheduler with booking privilege","1. Open the deceased patient | 2. Attempt to schedule a new future appointment | 3. Attempt Save","Patient dead=true; New Appt=2026-08-01","Scheduling is blocked or requires explicit override with warning that the patient is deceased; no silent booking","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-004","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-DEATH-0015","Death & Record Lifecycle","Downstream - Orders","Active drug and lab orders are discontinued or flagged on patient death","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Patient has active drug orders and pending lab orders; orders module enabled","1. Place active drug and lab orders for a living patient | 2. Mark the patient deceased | 3. Review the active orders list","Active drug order + pending lab order present; Death Date=2026-07-01","Active and future-dated orders are discontinued or flagged for review; clinicians are alerted; no medication continues active against a deceased patient","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-005","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0016","Death & Record Lifecycle","Downstream - Orders","Block placing new active medication orders for a deceased patient","Negative","Integration","P2","High","High","Patient flagged deceased; provider with ordering privilege","1. Open the deceased patient | 2. Attempt to place a new active drug order | 3. Save","Patient dead=true; Drug=Paracetamol 500mg","Order placement is blocked or requires an explicit justified override; deceased status is surfaced to the ordering provider","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-005","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-DEATH-0017","Death & Record Lifecycle","Downstream - Visits","Open active visit handling when a patient is marked deceased","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Patient has an open active visit; clinician","1. Ensure the patient has an active open visit | 2. Mark the patient deceased with death date within the visit window | 3. Review visit status","Active visit started 2026-06-30; Death Date=2026-07-01","Active visit is closed/stopped at or after the death datetime or flagged consistently; no active visit persists indefinitely for a deceased patient","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-004","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0018","Death & Record Lifecycle","Void Person/Patient","Void a patient record and verify it is excluded from searches and active lists","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Admin/superuser with void privilege; a non-deceased test patient","1. Open the patient | 2. Invoke Delete/Void with a reason | 3. Confirm | 4. Search for the patient in normal find-patient","Void Reason=Created in error","Patient is voided (soft-deleted); excluded from standard search and active patient lists; record retained in database with voided=true, voidReason, voidedBy, dateVoided","Automatable","REQ-DEATH-006","Data Integrity; Audit; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0019","Death & Record Lifecycle","Void Person/Patient","Reject voiding a patient without providing a void reason","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Admin with void privilege","1. Open the patient | 2. Invoke Void | 3. Leave the reason blank | 4. Attempt to confirm","Void Reason=(empty)","Void is blocked; validation requires a non-empty void reason; record remains active","Automatable","REQ-DEATH-006","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0020","Death & Record Lifecycle","Unvoid Person/Patient","Unvoid a previously voided patient and restore visibility","State Transition","System","P2","High","High","A voided patient exists; admin with manage privilege","1. Locate the voided patient via admin/manage | 2. Invoke Unvoid/Restore | 3. Search in normal find-patient","Patient voided=true","Patient is restored; voided=false; reappears in standard searches and active lists; restoration is audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-006","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0021","Death & Record Lifecycle","Void - Cascade","Voiding a patient cascades to associated encounters, visits and observations","Database","Integration","P2","High","High","Patient with encounters, visits and obs; admin with DB/audit visibility","1. Note encounter/visit/obs IDs for the patient | 2. Void the patient | 3. Inspect associated encounter, visit and obs voided flags","Patient with 2 encounters and obs","Associated encounters, visits and observations are marked voided with consistent voidReason and dateVoided; no orphaned active child records remain","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-006","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0022","Death & Record Lifecycle","Retire Metadata","Retire a death-related metadata concept and verify it is hidden from new entry but preserved on existing records","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Admin with manage-concepts privilege; an active cause-of-death concept used on a record","1. Mark a patient deceased using a cause concept | 2. Retire that concept with a reason | 3. Attempt to select it for a new death entry | 4. View the existing deceased patient","Concept=Old Cause Code; Retire Reason=Replaced by ICD mapping","Retired concept is unavailable for new selections but historical records still display the original value; retiredBy/dateRetired/retireReason set","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-007","Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0023","Death & Record Lifecycle","Retire vs Void","Differentiate retire (metadata) from void (data) behavior via decision table","Decision Table","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Admin with both privileges","1. For metadata object apply Retire and check new-entry availability and historical display | 2. For patient data apply Void and check search visibility | 3. Compare semantics","Metadata=Concept/Location; Data=Patient/Encounter","Retire hides metadata from new use while preserving history; Void soft-deletes data from active views; neither performs a hard delete; behaviors are not interchangeable","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-007","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0024","Death & Record Lifecycle","Archival","Archive a deceased patient record after the configured active-retention window","Functional","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Patient deceased beyond the configured active window; archival policy configured","1. Identify a deceased patient past the active-retention threshold | 2. Run/trigger the archival job or workflow | 3. Verify record moved to archived state","Death Date older than active window threshold","Record transitions to archived state; remains retrievable for legal/clinical retrieval but is excluded from day-to-day active workflows","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-008","Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-DEATH-0025","Death & Record Lifecycle","Retention Policy","Enforce minimum legal retention period before any purge of a deceased record","Boundary","System","P1","Critical","High","Retention policy with a defined minimum retention period from death date","1. Attempt to purge a deceased record before the retention minimum elapses | 2. Attempt to purge a record after the retention period elapses","Retention=10 years post-death; Record A death=2025-01-01; Record B death=2010-01-01","Purge is blocked for Record A (within retention) and only permitted for Record B (past retention); boundary at exactly the retention date is enforced per policy","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-008","Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity; PHI/Privacy","Platform"
"TC-DEATH-0026","Death & Record Lifecycle","Retention Policy - Boundary","Validate retention boundary on the exact expiry day (day-of vs day-after)","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Retention policy defined to the day","1. Set record death date so retention expires exactly today | 2. Evaluate purge eligibility on expiry day | 3. Evaluate on day after","Retention=7 years; Death so expiry=today","Eligibility honors the documented inclusive/exclusive boundary consistently; no off-by-one purge of still-protected records","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-008","Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DEATH-0027","Death & Record Lifecycle","Audit","Verify audit log immutability and completeness for the full death lifecycle","Audit","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Auditing enabled; admin audit access","1. Perform mark-deceased, reverse, void, unvoid, retire on test objects | 2. Open audit trail | 3. Attempt to edit or delete an audit entry","Sequence of lifecycle actions by clinician1/admin1","Every action is logged with actor, timestamp and before/after values; audit entries cannot be edited or deleted via the UI","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-009","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0028","Death & Record Lifecycle","RBAC - Security","Enforce privilege checks for mark-deceased, void and retire actions","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Users provisioned: clinician(no edit-patient), data-clerk, admin","1. As a user lacking the required privilege attempt mark-deceased | 2. Attempt void | 3. Attempt retire | 4. As privileged admin repeat","User without edit-patient/void/manage privileges","Each restricted action is denied for under-privileged users (403/no UI affordance) and permitted only for authorized roles; denials are logged","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-010","Security; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0029","Death & Record Lifecycle","Security","Prevent privilege escalation when reversing deceased or unvoiding via direct API","Security","Integration","P1","Critical","High","API access; a low-privilege token without edit-patient","1. Obtain a low-privilege session/token | 2. Call the REST endpoint to set dead=false or void=false directly | 3. Inspect response","REST PUT to patient with dead=false using clerk token","API rejects the unauthorized modification with 403; no state change occurs; attempt is audited","Automatable","REQ-DEATH-010","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0030","Death & Record Lifecycle","API - REST","Set deceased status via OpenMRS REST and verify persisted attributes","API","Integration","P2","High","Medium","REST enabled; privileged token; living test patient uuid","1. PUT/POST to /ws/rest/v1/patient/{uuid} or person with dead, deathDate, causeOfDeath | 2. GET the patient | 3. Inspect fields","dead=true; deathDate=2026-06-15; causeOfDeath=conceptUuid","API persists dead, deathDate and causeOfDeath; subsequent GET returns the same values with correct types","Automatable","REQ-DEATH-011","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0031","Death & Record Lifecycle","API - REST","Reject deceased update with an invalid causeOfDeath concept uuid","Negative","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","REST enabled; privileged token","1. PUT patient with dead=true and a non-existent causeOfDeath uuid | 2. Inspect response","causeOfDeath=00000000-bad-uuid","API returns a 4xx validation error; patient is not marked deceased with the invalid reference","Automatable","REQ-DEATH-011","Data Integrity; Standards-FHIR","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0032","Death & Record Lifecycle","FHIR - Patient.deceased","Expose deceased status via FHIR Patient.deceasedDateTime/deceasedBoolean","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","High","FHIR R4 module enabled; a deceased patient with a death date","1. GET /ws/fhir2/R4/Patient/{id} | 2. Inspect the deceased[x] element","Patient deceased with deathDate=2026-06-15","FHIR Patient returns deceasedDateTime=2026-06-15 (or deceasedBoolean=true when no date); element conforms to FHIR R4 Patient deceased[x] cardinality","Automatable","REQ-DEATH-012","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DEATH-0033","Death & Record Lifecycle","FHIR - deceasedBoolean","Represent deceased without a known date as deceasedBoolean=true","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR R4 enabled; patient flagged dead with no death date","1. Mark patient dead=true without a death date (if permitted) | 2. GET the FHIR Patient | 3. Inspect deceased[x]","dead=true; deathDate=null","FHIR returns deceasedBoolean=true and does not emit a fabricated deceasedDateTime","Automatable","REQ-DEATH-012","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DEATH-0034","Death & Record Lifecycle","FHIR - Reverse","Reverse deceased clears deceased[x] in the FHIR projection","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 enabled; a deceased patient subsequently reversed to living","1. Reverse the patient deceased status to living | 2. GET the FHIR Patient | 3. Inspect deceased[x]","Patient reversed to dead=false","FHIR Patient no longer contains deceasedDateTime/deceasedBoolean=true; resource reflects living status; projection is consistent","Automatable","REQ-DEATH-012","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DEATH-0035","Death & Record Lifecycle","HL7 - ADT A03","Outbound HL7 ADT^A03 discharge/death message carries patient death disposition","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 interface engine configured; outbound ADT feed for the SUT","1. Mark a patient deceased | 2. Capture the outbound HL7 message | 3. Inspect PID-29 (death date), PID-30 (death indicator) and PV1-36 discharge disposition","Death Date=2026-07-01; Disposition=Expired","ADT message populates PID-29 death date, PID-30 death indicator=Y and an Expired discharge disposition consistent with HL7 v2 semantics","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-013","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DEATH-0036","Death & Record Lifecycle","HL7 - Inbound","Inbound HL7 death notification updates patient deceased status idempotently","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 inbound listener configured; mapping for death fields","1. Send an inbound ADT message with PID-29/PID-30 death fields | 2. Re-send the identical message | 3. Inspect patient state","PID-29=20260701; PID-30=Y","Patient is marked deceased on first message; re-processing the identical message is idempotent and does not duplicate or corrupt the death record","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-013","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-DEATH-0037","Death & Record Lifecycle","Pairwise","Pairwise coverage of role, channel, date-validity and downstream-config","Pairwise","System","P2","High","Medium","Multiple roles, channels (UI/REST/HL7), and config flags available","1. Execute combinations: (Admin,UI,validDate,cascade-on),(Clinician,REST,futureDate,cascade-off),(Clerk,HL7,validDate,cascade-on),(Admin,REST,invalidDate,cascade-off) | 2. Record outcome per pairing","Role x Channel x DateValidity x CascadeConfig pairs","Each pairing behaves per its constraints: authorized+valid persists with correct cascade; unauthorized or invalid-date pairings are rejected; no pairing produces inconsistent state","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-001","Clinical; Security; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-DEATH-0038","Death & Record Lifecycle","Accessibility","Mark-deceased dialog is keyboard navigable and screen-reader accessible","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Screen reader and keyboard-only environment; clinician account","1. Open the Mark Patient Deceased dialog using keyboard only | 2. Tab through Dead toggle, date and cause fields | 3. Trigger a validation error | 4. Verify SR announcements and focus order","Keyboard-only; NVDA/VoiceOver","All controls are reachable and operable by keyboard; labels and required-field/error messages are announced; focus order is logical; meets WCAG 2.1 AA","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-014","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-DEATH-0039","Death & Record Lifecycle","Usability","Deceased indicator is clearly and consistently surfaced across patient views","Usability","Regression","P2","High","Medium","A deceased patient; access to dashboard, search results and header banner","1. Open the deceased patient dashboard | 2. View the header/banner | 3. Locate the patient in search results | 4. Open a clinical form","Patient dead=true","A consistent, prominent deceased indicator (banner/badge) is shown across dashboard, header, search results and clinical entry points to prevent ordering errors","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-015","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0040","Death & Record Lifecycle","Mark Deceased - Exploratory","Exploratory probe of conflicting and concurrent death edits","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Two clinician sessions on the same patient; test environment","1. Open the same living patient in two sessions | 2. In session A mark deceased and save | 3. In session B (stale view) attempt to edit demographics and save | 4. Observe conflict handling","Concurrent edit on patientUuid","Concurrency is handled safely (optimistic-lock/version error or last-consistent-write); no lost-update silently overwrites the death record; user is informed of the conflict","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-003","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0041","Death & Record Lifecycle","Database","Verify person table death attributes and child voided flags after lifecycle actions","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","DB read access to test instance; lifecycle actions performed","1. Query person row for dead, death_date, cause_of_death, changed_by, date_changed after mark-deceased | 2. Void the patient | 3. Query voided, voided_by, date_voided, void_reason on person and child encounter/obs rows","SQL on person, encounter, obs","Death attributes are stored with correct audit columns; void sets voided=1 with reason/actor/timestamp and cascades to children; no hard deletes occur","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-006","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-DEATH-0042","Death & Record Lifecycle","Billing - Downstream","Open billing/charges are flagged and new charges blocked on patient death","Functional","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Billing module enabled; patient with open charges; death applied","1. Ensure the patient has open/unsettled charges | 2. Mark the patient deceased | 3. Review billing status | 4. Attempt to add a new post-death dated charge","Open charge present; Death Date=2026-07-01","Open charges are flagged for estate/settlement handling; adding new service charges dated after death is blocked or warned; financial integrity preserved","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-016","Billing; Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-DEATH-0043","Death & Record Lifecycle","PHI/Privacy","Access to a deceased patient record still enforces PHI authorization and minimum-necessary","Security","System","P2","High","High","Deceased patient; users with and without legitimate access","1. As an authorized user open the deceased record | 2. As an unauthorized user attempt access | 3. Verify access is logged","Deceased patient; mixed-privilege users","Deceased records remain PHI-protected; unauthorized access is denied; all access is audited per minimum-necessary; post-mortem privacy obligations are honored","Partially-Automatable","REQ-DEATH-017","PHI/Privacy; Security; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","Standards"
"TC-DEATH-0044","Death & Record Lifecycle","Reverse - Decision Table","Decision table for reverse-deceased eligibility and downstream reconciliation","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Deceased patients in varied downstream states","1. R1 deceased with no downstream effects -> reverse | 2. R2 deceased with cancelled appts -> reverse + manual review | 3. R3 deceased with discontinued orders -> reverse + no auto-reactivation | 4. R4 archived/purged -> reverse blocked","Reverse against varying downstream states","Reverse succeeds where eligible and clears death attributes; downstream items are not auto-reactivated; reverse is blocked once record is archived/purged beyond reversible state","Manual-Only","REQ-DEATH-003","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0001","Inpatient / Ward Management","Admission (ADT)","Admit an active-visit patient to an inpatient ward via an Admission encounter","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active visit; an inpatient ward location with available beds exists","1. Open the patient with an active visit | 2. Start the Admit to Inpatient form | 3. Select admitting ward and admitting provider | 4. Enter admission datetime and admission diagnosis | 5. Save the encounter","Ward=Male Ward; Provider=Dr Smith; AdmitDate=now; Dx=Pneumonia","An Admission encounter is created, the patient is shown as Admitted to the selected ward, and the admission appears in the visit timeline with correct datetime and provider","Automatable","REQ-INPT-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0002","Inpatient / Ward Management","Admission (ADT)","Block admission when patient has no active visit","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient record exists with no active visit","1. Open the patient dashboard | 2. Attempt to start the Admit to Inpatient form","Visit=(none)","The system prevents admission and informs the user that an active visit is required before admitting","Automatable","REQ-INPT-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0003","Inpatient / Ward Management","Admission (ADT)","Reject a future-dated admission datetime beyond the allowed window","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active visit","1. Start the Admit to Inpatient form | 2. Set admission datetime to a future date/time | 3. Attempt to save","AdmitDate=now+2 days","A validation error is shown and the admission is not saved because the datetime is in the future","Automatable","REQ-INPT-002","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0004","Inpatient / Ward Management","Admission (ADT)","Reject admission datetime before the visit start datetime","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active visit started today","1. Start the Admit to Inpatient form | 2. Set admission datetime earlier than the visit start | 3. Attempt to save","VisitStart=08:00; AdmitDate=07:00 same day","A validation error is shown; admission cannot precede the visit start datetime","Automatable","REQ-INPT-002","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0005","Inpatient / Ward Management","Admission (ADT)","Prevent admitting a patient who is already admitted","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient already has an active inpatient admission","1. Open the admitted patient | 2. Attempt to start a second Admit to Inpatient form | 3. Observe behavior","Status=Already Admitted","The system blocks a duplicate admission and indicates the patient is already an inpatient","Automatable","REQ-INPT-003","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0006","Inpatient / Ward Management","Admission (ADT)","Admission requires an admitting provider","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active visit","1. Start the Admit to Inpatient form | 2. Leave admitting provider blank | 3. Attempt to save","Provider=(none)","A validation error is shown and the admission is not saved until a provider is selected","Automatable","REQ-INPT-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0007","Inpatient / Ward Management","ADT State Transition","Admit -> Transfer -> Discharge happy-path state transition","State Transition","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient admitted to Ward A; Ward B has free capacity","1. Confirm state Admitted in Ward A | 2. Perform Transfer to Ward B | 3. Confirm state Admitted in Ward B | 4. Perform Discharge | 5. Confirm state Discharged","WardA=Male Ward; WardB=ICU","Each transition is recorded as a discrete encounter with timestamps, the current state reflects the last action, and history shows Admit, Transfer, Discharge in order","Automatable","REQ-INPT-004","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0008","Inpatient / Ward Management","ADT State Transition","Disallow Transfer when patient is in Discharged state","State Transition","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient already discharged from current visit","1. Open the discharged patient | 2. Attempt to perform a Transfer action","State=Discharged","The Transfer action is unavailable or blocked because no active inpatient state exists","Automatable","REQ-INPT-004","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0009","Inpatient / Ward Management","ADT State Transition","Disallow Discharge when patient was never admitted","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active visit but no admission","1. Open the patient with an active outpatient visit | 2. Attempt to perform a Discharge action","State=Outpatient (not admitted)","The Discharge action is blocked or unavailable because there is no active admission to discharge","Automatable","REQ-INPT-004","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0010","Inpatient / Ward Management","ADT State Transition","Cancel an erroneous admission and verify state reverts","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in as Clinician with cancel privilege; patient admitted in error","1. Open the admitted patient | 2. Void or cancel the admission encounter with a reason | 3. Confirm","Reason=Entered in error","The admission is voided, the patient no longer shows as Admitted, the bed is released, and the void reason is auditable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-005","Patient Safety; Audit; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0011","Inpatient / Ward Management","Bed/Ward Assignment","Assign an available bed to an admitted patient","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; bed management configured; ward has at least one free bed","1. Open the admitted patient | 2. Open Assign Bed | 3. Select an available bed in the admitting ward | 4. Confirm assignment","Ward=ICU; Bed=ICU-03","The bed is assigned to the patient, the bed status changes to Occupied, and the ward view shows the patient in that bed","Automatable","REQ-INPT-010","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0012","Inpatient / Ward Management","Bed/Ward Assignment","Prevent assigning a bed already occupied by another patient","Negative","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; bed ICU-03 already occupied by Patient X","1. Open Patient Y admitted to ICU | 2. Open Assign Bed | 3. Attempt to select occupied bed ICU-03","Bed=ICU-03 (occupied)","The occupied bed is not selectable or assignment is rejected, preventing double-occupancy of a single bed","Automatable","REQ-INPT-011","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0013","Inpatient / Ward Management","Bed/Ward Assignment","Release a bed automatically on discharge","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient occupies bed ICU-03","1. Discharge the patient occupying ICU-03 | 2. Open the ward bed view","Bed=ICU-03","On discharge the bed status returns to Available and the bed is free for reassignment","Automatable","REQ-INPT-012","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0014","Inpatient / Ward Management","Bed/Ward Assignment","Reassign bed on ward transfer releases the source bed","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient in Male Ward bed MW-05; ICU has free bed","1. Transfer patient from Male Ward to ICU | 2. Assign ICU bed | 3. Check source bed MW-05 status","SrcBed=MW-05; DestBed=ICU-02","The source bed MW-05 is released to Available and the destination bed ICU-02 becomes Occupied","Automatable","REQ-INPT-012","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0015","Inpatient / Ward Management","Bed/Ward Assignment","Bed assignment respects gender-restricted ward configuration","Decision Table","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; Male Ward configured as male-only; Female Ward as female-only","1. Attempt to assign a female patient to a male-only bed | 2. Attempt to assign a male patient to a female-only bed | 3. Attempt valid same-gender assignments","PatientGender vs WardGender combinations","Mismatched gender assignments are blocked or warned per configuration; matching assignments succeed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-013","Clinical; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0016","Inpatient / Ward Management","Capacity Management","Block admission to a ward at full capacity","Boundary","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; target ward has all beds occupied","1. Attempt to admit/assign a patient to the full ward | 2. Observe capacity behavior","WardCapacity=10; Occupied=10","Admission/bed assignment to the full ward is blocked or routed to a waitlist with a capacity-full message","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-014","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0017","Inpatient / Ward Management","Capacity Management","Ward occupancy count updates on admit and discharge","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; ward shows 7/10 occupied","1. Admit one patient to the ward | 2. Verify occupancy 8/10 | 3. Discharge one patient | 4. Verify occupancy 7/10","Start=7/10","The occupancy counter increments on admission and decrements on discharge accurately and in real time","Automatable","REQ-INPT-014","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0018","Inpatient / Ward Management","Capacity Management","Ward occupancy dashboard shows correct percentages across wards","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Ward Manager; multiple wards with known occupancy","1. Open the ward occupancy dashboard | 2. Compare displayed occupancy % to known counts","ICU=8/10; MW=15/20","Each ward shows the correct occupied/total and percentage, and totals aggregate correctly","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-015","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0019","Inpatient / Ward Management","Ward Transfer","Transfer patient between wards records source and destination","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient admitted in Male Ward; ICU has capacity","1. Open the admitted patient | 2. Start Transfer form | 3. Select destination ICU and transfer datetime | 4. Enter transfer reason | 5. Save","Src=Male Ward; Dest=ICU; Reason=Deterioration","A Transfer encounter records source ward, destination ward, datetime and reason; current ward updates to ICU","Automatable","REQ-INPT-020","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0020","Inpatient / Ward Management","Ward Transfer","Reject transfer to the same ward the patient already occupies","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient currently in ICU","1. Start Transfer form | 2. Select destination = ICU (current ward) | 3. Attempt to save","Src=ICU; Dest=ICU","A validation error is shown; a no-op transfer to the same ward is not permitted","Automatable","REQ-INPT-020","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0021","Inpatient / Ward Management","Ward Transfer","Transfer datetime must not precede the admission datetime","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient admitted at 10:00 today","1. Start Transfer form | 2. Set transfer datetime to 09:00 same day | 3. Attempt to save","AdmitTime=10:00; TransferTime=09:00","A validation error is shown; a transfer cannot occur before admission","Automatable","REQ-INPT-021","Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0022","Inpatient / Ward Management","Ward Round Encounter","Record a ward round progress note for an inpatient","Functional","Sanity","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient is currently admitted","1. Open the admitted patient | 2. Start the Ward Round / Progress Note form | 3. Enter subjective, objective, assessment and plan | 4. Save","Note=SOAP; Provider=Dr Lee","A ward round encounter is saved under the active inpatient visit with provider, datetime and note content","Automatable","REQ-INPT-030","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0023","Inpatient / Ward Management","Ward Round Encounter","Multiple ward rounds across days appear chronologically in the visit","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient admitted for 3 days with one round per day","1. Open the patient visit timeline | 2. Review ward round encounters","Rounds=Day1,Day2,Day3","All ward round encounters display in correct chronological order with distinct dates and providers","Automatable","REQ-INPT-030","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0024","Inpatient / Ward Management","Ward Round Encounter","Ward round entry requires the patient to be currently admitted","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient discharged earlier today","1. Open the discharged patient | 2. Attempt to start a ward round on the closed inpatient context","State=Discharged","The ward round cannot be filed against a discharged/closed admission, or it warns the encounter falls outside an active admission","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-031","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0025","Inpatient / Ward Management","Inpatient Orders","Place an inpatient medication order tied to the active admission","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician with ordering privilege; patient admitted with active visit","1. Open the admitted patient | 2. Open Orders | 3. Add a drug order with dose, route, frequency and duration | 4. Sign the order","Drug=Ceftriaxone; Dose=1g; Route=IV; Freq=OD","The inpatient order is created active, linked to the admission encounter/visit, and appears on the active orders list","Automatable","REQ-INPT-040","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0026","Inpatient / Ward Management","Inpatient Orders","Discontinue an active inpatient order with a reason","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active inpatient drug order","1. Open active orders | 2. Discontinue the order | 3. Enter discontinue reason | 4. Sign","Reason=Therapy completed","The order transitions to Discontinued with a reason and stop datetime, and is no longer in active orders","Automatable","REQ-INPT-041","Clinical; Patient Safety; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0027","Inpatient / Ward Management","Inpatient Orders","Revise an active inpatient order preserves order history chain","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active drug order","1. Revise the dose of the active order | 2. Sign the revision | 3. Review order history","OldDose=1g; NewDose=2g","A new revision order is created linked to the previous order; history shows the original and revised orders with an audit trail","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-041","Clinical; Audit; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0028","Inpatient / Ward Management","Inpatient Orders","Allergy conflict warning when ordering a drug the patient is allergic to","Decision Table","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient admitted with a documented penicillin allergy","1. Place an order for a penicillin-class drug | 2. Observe interaction/allergy alert | 3. Acknowledge or cancel","Allergy=Penicillin; Order=Amoxicillin","An allergy alert is raised before signing; the clinician must acknowledge with a reason to override or cancel the order","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-042","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0029","Inpatient / Ward Management","Inpatient Orders","Active inpatient orders are auto-stopped on discharge per policy","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has active inpatient orders; auto-stop-on-discharge policy enabled","1. Discharge the patient | 2. Review the previously active inpatient orders","Policy=AutoStopOnDischarge","Active inpatient orders are stopped/expired at discharge so they do not remain active after the admission ends","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-043","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0030","Inpatient / Ward Management","Length of Stay","Length of stay computes correctly from admission to discharge","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient admitted and discharged on known dates","1. Open the completed admission | 2. View computed length of stay","Admit=2026-06-01 09:00; Discharge=2026-06-05 09:00","Length of stay is computed as 4 days (or per defined LOS rule), matching the admit-to-discharge interval","Automatable","REQ-INPT-050","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0031","Inpatient / Ward Management","Length of Stay","Same-day admission and discharge yields zero or one-day LOS per rule","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient admitted and discharged on the same calendar day","1. Admit at 08:00 | 2. Discharge at 14:00 same day | 3. View LOS","Admit=08:00; Discharge=14:00 same day","LOS reflects the configured same-day rule (e.g., 0 days or minimum 1 day) consistently","Automatable","REQ-INPT-050","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0032","Inpatient / Ward Management","Length of Stay","Current LOS for an in-progress admission counts from admit to now","Functional","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient still admitted (no discharge)","1. Open the active admission | 2. View current length of stay","Admit=3 days ago; Discharge=(none)","Current LOS shows elapsed time from admission to the current datetime and updates as time passes","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-051","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0033","Inpatient / Ward Management","Discharge (ADT)","Discharge an admitted patient with a discharge disposition","Functional","Sanity","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient currently admitted","1. Open the admitted patient | 2. Start the Discharge form | 3. Select disposition and discharge datetime | 4. Enter discharge diagnosis | 5. Save","Disposition=Home; Dx=Resolved pneumonia","A Discharge encounter is created, the patient state becomes Discharged, the bed is released, and the visit can be closed","Automatable","REQ-INPT-060","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0034","Inpatient / Ward Management","Discharge (ADT)","Discharge datetime must not precede the admission datetime","Boundary","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient admitted at a known datetime","1. Start the Discharge form | 2. Set discharge datetime before admission | 3. Attempt to save","Admit=2026-06-01 09:00; Discharge=2026-05-31","A validation error is shown; discharge cannot occur before admission","Automatable","REQ-INPT-061","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0035","Inpatient / Ward Management","Discharge (ADT)","Warn or block discharge with active unresolved critical orders","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active critical/stat order pending","1. Attempt to discharge the patient | 2. Observe warning regarding active orders | 3. Decide to proceed or cancel","ActiveOrders=1 critical pending","The system warns about active orders before discharge and requires acknowledgement, preventing silent loss of pending care","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-062","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0036","Inpatient / Ward Management","Discharge (ADT)","Discharge Against Medical Advice (AMA) requires reason and captures disposition","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient currently admitted requesting to leave","1. Start the Discharge form | 2. Select disposition Against Medical Advice | 3. Save without reason then with reason","Disposition=AMA; Reason=Patient request","AMA discharge requires a documented reason; once provided, the discharge is recorded with AMA disposition","Automatable","REQ-INPT-063","Clinical; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0037","Inpatient / Ward Management","Discharge (ADT)","Record an inpatient death/deceased discharge disposition","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient currently admitted","1. Start the Discharge form | 2. Select disposition Deceased | 3. Enter date/time of death | 4. Save","Disposition=Deceased; DeathDateTime=now","The discharge is recorded as Deceased, the patient deceased status/date is set, and the bed is released","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-064","Clinical; Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0038","Inpatient / Ward Management","Discharge Summary","Generate a discharge summary containing required clinical sections","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient discharged with documented admission diagnosis, treatment and medications","1. Open the discharged admission | 2. Generate the discharge summary | 3. Review sections","Patient=admitted+discharged","The discharge summary includes admission diagnosis, hospital course, procedures, discharge medications, follow-up and discharge instructions","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-070","Clinical; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0039","Inpatient / Ward Management","Discharge Summary","Block finalizing a discharge summary with missing mandatory sections","Negative","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; discharge summary draft missing follow-up instructions","1. Open the discharge summary draft | 2. Leave mandatory follow-up blank | 3. Attempt to finalize/sign","MissingField=Follow-up","Finalization is blocked with a validation message listing the missing mandatory sections","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-071","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0040","Inpatient / Ward Management","Discharge Summary","Amend a finalized discharge summary creates an addendum, not a silent edit","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; a finalized discharge summary exists","1. Open the finalized summary | 2. Add an amendment/addendum | 3. Sign | 4. Review document history","Amendment=Corrected dosage","An addendum is appended with author and timestamp; the original content is preserved and the change is auditable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-072","Clinical; Audit; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0041","Inpatient / Ward Management","Readmission","Detect a 30-day readmission for a recently discharged patient","Decision Table","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient discharged 10 days ago","1. Start a new admission for the same patient | 2. Observe readmission detection/flag","LastDischarge=10 days ago; Window=30 days","The new admission is flagged as a 30-day readmission for reporting; admission still proceeds","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-080","Clinical; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0042","Inpatient / Ward Management","Readmission","No readmission flag when prior discharge is outside the window","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient last discharged 45 days ago","1. Start a new admission for the same patient | 2. Observe readmission flag state","LastDischarge=45 days ago; Window=30 days","The admission is not flagged as a 30-day readmission since it falls outside the configured window","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-080","Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0043","Inpatient / Ward Management","RBAC / Security","Nurse without admit privilege cannot perform admission","Security","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Nurse role lacking the admit/ADT privilege","1. Open a patient with an active visit | 2. Attempt to start the Admit to Inpatient form","Role=Nurse (no admit privilege)","The admit action is hidden or denied with an authorization error; no admission is created","Automatable","REQ-INPT-090","Security; Patient Safety; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0044","Inpatient / Ward Management","RBAC / Security","Prevent privilege escalation to discharge via direct REST call","Security","Regression","P1","Critical","High","API access as a user lacking discharge privilege; valid session token","1. Send a REST request to create a Discharge encounter for an admitted patient | 2. Inspect response","Token=non-privileged user","The API returns 403 Forbidden and no discharge encounter is created, enforcing RBAC server-side not just in the UI","Automatable","REQ-INPT-091","Security; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0045","Inpatient / Ward Management","Audit","Admission, transfer and discharge actions are written to the audit log","Database","Regression","P2","High","Medium","DB/audit access; clinician performs ADT actions","1. Admit, transfer and discharge a patient | 2. Query the audit/encounter log","Actions=Admit,Transfer,Discharge","Each ADT action is recorded with actor, action type, patient, location and timestamp for later audit retrieval","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-092","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0046","Inpatient / Ward Management","Audit","PHI access to the ward census list is logged per accessing user","Security","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Audit logging enabled; user views ward census","1. View the ward census/patient list as User A | 2. Query access logs for the census view","User=A; View=Ward Census","An access event is logged identifying the user, the ward census resource and timestamp to support HIPAA access auditing","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-092","PHI/Privacy; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0047","Inpatient / Ward Management","FHIR Interop","Represent admission as a FHIR Encounter with class IMP","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR API enabled; patient admitted to an inpatient ward","1. GET the Encounter resource for the admission | 2. Inspect class, status, period and location","Encounter.class=IMP","The FHIR Encounter has class code IMP (inpatient encounter), status in-progress, a period.start, subject and the ward as a location reference","Automatable","REQ-INPT-100","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-INPT-0048","Inpatient / Ward Management","FHIR Interop","FHIR Encounter status transitions to finished on discharge","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR API enabled; patient discharged","1. GET the Encounter after discharge | 2. Inspect status and period.end","Encounter.status before=in-progress","After discharge the Encounter status is finished and period.end is populated with the discharge datetime","Automatable","REQ-INPT-100","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-INPT-0049","Inpatient / Ward Management","FHIR Interop","FHIR Encounter.location uses status active then completed across transfers","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","FHIR API enabled; patient transferred between two wards","1. GET the Encounter after a ward transfer | 2. Inspect Encounter.location entries","Transfer=WardA->WardB","Encounter.location lists both wards with appropriate location status (e.g., completed for source, active for destination) and periods","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-101","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-INPT-0050","Inpatient / Ward Management","FHIR Interop","Query active inpatients via FHIR Encounter search by class and status","FHIR","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","FHIR API enabled; multiple active and finished encounters exist","1. GET /Encounter?class=IMP&status=in-progress | 2. Inspect the returned bundle","Search=class=IMP,status=in-progress","The bundle returns only active inpatient encounters and excludes outpatient and finished encounters","Automatable","REQ-INPT-102","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-INPT-0051","Inpatient / Ward Management","HL7 Interop","Inbound HL7 v2 ADT^A01 admit message creates an inpatient admission","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 v2 inbound interface configured; matching patient exists","1. Send an ADT^A01 message with PV1 assigned patient location | 2. Process the message | 3. Verify admission","MsgType=ADT^A01; PV1-3=ICU^03","The patient is admitted to the mapped ward/bed, an admission is created, and an ACK is returned","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-110","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-INPT-0052","Inpatient / Ward Management","HL7 Interop","HL7 ADT^A02 transfer message updates patient location","HL7","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","HL7 v2 interface configured; patient currently admitted","1. Send an ADT^A02 transfer message with new PV1-3 location | 2. Process | 3. Verify ward","MsgType=ADT^A02; PV1-3=MW^05","The patient location updates to the new ward/bed per the A02 and a transfer is recorded","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-111","Standards-HL7; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-INPT-0053","Inpatient / Ward Management","HL7 Interop","HL7 ADT^A03 discharge message discharges the patient and sets disposition","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 v2 interface configured; patient currently admitted","1. Send an ADT^A03 with PV1-36 discharge disposition | 2. Process | 3. Verify discharge","MsgType=ADT^A03; PV1-36=Home","The patient is discharged, disposition mapped from PV1-36, and the encounter closed with the discharge datetime","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-112","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-INPT-0054","Inpatient / Ward Management","HL7 Interop","Reject or NACK an ADT message referencing an unknown patient identifier","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 v2 interface configured; identifier in message not present in system","1. Send an ADT^A01 with an unmatched PID-3 identifier | 2. Process the message","PID-3=UNKNOWN-999","The message is rejected with an application error/NACK (AE) and no admission is created from the unmatched identifier","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-113","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-INPT-0055","Inpatient / Ward Management","Concurrency","Two clinicians assigning the last free bed concurrently - only one succeeds","Negative","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Two sessions; ward has exactly one free bed; bed management enabled","1. User A and User B both open Assign Bed for the same free bed | 2. Both submit nearly simultaneously","FreeBeds=1; Users=A,B","Only one assignment succeeds; the other receives a conflict/already-occupied error, preventing double booking","Manual-Only","REQ-INPT-011","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0056","Inpatient / Ward Management","Pairwise Config","Pairwise admission across ward type, payer and admission type combinations","Pairwise","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; wards, payers and admission types configured","1. Execute admissions across pairwise combinations of ward type x payer x admission type | 2. Verify each admission and its derived attributes","WardType={ICU,General,Maternity}; Payer={Self,Insurance,Govt}; AdmType={Emergency,Elective,Transfer}","Each pairwise combination admits successfully with correct ward, payer linkage and admission type, with no invalid combination accepted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-120","Clinical; Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0057","Inpatient / Ward Management","Accessibility","Ward census and bed board are operable and labelled for screen readers","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Screen reader active; ward bed board open","1. Navigate the bed board grid using keyboard only | 2. Verify bed status and patient cells are announced | 3. Activate Assign Bed via keyboard","Tool=NVDA/VoiceOver","All beds are keyboard reachable, status (Occupied/Available) and patient identity are announced with accessible names, and actions are operable without a mouse","Manual-Only","REQ-INPT-130","Accessibility; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0058","Inpatient / Ward Management","Exploratory","Exploratory session on rapid admit-transfer-discharge cycling for state consistency","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; test ward available","1. Rapidly admit, transfer and discharge the same patient across several short cycles | 2. Interleave bed assignments and voids | 3. Observe state, bed status and history consistency","TimeBox=60 min","No orphaned beds, no stuck Admitted states, history remains coherent, and counters/occupancy stay accurate throughout","Manual-Only","REQ-INPT-004","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0059","Inpatient / Ward Management","Billing Linkage","Bed-day charges accrue per night of stay for an inpatient admission","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Billing module enabled; ward has a configured daily bed charge","1. Admit patient | 2. Advance/simulate multiple nights | 3. Discharge | 4. Review bed-day charges","BedRate=100/night; Nights=3","Bed-day charges accrue one charge per qualifying night per the LOS/charge rule, totalling correctly at discharge","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-140","Billing; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0060","Inpatient / Ward Management","Database","Voided admission encounter is soft-deleted and excluded from active census","Database","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","DB access; admission encounter voided with a reason","1. Void an admission encounter | 2. Query the encounter table | 3. Query the active ward census","Action=Void admission","The encounter row is retained with voided=true, void reason and voided_by populated, and the patient is excluded from the active census query","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-005","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-INPT-0061","Inpatient / Ward Management","Capacity Management","Negative capacity is never displayed when discharges exceed admissions in edge data","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Ward Manager; manipulated edge data with mismatched counts","1. Create edge scenario where discharge events exceed recorded admissions | 2. View occupancy counter","Occupied baseline=0","Occupancy never renders a negative value; it floors at zero and surfaces a data inconsistency warning where applicable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-015","Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-INPT-0062","Inpatient / Ward Management","Discharge Summary","Discharge summary medications reconcile against active inpatient orders","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient with active and discontinued inpatient drug orders being discharged","1. Generate the discharge summary | 2. Review the discharge medications section against order history","Active=2 drugs; Discontinued=1 drug","Discharge medications reflect medication reconciliation (continued, changed, stopped) consistent with the inpatient order history","Partially-Automatable","REQ-INPT-073","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","Platform"
"TC-TRIAGE-0001","Triage & Emergency","Acuity Scoring","Assign ESI Level 1 for a patient requiring immediate life-saving intervention","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Triage nurse logged in; an unassigned patient is checked into the ED queue","1. Open the triage assessment for the patient | 2. Indicate the patient requires immediate life-saving intervention (e.g. intubation) | 3. Confirm the acuity decision | 4. Save the triage record","Chief complaint=Cardiac arrest; Intervention=Airway support","Patient is assigned ESI Level 1, flagged as Resuscitation, and moved to the top of the queue with an immediate-attention indicator","Partially-Automatable","REQ-TRIAGE-001","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-TRIAGE-0002","Triage & Emergency","Acuity Scoring","Assign ESI Level 2 for high-risk presentation without immediate intervention","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Triage nurse logged in; patient in ED queue","1. Open triage assessment | 2. Record a high-risk situation (severe pain or confusion) without need for immediate life-saving care | 3. Confirm acuity | 4. Save","Chief complaint=Chest pain; Pain=9/10; LOC=Alert","Patient is assigned ESI Level 2 (Emergent) and prioritized above levels 3-5 in the queue","Partially-Automatable","REQ-TRIAGE-001","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-TRIAGE-0003","Triage & Emergency","Acuity Scoring","ESI Level 3 decision based on two-or-more resources prediction","Decision Table","System","P2","High","Medium","Triage nurse logged in; vitals captured within danger-zone-safe range","1. Open triage assessment | 2. Record stable vitals | 3. Predict two or more resources required (labs + imaging) | 4. Confirm acuity | 5. Save","Resources=Labs+CT; Vitals=Normal","Patient is assigned ESI Level 3 (Urgent) per the resource-prediction branch of the decision table","Partially-Automatable","REQ-TRIAGE-001","Clinical","Standards"
"TC-TRIAGE-0004","Triage & Emergency","Acuity Scoring","ESI decision-table coverage for resource count 0, 1 and many","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Triage nurse logged in; patient with stable vitals","1. Run triage with zero predicted resources -> expect Level 5 | 2. Run triage with one predicted resource -> expect Level 4 | 3. Run triage with two-plus resources and stable vitals -> expect Level 3","Resources={0,1,2+}; Vitals=Stable","System maps 0 resources to ESI 5, 1 resource to ESI 4 and 2+ resources to ESI 3 exactly per the ESI algorithm","Partially-Automatable","REQ-TRIAGE-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-TRIAGE-0005","Triage & Emergency","Acuity Scoring","Danger-zone vitals upgrade an ESI Level 3 to Level 2","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Triage nurse logged in; patient predicted to need 2+ resources","1. Begin triage with 2+ resources (tentative Level 3) | 2. Enter vitals that breach age-specific danger-zone thresholds | 3. Confirm acuity | 4. Save","HR=135 (adult); RR=32; SpO2=89%","System upgrades the acuity from ESI 3 to ESI 2 due to danger-zone vital signs","Partially-Automatable","REQ-TRIAGE-002","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-TRIAGE-0006","Triage & Emergency","Acuity Scoring","Reject triage save when acuity level is not selected","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","Triage nurse logged in; triage form open","1. Enter chief complaint and vitals | 2. Leave the acuity level unselected | 3. Attempt to save","Acuity=blank; Complaint=Headache","Save is blocked with a validation message requiring an acuity level; no triage record is persisted","Automatable","REQ-TRIAGE-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-TRIAGE-0007","Triage & Emergency","Acuity Scoring","Reject out-of-range acuity value submitted via API","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","API client authenticated with triage write scope","1. POST a triage observation with an acuity value outside 1-5 | 2. Inspect the response","Acuity=6","API rejects the request with a 400/422 validation error and no observation is created","Automatable","REQ-TRIAGE-001","Clinical; Data Integrity; Standards-FHIR","Standards"
