"TC-ORDSET-0009","Order Sets & Protocols","Protocol-Driven Orders","Weight-based protocol blocks when weight is missing","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Pediatric weight-based protocol; patient has no weight recorded","1. Open patient without weight | 2. Apply weight-based protocol | 3. Attempt to compute/sign","Protocol=Peds Fluid Resus; Patient=SYN-1006","System prompts for weight before dose computation; signing is blocked until weight provided; no zero/null doses created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-005","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0010","Order Sets & Protocols","Conditional Orders","Conditional member shown only when its trigger condition is true","Decision Table","System","P1","High","High","Order set with conditional member: ""Insulin sliding scale IF glucose > 250""","1. Apply order set with patient glucose=300 | 2. Observe conditional member | 3. Repeat with glucose=120","Glucose-A=300; Glucose-B=120; Patient=SYN-1007","With glucose=300 the conditional insulin order appears/auto-selects; with glucose=120 it is hidden or unchecked","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-006","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0011","Order Sets & Protocols","Conditional Orders","Decision table for renal-adjusted dosing across eGFR bands","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Order set with renal dose adjustment rules keyed on eGFR","1. Set eGFR per row | 2. Apply order set | 3. Verify chosen dose band","eGFR rows: >=60 full dose; 30-59 75%; 15-29 50%; <15 hold + alert","Each eGFR band maps to the correct dose tier; <15 holds the drug and raises an alert; boundaries 60/30/15 resolve to the documented band","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-006","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0012","Order Sets & Protocols","Conditional Orders","Conditional logic boundary at exact threshold value","Boundary","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Conditional rule ""order potassium IF K+ < 3.5""","1. Apply with K+ = 3.5 | 2. Apply with K+ = 3.4 | 3. Apply with K+ = 3.6","K+=3.5, 3.4, 3.6","K+=3.4 triggers the order; 3.5 and 3.6 do not (strict less-than); behavior is consistent and documented","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-006","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0013","Order Sets & Protocols","Conditional Orders","Conditional order with missing dependent observation","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Conditional rule depends on an observation not yet recorded","1. Apply order set where trigger obs is absent | 2. Observe handling of the conditional member","Patient=SYN-1008; TriggerObs=absent","Conditional member is shown as indeterminate/requires-input rather than silently included or excluded; clinician is prompted","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-006","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0014","Order Sets & Protocols","Modify Before Sign","Edit dose, frequency and route of a member order before signing","Functional","Sanity","P1","High","Medium","Order set selected, not yet signed","1. Expand a drug member | 2. Change dose 500mg->250mg | 3. Change frequency BID->TID | 4. Change route PO->IV | 5. Review","Drug=Metronidazole; Dose=250mg; Freq=TID; Route=IV","Edited values persist in the draft and are reflected at sign; defaults are overridden cleanly","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-007","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0015","Order Sets & Protocols","Modify Before Sign","Deselect optional members and keep mandatory members","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Order set with mandatory and optional members","1. Open expanded order set | 2. Uncheck two optional members | 3. Attempt to uncheck a mandatory member","OrderSet=Adult CAP","Optional members can be removed; mandatory members are locked/cannot be deselected and are clearly marked","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-007","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0016","Order Sets & Protocols","Modify Before Sign","Override a member dose beyond max allowed triggers validation","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Drug member has a defined max single dose","1. Edit member dose to exceed max | 2. Attempt to sign","Drug=Acetaminophen; Dose=8000mg","Validation blocks or hard-warns on the over-max dose; clinician must acknowledge/justify or correct before sign","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-008","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0017","Order Sets & Protocols","Modify Before Sign","Boundary on editable quantity/duration fields","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Member order with numeric duration field","1. Set duration=0 | 2. Set duration=negative | 3. Set duration at max allowed | 4. Set duration just above max","Duration=0, -1, 90, 91","0 and negative are rejected; max accepted; above-max rejected with a clear message","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-008","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0018","Order Sets & Protocols","Modify Before Sign","Add an ad-hoc order to the draft alongside order set members","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Low","Order set draft open","1. Add a free-standing order not in the set | 2. Confirm it joins the draft | 3. Sign all","AdHocOrder=CBC; OrderSet=Adult CAP","Ad-hoc order is added to the same signing batch and committed with the set; provenance distinguishes set vs ad-hoc","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-007","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0019","Order Sets & Protocols","Modify Before Sign","Discard draft order set without signing","State Transition","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Order set draft with edits exists","1. Make edits | 2. Click Cancel/Discard | 3. Confirm discard | 4. Re-open order entry","OrderSet=Adult CAP","Draft is discarded; no orders persisted; patient order list unchanged; re-opening starts clean","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-009","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0020","Order Sets & Protocols","Bulk Sign","Sign all selected order set members in a single action","Functional","Smoke","P1","Critical","High","Order set draft reviewed; clinician has signing authority","1. Review the full draft | 2. Click Sign All | 3. Authenticate if prompted | 4. Confirm","OrderSet=Adult CAP; Patient=SYN-1010","All members transition to active/signed atomically; one signing event recorded; orders appear in active orders list","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-010","Clinical; Patient Safety; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0021","Order Sets & Protocols","Bulk Sign","Partial bulk sign when one member fails validation","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","Draft contains one member that fails validation (e.g., over-max dose)","1. Attempt Sign All | 2. Observe outcome for valid vs invalid members","OrderSet with 1 invalid member","Either the whole batch is blocked atomically with the offending member flagged, or valid members commit and invalid ones are retained as draft with clear status; no partial silent loss","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-010","Clinical; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0022","Order Sets & Protocols","Bulk Sign","Bulk sign requires re-authentication / e-signature","Security","System","P1","High","High","E-signature/re-auth policy enabled for order signing","1. Click Sign All | 2. Enter wrong password | 3. Enter correct password","WrongPwd then CorrectPwd","Wrong password blocks signing; correct password completes; signing event records signer identity and timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-011","Security; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0023","Order Sets & Protocols","Bulk Sign","User without signing privilege cannot bulk sign","Security","Regression","P1","High","High","User role lacks order-signing privilege","1. Log in as restricted user | 2. Build order set draft | 3. Attempt Sign All","Role=Nurse-NoSign","Sign action is disabled/denied with authorization error; no orders are activated; attempt is audited","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-011","Security; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0024","Order Sets & Protocols","Bulk Sign","Concurrent bulk sign of the same draft by two sessions","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Same draft open in two sessions","1. Session A signs the draft | 2. Session B attempts to sign the same draft","Two sessions; same draft","Second sign is rejected or recognizes already-signed state; no duplicate orders are created; optimistic-lock/stale message shown","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-012","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0025","Order Sets & Protocols","Decision Support","Drug-drug interaction alert fires on an order set member","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","DDI rules active; patient on warfarin; order set adds an interacting drug","1. Apply order set adding an NSAID | 2. Observe interaction alert before sign","ActiveMed=Warfarin; New=Ibuprofen; Patient=SYN-1011","DDI alert displays severity and interacting pair; clinician must acknowledge/override-with-reason before signing that member","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-013","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0026","Order Sets & Protocols","Decision Support","Drug-allergy alert blocks/warns on order set member","Functional","System","P1","Critical","High","Patient has documented penicillin allergy; order set includes amoxicillin","1. Apply order set | 2. Observe drug-allergy alert | 3. Attempt override","Allergy=Penicillin; Drug=Amoxicillin; Patient=SYN-1012","Drug-allergy alert appears with reaction details; override requires a reason; event audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-013","Clinical; Patient Safety; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0027","Order Sets & Protocols","Decision Support","Duplicate-therapy alert when order set duplicates an active order","Functional","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Patient already has active order for a drug in the set","1. Apply order set containing the same drug class | 2. Observe duplicate alert","ActiveOrder=Ceftriaxone; SetDrug=Ceftriaxone","Duplicate/therapeutic-overlap alert is raised; clinician chooses to keep, replace, or cancel the duplicate","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-013","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0028","Order Sets & Protocols","Decision Support","Override reason is captured and audited for safety alerts","Audit","System","P1","High","High","A safety alert fires that requires override reason","1. Trigger a DDI alert | 2. Override with reason ""benefit outweighs risk"" | 3. Sign | 4. Open audit log","OverrideReason=benefit outweighs risk","Override reason, alert type, severity, user and timestamp are persisted in the audit trail and retrievable","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-014","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0029","Order Sets & Protocols","Decision Support","Pairwise alert-handling across alert type and user action","Pairwise","System","P2","High","Medium","Alert engine supports multiple alert types and actions","1. Generate each alert type | 2. Apply each user action | 3. Verify outcome","AlertType={DDI,Allergy,Duplicate,Renal}; Action={Accept,OverrideReason,Cancel}","Each pairwise combination yields the correct outcome: accept proceeds, override requires reason, cancel removes the member; no combination crashes or silently passes","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-014","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0030","Order Sets & Protocols","Decision Support","Hard-stop alert prevents signing without resolution","Negative","System","P1","Critical","High","A hard-stop (non-overridable) rule is configured (e.g., absolute contraindication)","1. Apply order set triggering hard-stop | 2. Attempt to override | 3. Attempt to sign","Rule=Absolute contraindication","Hard-stop cannot be overridden; the offending member cannot be signed; clinician must remove/modify it to proceed","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-014","Clinical; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0031","Order Sets & Protocols","Formulary Checks","Non-formulary drug in order set is flagged at selection","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Drug formulary configured; order set contains a non-formulary drug","1. Apply order set | 2. Observe formulary status on each drug member","SetDrug=Non-formulary brand X","Non-formulary member is flagged with a formulary indicator; justification or substitution is requested before sign","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-015","Clinical; Billing","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0032","Order Sets & Protocols","Formulary Checks","Therapeutic substitution suggested for non-formulary drug","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Formulary substitution mapping exists","1. Select non-formulary drug member | 2. Open substitution suggestion | 3. Accept formulary alternative","NonFormulary=BrandX; Formulary=GenericY","System suggests the formulary equivalent; accepting replaces the member while preserving dose intent; provenance notes substitution","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-015","Clinical; Billing","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0033","Order Sets & Protocols","Formulary Checks","Restricted/antimicrobial-stewardship drug requires approval","Security","System","P1","High","High","Drug flagged as restricted requiring stewardship approval","1. Apply order set with restricted antibiotic | 2. Attempt to sign without approval","RestrictedDrug=Meropenem","Member requires stewardship approval/role; signing without approval is blocked or routes for approval; action audited","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-016","Clinical; Regulatory/Compliance; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0034","Order Sets & Protocols","Formulary Checks","Decision table for formulary status by care setting and insurance","Decision Table","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Formulary varies by care setting and payer","1. Vary care setting and payer per row | 2. Check drug formulary status","Rows: Inpatient/PayerA=formulary; Outpatient/PayerA=non-formulary; Inpatient/PayerB=restricted","Each combination resolves to the documented formulary status and resulting prompt; defaults applied where mapping absent","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-015","Clinical; Billing","Platform"
"TC-ORDSET-0035","Order Sets & Protocols","API","Create orders from an order set via REST and verify persistence","API","Integration","P1","High","Medium","REST API access with ordering privileges; valid session token","1. POST order set application to the orders REST endpoint | 2. GET the created orders | 3. Validate fields","Endpoint=/ws/rest/v1/order; OrderSet payload","API returns 201 with created order resources; GET confirms members persisted with correct orderer, encounter and care setting","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-017","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0036","Order Sets & Protocols","API","Reject malformed order set payload with 400","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","REST API access","1. POST payload missing required orderer | 2. POST payload with invalid concept UUID","Missing orderer; bad concept UUID","API returns 400/422 with a descriptive validation error; no partial orders created","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-017","Data Integrity; Security","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0037","Order Sets & Protocols","API","Unauthorized order set creation is rejected","Security","Integration","P1","High","High","API reachable without/with insufficient token","1. POST order set with no auth token | 2. POST with token lacking order privilege","NoToken; LowPrivToken","Requests return 401/403; no orders created; attempts are logged","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-011","Security; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0038","Order Sets & Protocols","FHIR","Order set definition maps to FHIR PlanDefinition with actions","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","Medium","FHIR endpoint exposes plan definitions; order set published","1. GET PlanDefinition for the order set | 2. Validate action elements and references","Resource=PlanDefinition","PlanDefinition returned with action items referencing ActivityDefinition; conditions and dynamicValues represented; resource validates against the profile","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-018","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ORDSET-0039","Order Sets & Protocols","FHIR","Applying order set produces FHIR RequestGroup / order resources","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","Medium","FHIR $apply supported or RequestGroup generation available","1. Invoke PlanDefinition $apply for the patient | 2. Inspect resulting RequestGroup and referenced MedicationRequest/ServiceRequest","Operation=$apply; Patient=SYN-1013","A RequestGroup is returned linking generated MedicationRequest/ServiceRequest resources; each carries subject, authoredOn and requester; references resolve","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-018","Standards-FHIR; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ORDSET-0040","Order Sets & Protocols","FHIR","FHIR order resources reference correct code systems","FHIR","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Generated FHIR orders available","1. Retrieve a generated MedicationRequest | 2. Inspect medication coding system | 3. Retrieve a ServiceRequest and inspect coding","MedSystem=RxNorm; LabSystem=LOINC","Medication codes use RxNorm system URI; lab/service codes use LOINC; system URIs are correct and codes are valid","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-018","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ORDSET-0041","Order Sets & Protocols","HL7","Signed order set emits HL7 v2 ORM/OMP messages per member","HL7","Integration","P2","High","Medium","HL7 v2 outbound interface configured for orders","1. Sign an order set | 2. Capture outbound HL7 messages | 3. Parse ORC/OBR/RXO segments","Interface=ORM^O01 / OMP^O09","One order message per member is emitted with correct ORC placer order numbers, OBR/RXO details and patient/visit identifiers","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-019","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ORDSET-0042","Order Sets & Protocols","HL7","Order cancellation from set emits HL7 cancel control code","HL7","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","HL7 outbound configured; an active order from a set exists","1. Cancel a signed member order | 2. Capture outbound HL7 | 3. Inspect ORC-1 control code","ORC-1=CA (Cancel)","Cancellation message uses the correct ORC-1 control code referencing the original placer order number","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-019","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ORDSET-0043","Order Sets & Protocols","Database","Order set application is atomic and rolls back on failure","Database","Integration","P1","Critical","High","DB access to verify transaction; ability to inject a mid-batch failure","1. Apply and sign a multi-member set | 2. Force a failure on the last member | 3. Inspect orders table","Inject failure on member N","Either all members commit or none do; no orphan/partial rows; transaction rolls back cleanly on failure","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-020","Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0044","Order Sets & Protocols","Database","Each order persists provenance link to its source order set","Database","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Orders created from a set; DB read access","1. Apply and sign an order set | 2. Query order rows | 3. Verify source order set reference column/linkage","OrderSet=Adult CAP","Each generated order row carries a reference to the originating order set/protocol; query returns the linkage for reporting","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-020","Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0045","Order Sets & Protocols","Accessibility","Order set selection and sign flow is keyboard navigable","Accessibility","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Order entry UI loaded; keyboard only","1. Navigate catalog with Tab/arrows | 2. Expand a set with Enter/Space | 3. Toggle members | 4. Reach and activate Sign All","Keyboard-only navigation","All interactive elements are reachable and operable by keyboard with a visible focus indicator; no keyboard trap; logical tab order","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-021","Accessibility","Standards"
"TC-ORDSET-0046","Order Sets & Protocols","Accessibility","Safety alerts are announced to screen readers","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Screen reader active; alert-triggering set available","1. Apply a set that triggers a DDI alert | 2. Listen for the alert via screen reader","ScreenReader=NVDA/VoiceOver","The alert is exposed as an ARIA alert/live region and announced with its severity and message; override controls are labeled","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-021","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-ORDSET-0047","Order Sets & Protocols","Exploratory","Explore order set behavior with rapid edits and toggling","Exploratory","System","P3","Medium","Medium","Order set draft open","1. Rapidly toggle members on/off | 2. Edit then revert fields | 3. Add/remove ad-hoc orders quickly | 4. Attempt sign mid-edit","Charter: stress draft state machine","No stale/ghost members; computed values and alerts stay consistent with current selections; sign reflects the final visible state","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-022","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0048","Order Sets & Protocols","Exploratory","Explore order set versioning when an updated version publishes mid-draft","Exploratory","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","An order set has a draft open while a new version is published","1. Open a draft from order set v1 | 2. Publish v2 with changed defaults | 3. Continue and sign the v1 draft","OrderSet v1 draft; v2 published","System either pins the draft to v1 with a version note or warns of the new version; signed orders record which version was used; no silent mixing","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-002","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0049","Order Sets & Protocols","State Transition","Order lifecycle from draft to signed to discontinued","State Transition","System","P2","High","Medium","Member order signed and active","1. Verify state=Active after sign | 2. Discontinue the order with reason | 3. Verify state=Discontinued | 4. Attempt to edit discontinued order","States: Draft->Active->Discontinued","State transitions occur in order; discontinue requires reason; discontinued orders are immutable; invalid transitions rejected","Automatable","REQ-ORDSET-009","Clinical; Data Integrity; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-ORDSET-0050","Order Sets & Protocols","Pairwise","Pairwise across care setting, role and order set type","Pairwise","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Multiple care settings, roles and order set types configured","1. For each pair apply an order set | 2. Verify permission and applicability","CareSetting={Inpatient,Outpatient}; Role={Physician,Nurse,Pharmacist}; SetType={Med,Lab,Mixed}","Each pairwise combination enforces correct permissions and applicability; disallowed combinations are blocked with clear messaging","Manual-Only","REQ-ORDSET-016","Security; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0001","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Allergen Coding","Add a drug-class allergen (Penicillins) rather than a single drug and verify class-level coding","Functional","Regression","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient dashboard open; allergen concept set includes drug classes","1. Open Allergies widget | 2. Add New Allergy | 3. In allergen search type ""Penicillins"" | 4. Select the drug-class concept (not the individual product) | 5. Add reaction and severity | 6. Save","Allergen=Penicillins (class); Reaction=Anaphylaxis; Severity=Severe","Allergy persists referencing the drug-class concept; list shows class-level allergen so all member drugs are later cross-checked, not only one product","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-001","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0002","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Allergen Coding","Allergen coded concept maps to a non-retired RxNorm/SNOMED reference term","Database","Integration","P2","High","Medium","DB/concept access available; coded allergen recorded","1. Record a coded drug allergy | 2. Query concept_reference_map for the allergen concept | 3. Verify a mapped reference term in RxNorm or SNOMED CT | 4. Confirm source term is not retired","Allergen=Aspirin; ExpectedSource=RxNorm","Allergen concept carries a SAME-AS mapping to an active RxNorm/SNOMED term; no retired or missing mapping that would break cross-checks","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-002","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0003","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Allergen Coding","Reject saving a coded allergen whose underlying concept is retired","Negative","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; a retired allergen concept exists in the dictionary","1. Open Allergies widget | 2. Add New Allergy | 3. Attempt to select a retired allergen concept | 4. Attempt Save","Allergen=Retired-Concept-X","Retired concept is not offered in the picker, or save is blocked with a clear message; no allergy stored against a retired concept","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-002","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0004","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Reaction/Severity/Criticality","Distinguish per-reaction severity from overall criticality on a single allergen","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient dashboard open","1. Add allergy to Sulfa | 2. Add reaction Hives with severity Mild | 3. Add reaction Difficulty breathing with severity Severe | 4. Set overall criticality High | 5. Save | 6. Re-open the saved allergy","Allergen=Sulfa; Reaction1=Hives/Mild; Reaction2=Difficulty breathing/Severe; Criticality=High","Each reaction retains its own severity and the allergen retains a separate High criticality; severity and criticality are not conflated","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-003","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0005","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Reaction/Severity/Criticality","Decision table mapping severity and reaction type to overall criticality","Decision Table","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; criticality derivation rules configured","1. Create allergy: Mild + cutaneous reaction | 2. Create allergy: Moderate + GI reaction | 3. Create allergy: Severe + respiratory reaction | 4. Create allergy: any severity + Anaphylaxis | 5. Observe derived/required criticality for each","R1=Mild/Rash; R2=Moderate/Nausea; R3=Severe/Wheeze; R4=Mild/Anaphylaxis","Mild->Low criticality; Moderate->Low/Unable-to-assess; Severe->High; Anaphylaxis forces High criticality regardless of stated severity per rule table","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-003","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0006","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Reaction/Severity/Criticality","Boundary check on allergy onset date rejecting a future date","Boundary","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient dashboard open; current date 2026-07-01","1. Add New Allergy | 2. Select allergen | 3. Enter onset date in the future | 4. Save","Allergen=Codeine; Onset=2030-01-01","Save is blocked or warns; onset date cannot be in the future relative to server date","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-004","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0007","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Reaction/Severity/Criticality","Onset date equal to date of birth boundary is accepted","Boundary","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient DOB known","1. Add allergy | 2. Set onset date equal to patient DOB | 3. Save","Allergen=Latex; Onset=DOB=1990-01-01","Allergy saves; congenital/birth onset boundary is permitted and stored exactly","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-004","Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0008","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","No Known Allergies","Toggle NKA off then re-assert NKA after voiding the only allergy","State Transition","Regression","P2","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient currently No Known Allergies","1. From NKA, add an allergy (clears NKA) | 2. Void that allergy with a reason | 3. Re-assert No Known Allergies | 4. Verify final state","Allergen=Ibuprofen; VoidReason=Entered in error","State transitions NKA -> Has-Allergy -> (void) -> NKA cleanly; final widget shows No Known Allergies with no residual active allergy","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-005","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0009","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","No Known Allergies","Distinguish No Known Allergies from unassessed (no allergy data) status","Functional","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; one patient explicitly marked NKA and one patient never assessed","1. Open patient A marked NKA | 2. Note widget status | 3. Open patient B never assessed | 4. Note widget status | 5. Compare","PatientA=NKA-asserted; PatientB=never-assessed","NKA shows an explicit asserted ""No Known Allergies""; unassessed patient shows a distinct ""not recorded/unknown"" prompt, never silently implying no allergies","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-005","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0010","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","No Known Allergies","API rejects asserting NKA when active allergies exist","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Valid session; patient UUID with an existing active allergy","1. POST NKA assertion via REST for the patient | 2. Inspect response","Patient has active Penicillin allergy","API returns 4xx with a conflict/validation error; NKA flag not set while active allergies remain","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-005","Patient Safety; API; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0011","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Duplicate Detection","Block exact-duplicate allergen even when case/spacing of free-text differs","Negative","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient already has Other free-text allergen ""Bee venom""","1. Add New Allergy | 2. Select Other | 3. Enter ""  bee VENOM "" with different case and padding | 4. Save","Existing=Bee venom; New=""  bee VENOM ""","System detects the normalized duplicate and warns/blocks; no second near-identical free-text allergen is created","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-006","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0012","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Duplicate Detection","Allow same allergen if a prior entry for it was voided","State Transition","Regression","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient had Penicillin allergy that is now voided","1. Confirm prior Penicillin allergy is voided | 2. Add New Allergy for Penicillin | 3. Save","Allergen=Penicillin; prior entry voided","Re-adding the previously voided allergen is permitted; not treated as an active duplicate","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-006","Clinical; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0013","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Edit/Void","Voiding an allergy requires a non-empty void reason","Negative","Regression","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active allergy","1. Open the allergy | 2. Click Remove/Delete | 3. Leave void reason blank | 4. Confirm","Allergen=Penicillin; VoidReason=blank","Void is blocked until a reason is supplied; mandatory void-reason enforced and later auditable","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-007","Audit; Data Integrity; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0014","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Edit/Void","Voided allergy is excluded from active drug-allergy cross-check","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient's Penicillin allergy has been voided; ordering available","1. Confirm Penicillin allergy is voided | 2. Start a drug order for Amoxicillin | 3. Observe interaction checking","Voided Allergen=Penicillin; Order=Amoxicillin","No allergy alert fires from the voided entry; voided allergies do not participate in cross-check, preventing false alerts","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-007","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0015","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Edit/Void","Edit history of an allergy preserves prior values for audit","Database","Regression","P2","High","Medium","DB/audit access; an allergy that has been edited at least once","1. Edit an allergy changing severity Mild->Severe | 2. Query allergy/audit tables | 3. Verify prior value retained or change recorded","Allergen=Codeine; Old=Mild; New=Severe","Change is auditable with old and new values, editing user and timestamp; prior clinical value is not silently lost","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-008","Audit; Data Integrity; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0016","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Allergy Cross-Check","Direct drug-allergy match triggers an alert at order entry","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has active Penicillin allergy; CDS/interaction checking enabled; active visit","1. Open Orders | 2. Add a drug order for Penicillin V | 3. Proceed toward signing","Allergy=Penicillin; Order=Penicillin V","An allergy interaction alert is presented before the order is signed, naming the matching allergen and reaction","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-009","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0017","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Allergy Cross-Check","Class-level allergy triggers alert when ordering a class member drug","Functional","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has Penicillins (class) allergy; ordering enabled","1. Open Orders | 2. Order Amoxicillin (a penicillin-class member) | 3. Observe alert","Allergy=Penicillins(class); Order=Amoxicillin","Cross-check resolves the ordered drug to its class and fires the allergy alert even though the exact product was not the recorded allergen","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-009","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0018","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Allergy Cross-Check","Cross-reactivity alert for cephalosporin in a penicillin-allergic patient","Functional","Integration","P2","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has Penicillin allergy; cross-reactivity rules configured","1. Open Orders | 2. Order Cefalexin (cephalosporin) | 3. Observe whether a cross-reactivity advisory appears","Allergy=Penicillin; Order=Cefalexin","A cross-reactivity advisory (potential beta-lactam cross-sensitivity) is surfaced; clinician can review before signing","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-010","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0019","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Allergy Cross-Check","No alert when ordering an unrelated drug for an allergic patient","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient has Penicillin allergy only","1. Open Orders | 2. Order Paracetamol (unrelated) | 3. Observe alerts","Allergy=Penicillin; Order=Paracetamol","No allergy alert fires; cross-check does not raise false positives for unrelated agents","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-009","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0020","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Allergy Cross-Check","NKA patient ordering generates no allergy alert","Negative","Integration","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient explicitly marked No Known Allergies","1. Confirm NKA | 2. Order any drug | 3. Observe alerts","Status=NKA; Order=Amoxicillin","No drug-allergy alert; NKA suppresses allergy alerting while still permitting other interaction checks","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-009","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0021","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Allergy Cross-Check","Unassessed allergy status surfaces a prompt rather than silent no-alert","Functional","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient allergies never assessed","1. Confirm allergies not recorded | 2. Start a drug order | 3. Observe whether system prompts to record allergy status","Status=unassessed; Order=Amoxicillin","System prompts/flags that allergy status is unknown before signing rather than implying safety with silence","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-005","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0022","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Override/Decision Table","Decision table for alert action by criticality and clinician choice","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; allergy alerting with override workflow enabled","1. Order drug matching a High-criticality allergy and choose Override | 2. Order drug matching a Low-criticality allergy and choose Override | 3. Order matching High-criticality and choose Cancel | 4. Record outcomes","Criticality x Action: High/Override; Low/Override; High/Cancel","High-criticality override requires a documented reason (hard stop with reason); Low-criticality override may be soft; Cancel aborts the order in all cases per rule table","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-011","Patient Safety; Clinical; Audit","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0023","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Override/Decision Table","Override of a high-criticality allergy alert mandates an override reason","Negative","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has High-criticality Penicillin allergy; order matching it in progress","1. Trigger the allergy alert | 2. Choose Override | 3. Leave override reason blank | 4. Attempt to proceed","Allergy=Penicillin/High; OverrideReason=blank","Proceeding is blocked until a free-text override reason is entered; empty override is rejected","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-011","Patient Safety; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0024","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Override/Decision Table","Override reason and overriding user are captured to the audit trail","Database","Integration","P1","High","High","DB/audit access; an override of an allergy alert has occurred","1. Override a high-criticality allergy alert with reason | 2. Query the audit/override store | 3. Verify captured fields","OverrideReason=Benefit outweighs risk; User=clinician1","Audit record captures patient, ordered drug, matched allergen, override reason, user and UTC timestamp","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-012","Audit; Regulatory/Compliance; Patient Safety","Platform"
"TC-ALLERG2-0025","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Drug Interaction","Severe drug-drug interaction matrix triggers a hard interaction alert","Decision Table","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient already on Warfarin; DDI checking enabled","1. Order a drug with a known severe interaction (e.g. Aspirin) | 2. Observe interaction severity classification | 3. Repeat with a moderate-interaction drug | 4. Repeat with a no-interaction drug","Active=Warfarin; Orders=Aspirin(severe), Tramadol(moderate), Paracetamol(none)","Severe pair yields a hard/critical alert; moderate yields an advisory; none yields no alert, per interaction matrix classification","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-013","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0026","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Drug Interaction","Interaction check considers active medication list, not just current order","Functional","Integration","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has an active Warfarin order on the medication list","1. Open Orders | 2. Add new Aspirin order | 3. Observe whether interaction references existing active Warfarin","ActiveMed=Warfarin; NewOrder=Aspirin","Interaction is detected against the existing active medication, confirming the check spans the whole active list","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-013","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0027","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Drug Interaction","Discontinued/expired medications are excluded from interaction checking","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient's Warfarin order is discontinued/expired","1. Confirm Warfarin is discontinued | 2. Order Aspirin | 3. Observe alerts","Discontinued=Warfarin; Order=Aspirin","No DDI alert from the inactive Warfarin; only active medications participate, preventing stale false positives","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-013","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0028","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Drug Interaction","Pairwise coverage of interaction severity x clinician action x route","Pairwise","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; DDI checking enabled","1. Construct order scenarios pairwise across interaction severity, clinician action and order route | 2. Execute each | 3. Verify alert and outcome","Severity={Severe,Moderate,Minor}; Action={Proceed,Override,Cancel}; Route={Oral,IV}","Each pairwise combination behaves per rules with no crash, missing alert or inconsistent outcome across routes","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-013","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0029","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Condition Interaction","Drug-condition contraindication alert (NSAID with active peptic ulcer)","Functional","Integration","P2","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient has active condition Peptic ulcer disease; CDS rules configured","1. Open Orders | 2. Order Ibuprofen | 3. Observe contraindication advisory referencing the condition","Condition=Peptic ulcer; Order=Ibuprofen","A drug-condition contraindication advisory is surfaced citing the active condition before signing","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-014","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0030","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Condition Interaction","Pregnancy contraindication advisory for a category-X drug","Functional","Integration","P2","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; patient flagged pregnant; teratogenicity rules configured","1. Confirm pregnancy status | 2. Order a known teratogenic drug (e.g. Isotretinoin) | 3. Observe advisory","Status=Pregnant; Order=Isotretinoin","A pregnancy contraindication advisory is surfaced; clinician must acknowledge before proceeding","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-014","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0031","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Allergy Cross-Check","Duplicate-therapy alert when ordering a second drug of the same ingredient","Functional","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient already on Paracetamol; duplicate therapy checking enabled","1. Order a combination product also containing Paracetamol | 2. Observe duplicate therapy advisory","Active=Paracetamol; Order=Co-codamol (contains Paracetamol)","A duplicate/therapeutic-overlap advisory is surfaced warning of cumulative dosing of the shared ingredient","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-015","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0032","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Interaction Performance","Interaction check completes within acceptable latency at order entry","Functional","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient with 10 active meds and 5 allergies; ordering enabled","1. Add a new drug order | 2. Measure time from add to alert evaluation completion | 3. Repeat 10 times | 4. Compute p95","ActiveMeds=10; Allergies=5; Order=Aspirin","Interaction evaluation completes within the agreed SLA (e.g. <=2s p95) and does not block the UI; no missed alerts under load","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-016","Patient Safety; Clinical","Platform"
"TC-ALLERG2-0033","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Allergy Reconciliation","Reconcile imported external allergies against existing local allergies","Functional","Integration","P2","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; external allergy list received for an established patient","1. Open allergy reconciliation | 2. Review incoming vs existing allergies | 3. Mark a match to keep | 4. Add a new one | 5. Mark a stale one for void | 6. Confirm","Incoming={Penicillin(match), Shellfish(new)}; Existing stale={Latex}","Reconciliation merges without duplicating matched allergens, adds the new one, and voids/flags the stale one with audit of the reconciliation action","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-017","Patient Safety; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0034","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Allergy Reconciliation","Reconciliation conflict where severity differs between sources","Decision Table","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; incoming source lists same allergen with different severity","1. Start reconciliation | 2. Observe conflict on Penicillin severity Mild(local) vs Severe(incoming) | 3. Apply resolution rule | 4. Confirm","Local=Penicillin/Mild; Incoming=Penicillin/Severe","Conflict is surfaced; resolution rule (e.g. take most-severe/most-recent) is applied transparently and the chosen value is recorded with provenance","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-017","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0035","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","FHIR","FHIR AllergyIntolerance clinicalStatus and verificationStatus are populated","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","High","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; patient has an active confirmed allergy","1. GET /ws/fhir2/R4/AllergyIntolerance?patient={id} | 2. Inspect clinicalStatus and verificationStatus | 3. Validate codes against the FHIR value sets","Allergen=Penicillin; expected clinicalStatus=active; verificationStatus=confirmed","Resource carries clinicalStatus=active and verificationStatus=confirmed using the canonical FHIR code systems; values are not null","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-018","Standards-FHIR; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0036","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","FHIR","Voided allergy maps to FHIR verificationStatus entered-in-error","FHIR","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; an allergy voided as entered-in-error exists","1. Void an allergy with reason Entered in error | 2. GET the AllergyIntolerance resource | 3. Inspect verificationStatus","VoidReason=Entered in error","Resource verificationStatus maps to entered-in-error (or the entry is excluded per policy); voided clinical state is represented correctly to consumers","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-018","Standards-FHIR; Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0037","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","FHIR","FHIR AllergyIntolerance type and category fields are correct","FHIR","Integration","P2","Medium","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; drug and food allergies recorded","1. GET AllergyIntolerance for a drug allergy and a food allergy | 2. Inspect type and category | 3. Validate codes","Drug allergy; Food allergy","Drug allergy has type=allergy and category=medication; food allergy has category=food; codes drawn from the correct FHIR value sets","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-018","Standards-FHIR; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0038","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","FHIR","Create AllergyIntolerance via FHIR POST persists and is retrievable","FHIR","Integration","P1","High","High","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; write privilege; patient reference valid","1. POST a valid AllergyIntolerance resource | 2. Capture the returned id | 3. GET the resource by id | 4. Verify fields round-trip","code=RxNorm Penicillin; criticality=high; clinicalStatus=active","POST returns 201 with a logical id; GET returns the same coded allergen, criticality and status; round-trip is lossless","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-018","Standards-FHIR; API; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0039","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","FHIR","Reject FHIR AllergyIntolerance with an unbound criticality code","Negative","Integration","P2","High","Medium","FHIR R4 endpoint enabled; write privilege","1. POST AllergyIntolerance with criticality not in the value set | 2. Inspect response and OperationOutcome","criticality=EXTREME (invalid)","Server returns 4xx with an OperationOutcome describing the invalid code; no resource created","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-018","Standards-FHIR; API; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0040","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","HL7","Inbound HL7 v2 AL1 segment creates a patient allergy","HL7","Integration","P2","High","High","HL7 v2 inbound interface configured; AL1-capable ADT message accepted","1. Send an ADT message with an AL1 allergy segment | 2. Process the message | 3. Open the patient allergies","AL1: AllergyType=DA; AllergenCode=Penicillin; Severity=SV; Reaction=Hives","Allergy from AL1 is created with allergen, severity and reaction mapped; message is acknowledged with AA","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-019","Standards-HL7; Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0041","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","HL7","HL7 AL1 with unmapped severity code is rejected or defaulted safely","Negative","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 v2 inbound interface configured","1. Send ADT with AL1 severity code outside the configured table | 2. Process | 3. Inspect ACK and resulting allergy","AL1-4 Severity=ZZ (unmapped)","Message is rejected (AE/AR) or severity defaults to unknown with a flagged data-quality note; no silently wrong severity is stored","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-019","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0042","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","HL7","Multiple AL1 segments in one message create multiple allergies","HL7","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","HL7 v2 inbound interface configured","1. Send a message containing two AL1 segments | 2. Process | 3. Verify both allergies created","AL1-1=Penicillin; AL1-2=Peanut","Both allergies are created with correct set IDs and no overwrite/loss of the second segment","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-019","Standards-HL7; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0043","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","API","REST update of allergy severity reflects in subsequent GET","API","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Valid session; patient UUID with an existing allergy UUID","1. POST/PUT update to the allergy changing severity | 2. GET the allergy | 3. Compare","Old severity=MILD; New severity=SEVERE","Update succeeds (200) and GET returns the new severity; no stale cached value returned","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-020","API; Data Integrity; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0044","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","API","Allergy API rejects mismatched allergen category and concept","Negative","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Valid session; patient UUID known","1. POST allergy with category Food but a drug allergen concept | 2. Inspect response","category=FOOD; allergen=Penicillin(drug)","Server returns a validation error; inconsistent category/concept pairing is not persisted","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-020","API; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0045","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Security","Allergy override audit is tamper-evident and immutable to clinicians","Security","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Two roles: Clinician and a user with audit-read only; an override record exists","1. As Clinician attempt to edit/delete the override audit record via UI/API | 2. Verify it cannot be altered | 3. As audit reader view the record","OverrideRecord=existing; Role=Clinician","Clinicians cannot modify or delete override audit entries; record is immutable and remains intact for compliance","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-021","Security; Audit; Regulatory/Compliance","Platform"
"TC-ALLERG2-0046","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Security","IDOR check: clinician cannot read another patient's allergy by UUID","Security","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Valid session for Clinician without access to target patient; another patient's allergy UUID known","1. GET the other patient's allergy by direct UUID via REST | 2. Inspect response","TargetAllergyUUID=foreign; Requester lacks access","Server returns 403/404; no PHI for the unauthorized patient is disclosed via direct object reference","Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-022","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0047","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Security","Free-text allergen comment is sanitized against stored XSS","Security","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient dashboard open","1. Add allergy with Other free-text containing a script payload | 2. Save | 3. Re-open the allergy list and detail","FreeText=<script>alert(1)</script>","Payload is stored/encoded as inert text and never executes when the allergy list/detail renders","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-023","Security; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0048","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Accessibility","Allergy interaction alert is announced to screen readers as an alert","Accessibility","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; screen reader active; patient with allergy; ordering a matching drug","1. Trigger an allergy alert during order entry | 2. Observe screen reader behavior | 3. Verify focus and role","AT=NVDA/VoiceOver; Alert=Penicillin match","Alert uses an assertive live region/role=alert so it is announced immediately; focus moves to or references the alert; not silently visual-only","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-024","Accessibility; Patient Safety","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0049","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Accessibility","Severity and criticality are not conveyed by color alone","Accessibility","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; allergy list with varying severities displayed","1. View allergy list with Mild/Moderate/Severe entries | 2. Inspect indicators | 3. Verify text/icon accompanies any color cue","Severities=Mild,Moderate,Severe","Each severity/criticality has a text label or icon in addition to color, meeting WCAG use-of-color; distinguishable without color perception","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-024","Accessibility; Patient Safety","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0050","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Exploratory","Exploratory: concurrent allergy edits from two sessions on same patient","Exploratory","System","P2","High","Medium","Two clinician sessions open on the same patient allergy","1. In session A edit allergy severity | 2. In session B edit the same allergy reaction before A saves | 3. Save both | 4. Inspect final state and any conflict handling","Allergen=Penicillin; SessionA=severity; SessionB=reaction","No lost update silently overwrites the other change; system either merges, locks, or surfaces a stale-data conflict; final state is coherent and auditable","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-025","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0051","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Exploratory","Exploratory: ordering during alert evaluation race and double-submit","Exploratory","System","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient with matching allergy; ordering enabled","1. Add a matching drug order | 2. Rapidly double-click sign before the alert renders | 3. Observe whether order can bypass the alert","Allergy=Penicillin; Order=Penicillin V; double-submit","Alert cannot be bypassed by a double-submit/race; order is not signed without the allergy check completing; no duplicate order created","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-009","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0052","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Drug-Allergy Cross-Check","Pediatric weight-based order still cross-checks allergy independent of dose","Functional","Integration","P3","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; pediatric patient with Penicillin allergy; weight recorded","1. Open Orders for the pediatric patient | 2. Enter a weight-based Amoxicillin order | 3. Observe allergy alert regardless of computed dose","Patient=pediatric; Weight=15kg; Allergy=Penicillin; Order=Amoxicillin","Allergy cross-check fires based on the allergen/class match irrespective of the weight-based dose calculation","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-009","Patient Safety; Clinical","OpenMRS"
"TC-ALLERG2-0053","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Reaction/Severity/Criticality","Unable-to-assess criticality is a valid distinct value","Functional","Regression","P3","Medium","Low","Logged in as Clinician; patient dashboard open","1. Add allergy | 2. Set criticality to Unable to assess | 3. Save | 4. Re-open","Allergen=Shellfish; Criticality=Unable-to-assess","Allergy stores criticality as unable-to-assess distinctly from low/high and from null; value persists and renders correctly","Partially-Automatable","REQ-ALLERG2-003","Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-ALLERG2-0054","Allergies & Interactions (deep)","Override/Decision Table","Override does not propagate: a new order matching the same allergy re-alerts","State Transition","Integration","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; clinician overrode an allergy alert for one order earlier","1. After a prior override, start a NEW order matching the same allergy | 2. Observe whether the alert re-fires","Allergy=Penicillin; prior override exists; NewOrder=Penicillin V","The new order re-triggers the allergy alert; a prior override does not suppress future alerts for separate orders","Manual-Only","REQ-ALLERG2-011","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PEDS-0001","Pediatrics & Growth","Growth Charts","Plot weight-for-age on WHO growth chart for an infant under 24 months","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Logged in clinician; patient is a 12-month-old infant with at least 3 recorded weight observations","1. Open the infant patient record | 2. Navigate to the Growth Chart view | 3. Select WHO weight-for-age standard for the patient sex | 4. Confirm plotted points","Patient=Baby A (DOB makes age 12mo); Sex=Female; Weights=7.0kg@6mo,8.2kg@9mo,9.1kg@12mo","Three weight points are plotted on WHO weight-for-age (girls 0-2y) chart at correct ages with percentile/z-score curves visible","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PEDS-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PEDS-0002","Pediatrics & Growth","Growth Charts","Switch from WHO (0-2y) to CDC (2-20y) chart at the age-band boundary","Boundary","System","P2","High","Medium","Patient has growth data spanning the 24-month boundary","1. Open patient turning 24 months | 2. Open Growth Chart | 3. Observe chart selection at 23mo vs 24mo | 4. Verify reference standard switch","Patient age sweep=23mo,24mo,25mo; Standard=WHO 0-2y, CDC 2-20y","System uses WHO for ages under 24mo and CDC (or configured standard) for 24mo and over; transition occurs exactly at 24 completed months","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PEDS-001","Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PEDS-0003","Pediatrics & Growth","Percentiles","Calculate weight-for-age percentile and z-score for a known reference value","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Patient with sex and exact age in days; reference LMS tables available","1. Record a weight observation with exact datetime | 2. Open Growth Chart percentile readout | 3. Compare computed percentile/z-score against reference LMS value","Sex=Male; Age=730 days; Weight=12.2kg; Expected z near WHO median","Computed z-score and percentile match the LMS-derived reference within tolerance (z +/-0.05); median weight maps to ~50th percentile","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PEDS-002","Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PEDS-0004","Pediatrics & Growth","Percentiles","Reject percentile calculation when patient sex is unknown","Negative","System","P2","High","Medium","Patient record has sex recorded as Unknown","1. Open patient with Unknown sex | 2. Record weight | 3. Open Growth Chart | 4. Attempt percentile readout","Sex=Unknown; Weight=10kg; Age=18mo","System does not display a misleading percentile; it shows a clear message that sex is required for percentile/z-score and suppresses the readout","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PEDS-002","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","Standards"
"TC-PEDS-0005","Pediatrics & Growth","Percentiles","Flag severe acute malnutrition when weight-for-height z-score below -3","Decision Table","System","P1","Critical","High","Patient with valid length/height and weight; SAM threshold configured at z=-3","1. Record length and weight | 2. Open growth assessment | 3. Observe WFH/WFL z-score and nutritional flag","Sex=Female; Length=80cm; Weight=8.0kg producing WFL z below -3","System computes WFL z-score below -3 and raises a severe acute malnutrition flag/alert for clinician action","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PEDS-003","Patient Safety; Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PEDS-0006","Pediatrics & Growth","Percentiles","Decision table for nutritional status banding by z-score","Decision Table","System","P2","High","Medium","Growth assessment configured with WHO z-score bands","1. Enter weight/height combinations producing z in each band | 2. Read resulting nutritional category","z=-3.5 (severe), z=-2.5 (moderate), z=-1.0 (normal), z=+2.5 (overweight), z=+3.5 (obese)","Each z-score maps to the correct WHO category: <-3 severe wasting, -3 to -2 moderate, -2 to +2 normal, +2 to +3 overweight, >+3 obese","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PEDS-003","Clinical","Standards"
"TC-PEDS-0007","Pediatrics & Growth","Growth Charts","Detect implausible growth velocity (weight drop across visits)","Negative","System","P2","High","High","Patient with prior weight; new weight entered far below expected","1. Record weight much lower than prior visit | 2. Save observation | 3. Observe validation/alert","Prior=10kg@12mo; New=6kg@13mo","System raises an implausible-value or growth-faltering warning prompting verification before save; value not silently accepted","Partially-Automatable","REQ-PEDS-004","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
"TC-PEDS-0008","Pediatrics & Growth","Growth Charts","Length vs height measurement method affects chart selection","Decision Table","System","P2","Medium","Medium","Patient near 24 months where method matters","1. Record measurement with method=recumbent length | 2. Record with method=standing height | 3. Observe which reference applied","Age=24mo; Length(recumbent)=86cm; Height(standing)=85cm","System applies length-based reference for recumbent and height-based reference for standing, accounting for ~0.7cm method difference per WHO guidance","Manual-Only","REQ-PEDS-005","Clinical; Data Integrity","Standards"
